          "input": {
            "content": "# Factory monorepo\n\nFactory is an AI software engineering platform built around the Droid CLI — an autonomous coding agent that runs locally and interacts with cloud services through a background daemon. Engineers use Droid to work on codebases through natural language, with the agent handling planning, coding, testing, and committing changes.\n\nThis monorepo contains every layer of the platform: the CLI agent, the local daemon, backend APIs, the web and desktop frontends, and all shared packages.\n\n## What the platform does\n\nAt its core, Factory is a development loop:\n\n1. A user types a task in the Droid CLI (terminal-based TUI powered by Ink/React).\n2. The CLI agent streams to an LLM, executes tools (file reads, shell commands, search), and manages conversation state.\n3. The daemon (`factoryd`) runs as a background process, brokering communication between the CLI and the web/desktop frontend over WebSocket JSON-RPC.\n4. Results appear in the terminal and simultaneously in the web or desktop UI.\n\n## Repository map\n\n| Directory | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli` | Droid CLI — the primary user interface |\n| `apps/daemon` | `factoryd` — background daemon process |\n| `apps/backend` | Next.js 15 backend API (port 3000) |\n| `apps/web` | Vite + React web frontend (port 3002) |\n| `apps/desktop` | Electron desktop app |\n| `apps/admin` | Internal admin dashboard (port 3001) |\n| `apps/signal` | Signal analytics pipeline |\n| `apps/relay` | Relay proxy service |\n| `apps/functions` | Firebase Cloud Functions |\n| `apps/factory-vscode-extension` | VS Code extension |\n| `packages/droid-core` | AI agent core: LLM streaming, tools, prompts |\n| `packages/daemon-core` | Daemon session/terminal management |\n| `packages/frontend` | Shared React features (session UI, hooks) |\n| `packages/core-ui` | Design system — use for all UI work |\n| `packages/common` | Shared types, enums, API contracts |\n| `packages/services` | Business logic service layer |\n| `packages/models` | Data model definitions |\n| `packages/logging` | Structured logging + Sentry + metrics |\n| `packages/updater` | Auto-update utilities |\n| `packages/environment` | Typed env-var access |\n| `packages/eslint-config` | Shared ESLint rules |\n| `infra/` | OpenTofu (Terraform) infrastructure |\n\n## Quick links\n\n- [Architecture](./architecture.md) — system design and data flows\n- [Getting started](./getting-started.md) — setup, build, run\n- [How to contribute](../how-to-contribute/index.md) — workflow, testing, conventions\n- [Apps overview](../apps/index.md) — each deployable unit in detail\n- [Packages overview](../packages/index.md) — shared library documentation\n- [API reference](../api/index.md) — backend REST endpoints\n",
