            "content": "# Architecture\n\nFactory is a monorepo organized around a three-tier runtime stack: the Droid CLI (user-facing agent), the daemon (local broker), and the backend API (cloud services). These tiers communicate through defined protocols, and shared behavior lives in packages that any tier can import.\n\n## Language breakdown\n\n```mermaid\npie title Source code by language\n    \"TypeScript/TSX\" : 85\n    \"Python (infra)\" : 8\n    \"JavaScript (config)\" : 4\n    \"HCL (Terraform)\" : 3\n```\n\n~47,700 lines of TypeScript/TSX across ~6,000 source files (excluding node_modules and dist).\n\n## Runtime tiers\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    subgraph \"User interfaces\"\n        CLI[\"apps/cli\\nDroid CLI (Ink/React/Bun)\"]\n        WEB[\"apps/web\\nWeb UI (Vite/React)\"]\n        DESK[\"apps/desktop\\nElectron app\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Local machine\"\n        DAEMON[\"apps/daemon\\nfactoryd (Bun, WebSocket)\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Cloud\"\n        BACKEND[\"apps/backend\\nNext.js 15 API\"]\n        FIREBASE[\"Firebase/Firestore\"]\n        E2B[\"E2B sandboxes\\n(remote CDEs)\"]\n    end\n\n    CLI -->|\"stdin/stdout JSON-RPC\"| DAEMON\n    WEB -->|\"WebSocket JSON-RPC\"| DAEMON\n    DESK -->|\"WebSocket JSON-RPC\"| DAEMON\n    DAEMON -->|\"spawns + manages\"| CLI\n    DAEMON -->|\"HTTP/REST\"| BACKEND\n    CLI -->|\"HTTP/REST\"| BACKEND\n    BACKEND -->|\"reads/writes\"| FIREBASE\n    DAEMON -->|\"connects to\"| E2B\n```\n\n## Data flow: a user message\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant CLI as apps/cli (TUI)\n    participant Daemon as apps/daemon (factoryd)\n    participant Frontend as apps/web or desktop\n    participant Backend as apps/backend\n    participant LLM as LLM provider\n\n    User->>CLI: types message + presses Enter\n    CLI->>CLI: useAgent hook streams to LLM\n    CLI->>LLM: streaming request via droid-core\n    LLM-->>CLI: tokens stream back\n    CLI->>CLI: executes tools (read/write/shell)\n    CLI->>Daemon: JSON-RPC notification (stdout)\n    Daemon->>Frontend: WebSocket relay\n    Frontend->>Frontend: renders tool results, messages\n    CLI->>Backend: persists session events\n```\n\n## Package dependency graph\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    subgraph \"Apps\"\n        CLI2[\"apps/cli\"]\n        DAEMON2[\"apps/daemon\"]\n        BACKEND2[\"apps/backend\"]\n        WEB2[\"apps/web\"]\n        DESKTOP2[\"apps/desktop\"]\n        ADMIN[\"apps/admin\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Key packages\"\n        DROID_CORE[\"@factory/droid-core\\nLLM + tools\"]\n        DAEMON_CORE[\"@factory/daemon-core\\nSession + terminal\"]\n        FRONTEND[\"@factory/frontend\\nReact features\"]\n        CORE_UI[\"@factory/core-ui\\nDesign system\"]\n        COMMON[\"@factory/common\\nTypes + enums\"]\n        SERVICES[\"@factory/services\\nBusiness logic\"]\n        LOGGING[\"@factory/logging\"]\n        ENV[\"@factory/environment\"]\n    end\n\n    CLI2 --> DROID_CORE\n    CLI2 --> COMMON\n    CLI2 --> LOGGING\n    CLI2 --> ENV\n    DAEMON2 --> DAEMON_CORE\n    DAEMON2 --> LOGGING\n    BACKEND2 --> SERVICES\n    BACKEND2 --> COMMON\n    WEB2 --> FRONTEND\n    DESKTOP2 --> FRONTEND\n    ADMIN --> CORE_UI\n    FRONTEND --> CORE_UI\n    FRONTEND --> DROID_CORE\n    DROID_CORE --> COMMON\n    DAEMON_CORE --> COMMON\n```\n\n## Communication protocols\n\n| Link | Protocol | Direction |\n|---|---|---|\n| CLI ↔ Daemon | stdin/stdout JSON-RPC 2.0 | bidirectional |\n| Web/Desktop ↔ Daemon | WebSocket JSON-RPC 2.0 | bidirectional |\n| CLI → Backend | HTTP REST | client → server |\n| Daemon → Backend | HTTP REST | client → server |\n| Backend ↔ Firebase | Firebase SDK | bidirectional |\n\nThe JSON-RPC schema contracts live in `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/` and `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`. Any new notification type must be added there before use.\n\n## Key design decisions\n\n- **Bun runtime for CLI + daemon**: Bun was chosen for fast startup and native TypeScript execution without a separate compile step. This makes the development loop (source-edit → test) faster than Node.js equivalents.\n- **Ink/React for TUI**: The CLI renders its terminal UI using [Ink](https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink), which allows the same React component model used in web apps. This unifies the component library and enables code sharing between CLI and web.\n- **Single package for shared contracts**: All API types, enums, and JSON-RPC schemas live in `@factory/common` (`packages/common/`). This makes it impossible to have type drift between the CLI, daemon, and frontend.\n- **Daemon as local broker**: Rather than having the web UI call the CLI directly, the daemon acts as a stable WebSocket server that the CLI streams into. This lets multiple frontends (web, desktop, terminal) observe the same session.\n\nSee [background/design-decisions.md](../background/design-decisions.md) for more on architectural rationale.\n",
