            "content": "# Getting started\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- **Node.js 18.x** — check `.nvmrc` at the repo root; use `nvm use` to switch.\n- **npm 11.x** — specified in `package.json` as `\"packageManager\": \"npm@11.2.0\"`.\n- **Bun 1.3.x** — required for `apps/cli` and `apps/daemon`. Install from [bun.sh](https://bun.sh).\n- **Firebase CLI** — needed for functions and Firestore rules: `npm install -g firebase-tools`.\n\n## Install\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/Factory-AI/factory-mono.git\ncd factory-mono\nnpm install\n```\n\n`postinstall` runs `turbo run setup` automatically, which builds packages in dependency order.\n\n## Build\n\n```bash\nnpm run build                        # build everything (force + continue on errors)\n\n# Filter to specific workspaces (note the -- before --filter):\nnpm run build -- --filter=apps/cli\nnpm run build -- --filter=@factory/droid-core\n```\n\n## Test\n\n```bash\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common   # one package\nnpm run typecheck -- --filter=apps/cli     # typecheck one package\n\n# Single test file (in the package directory):\ncd apps/cli && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run path/to/file.test.ts\n```\n\n**Warning**: Running `npm run test` without a filter builds every package and uses ~9 GB of RAM.\n\n## Run locally\n\nThe dev stack is split into two profiles depending on where you're running.\n\n### Over SSH or on a remote machine\n\n```bash\nnpm run dev:web\n```\n\nStarts: backend (port 3000), web (port 3002), storybook, admin (port 3001), daemon.\n\n### Local machine with Electron desktop\n\n```bash\nnpm run dev:desktop\n```\n\nStarts the same stack, but with the Electron desktop app instead of the daemon.\n\n### Dev server logs\n\n| App | Log file |\n|---|---|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n| daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n\n```bash\ntail -f /tmp/factory-dev-backend.log   # live-stream\n```\n\n## Droid CLI dev\n\nFor working on the CLI itself:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup   # build and link droid-dev / droid-localhost wrappers\ndroid-dev                      # runs CLI from source, calls hosted dev API\ndroid-localhost                # runs CLI from source, calls local API\n```\n\nAfter modifying CLI or daemon source:\n1. `cd apps/cli && npm run setup` (or `cd apps/daemon && npm run setup`).\n2. Restart the daemon process.\n3. Start a new session — old sessions won't pick up changes.\n\nCLI logs are in `~/.factory-dev/logs/` (dev) or `~/.factory/logs/` (prod).\n\n## Linting and formatting\n\n```bash\nnpm run fix    # lint + format all packages (preferred)\nnpm run lint   # lint only\n```\n\n## Environment variables\n\nEach app has `.env`, `.env.development`, `.env.production`, etc. For local overrides, create `.env.local` in the app directory — it takes precedence and is gitignored.\n\nThe `@factory/environment` package (`packages/environment/`) provides typed access to environment variables. Avoid using `process.env` directly; use `getEnvironment()` instead.\n",
