            "content": "# Glossary\n\nProject-specific terms used throughout the Factory codebase and documentation.\n\n| Term | Definition |\n|---|---|\n| **Droid** | The AI coding agent. Refers to both the CLI tool (`droid` binary) and the underlying agent loop. |\n| **factoryd** | The Factory daemon process. Runs as a background service, managing droid sessions and terminals. Source in `apps/daemon/`. |\n| **Session** | A single Droid work session — one conversation context with its own message history, tool calls, and state. Sessions are identified by a UUID and persisted in Firestore. |\n| **JSON-RPC** | The inter-process protocol used between CLI, daemon, and frontend. All messages are JSON-RPC 2.0 objects over stdin/stdout (CLI↔daemon) or WebSocket (daemon↔frontend). |\n| **TUI** | Terminal user interface. The Droid CLI renders its interface using [Ink](https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink), a React renderer for terminals. |\n| **CDE** | Cloud development environment — a remote machine (E2B sandbox) where a droid session runs. Contrasted with local sessions. |\n| **Daemon-core** | The `@factory/daemon-core` package (`packages/daemon-core/`). Implements the WebSocket server, session lifecycle, and terminal (PTY) management. `apps/daemon` is a thin wrapper around it. |\n| **Droid-core** | The `@factory/droid-core` package (`packages/droid-core/`). Implements LLM streaming, tool definitions, prompt management, and message handling. |\n| **Hypercode** | A legacy codebase indexing/RAG system. Now deprecated; the last active code was removed around mid-2025. |\n| **Assembly** | An older term for the web frontend session UI state manager (`state/assembly`). The name lives on in Redux slice names in `packages/frontend/`. |\n| **Missions / Colossus** | The multi-agent task decomposition feature (AGI Mode). A \"mission\" spawns multiple worker sessions orchestrated by a planner. |\n| **Relay** | The `apps/relay` service — a proxy that handles routing between the daemon running in a CDE and the backend. |\n| **Signal** | The `apps/signal` analytics pipeline. Processes session events for friction/quality analysis. |\n| **Feature flag** | Runtime toggles managed via [Statsig](https://statsig.com). Flag definitions live in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`. |\n| **SEA** | Single executable archive — the distribution format for the Droid CLI binary, built by Bun. |\n| **Orb** | The billing provider ([Orb.com](https://www.withorb.com/)). Subscription and usage metering go through the `orb-billing` SDK. |\n| **WorkOS** | The authentication provider. Handles SSO and user identity. The frontend uses `@workos-inc/authkit-react`. |\n| **MCP** | Model Context Protocol — an open standard for plugging external tool servers into AI agents. The CLI supports MCP via `apps/cli/src/mcp/`. |\n| **ACP** | Agent Capability Protocol — Factory's protocol for agentic tool calls. Source in `apps/cli/src/acp/` and `apps/cli/acp/`. |\n| **Knip** | Dead-code detection tool. Run `npm run knip` to find unused exports across the monorepo. |\n| **Turbo / Turborepo** | The monorepo build orchestrator. Caches build artifacts per package and parallelizes tasks across the workspace. |\n| **@factory/common** | The shared-contracts package. All API types, enums, JSON-RPC schemas, and feature flag definitions live here. |\n| **@factory/core-ui** | The mandatory design system package. All UI components must use primitives from this package. |\n",
