            "content": "# Codebase lore\n\nThe history of how Factory's codebase evolved from a Next.js frontend stub into a full AI software engineering platform.\n\n## Eras\n\n### Era 1: The web frontend (Sep–Nov 2024)\n\nThe monorepo started on 2024-09-30 with \"Initial commit from Create Next App.\" The first weeks were pure frontend work: a Next.js web app with Redux state, styled-components, WorkOS authentication, and a design system. The CLI and daemon were not yet present.\n\nKey events:\n- 2024-09-30 — Initial commit; basic auth, Redux store, fonts, favicon\n- 2024-10 — First substantial feature work: chat UI, session management, component library foundations\n- 2024-11 — Client-side feature flags (Statsig), integrations panel, local repo indexing worker\n\nThe codebase was a ~300 commit/month product at this point — entirely web-focused.\n\n### Era 2: Hypercode + context indexing (Oct 2024 – Jun 2025)\n\nHypercode was a RAG system that indexed codebases to provide context to the AI agent. It used a dedicated indexing pipeline, BigQuery for analytics, and had its own API surface. The system had at least three major versions (v1, v2, v3).\n\nKey events:\n- 2024-10/11 — Local repo indexing with a web worker for continuous traversal\n- 2025-05 — Hypercode v3 dynamic context and retrieval improvements\n- 2025-07 — Last active Hypercode references (indexing summary/overview status)\n- 2025-09 — \"Hypercode V3 API empty repo handling\" — one of the final patches before deprecation\n- Late 2025 — Hypercode replaced by a simpler context approach as the CLI agent matured\n\nHypercode's BigQuery analytics code was also removed in this period (the signal analysis stack that used `apps/admin/src/services/bigquery/` was deleted).\n\n### Era 3: CLI and daemon join the monorepo (Nov 2024 – Feb 2025)\n\nThe Droid CLI and daemon were integrated into the monorepo at some point in late 2024 / early 2025. The earliest commits in the current history that reference the CLI are from 2024-11. By 2024-12, both `apps/cli` and `apps/daemon` were active workspaces.\n\nKey events:\n- 2024-12 — Next.js 15 migration for the backend\n- 2025-01 — Active CLI session management, ConversationStateManager introduced\n- 2025-02 — Electron desktop app work begins; daemon bundling explored\n- 2025-03 — `@factory/daemon-core` established as a separate package\n\nThis era saw commit rate grow from ~400/month to ~500/month as more engineers joined the CLI and daemon work.\n\n### Era 4: The CLI-first product (Mar – Aug 2025)\n\nFactory pivoted toward a CLI-first product with the web/desktop as companion viewers. The CLI agent loop became the core investment: LLM streaming, tool execution, conversation state, and TUI rendering in `apps/cli/src/app.tsx`.\n\nKey events:\n- 2025-03 — `@factory/droid-core` formalized with LLM streaming, tools, prompts\n- 2025-05 — Missions (multi-agent task decomposition) first shipped behind a feature flag\n- 2025-06 — Relay service introduced for CDE routing\n- 2025-07 — Peak activity month (527 commits); heavy investment in agent reliability\n- 2025-08 — CDE (E2B sandbox) support stabilized; update-workspace-cli automation\n\n### Era 5: Scale and model diversity (Aug 2025 – present)\n\nWith the core agent loop stable, the focus shifted to supporting multiple LLM providers, enterprise features, and platform reliability.\n\nKey events:\n- 2025-08 — Commit rate hits 637/month; Bedrock (AWS) + Anthropic SDK integration\n- 2025-09 — 741 commits — the busiest month; model registry growth, thinking/reasoning support\n- 2025-10 — BYOK (bring your own key) Anthropic support, interleaved thinking modes\n- 2025-11 — Agent Capability Protocol (ACP) work, MCP (Model Context Protocol) OAuth\n- 2025-12 — Missions (Colossus) graduated from feature flag to production; bun-pty native lib fixes\n- 2026-01 — `@factory/runtime` package introduced for auth abstraction\n- 2026-02 — Wiki feature development begins (`apps/signal`, `packages/common/src/wiki`)\n- 2026-03 — Wiki dashboard UI, droid wiki-upload CLI, wiki skill refinement\n\n## Longest-standing features\n\n**Redux + styled-components session UI** — First introduced in Oct 2024 and still active. The `assembly` Redux slice in `packages/frontend/` has survived multiple rewrites of the surrounding session management code. The name \"assembly\" comes from an early internal term for a session.\n\n**WorkOS authentication** — In place since the very first weeks (Oct 2024). The `@workos-inc/authkit-react` integration has barely changed despite the surrounding auth infrastructure evolving significantly.\n\n**Feature flags via Statsig** — Introduced Nov 2024. `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts` is one of the highest-churn files in the codebase, with 78 changes in the last 90 days alone — every new feature gets a flag, every launched feature gets its flag removed.\n\n**`apps/cli/src/app.tsx`** — The main TUI renderer. Introduced when the CLI joined the monorepo and has grown continuously. At ~4,500+ lines, it is the largest single file in the codebase.\n\n## Deprecated features\n\n**Hypercode (all versions)** — A codebase indexing and semantic search system. Built through three major versions between 2024–2025. The last active code was cleaned up in mid-2025 as the approach was superseded by the CLI agent's native file-reading tools. No replacement was built — the agent now reads files directly.\n\n**Crucible** — An internal evaluation/testing system. Removed in 2025-09 with `chore(backend): nuke crucible code (#9182)`.\n\n**BigQuery signal analytics** — Session friction analysis that ran against BigQuery. The entire stack (`apps/admin/src/services/bigquery/`) was deleted at some point in 2025 when the analytics approach changed.\n\n**AssemblyV2 (legacy session API)** — The `sessionV2` types in `packages/common/src/sessionV2/` represent an older session data model. The \"V2\" suffix suggests there was at least one prior schema. Assembly V3 was initiated in May 2025 (`feat(web): Init Assembly V3 app`).\n\n**Cloudflare + Sprites computer providers** — Alternative compute/sandbox providers. Removed Feb 2026 in `chore(backend): remove Cloudflare and Sprites computer providers (#10823)`.\n\n**Legacy OpenAI preview models** — Deprecated model IDs periodically culled from the model registry. Most recent: `chore(monorepo): deprecate legacy OpenAI preview models (#10741)` in early 2026.\n\n**Ink dependency in agent core** — The CLI used Ink (React for terminals) in `@factory/droid-core` but this dependency was removed in late 2025 (`refactor(cli): remove ink dep from agent core (#10688)`) to keep the core library environment-agnostic.\n\n## Major rewrites\n\n**Next.js 15 migration (Dec 2024)** — The backend and admin apps migrated from Next.js 14 to 15 (`Migrate to Next 15 (#952)`). Route handlers and middleware patterns changed.\n\n**Daemon refactor: monolith → daemon-core package** — The daemon started as `apps/daemon` with all logic inline. By early 2025, the core was extracted into `packages/daemon-core` so that alternative daemon hosts (e.g., remote CDEs) could reuse the same WebSocket server and session management code without depending on the full daemon app.\n\n**Auth abstraction: runtime/auth (Feb 2026)** — Authentication logic was consolidated into a new `packages/runtime` package (`feat(runtime): introduce packages/runtime/auth`). Previously, auth storage and token retrieval were scattered across the CLI, daemon, and desktop apps.\n\n**Assembly V3 (May 2025)** — A major rewrite of the session UI state management on the web frontend (`feat(web): Init Assembly V3 app`). The earlier Assembly V1 and V2 architectures are partially visible in legacy type names in `packages/common/src/sessionV2/`.\n\n## Growth trajectory\n\nThe monorepo grew from a single Next.js app (Sep 2024) to 21 apps and 22 packages by Mar 2026. Notable additions:\n\n| Month | Addition |\n|---|---|\n| 2024-09 | Initial: `apps/backend` (web), `packages/frontend`, `packages/core-ui` |\n| 2024-10–11 | `apps/admin`, signal analytics |\n| Late 2024 | `apps/cli`, `apps/daemon` join the monorepo |\n| 2025-02 | `apps/desktop` (Electron) |\n| 2025-03 | `packages/daemon-core` extracted from `apps/daemon` |\n| 2025-06 | `apps/relay` |\n| 2025-07 | `apps/signal` |\n| 2025-11 | `apps/bridge`, `apps/bridge-cli-mcp-server` |\n| 2026-02 | `packages/runtime` |\n\nThe top contributors changed over time: early months were dominated by the web frontend team; by mid-2025, CLI and daemon contributors (Arman, Stepan, Luke) are among the most active.\n",
