            "content": "# Fun facts\n\n## The oldest surviving file\n\n`packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts` was first committed on 2025-01-27 and is now one of the highest-churn files in the entire codebase — 78 changes in the last 90 days. It started as a small list of flags and grew into a 150+ entry catalog as features shipped and old flags were pruned. It's effectively a living log of every feature that has shipped or been killed.\n\n## The repo that builds itself\n\nA non-trivial fraction (about 11%) of all commits carry a `Co-authored-by: factory-droid[bot]` trailer. The Factory platform — the thing this repo builds — was used to write much of this repo. The percentage is a lower bound; Copilot and Cursor leave no git trace.\n\n## `app.tsx`: the file that ate the CLI\n\n`apps/cli/src/app.tsx` is the monolithic React/Ink component that renders the entire Droid terminal UI. At over 4,500 lines, it is the largest source file in the monorepo and has been changed in 63 out of the last 90 days of tracked git history. The name is deceptively simple for a file that contains the session header, conversation thread, tool result display, model selector, settings panel, and more.\n\n## The naming archaeology\n\nInternal names leave traces:\n- **Assembly** — the original codename for the session UI state manager (`state/assembly`). It lives on in Redux slice names in `packages/frontend/src/features/sessions/`. There is an `AssemblyV3` app-level component that replaced V2.\n- **Hypercode** — a Dune reference (the navigators in *Dune* use \"hyperspace\"; the team named their code indexing system after this). Despite three versions and a year of investment, it was ultimately retired in favor of the agent reading files directly.\n- **Crucible** — the internal evaluation system, also named after a furnace for testing metals. Nuked in Sep 2025.\n- **Missions / Colossus** — the multi-agent orchestration feature is internally called \"Colossus\" (after the 1970 sci-fi 