            "content": "# How to contribute\n\nThis section covers everything you need to know to work effectively in the Factory monorepo: from picking up a ticket to getting a PR merged.\n\n## Work pickup\n\n1. Pick up a Linear ticket (FAC-XXXX). All PRs must reference a Linear ticket.\n2. Create a branch from `dev` (the default branch). Branch names are free-form but conventional commits in the title help.\n3. Implement the change. See [development workflow](./development-workflow.md) for build/run commands.\n4. Test your change locally. See [testing](./testing.md).\n5. Open a PR against `dev` using the [PR template](./../reference/configuration.md).\n6. Wait for review. At least one approval is required before merge.\n7. Squash and merge to `dev`; the PR author merges after approval.\n8. Releases to `main` (production) are cut periodically by the release process.\n\n## PR conventions\n\n**Title format**: `type(scope): description`\n\n- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`\n- Scope: workspace name from `apps/*` or `packages/*`, or `monorepo`\n- Examples: `feat(cli): add wiki generation command`, `fix(daemon): handle null session gracefully`\n\n**PR body**: Use the template at `.github/pull_request_template.md`. Required sections:\n- Description\n- Related Issue (Linear ticket, `closes FAC-XXXX`)\n- Potential Risk & Impact\n- How Has This Been Tested\n\n## Review expectations\n\n- Reviews focus on correctness, risk, and design — not style (the linter handles style).\n- The author is responsible for addressing review comments and re-requesting review.\n- Breaking API contracts in `@factory/common` requires coordination with affected teams.\n- UI changes should include a screenshot or recording in the PR body.\n- Changes to the CLI agent loop, LLM streaming, or conversation state (the files listed in CODEOWNERS) need review from the owners listed there.\n\n## Definition of done\n\nA change is done when:\n- Tests pass (CI is green).\n- Typecheck passes.\n- Linting passes (`npm run fix` produces no errors).\n- The PR has at least one approval.\n- The Linear ticket is linked and will auto-close on merge.\n\n## Subsections\n\n- [Development workflow](./development-workflow.md) — branch, build, run, PR cycle\n- [Testing](./testing.md) — frameworks, patterns, running tests\n- [Debugging](./debugging.md) — logs, common issues, troubleshooting\n- [Patterns and conventions](./patterns-and-conventions.md) — error handling, coding style\n- [Tooling](./tooling.md) — build system, linters, CI\n",
