            "content": "# Development workflow\n\n## Branch and develop\n\n```bash\n# Start from dev\ngit checkout dev && git pull\n\n# Create your branch\ngit checkout -b feat/fac-12345-my-feature\n\n# ... make changes ...\n\nnpm run fix         # lint + format\nnpm run typecheck   # typecheck all packages (or filter to your workspace)\n```\n\n## Build\n\nThe root `npm run build` runs Turborepo across all workspaces. For development, you usually only need to build the package you changed:\n\n```bash\n# Build a specific workspace (note the -- before --filter):\nnpm run build -- --filter=@factory/droid-core\nnpm run build -- --filter=apps/cli\n```\n\nTurbo caches build outputs by content hash. If you haven't changed a package's inputs, `turbo` skips the rebuild. Run `npm run clean` to wipe caches when you need a fresh build.\n\n## Run the dev stack\n\n### Web dev (works over SSH)\n\n```bash\nnpm run dev:web\n```\n\nStarts: backend (port 3000), web (port 3002), storybook, admin (port 3001), daemon.\n\n### Desktop dev (local only)\n\n```bash\nnpm run dev:desktop\n```\n\n### Logs\n\n| App | Log file |\n|---|---|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n| daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n\n### CLI dev\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup   # builds wrappers: droid-dev, droid-localhost\ndroid-dev                      # runs CLI against dev API\ndroid-localhost                # runs CLI against local API\n```\n\nAfter any CLI or daemon source change:\n1. `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`\n2. Kill and restart the daemon\n3. Start a new session\n\n## Open a PR\n\n1. Push your branch: `git push -u origin feat/fac-12345-my-feature`\n2. Open a PR against `dev` on GitHub.\n3. Fill in the PR template: description, Linear ticket (`closes FAC-XXXX`), risk, testing notes.\n4. Request review from relevant CODEOWNERS (see `.github/CODEOWNERS`).\n5. Address review comments, push updates, re-request review.\n6. Squash and merge after approval.\n\n## Turborepo filter syntax\n\nAlways use `--` before `--filter` when running root scripts, or `npm` eats the flag:\n\n```bash\n# Correct:\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common --filter=@factory/daemon-core\n\n# Wrong (turbo runs all packages):\nnpm run test --filter=@factory/common\n```\n\nThis applies to `test`, `typecheck`, `lint`, `fix`, and `build`.\n",
