            "content": "# Testing\n\n## Test runners by workspace\n\n| Workspace | Framework | Command |\n|---|---|---|\n| `apps/cli` | Jest + ts-jest | `cd apps/cli && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts` |\n| `apps/daemon` | Jest + ts-jest | `cd apps/daemon && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts` |\n| `apps/backend` | Jest + ts-jest | `cd apps/backend && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts` |\n| `packages/frontend` | Vitest | `cd packages/frontend && npx vitest run path/to/file.test.ts` |\n| `apps/web` | Playwright (E2E) | `cd apps/web && npm run test:e2e` |\n\nRun all tests for a specific workspace from the root:\n\n```bash\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common\nnpm run test -- --filter=apps/cli\n```\n\n**Do not run `npm run test` without a filter** — it builds all packages and uses ~9 GB of RAM.\n\n## Frontend tests: jsdom environment\n\nAny test that uses React hooks, DOM APIs, or browser globals needs this at the top:\n\n```ts\n/**\n * @jest-environment jsdom\n */\n```\n\nWithout it you get `ReferenceError: document is not defined`.\n\n## Mocking pattern\n\nUse top-level `jest.mock()` with `requireActual` to preserve real utilities:\n\n```ts\njest.mock('./module', () => ({\n  ...jest.requireActual('./module'),\n  functionToMock: jest.fn(),\n}));\n\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetAllMocks());\n```\n\n**Rules:**\n- Mock heavy cross-file calls or non-deterministic behavior.\n- Keep pure helpers, utilities, and logging real (don't mock them).\n- Avoid `jest.doMock` and dynamic imports in tests.\n- One test file per source file — test only that file's public API.\n\n## Singleton testing\n\nFor modules with singletons or module-level side effects, use `jest.resetModules()` instead of trying to reset state:\n\n```ts\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetModules());\n\nit('test', async () => {\n  const { getService } = await import('./service');\n  // Each test gets a fresh module instance\n});\n```\n\n## E2E tests\n\nThe CLI has two E2E test layers:\n\n1. **`apps/cli/e2e-tests/`** — TUI-level tests using `@microsoft/tui-test`. They launch the CLI in a pseudo-terminal and assert on rendered output.\n2. **`apps/cli/e2e-stream-jsonrpc/`** — Stream-level tests that verify JSON-RPC message sequences between CLI and daemon.\n\nE2E tests require a running daemon and valid API credentials. See `apps/cli/tui-test.config.ts` for setup.\n\nFrontend E2E tests use Playwright:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/web && npm run test:e2e           # headless\ncd apps/web && npm run test:e2e -- --headed --debug  # visual\n```\n\n## Conventions\n\n- Colocate test files with source: `foo.ts` → `foo.test.ts` in the same directory.\n- Use absolute imports (`@/...`, `@factory/...`) in tests, not relative paths.\n- Always `await` async operations — unhandled promise rejections fail silently in some configurations.\n- Be pragmatic with types in tests; type assertions are acceptable for fakes and stubs.\n\nFull testing conventions: `docs/unit-tests.md` in the repo root.\n",
