            "content": "# Patterns and conventions\n\n## Error handling\n\nFactory has a strict error-handling convention. The full guide is in `docs/error-handling.md`.\n\n**Core rules:**\n1. Use `MetaError` for internal bugs and unexpected failures — never throw `new Error(...)`.\n2. Use `ResponseErrorXXX` classes for HTTP responses (e.g., `ResponseError404NotFound`).\n3. If you call `logException`, you handle the error locally and do not rethrow.\n4. If you don't handle, don't log — just add breadcrumbs with `logInfo`/`logWarn` and let the error propagate.\n5. Never call `logError` — use `logException` with the original error object.\n\n```typescript\nimport { MetaError, ResponseError404NotFound } from '@factory/logging/errors';\nimport { logInfo, logException } from '@factory/logging';\n\n// Breadcrumb before a risky call:\nlogInfo('Starting file sync', { sessionId });\n\n// Handled error:\ntry {\n  await riskyOperation();\n} catch (error) {\n  logException(error, 'File sync failed', { sessionId });\n  // Do not rethrow — you've handled it here\n}\n\n// Unhandled: just use MetaError and throw\nthrow new MetaError('Unexpected state', { field: value });\n```\n\n## Environment variables\n\nNever use `process.env` directly. Use the `@factory/environment` package:\n\n```typescript\nimport { getEnvironment } from '@factory/environment';\n\nconst env = getEnvironment();\nconst apiUrl = env.apiBaseUrl;\n```\n\nThe `no-direct-process-env` ESLint rule enforces this. Exceptions require an `eslint-disable` comment with a justification.\n\n## API type conventions\n\nAll API request and response types must be defined in `@factory/common`:\n\n```\npackages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts\n```\n\nImport from `@factory/common/{service}` — never define inline types in route handlers.\n\n## File organization\n\nESLint enforces these rules automatically:\n\n| Rule | Convention |\n|---|---|\n| Enums | Define in `enums.ts` in the same directory |\n| Types | Define in `types.ts` in the same directory |\n| API types | `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts` |\n| Imports | Absolute (`@factory/...`, `@/...`), not relative `../../` |\n| `require()` | Forbidden — use ES6 `import` |\n\nThe full file organization guide is in `docs/file-organization.md`.\n\n## UI components\n\n- Always use `@factory/core-ui` primitives. Never use raw `<div>`, `<button>`, `<input>`, etc.\n- Use `Box`, `Flex`, `Grid` for layout; `Button`, `Input`, `Dropdown` for form elements.\n- Use `colors.semantics.*` for colors — never hardcode hex values.\n- All UI work must be approved through Design; design is the source of truth for UI/UX decisions.\n\n## Redux state selection\n\nSelect state precisely — don't grab entire slices:\n\n```typescript\n// Correct:\nconst sessionId = useSelector((state: RootState) => state.assembly.currentSession?.id);\n\n// Wrong (re-renders on any slice change):\nconst { currentSession } = useSelector((state: RootState) => state.assembly);\n```\n\n## Feature flags\n\nNew features ship behind a Statsig feature gate. Add the flag definition to `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts` and check it with `useFeatureFlagValue` (frontend) or `featureFlags.checkFlag` (backend). See `docs/feature-flags.md` for the full process.\n\n## Dead code detection\n\nRun `npm run knip` to find unused exports. New exports that are never imported will fail the CI `knip` check. The config is in `knip.json` at the root.\n",
