            "content": "# Tooling\n\n## Build system: Turborepo + npm workspaces\n\nThe monorepo uses [Turborepo](https://turbo.build) as the task runner on top of npm workspaces. Turborepo:\n\n- Runs tasks in topological dependency order (builds package dependencies before the packages that import them)\n- Caches task outputs by content hash (skips rebuilds when inputs haven't changed)\n- Parallelizes tasks that don't depend on each other\n\nThe task config is in `turbo.json` at the repo root. The key tasks are `build`, `test`, `typecheck`, `lint`, `fix`, and `setup`.\n\n**Important**: always use `--` before `--filter` to pass flags through npm to turbo:\n\n```bash\nnpm run build -- --filter=apps/cli    # correct\nnpm run build --filter=apps/cli       # wrong — npm eats the flag\n```\n\n## Linting: ESLint + Prettier + Stylelint\n\n| Tool | Config | Command |\n|---|---|---|\n| ESLint | `packages/eslint-config/` (shared), per-app `.eslintrc.*` | `npm run lint` |\n| Prettier | `.prettierrc.json` | included in `npm run fix` |\n| Stylelint | `.stylelintrc` | `npm run stylelint` |\n\n`npm run fix` runs lint + format together. Use this instead of running them separately. The `@factory/eslint-config` package contains project-specific rules including:\n- `no-direct-process-env` — enforces `@factory/environment` usage\n- Import order rules\n- Enum/type file location rules\n\n## TypeScript\n\nEach app and package has its own `tsconfig.json` that extends a root `tsconfig.json`. The root config sets `strict: true` and `target: ES2022`. The CLI and daemon use Bun-specific type definitions (`@types/bun`).\n\nRun typecheck:\n\n```bash\nnpm run typecheck                           # all packages\nnpm run typecheck -- --filter=apps/cli     # one package\n```\n\n## Dead code detection: Knip\n\n[Knip](https://knip.dev) finds unused exports, unreferenced files, and unused dependencies. Config is in `knip.json`.\n\n```bash\nnpm run knip\n```\n\nCI runs knip with `--reporter github-actions` to annotate PRs with dead export warnings.\n\n## Husky + pre-commit hooks\n\n`.husky/` contains pre-commit hooks. They run `npm run fix` (lint + format) before each commit to keep the tree clean.\n\n## Runtime: Bun\n\n`apps/cli` and `apps/daemon` use [Bun](https://bun.sh) as their runtime and bundler:\n\n- Fast native TypeScript execution (no compile step for dev)\n- ESBuild-based bundler for production SEA (single executable archive) builds\n- `bun-pty` for PTY (pseudo-terminal) management in the daemon\n\nBuild configuration for the CLI is in `apps/cli/esbuild.config.js`.\n\n## CI/CD: GitHub Actions\n\nWorkflows live in `.github/workflows/`. Key workflows:\n\n| Workflow | Trigger | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| PR checks | PR open/update | typecheck, lint, test |\n| CLI release | Push to `dev`/`main` | build + distribute CLI binary |\n| Daemon update | Push to `dev`/`main` | update workspace CDEs |\n| Infra | PR/push | `tofu validate` + `tofu plan` |\n\nCustom GitHub Actions are in `.github/actions/`.\n\n## Infrastructure: OpenTofu\n\nThe `infra/` directory contains OpenTofu (open-source Terraform fork) configuration for cloud resources. Validate with:\n\n```bash\ncd infra && tofu init && tofu validate && tofu fmt\n```\n\nDo **not** run `terraform` for infra validation — the project uses OpenTofu.\n",
