            "content": "# CLI (apps/cli)\n\nActive contributors: arman, stepan, luke\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/cli` is the Droid CLI — the primary user interface for the Factory platform. It runs as a Bun process and supports two modes: an interactive TUI (Ink/React terminal app) for conversational AI sessions, and a headless exec mode for non-interactive use. The CLI agent reads files, runs shell commands, manages conversation state, and streams LLM completions.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/cli/src/\n├── index.ts               # Entry point — mode detection, init, Commander setup\n├── app.tsx                # Main TUI component (~4500+ lines)\n├── commands/              # All CLI subcommands (96 files)\n│   ├── exec.ts            # droid exec — headless execution mode\n│   ├── wiki-upload.ts     # droid wiki-upload — wiki upload command\n│   ├── mcp/               # MCP server management commands\n│   ├── skills/            # Skill management commands\n│   └── ...\n├── agent/                 # Agent loop utilities\n├── hooks/                 # React hooks (useAgent, useLLMStreaming, etc.)\n├── services/              # Session, settings, MCP, update services\n├── components/            # TUI React components\n├── exec/                  # Exec (headless) mode runner\n├── controllers/           # Session lifecycle controllers\n├── llm-proxy/             # Local LLM proxy for BYOK\n├── mcp/                   # MCP (Model Context Protocol) integration\n├── tools/                 # CLI-level tool implementations\n├── models/                # Model registry and selection\n├── acp/                   # Agent Capability Protocol\n└── utils/                 # Shared CLI utilities (197 files)\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `src/index.ts` | Entry point; initializes auth, telemetry, env; routes to TUI or headless |\n| `src/app.tsx` | Monolithic TUI component; renders the entire interactive terminal UI |\n| `src/hooks/useAgent.ts` | Core agent loop React hook — owned by arman, stepan, luke |\n| `src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` | LLM token streaming orchestration |\n| `src/hooks/useToolExecution.ts` | Tool call execution and result handling |\n| `src/services/ConversationStateManager.ts` | Maintains message history and session state |\n| `src/services/SessionService.ts` | Session lifecycle (create, load, persist, end) |\n| `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` | Exec mode runner; emits JSON-RPC to daemon |\n| `src/commands/exec.ts` | `droid exec` command handler |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Interactive mode (default)\n\nWhen invoked without arguments, the CLI enters TUI mode:\n\n1. `src/index.ts` initializes environment, auth storage, telemetry, and Statsig feature flags.\n2. Ink renders `src/app.tsx` — a React component tree that manages the session lifecycle.\n3. `useAgent` drives the agent loop: user input → LLM stream → tool calls → response.\n4. `useLLMStreaming` manages streaming state and chunked token assembly.\n5. `useToolExecution` dispatches tool calls (read file, run shell, grep, etc.) to `@factory/droid-core`.\n6. Notifications are sent to the daemon via stdout JSON-RPC (`streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts`).\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant App as app.tsx (TUI)\n    participant Agent as useAgent hook\n    participant LLM as useLLMStreaming\n    participant Tools as useToolExecution\n    participant Daemon as factoryd (stdout)\n\n    User->>App: types message\n    App->>Agent: onSendMessage()\n    Agent->>LLM: stream to LLM\n    LLM-->>Agent: tokens\n    Agent->>Tools: dispatch tool call\n    Tools-->>Agent: result\n    Agent->>Daemon: JSON-RPC notification (stdout)\n    Agent->>App: update conversation state\n```\n\n### Exec mode (headless)\n\n`droid exec \"task description\"` runs the agent non-interactively:\n\n1. `src/commands/exec.ts` parses options and calls the exec runner.\n2. `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` manages the same agent loop as TUI mode but without Ink rendering.\n3. Results are streamed as JSON-RPC over stdout for the daemon to relay to the frontend.\n\n## CLI commands\n\nThe `src/commands/` directory has ~96 command files. Key commands:\n\n| Command | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `droid exec` | `commands/exec.ts` | Non-interactive task execution |\n| `droid wiki-upload` | `commands/wiki-upload.ts` | Upload wiki to Factory |\n| `droid sessions` | `commands/sessions.ts` | List and manage sessions |\n| `droid settings` | `commands/settings.ts` | Manage CLI settings |\n| `droid mcp` | `commands/mcp/` | MCP server management |\n| `droid skills` | `commands/skills/` | Skill management |\n| `droid missions` | `commands/missions.ts` | Multi-agent mission control |\n| `droid computer` | `commands/computer.ts` | Manage CDE computers |\n| `droid bug` | `commands/bug.ts` | Bug report generation |\n| `droid update` | `commands/update.ts` | CLI self-update |\n| `droid ssh` | `commands/ssh.ts` | SSH workspace connections |\n| `droid model` | `commands/model.ts` | Model selection |\n\n## Integration points\n\n- Communicates with the daemon via **stdout JSON-RPC** (`streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts`)\n- Calls the **backend API** for session persistence, billing checks, and integrations\n- Uses **`@factory/droid-core`** for LLM streaming, tool definitions, and prompt management\n- Uses **`@factory/common`** for all shared types, enums, and session schemas\n- Manages **MCP servers** via `src/mcp/` (external tool plugins)\n- Loads **skills** from `.factory/skills/` in the project or user directory\n\n## Distribution\n\nThe CLI is distributed as a SEA (single executable archive) built by Bun. The build config is in `apps/cli/esbuild.config.js`. Development wrappers (`droid-dev`, `droid-localhost`) are created by `npm run setup` and run the CLI from source using Bun's TypeScript runner.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/index.ts` | Entry point — initializes the entire CLI |\n| `src/app.tsx` | TUI rendering — the full interactive terminal UI |\n| `src/hooks/useAgent.ts` | Agent loop — the most critical file for CLI behavior |\n| `src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` | LLM stream management |\n| `src/services/ConversationStateManager.ts` | Conversation history and state |\n| `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` | Exec mode + daemon communication |\n| `src/commands/exec.ts` | `droid exec` implementation |\n\nSee also: [daemon](../daemon.md) for how the CLI communicates with factoryd, and [packages/droid-core](../../packages/droid-core.md) for the agent core library.\n",
