            "content": "# CLI command structure\n\nThe Droid CLI uses [Commander.js](https://github.com/tj/commander.js) for subcommand routing in headless/exec mode, and [Ink](https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink) for the interactive TUI.\n\n## Mode detection\n\n`src/index.ts` detects the invocation mode:\n\n- **No arguments or just flags** → interactive TUI (renders `app.tsx` with Ink)\n- **`exec` subcommand** → headless exec mode (`commands/exec.ts`)\n- **Any other subcommand** → Commander routes to the appropriate command file\n\n```typescript\n// Simplified from src/index.ts\nif (process.argv.slice(2).length === 0) {\n  renderApp(); // Ink TUI\n} else {\n  program.parse(process.argv); // Commander\n}\n```\n\n## Command categories\n\n### Session management\n- `droid exec <task>` — non-interactive task execution\n- `droid sessions` — list sessions\n- `droid new` — start a new session\n- `droid rename` — rename the current session\n- `droid fork` — fork the current session\n- `droid rewind` — rewind session to a checkpoint\n\n### Workspace and environment\n- `droid ssh` — connect to an SSH workspace\n- `droid ide` — IDE integration (VS Code)\n- `droid computer` — manage CDE (cloud dev environment) computers\n- `droid terminal-setup` — configure terminal settings\n\n### AI and models\n- `droid model` — select or change the active LLM model\n- `droid missions` / `droid enter-mission` / `droid exit-mission` — multi-agent mission control\n\n### MCP (Model Context Protocol)\n- `droid mcp list` — list connected MCP servers\n- `droid mcp add` — add an MCP server\n- `droid mcp remove` — remove an MCP server\n- Commands in `src/commands/mcp/`\n\n### Skills\n- `droid skills` — list available skills\n- `droid create-skill` — create a new skill from a session\n- Commands in `src/commands/skills/`\n\n### Configuration\n- `droid settings` — manage CLI settings\n- `droid language` — set preferred language\n- `droid limits` — configure token/cost limits\n- `droid hooks` — manage lifecycle hooks\n\n### Utilities\n- `droid wiki-upload` — upload a generated wiki to Factory\n- `droid update` — update the CLI binary\n- `droid bug` — generate a bug report\n- `droid diagnostics` — run diagnostic checks\n- `droid search` — search sessions and content\n- `droid share` — share session or output\n- `droid stats` — usage statistics\n\n### Auth and account\n- `droid login` / `droid logout` — authentication\n- `droid account` — account information\n- `droid billing` — billing status\n\n## Adding a new command\n\n1. Create `src/commands/my-command.ts` — export a function that sets up a Commander command.\n2. Register it in `src/commands/index.ts` (the command registry).\n3. Add tests in `src/commands/my-command.test.ts`.\n\nLook at `src/commands/rename.ts` for a minimal example or `src/commands/exec.ts` for a complex one.\n\n## The exec command in depth\n\n`src/commands/exec.ts` (60KB) is the most complex command. It handles:\n- Option parsing (model, autonomy level, BYOK, worktree, spec mode)\n- Pre-flight checks (auth, billing, session readiness)\n- Launching the agent via `streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts`\n- Streaming results to stdout as JSON-RPC for the daemon\n- Error handling and exit codes\n\nThe exec command is the primary entry point for non-interactive use — CI/CD integrations, programmatic use, and the daemon's `droid exec` invocations all go through here.\n",
