            "content": "# Daemon (apps/daemon)\n\nActive contributors: arman, stepan, nikita\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/daemon` is `factoryd` — a background process that runs on the user's machine (or in a CDE). It manages droid sessions, brokers WebSocket communication between the CLI and the web/desktop frontend, provides PTY (pseudo-terminal) access, and handles auto-updates for remote deployments. The daemon is a thin wrapper around `@factory/daemon-core` (`packages/daemon-core/`).\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/daemon/src/\n├── index.ts          # Entry point — env init, auto-update, Commander config\n├── environment.ts    # Environment variable loading and typing\n├── constants.ts      # Daemon-specific constants\n├── types.ts          # Daemon-specific types\n├── services/\n│   └── UpdateService.ts   # Daemon auto-update logic\n├── telemetry/\n│   └── DaemonOtelTracingClient.ts  # OTEL tracing client\n└── utils/\n    ├── exit-with-code.ts\n    ├── parent-health-monitor.ts    # Monitors parent process (Electron/desktop)\n    └── command-wrapper.ts\n```\n\nThe bulk of the daemon logic lives in `packages/daemon-core/`.\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `src/index.ts` | Entry point; loads env, runs auto-update, starts DaemonCore |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/index.ts` | DaemonCore class — WebSocket server, session lifecycle |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/` | WebSocket server and JSON-RPC handlers |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/` | PTY management |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/droid/` | Droid session request handling |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/relay/` | CDE relay connection |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Startup sequence\n\n1. Load `.env` files\n2. Embed native libraries (bun-pty requires native code)\n3. Initialize telemetry and OTEL tracing\n4. Run auto-update check (skipped if `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=true`)\n5. Parse CLI arguments (port, host, unix socket, droid path, debug)\n6. Load shell environment (to get full PATH and env vars for terminal sessions)\n7. Construct `DaemonCoreConfig` and start `DaemonCore`\n\n### Ports\n\n| Environment | Port |\n|---|---|\n| Production | 37643 |\n| Development | 41723 |\n\nUnix socket mode is also supported (`--unix <path>`) for zero-downtime restarts via systemd proxy.\n\n### Session management\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Frontend as Web/Desktop\n    participant Daemon as factoryd (DaemonCore)\n    participant CLI as apps/cli (droid exec)\n\n    Frontend->>Daemon: WebSocket connect\n    Frontend->>Daemon: initializeSession (JSON-RPC)\n    Daemon->>CLI: spawn \"droid exec <task>\"\n    CLI-->>Daemon: stdout JSON-RPC notifications\n    Daemon-->>Frontend: relay notifications via WebSocket\n    Frontend->>Daemon: interruptSession (JSON-RPC)\n    Daemon->>CLI: SIGINT\n```\n\n### PTY / terminal\n\nThe daemon manages terminal sessions using `bun-pty` (a Bun-native fork of `node-pty`). Each terminal session gets a PTY that the frontend can connect to over the WebSocket, providing full terminal-in-browser functionality.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- Frontend connects via **WebSocket JSON-RPC** on port 37643 (prod) or 41723 (dev)\n- CLI is spawned as a subprocess; communicates via **stdin/stdout JSON-RPC**\n- Connects to the **backend API** for session registration and event reporting\n- Uses `@factory/daemon-core` for all session and server logic\n- Monitors parent process health (for Electron app — if the desktop app dies, the daemon exits)\n\n## Auto-update\n\nFor remote CDE deployments, the daemon runs `UpdateService.runAutoUpdate()` on startup and after each session completes (for `MachineType.Computer` machines). This pulls the latest CLI/daemon bundle from S3.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/daemon/src/index.ts` | Daemon entry point |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/index.ts` | DaemonCore — the WebSocket server |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/` | Request handlers and JSON-RPC routing |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/` | PTY session management |\n\nSee [packages/daemon-core](../packages/daemon-core.md) for the full daemon-core documentation and [systems/daemon-cli-protocol.md](../systems/daemon-cli-protocol.md) for the communication protocol.\n",
