            "content": "# Backend (apps/backend)\n\nActive contributors: jerry, sherry, theo\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/backend` is the Factory platform's backend API service — a Next.js 15 app that exposes REST endpoints for authentication, session management, billing, integrations, LLM proxying, and organizational management. The web UI that used to live here is deprecated; use `apps/web` for the frontend.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/backend/src/\n├── app/\n│   └── api/\n│       ├── _utils/           # Shared middleware and error handling\n│       ├── auth/             # Authentication endpoints\n│       ├── billing/          # Billing and subscription management (Orb)\n│       ├── sessions/         # Session CRUD and management\n│       ├── organization/     # Org management, members, roles\n│       ├── integrations/     # GitHub, Linear, Slack, etc.\n│       ├── llm/              # LLM proxy endpoints\n│       ├── cli/              # CLI-specific endpoints\n│       ├── daemon/           # Daemon registration endpoints\n│       ├── v0/               # Current API version (sessions, computers)\n│       ├── cron/             # Background cron jobs\n│       ├── github/           # GitHub webhooks and OAuth\n│       ├── webhooks/         # External webhook handlers\n│       ├── feature-flags/    # Feature flag evaluation\n│       ├── telemetry/        # CLI telemetry ingestion\n│       └── admin/            # Admin-only endpoints\n├── services/                 # Business logic services\n├── features/                 # Feature-level server code (feature flags, auth)\n├── middleware.ts             # Next.js middleware (auth, rate limiting)\n├── routes.ts                 # Route configuration\n└── constants.ts             # Backend constants\n```\n\n## Key route groups\n\n| Route prefix | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `/api/auth/` | WorkOS authentication, session tokens |\n| `/api/sessions/` | Session CRUD, stop-droid |\n| `/api/v0/sessions/` | Current session API (create, get, events) |\n| `/api/v0/computers/` | CDE computer management |\n| `/api/billing/` | Subscription plans, usage, Orb integration |\n| `/api/organization/` | Members, roles, invites |\n| `/api/integrations/` | GitHub, Linear, Slack, SCM repos |\n| `/api/llm/` | LLM proxy — streams completions for BYOK |\n| `/api/cli/` | CLI-specific endpoints (org info, settings) |\n| `/api/telemetry/` | CLI telemetry ingestion |\n| `/api/feature-flags/` | Client-side flag evaluation |\n| `/api/cron/` | Scheduled jobs (cleanup, billing sync, etc.) |\n| `/api/github/` | GitHub app webhooks and OAuth callbacks |\n\n## External integrations\n\n| Service | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| Firebase/Firestore | Primary data store for sessions, orgs, users |\n| WorkOS | Authentication and SSO |\n| Orb | Billing and usage metering |\n| GitHub | Repository integration, webhooks |\n| Linear | Issue tracking integration |\n| Slack | Notifications and integrations |\n| Statsig | Feature flag evaluation |\n| Sentry | Error tracking |\n| E2B | Cloud development environment provisioning |\n\n## Middleware\n\n`src/middleware.ts` handles authentication checks and routing on every request. API routes that require authentication use `handleRouteMiddleware` from `src/app/api/_utils/middleware.ts`.\n\n## Error handling\n\nBackend routes throw `ResponseErrorXXX` errors (defined in `@factory/logging/errors`) and let the middleware format the HTTP response. See [patterns and conventions](../how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md) for the full pattern.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/middleware.ts` | Auth + rate limiting for all routes |\n| `src/app/api/_utils/middleware.ts` | Route-level middleware helpers |\n| `src/app/api/v0/sessions/` | Current session API |\n| `src/app/api/llm/` | LLM proxy for BYOK |\n| `src/services/` | Business logic (session management, orgs, billing) |\n\nSee [API reference](../api/index.md) for the full endpoint inventory.\n",
