            "content": "# Desktop (apps/desktop)\n\nActive contributors: luke, nikita\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/desktop` is the Factory Electron desktop application. It wraps `apps/web` in a native window and adds local system integration: it bundles and manages the `factoryd` daemon process, handles native file system access, and ships the Droid CLI binary alongside it. The desktop app supports macOS, Windows, and Linux.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/desktop/src/\n├── main/                  # Electron main process\n│   ├── index.ts           # Entry point — Electron app lifecycle\n│   ├── daemon/            # factoryd process management\n│   ├── updater/           # Auto-updater (S3-based distribution)\n│   └── ...\n├── renderer/              # Renderer process (loads apps/web)\n│   └── ...\n├── preload/               # Electron preload script\n└── config/                # App configuration\n```\n\n## Key responsibilities\n\n**Daemon management**: The desktop app bundles `factoryd` and manages its lifecycle. It starts the daemon on app launch, monitors it for crashes, and restarts it. The daemon auto-update is disabled in the desktop bundle (`FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=true`) since the app ships a specific version.\n\n**CLI bundling**: The desktop app includes the `droid` CLI binary (`chore(desktop): bundle in droid executable`). On launch, it prompts users to install the CLI into their PATH.\n\n**Auto-updates**: The desktop app uses `packages/updater` and an S3-based distribution for auto-updates. The updater checks for new versions and installs them in the background.\n\n**Parent process monitoring**: The daemon's `ParentHealthMonitor` watches for the desktop process to exit. If the Electron app is killed, the daemon shuts down cleanly.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/main/index.ts` | Main process entry — window, daemon, lifecycle |\n| `src/main/daemon/` | Daemon process management |\n| `src/main/updater/` | Desktop app auto-updater |\n| `src/preload/` | Electron preload for IPC |\n\nFor the web UI that the desktop app loads, see [apps/web](./web.md) and [packages/frontend](../packages/frontend.md).\n",
