            "content": "# Admin (apps/admin)\n\nActive contributors: octavian, jerry\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/admin` is the internal admin dashboard — a Next.js 15 app used by Factory team members to manage the platform. It provides user analytics, organization management, billing oversight, feature flag controls, and system monitoring.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/admin/src/\n├── app/\n│   ├── api/              # Admin API routes (internal only)\n│   └── ...               # Admin page routes\n├── components/           # Admin UI components\n├── services/             # Admin service layer\n│   └── bigquery/         # (legacy, now removed)\n└── utils/\n```\n\n## Key features\n\n- **User management** — view and manage users, organizations, and members\n- **Analytics** — session statistics, usage metrics, friction analysis\n- **Feature flag management** — override Statsig flags for testing/rollout\n- **Billing** — subscription overview, usage data via Orb integration\n- **System monitoring** — service health, error rates\n\n## Tech stack\n\nNext.js 15, React 19, Redux Toolkit, styled-components. Unlike the main web app, the admin dashboard uses styled-components and Redux more extensively since it predates the `@factory/core-ui` mandate.\n\n## Access\n\nAdmin is an internal tool — not exposed to end users. It runs on port 3001 in development.\n",
