            "content": "# Packages\n\nThe monorepo has 22 packages. They split into three groups: core packages that most engineers will touch, feature packages for specific domains, and utility packages.\n\n## Core packages\n\n| Package | Key for |\n|---|---|\n| [@factory/droid-core](./droid-core.md) | LLM streaming, tool definitions, agent prompts |\n| [@factory/daemon-core](./daemon-core.md) | WebSocket server, PTY, session lifecycle |\n| [@factory/frontend](./frontend.md) | Session UI, React hooks, service layer |\n| [@factory/core-ui](./core-ui.md) | Design system — use for all UI work |\n| [@factory/common](./common.md) | Shared types, enums, API contracts |\n| [@factory/services](./services.md) | Business logic service layer |\n\n## Feature packages\n\n| Package | Key for |\n|---|---|\n| `@factory/component-library` | Higher-level chat/session UI components |\n| `@factory/models` | Data model type definitions |\n| `@factory/signal-core` | Signal analytics core types |\n| `@factory/mcp` | MCP (Model Context Protocol) client |\n| `@factory/droid-sdk` | External SDK for integrating with Factory |\n| `@factory/runtime` | Auth abstraction layer (new, Feb 2026) |\n\n## Utility packages\n\n| Package | Key for |\n|---|---|\n| `@factory/logging` | Structured logging, Sentry, metrics, OTEL tracing |\n| `@factory/updater` | Auto-update utilities for CLI and daemon |\n| `@factory/environment` | Typed environment variable access |\n| `@factory/utils` | Shared utility functions |\n| `@factory/eslint-config` | Shared ESLint rules |\n| `@factory/test-utils` | Shared test helpers |\n| `@factory/daemon-client` | Client library for talking to factoryd |\n\n## Dependency rules\n\n- All apps can import packages.\n- Packages should not import apps.\n- `@factory/common` has no internal Factory dependencies — it's the shared contracts package.\n- `@factory/core-ui` is mandatory for all UI work. Never use raw HTML elements.\n- Environment variables must go through `@factory/environment`, not `process.env`.\n",
