            "content": "# @factory/droid-core (packages/droid-core)\n\nActive contributors: arman, stepan, luke\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/droid-core` is the AI agent core library. It provides LLM streaming infrastructure, tool definitions, message management, prompt templates, and automation types that the CLI uses to run the agent loop. It is environment-agnostic — it has no dependency on Ink, Bun, or any specific runtime.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/droid-core/src/\n├── llms/               # LLM provider adapters and streaming\n├── tools/              # Tool definitions and execution\n│   ├── definitions/    # Individual tool implementations\n│   │   ├── file-tools/ # File read/write/patch tools\n│   │   ├── cli/        # CLI-specific tools\n│   │   ├── mission/    # Mission (multi-agent) tools\n│   │   ├── todo/       # Todo list tools\n│   │   ├── slack/      # Slack integration tools\n│   │   └── web/        # Web browser tools\n│   ├── registry.ts     # Tool registry\n│   └── types.ts        # Tool type definitions\n├── messages/           # Message types and transformation\n├── prompts/            # System prompt templates\n├── streaming/          # Streaming utilities and chunk assembly\n├── automations/        # Automation-related types\n├── api/                # API client utilities\n├── droids/             # Droid configuration types\n├── core/               # Core agent types\n└── feature-flags/      # Feature flag types\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `src/llms/` | LLM provider adapters (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, Bedrock) |\n| `src/tools/registry.ts` | Tool registry — maps tool names to implementations |\n| `src/tools/types.ts` | Tool definition interfaces (`ToolDefinition`, `ToolResult`) |\n| `src/tools/definitions/schema.ts` | JSON schema for all built-in tools |\n| `src/messages/` | Message type definitions and transformers |\n| `src/streaming/` | Token streaming utilities, chunk assembly |\n| `src/prompts/` | System prompt templates for the agent |\n\n## Built-in tools\n\nThe agent has access to these tools (defined in `src/tools/definitions/`):\n\n| Category | Tools |\n|---|---|\n| File operations | read file, write file, edit file (patch), view folder |\n| Search | grep search, glob search |\n| Shell | bash command execution |\n| Browser | web fetch, screenshot |\n| Todo | read todos, write todos |\n| Mission | worker spawning (for multi-agent mode) |\n| Slack | send message |\n| CLI | specialized CLI-level tools |\n\n## LLM providers\n\nThe `src/llms/` directory contains adapters for:\n- **Anthropic** (Claude family) — primary provider\n- **OpenAI** (GPT family)\n- **Google** (Gemini family)\n- **AWS Bedrock** (Anthropic via AWS)\n- **BYOK** (Bring Your Own Key) — user-supplied API keys proxied through the backend\n\nProvider selection happens via the model registry in `packages/utils/src/llm/model-registry.ts`.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- Imported by `apps/cli` as the primary dependency for agent logic\n- Imported by `packages/frontend` for message type definitions\n- Tool schemas are shared with `@factory/common` for frontend display\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\nTo add a new tool: create a definition file in `src/tools/definitions/`, add it to `src/tools/registry.ts`, and add its schema to `src/tools/definitions/schema.ts`.\n\nTo add a new LLM provider: create an adapter in `src/llms/` following the existing provider pattern, then register it in the model registry.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/tools/registry.ts` | Tool registration and lookup |\n| `src/tools/definitions/schema.ts` | Tool JSON schemas (used by LLM for function calling) |\n| `src/streaming/` | LLM token streaming utilities |\n| `src/prompts/` | System prompt templates |\n",
