            "content": "# @factory/daemon-core (packages/daemon-core)\n\nActive contributors: arman, stepan, nikita\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/daemon-core` implements the daemon's WebSocket server, session lifecycle management, terminal (PTY) support, and droid request handling. `apps/daemon` is a thin environment wrapper around this package, which allows the core functionality to be reused by alternative daemon hosts (e.g., remote CDEs).\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/daemon-core/src/\n├── index.ts            # DaemonCore class — public entry point\n├── types.ts            # DaemonCoreConfig and related types\n├── constants.ts        # Port defaults, protocol constants\n├── server/             # WebSocket server and JSON-RPC routing\n│   └── handlers/       # Individual JSON-RPC method handlers\n├── droid/              # Droid session request handling\n│   └── droid-request-handler.ts  # Spawns and manages CLI process\n├── terminal/           # PTY (pseudo-terminal) management\n├── relay/              # CDE relay connection management\n├── services/           # Session and lifecycle services\n├── automations/        # Automation-related session logic\n├── code-server/        # VS Code server integration\n└── utils/              # Internal utilities\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `src/index.ts` | `DaemonCore` class — creates WebSocket server, registers handlers |\n| `src/server/` | WebSocket server; dispatches JSON-RPC requests to handlers |\n| `src/droid/droid-request-handler.ts` | Spawns `droid exec`, manages the CLI subprocess lifecycle |\n| `src/terminal/` | PTY session management for in-browser terminal |\n| `src/relay/` | Connects to relay service for CDE routing |\n| `src/types.ts` | `DaemonCoreConfig` — configuration interface |\n\n## How it works\n\n### WebSocket server\n\n`DaemonCore` creates a WebSocket server and registers JSON-RPC handlers. When a client (web or desktop) connects, it can call methods like `initializeSession`, `interruptSession`, `loadSession`, and `createTerminal`.\n\n### Session lifecycle\n\n```mermaid\nstateDiagram-v2\n    [*] --> Connected: WebSocket connect\n    Connected --> Initializing: initializeSession\n    Initializing --> Running: droid exec spawned\n    Running --> Interrupted: interruptSession\n    Interrupted --> Running: resume\n    Running --> Ended: session complete\n    Ended --> [*]\n```\n\n### Droid request handler\n\n`droid-request-handler.ts` spawns the CLI (`droid exec`) as a subprocess and manages its lifecycle:\n\n1. Spawns `droid exec <task>` via Bun subprocess\n2. Reads stdout (JSON-RPC notifications) and relays them to connected WebSocket clients\n3. Writes stdin to send commands to the CLI\n4. Monitors exit codes and relays completion/error states\n\n### Terminal sessions\n\nEach terminal session gets a PTY via `bun-pty`. The PTY's stdin/stdout are piped to the WebSocket, providing a full interactive terminal in the browser or desktop app.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- `apps/daemon` instantiates `DaemonCore` with a `DaemonCoreConfig`\n- `packages/daemon-client` provides the client-side WebSocket interface\n- `packages/common/src/daemon/` contains the shared protocol types and constants\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\nTo add a new WebSocket method: add a handler in `src/server/handlers/` and register it in `src/server/`.\n\nTo change the CLI spawning behavior: modify `src/droid/droid-request-handler.ts`.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/index.ts` | DaemonCore entry point |\n| `src/droid/droid-request-handler.ts` | CLI process management |\n| `src/terminal/` | PTY sessions |\n| `src/server/` | WebSocket server and request routing |\n",
