            "content": "# @factory/frontend (packages/frontend)\n\nActive contributors: luke, theo, sherry\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/frontend` is the shared frontend package. It contains the session UI, React features, hooks, and service layer that are shared between `apps/web` and `apps/desktop`. Most visible product features live here.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/frontend/src/\n├── features/\n│   ├── sessions/         # Core session UI — chat, tools, diffs (most active)\n│   │   ├── modules/      # Page-level components (NewSession, ActiveSession, etc.)\n│   │   ├── pages/        # Route-level page components\n│   │   └── ...\n│   ├── settings/         # User settings UI\n│   ├── automations/      # Automation management UI\n│   ├── missions/         # Multi-agent missions UI\n│   ├── wiki/             # Wiki dashboard UI (new, Feb 2026)\n│   ├── feature-flags/    # Feature flag client\n│   ├── analytics/        # Analytics tracking\n│   ├── onboarding/       # Onboarding flows\n│   └── ...\n├── services/\n│   └── session/\n│       └── DaemonSessionController.ts  # WebSocket connection to daemon\n├── api/                  # API client functions\n├── hooks/                # Shared React hooks\n├── router/               # Client-side routing\n├── app/                  # App-level providers and setup\n└── layouts/              # Page layouts\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `src/features/sessions/` | Session chat UI — the main product feature |\n| `src/features/sessions/modules/NewSession.module.tsx` | New session creation flow |\n| `src/features/sessions/modules/ActiveSession.module.tsx` | Active session rendering |\n| `src/features/sessions/pages/SessionDetail.page.tsx` | Session detail page |\n| `src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | Manages WebSocket connection to daemon |\n| `src/features/wiki/` | Wiki dashboard feature (2026) |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Session connection\n\n`DaemonSessionController.ts` manages the WebSocket lifecycle for a session:\n\n1. Opens a WebSocket connection to `factoryd` on the local daemon port\n2. Sends `initializeSession` or `loadSession` JSON-RPC calls\n3. Listens for `SessionNotification` events (new messages, tool results, completion)\n4. Updates the Redux store with incoming events\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    SessionDetail[\"SessionDetail.page.tsx\"] --> Controller[\"DaemonSessionController.ts\"]\n    Controller -->|\"WebSocket JSON-RPC\"| Daemon[\"factoryd\"]\n    Controller --> Redux[\"Redux store (assembly slice)\"]\n    SessionDetail --> Redux\n```\n\n### State management\n\nThe session UI uses Redux Toolkit with entity adapters. The `assembly` slice (named for a legacy internal term) manages:\n- Current session and message history\n- Tool results and file diffs\n- Streaming state (in-progress tokens)\n- Session metadata\n\n### Wiki dashboard (2026)\n\nThe `features/wiki/` feature provides the wiki dashboard UI — the repo list with freshness indicators, wiki page tree navigation, and stats. Added in Feb 2026 on the `fac-16604-wiki-dashboard` branch.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- `apps/web` and `apps/desktop` both import from `@factory/frontend`\n- Uses `@factory/core-ui` for all UI components\n- Connects to `apps/daemon` via WebSocket (DaemonSessionController)\n- Calls `apps/backend` REST API for data fetching\n- Uses `@factory/common` for type definitions\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | WebSocket session management |\n| `src/features/sessions/modules/ActiveSession.module.tsx` | Active session rendering |\n| `src/features/sessions/modules/NewSession.module.tsx` | New session creation |\n| `src/features/wiki/` | Wiki dashboard |\n\nSee [packages/core-ui](./core-ui.md) for the design system, and [systems/daemon-cli-protocol.md](../systems/daemon-cli-protocol.md) for the communication protocol that DaemonSessionController implements.\n",
