            "content": "# @factory/core-ui (packages/core-ui)\n\nActive contributors: luke, theo\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/core-ui` is the Factory design system. It is **mandatory** for all UI development — never use raw HTML elements (`<div>`, `<button>`, `<input>`) when building UI for this project. All components must use primitives from this package.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/core-ui/src/\n├── primitives/          # Core layout and form primitives (32 components)\n├── colors/              # Semantic color system\n├── typography/          # Text components (Header, Text, Label)\n├── tokens/              # Design tokens (spacing, sizing, etc.)\n├── icons/               # Icon components\n├── fonts/               # Font definitions\n├── styles/              # Global style utilities\n├── hooks/               # Design-system hooks\n├── form/                # Form utilities\n└── index.ts             # Public exports\n```\n\n## Key primitives\n\n| Component | Use for |\n|---|---|\n| `Box` | Generic container (replaces `<div>`) |\n| `Flex` | Flexbox layout container |\n| `Grid` | Grid layout container |\n| `Button` | All clickable actions |\n| `Input` | Text input fields |\n| `Dropdown` | Select/dropdown menus |\n| `Header` | Page and section headings |\n| `Text` | Body text |\n| `Label` | Small labels and captions |\n| `Collapsible` | Expandable/collapsible sections |\n| `Toast` | Notification toasts |\n\n## Color system\n\nColors are defined as semantic tokens in `src/colors/`. Always use semantic colors — never hardcode hex values:\n\n```typescript\nimport { colors } from '@factory/core-ui';\n\n// Correct:\ncolor: colors.semantics.text.primary\nbackgroundColor: colors.semantics.background.secondary\n\n// Wrong:\ncolor: '#1a1a1a'\nbackgroundColor: '#f5f5f5'\n```\n\nThe color system supports light and dark modes automatically.\n\n## Usage rules\n\nFrom `AGENTS.md`:\n- Do **not** create custom UI primitives — extend `@factory/core-ui` instead\n- Do **not*