            "content": "# @factory/common (packages/common)\n\nActive contributors: arman, stepan, luke, jerry\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/common` is the shared contracts package. It defines TypeScript types, enums, API shapes, JSON-RPC schemas, and feature flag definitions that are shared between the CLI, daemon, frontend, and backend. It has no internal Factory dependencies.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/common/src/\n├── droid/               # CLI↔daemon JSON-RPC protocol\n│   ├── enums.ts         # SessionNotificationType and other enums\n│   └── schemas/         # JSON-RPC message schemas\n├── session/             # Session data types and enums\n├── sessionV2/           # Legacy session types (V2 schema)\n├── feature-flags/\n│   └── constants.ts     # All Statsig feature gate definitions\n├── api/                 # API request/response types by service\n├── llm/                 # LLM message and provider types\n├── integrations/        # Integration (GitHub, Linear, Slack) types\n├── organization/        # Org, member, role types\n├── billing/             # Billing and subscription types\n├── daemon/              # Daemon port/config constants\n├── tools/               # Tool result and display types\n├── settings/            # Settings types and enums\n├── automations/         # Automation types\n├── repositories/        # Repository types\n├── usage/               # Usage metering types\n├── relay/               # Relay service types\n├── wiki/                # Wiki types (new, Feb 2026)\n└── shared/              # Cross-cutting shared utilities\n```\n\n## Rules for using this package\n\n1. All API request/response types must be defined here: `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts`\n2. All enums must be in `enums.ts` files within the relevant subdirectory\n3. This is the single source of truth for the CLI↔daemon JSON-RPC protocol\n4. Do not add runtime logic here — types and constants only\n\n## Feature flags\n\n`src/feature-flags/constants.ts` is the catalog of all Statsig feature gates. This is one of the most frequently changed files in the codebase (78 changes in the last 90 days) — every new feature gets a flag, and flags are removed when features launch.\n\n```typescript\nexport const FactoryFeatureFlags = {\n  MyNewFeature: {\n    displayName: 'My New Feature',\n    statsigName: 'my_new_feature',\n    defaultValue: false,\n  },\n};\n```\n\n## JSON-RPC protocol\n\n`src/droid/enums.ts` defines `SessionNotificationType` — the full list of event types the CLI can send to the daemon/frontend. `src/droid/schemas/` defines the Zod schemas for each message type.\n\nWhen adding a new notification type:\n1. Add it to `SessionNotificationType` in `src/droid/enums.ts`\n2. Add its schema in `src/droid/schemas/cli.ts`\n3. Add a handler in `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts`\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/droid/enums.ts` | SessionNotificationType — the JSON-RPC event catalog |\n| `src/droid/schemas/` | Zod schemas for all CLI↔daemon messages |\n| `src/feature-flags/constants.ts` | All Statsig feature gate definitions |\n| `src/session/` | Session data types |\n| `src/api/` | API type definitions by service |\n",
