            "content": "# @factory/services (packages/services)\n\nActive contributors: jerry, sherry, theo\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/services` is the business logic service layer. It contains shared server-side services that both `apps/backend` and other parts of the platform use: session management, settings, integrations, and external API clients.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/services/src/\n├── sessions/           # Session service (create, update, query)\n├── settings/           # User/org settings management\n├── integrations/       # Integration clients (GitHub, Linear, Slack)\n└── ...\n```\n\n## Key services\n\n- **Session service** — CRUD operations for droid sessions, event streaming\n- **Settings service** — Plugin marketplace, user preferences, CLI settings\n- **Integration services** — GitHub repository access, Linear issue syncing, Slack notifications\n\n## Integration points\n\n- Imported by `apps/backend` for route handler business logic\n- Imported by `apps/admin` for admin operations\n- Uses `@factory/common` for type definitions\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/sessions/` | Session business logic |\n| `src/settings/` | Settings management |\n",
