            "content": "# Systems\n\nThese are the cross-cutting systems that span multiple apps and packages. They don't map 1:1 to a single workspace but are important to understand as architectural patterns.\n\n| System | Description |\n|---|---|\n| [Daemon–CLI protocol](./daemon-cli-protocol.md) | The JSON-RPC communication layer between CLI, daemon, and frontend |\n| [LLM streaming](./llm-streaming.md) | How LLM completions are streamed through the stack |\n| [Feature flags](./feature-flags.md) | Statsig feature gate system |\n| [Authentication](./authentication.md) | WorkOS auth, API keys, BYOK |\n\n## Why a systems section?\n\nSome important behavior in Factory spans many files across different packages:\n\n- The **daemon-CLI protocol** has contracts in `@factory/common`, implementation in `apps/cli` and `@factory/daemon-core`, and a consumer in `@factory/frontend`. No single package \"owns\" the full picture.\n- **LLM streaming** involves `@factory/droid-core` (provider adapters), `apps/cli` (agent hook), and `@factory/frontend` (UI rendering of partial tokens).\n- **Auth** touches the backend middleware, the CLI credential storage (`@factory/runtime/auth`), the daemon session config, and the frontend auth provider.\n\nThese system pages trace the end-to-end flow across those boundaries.\n",
