            "content": "# Daemon–CLI protocol\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe daemon–CLI protocol is the JSON-RPC 2.0 message layer that connects the Droid CLI agent to the daemon and frontend. It defines how events, notifications, and commands flow between the three layers.\n\n## Transport\n\n| Connection | Transport | Direction |\n|---|---|---|\n| CLI → Daemon | stdout (process pipe) | CLI writes, daemon reads |\n| Daemon → Frontend | WebSocket | bidirectional |\n| Frontend → Daemon | WebSocket | bidirectional |\n\nThe CLI communicates exclusively through its stdout. The daemon spawns `droid exec` as a subprocess and reads its stdout as a stream of newline-delimited JSON-RPC messages.\n\n## Schema contracts\n\nAll message schemas are defined in `packages/common/`:\n\n| File | Contents |\n|---|---|\n| `src/droid/enums.ts` | `SessionNotificationType` — all event type names |\n| `src/droid/schemas/cli.ts` | Zod schemas for CLI→daemon notifications |\n| `src/daemon/` | Daemon port constants and shared daemon types |\n\n## Message flow\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant CLI as apps/cli (droid exec)\n    participant Daemon as @factory/daemon-core\n    participant Frontend as packages/frontend\n\n    CLI->>Daemon: stdout JSON-RPC notification\\n(e.g., \"session.message.created\")\n    Daemon->>Frontend: WebSocket relay\\n(same notification)\n    Frontend->>Daemon: WebSocket JSON-RPC request\\n(e.g., \"interruptSession\")\n    Daemon->>CLI: stdin JSON-RPC\\n(e.g., interrupt signal)\n```\n\n## Notification types\n\n`SessionNotificationType` in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` lists all event types. Examples:\n\n- `session.message.created` — a new AI message started\n- `session.message.chunk` — a streamed token chunk\n- `session.message.completed` — a message finished\n- `session.tool.started` — a tool call began\n- `session.tool.completed` — a tool call finished\n- `session.completed` — the full session ended\n- `session.error` — an error occurred\n\n## Key implementation files\n\n| Layer | File |\n|---|---|\n| CLI sender | `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` |\n| Daemon receiver | `packages/daemon-core/src/droid/droid-request-handler.ts` |\n| Frontend consumer | `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` |\n| Schema definitions | `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/cli.ts` |\n| Type catalog | `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` |\n\n## Adding a new notification type\n\n1. Add the type to `SessionNotificationType` in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`.\n2. Add its Zod schema in `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/cli.ts`.\n3. Emit it in the CLI where appropriate (via `streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts`).\n4. Add a handler in `DaemonSessionController.ts` in `packages/frontend`.\n5. The daemon relays all known notification types automatically.\n\n**Important**: Notifications sent before the session is registered with the daemon are silently dropped. Always emit notifications after session initialization completes.\n\n## Common debugging issues\n\nSee [how-to-contribute/debugging.md](../how-to-contribute/debugging.md) for:\n- How to trace messages at each layer\n- Schema mismatch diagnosis\n- Timing issues with session registration\n",
