            "content": "# LLM streaming\n\n## Purpose\n\nLLM streaming is the system that moves tokens from an LLM provider (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, Bedrock) through the agent loop, into the daemon protocol, and ultimately to the frontend UI. The architecture ensures partial tokens appear in the UI within milliseconds of leaving the provider.\n\n## Data flow\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    Provider[\"LLM Provider\\n(Anthropic/OpenAI/Google)\"]\n    DroidCore[\"@factory/droid-core\\nsrc/llms/ + src/streaming/\"]\n    UseAgent[\"apps/cli\\nuseAgent hook\"]\n    UseLLM[\"apps/cli\\nuseLLMStreaming hook\"]\n    Runner[\"apps/cli\\nstreamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts\"]\n    Daemon[\"@factory/daemon-core\"]\n    Frontend[\"packages/frontend\\nDaemonSessionController\"]\n    UI[\"Session UI\\nActiveSession.module.tsx\"]\n\n    Provider -->|\"chunked SSE\"| DroidCore\n    DroidCore -->|\"token chunks\"| UseLLM\n    UseLLM -->|\"streaming state\"| UseAgent\n    UseAgent -->|\"JSON-RPC notifications\"| Runner\n    Runner -->|\"stdout\"| Daemon\n    Daemon -->|\"WebSocket\"| Frontend\n    Frontend -->|\"Redux updates\"| UI\n```\n\n## Key components\n\n### Provider adapters (`@factory/droid-core/src/llms/`)\n\nEach LLM provider (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, Bedrock) has an adapter that:\n- Sends the API request with streaming enabled\n- Reads the SSE (Server-Sent Events) response\n- Emits normalized `TokenChunk` objects\n\n### Stream assembly (`@factory/droid-core/src/streaming/`)\n\nThe streaming utilities handle:\n- Reassembling tokens into complete messages\n- Tracking thinking/reasoning blocks (for extended thinking models)\n- Managing interleaved tool calls within a stream\n\n### `useLLMStreaming` (`apps/cli/src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts`)\n\nThe CLI's React hook that:\n- Calls the appropriate provider adapter\n- Manages in-flight streaming state\n- Handles stream interruption (user pressing Ctrl-C)\n- Owned by: arman, stepan, luke (see CODEOWNERS)\n\n### `useAgent` (`apps/cli/src/hooks/useAgent.ts`)\n\nThe top-level agent loop hook that:\n- Drives the user message → LLM → tool call → response cycle\n- Calls `useLLMStreaming` for each LLM turn\n- Owned by: arman, stepan, luke (see CODEOWNERS)\n\n## Thinking and reasoning models\n\nSome models (Claude with extended thinking, OpenAI o-series) produce \"thinking\" content before their response. The streaming system handles:\n- Interleaved thinking blocks within the stream\n- `thinking` block types in the message schema\n- Thinking content display in the CLI TUI and web UI\n\n## BYOK (Bring Your Own Key)\n\nFor BYOK sessions, the backend (`apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/`) acts as an LLM proxy. The CLI sends LLM requests through the backend rather than directly to the provider. The stream response is forwarded back to the CLI.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/hooks/useAgent.ts` | Top-level agent loop |\n| `apps/cli/src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` | LLM stream management |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/llms/` | Provider adapters |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/` | Stream assembly utilities |\n| `packages/utils/src/llm/model-registry.ts` | Model registry and selection |\n",
