            "content": "# Authentication\n\n## Purpose\n\nFactory uses [WorkOS](https://workos.com) for user authentication and SSO. The CLI uses keytar (OS credential storage) to persist auth tokens locally. API keys provide an alternative authentication path for programmatic use.\n\n## Authentication paths\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    subgraph \"Web / Desktop\"\n        Frontend[\"Frontend\\n(AuthKit React)\"] -->|\"OAuth redirect\"| WorkOS[\"WorkOS\"]\n        WorkOS -->|\"user token\"| Backend[\"apps/backend\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"CLI\"\n        CLI[\"apps/cli\"] -->|\"keytar storage\"| Token[\"Access token\\n(OS credential store)\"]\n        CLI -->|\"HTTP header\"| Backend\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"API key auth\"\n        APIKey[\"FACTORY_API_KEY\\nenv var\"] -->|\"header\"| Backend\n    end\n\n    Backend -->|\"validate\"| WorkOS\n    Backend -->|\"read\"| Firestore[\"Firebase\"]\n```\n\n## Web and desktop auth\n\n`apps/web` and `apps/desktop` use `@workos-inc/authkit-react` for authentication. The user is redirected to WorkOS for login, then a session token is set. The token is validated by the backend middleware (`apps/backend/src/middleware.ts`).\n\n## CLI auth\n\nThe CLI stores credentials using the OS keychain via `keytar`. The auth module is `packages/runtime/auth` (introduced Feb 2026 in `feat(runtime): introduce packages/runtime/auth`).\n\n```typescript\nimport { getAuthToken } from '@factory/runtime/auth';\nconst token = await getAuthToken();\n```\n\nBefore `packages/runtime` was introduced, auth storage was scattered across `apps/cli`, `apps/daemon`, and `apps/desktop`.\n\n## BYOK (Bring Your Own Key)\n\nBYOK lets users supply their own Anthropic, OpenAI, or Google API keys. The CLI sends these keys to the backend LLM proxy (`apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/`), which makes the provider call on behalf of the user.\n\nBYOK session detection happens in `apps/cli/src/commands/exec.ts` — if a BYOK key is configured, the model selection and auth skip checks are different.\n\n## Daemon auth\n\nThe daemon authenticates with the backend using a session token or the `FACTORY_API_KEY` environment variable. For CDE (remote) deployments, the daemon uses a machine-specific token injected by the provisioning system.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/runtime/auth/` | Shared auth token management (new) |\n| `apps/backend/src/middleware.ts` | Request authentication middleware |\n| `apps/backend/src/app/api/auth/` | Login, callback, session endpoints |\n| `apps/cli/src/services/` | CLI auth initialization |\n| `packages/frontend/src/auth/` | Frontend WorkOS integration |\n",
