            "content": "# API reference\n\n`apps/backend` exposes a REST API over Next.js App Router route handlers. All routes are under `/api/`. The backend also acts as an LLM proxy for BYOK sessions.\n\n## Authentication\n\nMost routes require a valid session token (from WorkOS auth) passed as a cookie or `Authorization: Bearer` header. CLI routes can also authenticate with `FACTORY_API_KEY`.\n\n## Route groups\n\n### Session management\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/v0/sessions` | POST | Create a new session |\n| `/api/v0/sessions/:id` | GET | Get session details |\n| `/api/v0/sessions/:id/events` | GET | Stream session events |\n| `/api/sessions/:id/stop-droid` | POST | Stop the droid for a session |\n\n### User and organization\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/app/auth/me` | GET | Current user info |\n| `/api/organization` | GET | Get organization info |\n| `/api/organization/members` | GET/POST | Member management |\n| `/api/organization/members/remove` | POST | Remove a member |\n| `/api/organization/members/update-role` | POST | Update member role |\n\n### Billing\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/billing/subscription` | GET | Current subscription plan |\n| `/api/billing/usage` | GET | Usage data |\n| `/api/billing/checkout` | POST | Create checkout session |\n| `/api/billing/portal` | POST | Create billing portal session |\n\n### Integrations\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/integrations/scm/repositories` | GET | List connected repositories |\n| `/api/integrations/scm/repositories/enable` | POST | Enable a repository |\n| `/api/github/` | POST | GitHub webhook handler |\n| `/api/github/oauth/callback` | GET | GitHub OAuth callback |\n\n### CLI-specific\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/cli/org` | GET | Org info for CLI |\n| `/api/feature-flags` | POST | Evaluate feature flags |\n| `/api/telemetry/cli-ingest` | POST | CLI telemetry ingestion |\n| `/api/bug-reports` | POST | Submit a bug report |\n\n### LLM proxy\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/llm/stream` | POST | Stream LLM completions (BYOK) |\n\n### Computers (CDEs)\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/v0/computers` | POST | Provision a CDE |\n| `/api/v0/computers/:id` | GET/DELETE | Get or delete a CDE |\n\n### Admin (internal only)\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/admin/organizations` | GET | List organizations |\n| `/api/admin/users` | GET | List users |\n\n### Cron jobs\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/cron/*` | GET | Various scheduled jobs (cleanup, billing sync, etc.) |\n\n## API type conventions\n\nAll request and response types must be defined in `@factory/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts`. Route handlers import from there — types are never defined inline.\n\n## Versioning\n\nThe current API version is `v0` (under `/api/v0/`). Some older routes under `/api/sessions/` and `/api/organization/` predate the versioning convention and exist for backward compatibility.\n\n## Error format\n\nAll errors follow the `ResponseErrorXXX` format from `@factory/logging/errors`. The middleware in `apps/backend/src/app/api/_utils/middleware.ts` formats them as JSON responses with the appropriate HTTP status code.\n\nSee [patterns and conventions](../how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md) for the error handling pattern.\n",
