            "content": "# Logging\n\n## Log infrastructure\n\nLogging is centralized in `@factory/logging` (`packages/logging/`). All logging goes through three channels:\n\n1. **Log files** — written to `~/.factory/logs/` (prod) or `~/.factory-dev/logs/` (dev)\n2. **Sentry** — exceptions and errors are forwarded to [Sentry](https://sentry.io)\n3. **Custom telemetry** — structured events sent to the Factory backend for analysis\n\n## API\n\n```typescript\nimport { logInfo, logWarn, logException } from '@factory/logging';\n\nlogInfo('Session started', { sessionId, userId });\nlogWarn('Rate limit approaching', { usage: 950, limit: 1000 });\n\ntry {\n  await riskyOperation();\n} catch (error) {\n  logException(error, 'Operation failed', { context });\n  // Do not rethrow if you call logException — you've handled it\n}\n```\n\nFunctions:\n- `logInfo(message, metadata?)` — informational, for debugging and tracing\n- `logWarn(message, metadata?)` — warnings that don't break functionality\n- `logException(error, message, metadata?)` — errors with full stack trace; forwards to Sentry\n- `LogOnce.logError(...)` — log once per session to prevent spam in loops\n\n**Never call `logError` directly** — use `logException` with the original error object.\n\n## Log files\n\n| Environment | Location | Key files |\n|---|---|---|\n| Production (CLI) | `~/.factory/logs/` | `droid-log-single.log`, `console.log` |\n| Development (CLI) | `~/.factory-dev/logs/` | Same |\n| Production (daemon) | `~/.factory/logs/` | `factoryd.log` |\n| Development (daemon) | `~/.factory-dev/logs/` | `factoryd.log` |\n\n```bash\ntail -f ~/.factory-dev/logs/factoryd.log       # daemon\ntail -f ~/.factory-dev/logs/droid-log-single.log  # CLI\n```\n\n## Dev server logs\n\nWhen running `npm run dev:web`, each app streams to both console and a log file:\n\n| App | File |\n|---|---|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n| admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n\n## Secret scrubbing\n\nThe logging package automatically scrubs secrets before writing to disk or sending to Sentry. This covers API keys, tokens, and other common credential patterns. You do not need to manually redact sensitive data, but you should still avoid logging unnecessary PII.\n\n## Log levels\n\n| Level | Function | When to use |\n|---|---|---|\n| Info | `logInfo` | Normal operations, debugging |\n| Warn | `logWarn` | Potential issues, degraded behavior |\n| Error | `logException` | Errors that need investigation |\n\n## Sentry integration\n\nSentry is configured in each app's `sentry.config.ts`. The `logException` function forwards exceptions to Sentry with the provided metadata as breadcrumbs. The Sentry project is configured with `user_id`, `org_id`, and `session_id` enrichment (added Dec 2024).\n",
