            "content": "# Metrics\n\n## Metrics infrastructure\n\nFactory uses a custom metrics system in `@factory/logging` (`packages/logging/`) for structured metric emission. The backend uses `fetchWithMetrics` and `callWithMetrics` to instrument external API calls.\n\n## Emitting metrics\n\n```typescript\nimport { Metrics } from '@factory/logging';\n\n// Counter — increment by value\nMetrics.addToCounter('llm_completion_count', 1, { model: 'claude-3-5-sonnet', status: 'success' });\n\n// Gauge — set current value\nMetrics.setGauge('active_sessions_count', 42);\n\n// Histogram — record distributions (latency, sizes)\nMetrics.recordHistogram('session_initialize_latency_ms', duration, { provider: 'anthropic' });\n```\n\nUse descriptive names with units: `_ms` for milliseconds, `_bytes` for bytes, `_count` for counts.\n\n## Instrumenting external calls\n\n```typescript\nimport { fetchWithMetrics, callWithMetrics } from '@/app/api/_utils/metrics';\nimport { ExternalDependency } from '@/app/api/_utils/metrics/enums';\n\n// For HTTP requests:\nconst response = await fetchWithMetrics(fetch, ExternalDependency.OPENAI, {\n  labels: { model: 'gpt-4' },\n}, url, requestOptions);\n\n// For any function calls:\nconst result = await callWithMetrics(processDocument, ExternalDependency.FIREBASE, {\n  labels: { documentType: 'session' },\n}, documentId);\n```\n\nWhen adding a new external service, add it to `ExternalDependency` in `apps/backend/src/app/api/_utils/metrics/enums.ts`.\n\n## Key tracked metrics\n\n- LLM completion counts and latency per model and provider\n- Session initialization latency\n- External dependency call success/failure rates\n- Active session counts\n\n## CLI telemetry\n\nThe CLI emits telemetry events through `CliTelemetryClient` (`apps/cli/src/utils/cliTelemetryClient.ts`). These are sent to `apps/backend/api/telemetry/cli-ingest` and include anonymized usage patterns.\n\nFull metrics guide: `docs/metrics-logging.md`.\n",
