            "content": "# Tracing\n\n## OTEL (OpenTelemetry)\n\nThe daemon and backend support distributed tracing via OpenTelemetry. Tracing is disabled by default and enabled via environment variable.\n\n### Enabling tracing\n\n```bash\n# In apps/daemon/.env.local or as an env var:\nFACTORY_OTEL_ENABLED=true\n```\n\n### Implementation\n\nThe daemon initializes the OTEL client in `apps/daemon/src/telemetry/DaemonOtelTracingClient.ts`:\n\n```typescript\nconst otelClient = new DaemonOtelTracingClient({\n  enabled: getDaemonEnvironment().extras.otelEnabled,\n});\nOtelTracing.initialize(otelClient);\n```\n\nThe `OtelTracing` singleton from `@factory/logging/tracing` wraps the OTEL SDK. Spans are emitted for:\n- Session initialization and completion\n- LLM API calls\n- Tool executions\n\n### Backend instrumentation\n\nThe backend uses Next.js's built-in instrumentation hook (`apps/backend/src/instrumentation.ts`) for request tracing.\n\n### Auth span enrichment\n\nAuth context (user ID, org ID) is added to OTEL spans. See `fix(logging, cli, daemon, frontend): clean up auth enrichment on OTEL tracing spans (#10253)` for the current implementation.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/daemon/src/telemetry/DaemonOtelTracingClient.ts` | Daemon OTEL client |\n| `packages/logging/src/tracing/` | OtelTracing wrapper |\n| `apps/backend/src/instrumentation.ts` | Backend instrumentation |\n",
