            "content": "# Alerting\n\n## Sentry alerts\n\nSentry is the primary alerting system. Each app has its own Sentry project configured in its `sentry.config.ts`. Alerts fire on:\n- High error rate for a route or component\n- New error types that haven't been seen before\n- Specific critical errors (LLM API failures, session initialization failures)\n\nThe on-call rotation monitors Sentry for new issues. See the internal on-call runbook for escalation paths.\n\n## Key alert areas\n\n**Backend API** — Monitor `/api/v0/sessions` and `/api/llm/stream` for elevated error rates. These are the highest-traffic and most critical endpoints.\n\n**CLI errors** — CLI exceptions are forwarded to Sentry via `logException`. Filter by `platform: cli` in Sentry.\n\n**Daemon crashes** — Daemon process exits are logged to `factoryd.log`. Unexpected exits show up in Sentry with the last exception before exit.\n\n**LLM provider errors** — The LLM proxy and CLI both forward provider errors to Sentry. Filter by `external_dependency: openai/anthropic/google` for provider-specific issues.\n\n## Adding alerts\n\n1. Use `logException` in the code path you want to alert on — this automatically forwards to Sentry.\n2. Create a Sentry alert rule in the console for the specific error pattern.\n3. Set the threshold and notification channel (Slack, PagerDuty, email).\n\n## Known noisy alerts\n\n- WorkOS token expiry during long CLI sessions — users need to re-authenticate. These are user errors, not platform errors.\n- E2B sandbox startup timeouts — occasional infrastructure issue, not actionable for the CLI team.\n",
