            "content": "# Deployment\n\n## Services and their deployment targets\n\n| Service | Platform | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `apps/backend` | Vercel | Auto-deploys on push to `dev`/`main` |\n| `apps/admin` | Vercel | Auto-deploys on push to `dev`/`main` |\n| `apps/web` | Vercel | Auto-deploys on push to `dev`/`main` |\n| `apps/cli` | S3 + npm | Release workflow builds SEA binary |\n| `apps/daemon` | S3 | Bundled with desktop; remote CDEs pull from S3 |\n| `apps/desktop` | GitHub Releases + S3 | Electron packager builds platform binaries |\n| `apps/functions` | Firebase | Deployed via `firebase-tools` |\n| `infra/` | AWS | OpenTofu managed |\n\n## Environments\n\n| Environment | Branch | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Production | `main` | Users see this |\n| Development (staging) | `dev` | Team uses this for testing |\n| Localhost | local | `.env.localhost` variants |\n| Preprod | PR branches | `.env.preprod` for select PRs |\n\n## CLI release process\n\nThe CLI is distributed as a SEA (single executable archive). The GitHub Actions release workflow:\n\n1. Builds the SEA for macOS (arm64, x64), Linux (arm64, x64), and Windows (x64)\n2. Code-signs the macOS binary\n3. Uploads to S3\n4. Publishes to npm as `@factory/cli`\n5. Updates the version string in `apps/cli/package.json`\n\nAfter release, CDEs running the daemon receive the new CLI via auto-update (`UpdateService.runAutoUpdate()`).\n\n## Infrastructure (OpenTofu)\n\nAWS infrastructure is managed with OpenTofu in `infra/`. To validate:\n\n```bash\ncd infra && tofu init && tofu validate && tofu fmt\n```\n\nDo not use `terraform` — the project uses OpenTofu (the open-source fork).\n\n## Firebase\n\nFirebase resources (Firestore rules, indexes, Cloud Functions) are deployed with:\n\n```bash\nfirebase deploy --only firestore:rules\nfirebase deploy --only firestore:indexes\nfirebase deploy --only functions\n```\n\nConfig files: `firebase.json`, `firestore.rules`, `firestore.indexes.json`, `storage.rules`.\n\n## Rollback\n\n- **Backend/web/admin**: Vercel dashboard → Deployments → roll back to previous deployment.\n- **CLI**: Publish a patch release with a fix. The auto-updater on remote CDEs will pick it up.\n- **Desktop**: Publish a new release. The in-app updater will prompt users.\n- **Infrastructure**: Revert the OpenTofu state manually or via a revert PR.\n",
