            "content": "# Security\n\n## Trust boundaries\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    User[\"User (browser/terminal)\"]\n    CLI[\"Droid CLI\\n(local process)\"]\n    Daemon[\"factoryd\\n(local process)\"]\n    Backend[\"Backend API\\n(Vercel)\"]\n    Firestore[\"Firebase/Firestore\"]\n    Providers[\"LLM Providers\\n(Anthropic/OpenAI/Google)\"]\n\n    User -->|\"authenticated session\"| Backend\n    User -->|\"local IPC\"| CLI\n    CLI -->|\"stdout JSON-RPC\"| Daemon\n    Daemon -->|\"authenticated HTTP\"| Backend\n    CLI -->|\"authenticated HTTP\"| Backend\n    Backend -->|\"service account\"| Firestore\n    Backend -->|\"API key (BYOK)\"| Providers\n```\n\n## Authentication and authorization\n\n- **Web/Desktop**: WorkOS handles login. Session tokens are short-lived JWTs. The backend middleware validates every request.\n- **CLI**: Tokens stored in the OS keychain via `packages/runtime/auth`. The daemon inherits the user's session when spawned by the desktop app.\n- **API keys**: `FACTORY_API_KEY` provides programmatic access. Keys are org-scoped.\n- **Admin routes**: `/api/admin/` routes require admin-level authentication — checked separately from regular auth.\n\n## Input validation\n\nAPI routes use Zod for request validation. Invalid inputs return `ResponseError422InvalidData`. Tool inputs from the LLM are also validated against the tool schema before execution.\n\n## Secret handling\n\n- The logging package scrubs secrets before writing to disk or Sentry. Never log secrets manually.\n- Environment variables are accessed via `@factory/environment` — the `no-direct-process-env` lint rule enforces this.\n- `.env.local` files are gitignored across all apps.\n- BYOK API keys are transmitted to the backend proxy and never stored.\n\n## CLI security model\n\nThe CLI runs with full user permissions (it needs to read and write files, run shell commands, etc.). The `exec` tool runs arbitrary shell commands in the user's environment. Users are presented with tool calls before they execute (in interactive mode) and can interrupt at any time.\n\nThe tool permissions system (`src/commands/resolveToolSelection.ts`) allows restricting which tools are available per session.\n\n## Firestore security rules\n\n`firestore.rules` defines document-level access control. Users can only access documents for their own organization. Admin routes bypass Firestore rules via a service account.\n\n## Dependency security\n\nThe monorepo has override rules in `package.json` for known vulnerable transitive dependencies (e.g., `cookie@<0.7.0`, `path-to-regexp` versions). The Dependabot configuration auto-creates PRs for dependency updates.\n",
