            "content": "# Complexity hotspots\n\nFiles that are large, frequently changed, or cover too many concerns.\n\n## Largest source files\n\n| File | Lines | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/droid-request-handler.test.ts` | 11,857 | Test file for the daemon's core handler |\n| `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.test.ts` | 5,457 | Test file for exec mode |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/droid-request-handler.ts` | 4,994 | Core daemon request handler — the most complex source file |\n| `apps/cli/src/app.tsx` | 4,556 | Monolithic TUI component |\n| `apps/cli/src/services/SessionService.ts` | 3,579 | Session lifecycle service |\n| `apps/cli/src/core/AgentLoop.ts` | 2,647 | Agent loop implementation |\n| `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | 2,572 | WebSocket session controller |\n| `apps/cli/src/hooks/useChatKeyboardInput.ts` | 2,243 | Keyboard input hook |\n\n## The `app.tsx` problem\n\n`apps/cli/src/app.tsx` (4,556 lines) is the monolithic TUI rendering component for the Droid CLI. It contains the session header, conversation thread, tool results display, model selector, settings panel, keyboard shortcuts, and more.\n\nThis file is changed in ~63 of every 90 days. It's one of the highest-friction files to work in — a change to a small component often requires scrolling through thousands of lines to find the right place.\n\n**What would help**: Extract major sections (settings panel, tool result renderers, model selector) into their own component files. The pattern exists in `apps/cli/src/components/` for newer components.\n\n## `droid-request-handler.ts`\n\n`packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/droid-request-handler.ts` (4,994 lines) handles all CLI–daemon communication. It covers session initialization, message relaying, terminal management, computer provisioning, and more.\n\nIts test file is 11,857 lines — the largest file in the project.\n\n**What would help**: 