          "type": "tool_use",
          "name": "Create",
          "input": {
            "content": "# Packages\n\nThe `packages/` directory contains shared libraries that are consumed across Factory's apps (`web`, `desktop`, `backend`, `admin`, `daemon`, `cli`). They are published as npm workspace packages and referenced via `@factory/` scoped imports throughout the monorepo.\n\n| Package | npm name | Purpose |\n|---------|----------|---------|\n| `core-ui` | `@factory/core-ui` | **Mandatory design system.** Layout primitives, form controls, color tokens, typography, and icons for all Factory UI surfaces. |\n| `component-library` | `@factory/component-library` | Reusable layout-focused React components (higher-level than core-ui primitives). |\n| `frontend` | `@factory/frontend` | Platform-agnostic React features, hooks, and services shared between `apps/web` and `apps/desktop`. |\n| `common` | `@factory/common` | Shared TypeScript types, enums, and API contracts between frontend and backend. **The cross-cutting contract layer.** |\n| `droid-core` | `@factory/droid-core` | AI agent core library — tool definitions, LLM provider adapters, streaming utilities, and message types. |\n| `daemon-core` | `@factory/daemon-core` | Business logic for the Factory daemon — session management, WebSocket server, terminal access. |\n| `services` | `@factory/services` | Service layer with settings management, plugin marketplace, and external service integrations. |\n| `logging` | `@factory/logging` | Centralized structured logging, error classes, and metrics instrumentation. |\n| `daemon-client` | `@factory/daemon-client` | Client-side bindings for communicating with the daemon process. |\n| `environment` | `@factory/environment` | Strongly-typed environment variable access (replaces raw `process.env`). |\n| `models` | `@factory/models` | Shared data model definitions. |\n| `updater` | `@factory/updater` | Auto-update logic for the desktop app. |\n| `utils` | `@factory/utils` | General-purpose utilities shared across packages. |\n| `signal-core` | `@factory/signal-core` | Reactive signal primitives. |\n| `runtime` | `@factory/runtime` | Runtime environment detection and helpers. |\n| `mcp` | `@factory/mcp` | Model Context Protocol (MCP) client/server primitives. |\n| `eslint-config` | `@factory/eslint-config` | Shared ESLint configuration for the monorepo. |\n| `test-utils` | `@factory/test-utils` | Test helpers and shared mocks. |\n\n## Packages with cross-cutting importance\n\n- **`@factory/core-ui`** — mandatory for all UI work; never reach for raw `<div>`, `<button>`, or `<input>`. See [`packages/core-ui.md`](./core-ui.md).\n- **`@factory/common`** — every new backend API endpoint must have its request/response types defined here first. See [`packages/common.md`](./common.md).\n- **`@factory/logging`** — all code (server, daemon, CLI) imports `logInfo`, `logWarn`, `logException`, and error classes from here. See [`packages/logging.md`](./logging.md).\n- **`@factory/droid-core`** — the AI agent's tool registry and LLM abstraction live here. See [`packages/droid-core.md`](./droid-core.md).\n",
