            "content": "# @factory/droid-core\n\n**Active contributors (last 90 days):** Leo Tchourakov, Abhay Singhal\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/droid-core` is the AI agent core library. It owns the tool registry, LLM provider adapters, streaming pipeline, and message type definitions that power the Droid CLI agent. The daemon and CLI both depend on this package to execute agent loops.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/droid-core/src/\n├── api/                     # Factory API client helpers (fetch, config, readiness, droid endpoints)\n│   ├── config.ts\n│   ├── droid.ts\n│   ├── fetch.ts\n│   ├── readiness.ts\n│   └── types.ts\n├── automations/             # Automation triggering and management\n├── core/                    # Agent loop core logic\n├── droids/                  # Droid identity and configuration\n├── feature-flags/           # Feature flag evaluation at agent level\n├── llms/                    # LLM provider abstraction layer\n│   ├── provider/\n│   │   ├── anthropic/       # Anthropic (Claude) adapter\n│   │   ├── google/          # Google (Gemini) adapter\n│   │   ├── openai/          # OpenAI adapter\n│   │   └── utils/\n│   ├── errors/              # LLM-specific error types (20 error classes)\n│   ├── index.ts\n│   ├── price.ts\n│   └── types.ts\n├── machine-connection/      # Machine/sandbox connection primitives\n├── messages/                # Message utilities and legacy message types\n│   └── legacy/\n├── prompts/                 # System prompt construction utilities\n├── streaming/               # Streaming data pipeline\n│   ├── schema.ts            # Zod schemas for all stream part types\n│   ├── data-stream-parts.ts # Stream part serialization / deserialization\n│   ├── enums.ts             # StreamPartType enum\n│   ├── types.ts             # Typed stream part interfaces\n│   ├── constants.ts\n│   └── metrics/             # Streaming metrics tracking\n├── test-utils/              # Shared test helpers\n└── tools/                   # Tool registry and definitions\n    ├── registry.ts          # Central tool registry\n    ├── create-tool.ts       # Factory function for defining tools\n    ├── types.ts             # Tool input/output types\n    ├── enums.ts             # ToolName enum\n    ├── definitions/         # Individual tool definitions\n    │   ├── cli/             # CLI-specific tools (21 definitions)\n    │   ├── file-tools/      # File read/write/edit tools (14 definitions)\n    │   ├── mission/         # Mission decomposition tools\n    │   ├── slack/           # Slack integration tools\n    │   ├── todo/            # TodoWrite tool\n    │   └── web/             # Web search tools\n    ├── utils/               # 37 tool utility helpers\n    └── legacy/              # Legacy tool wrappers\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Abstraction | Location | What it does |\n|-------------|----------|--------------|\n| Tool registry | `tools/registry.ts` | Maps `ToolName` → tool definition; the CLI queries this to decide which tools are available in a session |\n| Tool definition | `tools/create-tool.ts` | `createTool({ name, description, inputSchema, execute })` — typed tool factory |\n| LLM provider adapters | `llms/provider/{anthropic,google,openai}/` | Translate droid-core message format ↔ provider-specific API format; handle streaming, token counting, retries |\n| Stream parts | `streaming/schema.ts` + `streaming/enums.ts` | Typed, versioned schema for every chunk that flows over the streaming pipeline (tool calls, text deltas, errors, usage, etc.) |\n| Message types | `messages/` | Canonical message shape shared between CLI and daemon |\n| Prompts | `prompts/` | Helpers for constructing system prompts and injecting context |\n| Feature flags | `feature-flags/` | Evaluated per-agent-call; gates new tool behaviors or model routing |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Tool registry\n\nEach tool is created with `createTool(...)` and registered in `tools/registry.ts`. The registry exposes a typed map so the CLI can enumerate available tools at startup, build the tool list sent to the LLM, and dispatch tool-call results back into the agent loop.\n\n### LLM provider abstraction\n\nThe provider layer normalizes the differences between Anthropic, OpenAI, and Google APIs. Each adapter:\n\n1. Converts droid-core's internal message format to the provider's wire format.\n2. Sends the request (streaming or non-streaming).\n3. Parses the provider's response chunks into typed `StreamPart` objects.\n4. Handles provider-specific errors (see `llms/errors/` — 20 error classes).\n\n### Streaming pipeline\n\nAll LLM responses travel as a sequence of typed `StreamPart` values defined in `streaming/schema.ts`. Consumers (the CLI runner, daemon handler) switch on `StreamPartType` to handle text deltas, tool calls, usage stats, and error conditions in a uniform way.\n\n## LLM request flow\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant CLI as CLI runner\n    participant Core as droid-core agent loop\n    participant Registry as Tool Registry\n    participant Adapter as LLM Provider Adapter\n    participant LLM as LLM API (Anthropic/OpenAI/Google)\n\n    CLI->>Core: send messages + context\n    Core->>Registry: resolve available tools\n    Core->>Adapter: buildRequest(messages, tools)\n    Adapter->>LLM: POST /messages (streaming)\n    LLM-->>Adapter: stream chunks\n    Adapter-->>Core: typed StreamParts\n    Core-->>CLI: forward StreamParts\n    Note over Core: on tool_use chunk → execute tool → append result → loop\n```\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **`apps/cli`** — imports `@factory/droid-core` for tool definitions, LLM adapters, and streaming utilities. The CLI runner drives the agent loop using core's primitives.\n- **`packages/daemon-core`** — imports certain message types and tool schemas from droid-core for the daemon-side request handler.\n- **`apps/backend`** — may use the API client helpers (`api/`) for backend-to-agent calls.\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n| What you want to do | Where to start |\n|---------------------|----------------|\n| Add a new LLM provider | Create `llms/provider/<provider>/` following the pattern of the existing `anthropic/`, `openai/`, or `google/` directories; register in `llms/index.ts` |\n| Add a new tool | Create `tools/definitions/<category>/<tool-name>.ts` using `createTool()`; register in `tools/registry.ts` and add to the `ToolName` enum in `tools/enums.ts` |\n| Change the streaming schema | Edit `streaming/schema.ts` (Zod) and keep `streaming/enums.ts` in sync; update consumers in CLI and daemon |\n| Add a new prompt template | Add a helper in `prompts/` |\n",
