            "content": "# @factory/frontend\n\n**Active contributors (last 90 days):** Andrei Savin, factory-sherry, Alvin Sng\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/frontend` is the shared React feature library for Factory's UI applications. It provides the Redux store, feature modules, routing, auth utilities, services, hooks, and the `DaemonSessionController` — the WebSocket/JSON-RPC bridge to the daemon process. Both `apps/web` and `apps/desktop` import from this package.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/frontend/src/\n├── index.ts                         # Barrel export\n├── api/                             # API client wrappers (HTTP to backend)\n├── app/                             # Redux store setup, root reducers, middleware\n├── auth/                            # Authentication state, guards, user selectors\n├── errors/                          # Frontend error types\n├── features/                        # Feature slices (23 modules)\n│   ├── analytics/\n│   ├── attribution/\n│   ├── auth/\n│   ├── automations/\n│   ├── banner/\n│   ├── debug/\n│   ├── e2e/\n│   ├── error/\n│   ├── feature-flags/\n│   ├── ga-analytics/\n│   ├── health/\n│   ├── home/\n│   ├── missions/\n│   ├── onboarding/\n│   ├── referral/\n│   ├── sessions/\n│   ├── settings/\n│   ├── support/\n│   ├── terminal/\n│   ├── utility/\n│   └── wiki/\n├── hooks/                           # Shared React hooks\n├── layouts/                         # Layout wrapper components\n├── router/                          # Client-side routing (React Router)\n├── services/\n│   └── session/\n│       └── DaemonSessionController.ts  # WebSocket/JSON-RPC bridge to daemon\n├── types/                           # Frontend-specific TypeScript types\n├── utils/                           # Shared utility functions\n└── views/                           # Top-level page views\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Abstraction | Location | What it does |\n|-------------|----------|--------------|\n| `DaemonSessionController` | `services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | Manages the WebSocket connection to the daemon; exposes typed JSON-RPC methods for every daemon operation (session init, terminal I/O, MCP, automations, etc.) |\n| Redux store | `app/` | RTK (Redux Toolkit) store with entity adapters; all feature state lives here |\n| Feature modules | `features/<name>/` | Each module owns its slice, selectors, thunks, and React components for a product area |\n| Router | `router/` | React Router configuration; handles deep-links and auth guards |\n| Auth | `auth/` | Authentication state, user selectors, protected route guards |\n| API client | `api/` | Typed HTTP wrappers calling the `apps/backend` Next.js API routes |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Redux Toolkit + entity adapters\n\nState management uses Redux Toolkit throughout. Feature slices use `createEntityAdapter` for collections (sessions, terminals, automations) and `createSlice` for scalar state. Async work uses `createAsyncThunk`.\n\n### DaemonSessionController — the WebSocket/JSON-RPC bridge\n\n`DaemonSessionController` is the most critical service in this package. It:\n\n1. Opens and maintains a WebSocket connection to `apps/daemon`.\n2. Sends JSON-RPC 2.0 method calls (e.g., `initializeSession`, `createTerminal`, `writeData`, `runAutomation`) and awaits responses.\n3. Subscribes to daemon push notifications (`DaemonDroidEvent`, `DaemonTerminalEvent`, session status changes) and dispatches them to the Redux store.\n4. Handles reconnection, authentication handshake, and connection-state tracking (`ConnectionState` enum).\n\nIt imports its type contracts entirely from `@factory/common/daemon` — `DaemonSessionController.ts` is ~2 500 lines and covers the full surface area of daemon-to-frontend communication.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **`apps/web`** — imports all feature modules, the Redux store, router, and `DaemonSessionController`. The web app is the primary consumer.\n- **`apps/desktop`** — imports the same package; the Electron layer may override specific services (e.g., IPC vs. WebSocket transport), but all feature logic is shared.\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n| What you want to do | Where to start |\n|---------------------|----------------|\n| Add a new product feature | Create `features/<feature-name>/` with a Redux slice, selectors, and components; register the slice in `app/` |\n| Add a new daemon method call | Add the typed method to `DaemonSessionController.ts` (imports from `@factory/common/daemon`) |\n| Add a new route | Edit `router/` and wire the new view from `views/` |\n| Add a shared hook | `hooks/` |\n| Add a backend API call | `api/` — add a typed fetch helper that calls the Next.js API route |\n",
