            "content": "# @factory/common\n\n**Active contributors (last 90 days):** factory-octavian, Arman Bolat, Leo Tchourakov\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/common` is the contract layer for the entire monorepo. It holds shared TypeScript types, enums, Zod schemas, and API type definitions that are imported by virtually every other package — frontend, backend, daemon, CLI, and daemon-core. Defining types here first is a hard rule: **all new backend API endpoints must have their request and response types in `@factory/common` before implementation begins.**\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/common/src/\n├── api/                        # API contracts between services\n│   ├── agent-readiness/        # Agent readiness check types\n│   ├── analytics/              # Analytics event types\n│   ├── backend/                # Backend (Next.js) API types and schemas\n│   ├── daemon/                 # Daemon JSON-RPC types and schemas\n│   ├── shared/                 # Types shared across multiple API surfaces\n│   └── v0/                     # V0 API types\n│       ├── computers/          # Computer/machine types\n│       ├── errors/             # API error shapes\n│       ├── git-ai/             # Git AI feature types\n│       ├── machine-templates/  # Machine template types\n│       ├── organization/       # Organization types\n│       ├── pagination/         # Pagination types\n│       ├── sessions/           # Session types (legacy v0)\n│       └── wiki/               # Wiki types\n├── agent/                      # Agent identity and configuration types\n├── agentReadiness/             # Agent readiness state types\n├── automations/                # Automation types and enums\n├── billing/                    # Billing and subscription types\n├── cli/                        # CLI-specific shared types\n├── daemon/                     # Daemon protocol types (re-exported to consumers)\n├── desktop/                    # Desktop-specific shared types\n├── documents/                  # Document model types\n├── droid/                      # Droid configuration and metadata types\n├── events/                     # Cross-service event types\n├── feature-flags/              # Feature flag name constants and types\n├── images/                     # Image model types\n├── integrations/               # External service integration types\n├── llm/                        # LLM model and usage types\n├── memory/                     # Memory/context storage types\n├── node/                       # Node/machine types\n├── organization/               # Organization model types\n├── policy/                     # Policy and permissions types\n├── relay/                      # Relay service types\n├── repositories/               # Repository model types\n├── security/                   # Security-related types\n├── session/                    # Session model types (18 sub-modules)\n├── sessionV2/                  # Session V2 types\n├── settings/                   # Settings schema types\n├── shared/                     # Cross-cutting shared utilities and types\n├── tags/                       # Tag model types\n├── terminal/                   # Terminal types\n├── timeline/                   # Timeline event types\n├── tools/                      # Tool input/output contract types\n├── ui/                         # UI-specific shared types\n├── updater/                    # Updater types\n├── usage/                      # Usage and quota types\n├── wiki/                       # Wiki feature types\n└── workspaces/                 # Workspace types\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Domain | Location | What it covers |\n|--------|----------|----------------|\n| Daemon protocol | `api/daemon/`, `daemon/` | JSON-RPC method names, params and results for every daemon call (sessions, terminals, MCP, automations) |\n| Backend API | `api/backend/` | Request/response shapes for Next.js API routes |\n| Session types | `session/` | Session model, status enums, event types across 18 sub-modules |\n| Feature flags | `feature-flags/` | Flag name constants — all Statsig flag names live here |\n| LLM types | `llm/` | Model names, provider enums, token usage shapes |\n| Tool contracts | `tools/` | Tool input/output types shared between frontend and daemon |\n| Integrations | `integrations/` | Types for GitHub, Slack, AWS, and other external integrations |\n| Settings schema | `settings/` | Typed settings object shape |\n| Organization | `organization/` | Org, team, and member types |\n\n## Convention: `src/api/{service}/types.ts`\n\nAll new API types follow the pattern:\n\n```\npackages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts    # TypeScript interfaces\npackages/common/src/api/{service}/schemas.ts  # Zod validation schemas (where needed)\npackages/common/src/api/{service}/index.ts    # Barrel re-export\n```\n\nFor example, daemon method params live in `src/api/daemon/types.ts` and are imported in both `packages/daemon-core` (server side) and `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` (client side).\n\n## Rule: types before implementation\n\nBefore opening a PR that adds or changes an API endpoint:\n\n1. Define request params and result types in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts`.\n2. If validation is needed server-side, add a Zod schema in `schemas.ts`.\n3. Export from `index.ts`.\n4. Only then write the implementation in `apps/backend` or `packages/daemon-core`.\n\n## Integration points\n\n`@factory/common` is imported by:\n\n- `packages/frontend` — session types, API types, daemon protocol\n- `packages/daemon-core` — daemon method types, session types\n- `packages/droid-core` — tool contract types, LLM types\n- `packages/services` — settings schema, integration types\n- `packages/logging` — error shapes\n- `apps/backend` — backend API types\n- `apps/cli` — CLI types, tool names\n- `apps/daemon` — re-exports from daemon-core which imports common\n",
