            "content": "# @factory/services\n\n**Active contributors (last 90 days):** Arman Bolat, Alvin Sng, Ricky S\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/services` is the service layer that lives between the `apps/backend` API routes and external dependencies. It encapsulates settings management, plugin/marketplace operations, session search, feature-flag evaluation, and integrations with third-party platforms. Daemon-side code also imports some of these services (particularly settings).\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/services/src/\n├── constants.ts\n├── enums.ts\n├── types.ts\n├── feature-flags/               # Statsig feature-flag evaluation helpers\n├── plugins/                     # Plugin registry and installer\n│   ├── MarketplaceService.ts    # Plugin marketplace catalogue queries\n│   ├── PluginInstaller.ts       # Installs/uninstalls plugins to agent settings\n│   ├── PluginLoader.ts          # Loads installed plugin definitions at runtime\n│   ├── PluginRegistry.ts        # In-memory registry of loaded plugins\n│   └── types.ts\n├── services/                    # External service integrations\n│   ├── anthropic/               # Anthropic API client\n│   ├── aws/                     # AWS SDK wrappers (15 files — S3, EC2, SSM, etc.)\n│   ├── firebase/                # Firebase/Firestore client helpers (10 files)\n│   ├── gcp/                     # GCP client helpers\n│   ├── openai/                  # OpenAI API client\n│   ├── orb/                     # Orb billing service client (7 files)\n│   ├── slack/                   # Slack API client\n│   ├── stripe/                  # Stripe payment service client (7 files)\n│   └── workos/                  # WorkOS auth/SSO client (18 files)\n├── session-search/              # Full-text session search (14 files)\n├── settings/                    # Settings manager — the largest sub-module (41 files)\n│   ├── SettingsManager.ts       # Reads, merges, and writes agent settings\n│   ├── FactorySettingsFolder.ts # ~/.factory settings folder access\n│   ├── AgentSettingsFolder.ts   # Per-agent settings folder\n│   ├── McpSettingsManager.ts    # MCP server settings\n│   ├── PluginMarketplaceManager.ts # Plugin marketplace manager\n│   ├── PluginSettingsLoader.ts  # Loads settings from installed plugins\n│   ├── SettingsResolver.ts      # Resolves the effective settings from multiple sources\n│   ├── SettingsParsing.ts       # Parses raw settings files\n│   ├── RuntimeSettingsOverlay.ts# Applies runtime overrides on top of file settings\n│   └── SkillImportService.ts    # Imports droid skills from git/marketplace\n└── utils/                       # Service utility helpers\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Abstraction | Location | What it does |\n|-------------|----------|--------------|\n| `SettingsManager` | `settings/SettingsManager.ts` | Central settings read/write API; merges settings from project folder, agent folder, plugins, and runtime overlays |\n| `FactorySettingsFolder` | `settings/FactorySettingsFolder.ts` | Access to `~/.factory/` settings directory |\n| `SettingsResolver` | `settings/SettingsResolver.ts` | Resolves the final effective settings by layering sources (global → project → plugin → runtime) |\n| `McpSettingsManager` | `settings/McpSettingsManager.ts` | Manages MCP server configuration (add, remove, toggle) |\n| `PluginMarketplaceManager` | `settings/PluginMarketplaceManager.ts` | Installs/removes plugins from the marketplace |\n| `MarketplaceService` | `plugins/MarketplaceService.ts` | Queries the plugin catalogue |\n| `PluginLoader` | `plugins/PluginLoader.ts` | Loads plugin definitions at daemon startup |\n| External service clients | `services/{anthropic,aws,firebase,openai,orb,stripe,workos,…}/` | Typed wrappers around AWS SDK, Firebase, WorkOS SSO, Stripe, Orb, Slack, etc. |\n| Session search | `session-search/` | Full-text search index over session history |\n| Feature flags | `feature-flags/` | Statsig evaluation helpers |\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **`apps/backend`** — imports the external service clients (`services/`) and settings helpers for API route handlers.\n- **`apps/daemon`** / **`packages/daemon-core`** — imports `SettingsManager`, `FactorySettingsFolder`, and plugin services to read the user's configuration at daemon startup and on settings updates.\n- **`apps/cli`** — imports settings-related services for local configuration management.\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n| What you want to do | Where to start |\n|---------------------|----------------|\n| Add a new external service integration | Create `services/<service-name>/` with a typed client class; follow the pattern in `services/aws/` or `services/stripe/` |\n| Add or change a settings field | Update the settings schema in `@factory/common/src/settings/`, then update `SettingsManager.ts` and `SettingsParsing.ts` |\n| Add a feature flag | Add the flag name to `@factory/common/src/feature-flags/`, then use the flag in `feature-flags/` evaluation helpers |\n| Add a plugin marketplace feature | `plugins/MarketplaceService.ts` and `settings/PluginMarketplaceManager.ts` |\n",
