          "type": "tool_use",
          "name": "Create",
          "input": {
            "content": "# API\n\n`apps/backend` is the central REST API for the Factory platform, built on Next.js 15 App Router and deployed on Vercel. All product surfaces — web, desktop, CLI, admin, and IDE extensions — talk to this service for session management, authentication, billing, LLM proxying, and integrations. Types for every endpoint are defined in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts` and inferred from Zod schemas, ensuring the same contract is enforced at runtime and compile time.\n\n## Conventions\n\n**Base URL:** `https://api.factory.ai` (production) · `https://dev.api.factory.ai` (dev) · `http://localhost:3000` (local)\n\n**Authentication:** Every request must include a bearer token in the `Authorization` header:\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <token>\n```\n\nTwo token types are accepted:\n- **WorkOS access token** — issued by WorkOS AuthKit after the user signs in; validated by `src/app/api/_utils/middleware.ts`.\n- **Factory API key** — a long-lived key with `fk_` prefix, created in Settings → API Keys; validated against Firestore.\n\nUnauthenticated requests to protected endpoints return `401`. Requests from users without an org affiliation return `403`.\n\n**Request/response format:** JSON for all endpoints except the LLM streaming proxy (`/api/llm/`), which streams via [Server-Sent Events](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Server-sent_events).\n\n**CORS:** The backend middleware (`src/middleware.ts`) validates the `Origin` header against an allowlist and sets `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` accordingly. Allowed origins include the Factory web app, desktop app, Vercel preview deployments, and localhost during development.\n\n**Security headers:** Every response carries `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`, a strict `Content-Security-Policy`, `Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy: same-origin`, and `Referrer-Policy: strict-origin`.\n\n**Rate limiting:** Some endpoints enforce per-user rate limits via `src/app/api/_utils/rate-limit.ts`.\n\n## Sub-pages\n\n- [REST endpoints](./rest-endpoints.md) — endpoint groups, routes, and type file locations\n- [WebSocket protocol](./websocket-protocol.md) — daemon WebSocket/JSON-RPC 2.0 API\n\n## WebSocket API\n\nThe real-time channel between the frontend and droid agent processes runs through the **daemon** (`apps/daemon`), not through the backend REST API. See [apps/daemon.md](../apps/daemon.md) and [WebSocket protocol](./websocket-protocol.md) for details.\n",
            "file_path": "/Users/jonathanlucuix-andre/Documents/test-repos/factory-mono/droid-wiki/api/index.md"
