            "content": "# REST endpoints\n\nAll routes live under `apps/backend/src/app/api/` using Next.js 15 App Router conventions. Each directory contains a `route.ts` file that exports HTTP method handlers (`GET`, `POST`, `PATCH`, `DELETE`).\n\nTypes for every group are defined in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts` and inferred from Zod schemas. The API type directories mirror the backend route structure.\n\n---\n\n## `/api/auth/` — Authentication\n\nHandles WorkOS callback and token exchange after the OAuth redirect.\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/auth/actions` | POST | Triggers WorkOS auth actions (e.g., sign-in initiation) |\n| `/api/auth/set-integration-token` | POST | Stores an integration OAuth token for the authed user |\n| `/api/auth/verify-token` | GET | Verifies a bearer token and returns the decoded user |\n\nNo dedicated types package — auth types live in `packages/common/src/api/backend/types.ts`.\n\n---\n\n## `/api/sessions/` — Session management\n\nCRUD and lifecycle operations for droid agent sessions. Sessions are the core data model — each one represents a conversation with the AI agent.\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/sessions/create` | POST | Creates a new session |\n| `/api/sessions/archived` | GET | Lists archived sessions |\n| `/api/sessions/search` | GET | Full-text search across sessions |\n| `/api/sessions/[sessionId]` | GET / DELETE | Fetch or delete a session |\n| `/api/sessions/[sessionId]/archive` | POST | Archive a session |\n| `/api/sessions/[sessionId]/unarchive` | POST | Unarchive a session |\n| `/api/sessions/[sessionId]/memory` | GET / POST | Read or write session memory |\n| `/api/sessions/[sessionId]/message` | POST | Append a message |\n| `/api/sessions/[sessionId]/privacy` | PATCH | Change the session privacy level |\n| `/api/sessions/[sessionId]/sandbox` | POST | Create a sandbox from the session workspace |\n| `/api/sessions/[sessionId]/stop-droid` | POST | Stop the running droid process |\n| `/api/sessions/[sessionId]/update-title` | POST | Rename a session |\n| `/api/sessions/[sessionId]/droid-status` | GET | Current droid execution state |\n| `/api/sessions/v2/` | — | V2 session API (see `packages/common/src/api/v0/sessions/`) |\n\nTypes: `packages/common/src/api/v0/sessions/types.ts`\n\n---\n\n## `/api/organization/` — Organization and members\n\nOrg-level configuration, member management, and billing subscription.\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/organization/info` | GET | Org details |\n| `/api/organization/create` | POST | Create a new org |\n| `/api/organization/members` | GET / POST / DELETE | List, invite, or remove members |\n| `/api/organization/policy` | GET / PUT | Read or update org-wide AI policies |\n| `/api/organization/managed-settings` | GET / PUT | Org-level managed settings |\n| `/api/organization/subscription` | GET / POST | Current plan and subscription management |\n| `/api/organization/integrations` | GET | List connected integrations |\n| `/api/organization/agent-readiness-reports` | GET / POST | Agent readiness assessment results |\n| `/api/organization/onboarding` | POST | Mark onboarding steps complete |\n| `/api/organization/referral` | GET | Fetch referral code |\n| `/api/organization/tool-settings` | GET / PATCH | Tool-call settings (confirmations, timeouts) |\n| `/api/organization/user-profile` | GET / PUT | Per-user profile within an org |\n\nTypes: `packages/common/src/api/backend/types.ts`, `packages/common/src/api/agent-readiness/types.ts`\n\n---\n\n## `/api/llm/` — LLM proxy\n\nForwards streaming chat completion requests to the upstream LLM provider selected by the client. This is the highest-traffic endpoint.\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/llm/a` | POST | Streaming completions via Anthropic |\n| `/api/llm/g` | POST | Streaming completions via Google |\n| `/api/llm/o` | POST | Streaming completions via OpenAI |\n| `/api/llm/custom` | POST | Completions via a user-configured custom provider |\n| `/api/llm/failed-requests` | POST | Logs failed LLM requests for debugging |\n\nThe proxy validates entitlements, streams Server-Sent Events back to the client, and meters usage through Orb.\n\nTypes: `packages/common/src/api/backend/types.ts`\n\n---\n\n## `/api/billing/` — Billing\n\nBilling portal access, plan limits, and payment method management.\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/billing/portal` | POST | Returns a Stripe billing portal URL |\n| `/api/billing/payment-method` | GET / POST | Read or update payment method |\n| `/api/billing/overage` | GET | Current overage details |\n| `/api/billing/user-limits` | GET | Per-user usage limits |\n| `/api/billing/limits` | GET | Org-level limits |\n| `/api/billing/extra-usage` | POST | Request additional usage |\n\nTypes: `packages/common/src/api/backend/types.ts`\n\n---\n\n## `/api/integrations/` — Third-party integrations\n\nOAuth flows and integration management for GitHub, GitLab, Jira, Linear, Notion, PagerDuty, Sentry, and Slack.\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/integrations/oauth-client-ids` | GET | Returns public OAuth client IDs per provider |\n| `/api/integrations/generate-oauth-state` | POST | Generates a CSRF state token for OAuth |\n| `/api/integrations/redirect` | GET | OAuth redirect callback handler |\n| `/api/integrations/get-usernames` | GET | Fetch usernames from connected SCM accounts |\n| `/api/integrations/validate-username` | GET | Check if a username is valid for a provider |\n| `/api/integrations/scm` | GET / POST | Source control manager integration config |\n| `/api/integrations/slack` | GET / POST | Slack integration config |\n| `/api/integrations/org` | GET | Org-level integration status |\n| `/api/integrations/user` | GET | User-level integration status |\n\nIntegration tokens are encrypted with AES before storage in Firestore (see `packages/services/src/utils/encryption/encryptionManager.ts`).\n\nTypes: `packages/common/src/api/backend/types.ts`\n\n---\n\n## `/api/github/` — GitHub-specific\n\nGitHub OAuth, webhook processing, and PR comment management.\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/github/` | GET / POST | GitHub OAuth callback and webhook ingestion |\n| `/api/github/pr-comments` | GET | List PR review comments |\n\nTypes: `packages/common/src/api/backend/types.ts` (`PRCommentsResponse`, `ExternalPRComment`)\n\n---\n\n## `/api/tools/` — Tool call results\n\nStores tool call results and confirmations from agent sessions.\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/tools/` | POST | Record the result of a tool call |\n\n---\n\n## `/api/feature-flags/` — Feature flags\n\nEvaluates Statsig feature flags for the requesting user/org.\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/feature-flags/` | GET | Evaluates all flags for the authenticated user |\n| `/api/feature-flags/[flagName]` | GET | Evaluates a single flag |\n\n---\n\n## `/api/daemon/` — Daemon download and heartbeat\n\nServes the daemon binary download manifest and receives heartbeat pings from running daemon processes.\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/daemon/` | GET | Download manifest for the latest daemon binary |\n\nTypes: `packages/common/src/api/daemon/types.ts` (`DaemonHeartbeatRequest`, `DaemonHeartbeatResponse`)\n\n---\n\n## `/api/cli/` — CLI download\n\nServes the CLI binary download manifest.\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/cli/` | GET | Download manifest for the latest CLI binary |\n\n---\n\n## `/api/desktop/` — Desktop update manifest\n\nVersion information for the Electron desktop app.\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/desktop/` | GET | Minimum required desktop version |\n\nTypes: `packages/common/src/api/backend/types.ts` (`MinimumVersionResponse`)\n\n---\n\n## `/api/workspaces/` — Cloud development environments\n\nWorkspace (CDE) lifecycle management.\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/workspaces/[workspaceId]/sandbox/create` | POST | Provision a sandbox from a workspace |\n\nTypes: `packages/common/src/api/backend/types.ts` (`CreateSandboxFromWorkspaceResponse`)\n\n---\n\n## `/api/v0/` — Versioned API (v0)\n\nThe `/api/v0/` namespace groups newer endpoints that are versioned from the start.\n\n### `/api/v0/wiki/` — Wiki runs\n\nManages wiki generation runs for repositories.\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/v0/wiki` | GET | List the latest wiki run per repo |\n| `/api/v0/wiki` | POST | Trigger a new wiki run |\n| `/api/v0/wiki/[wikiRunId]` | GET | Get a specific wiki run |\n| `/api/v0/wiki/[wikiRunId]/pages/[pageId]` | GET | Get a single wiki page |\n| `/api/v0/wiki/history/[repoUrl]` | GET | List historical wiki runs for a repo |\n\nTypes: `packages/common/src/api/v0/wiki/types.ts`\n\n### `/api/v0/sessions/` — V2 session API\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/v0/sessions` | GET / POST | List or create sessions (v0 schema) |\n| `/api/v0/sessions/[sessionId]/messages` | GET | Paginated message history |\n\nTypes: `packages/common/src/api/v0/sessions/types.ts`\n\n### `/api/v0/computers/` — Computer-use sessions\n\nManages computer-use agent sessions (browser automation, BYOI desktop).\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/v0/computers` | GET / POST | List or create computer sessions |\n| `/api/v0/computers/name` | GET | Suggest a session name |\n| `/api/v0/computers/[computerId]` | GET / PATCH / DELETE | Manage a computer session |\n\nTypes: `packages/common/src/api/v0/computers/types.ts`\n\n### `/api/v0/git-ai/` — Git AI\n\nAI-assisted git operations.\n\nTypes: `packages/common/src/api/v0/git-ai/types.ts`\n\n### `/api/v0/organization/` — Org v0 endpoints\n\n| Route | Method | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/api/v0/organization` | GET | Org info (v0 schema) |\n\nTypes: `packages/