            "content": "# Factory monorepo overview\n\nFactory is an AI software engineering platform built around a CLI agent called Droid. The platform lets developers run AI-powered sessions that can read files, execute commands, write code, and interact with external tools—all orchestrated through a local daemon and backed by a cloud API.\n\nThe monorepo ships every piece of that system: the CLI, daemon, web app, desktop app, backend API, internal tooling, shared packages, and infrastructure.\n\n## What the product does\n\n- **Droid CLI (`apps/cli`)** — a terminal-based AI coding assistant. Users type in natural language; Droid plans and executes multi-step coding tasks using tools (file read/write, shell execution, search, MCP tools, etc.)\n- **Factory web app (`apps/web`)** — a browser-based interface to view and manage Droid sessions\n- **Factory Desktop (`apps/desktop`)** — an Electron wrapper that bundles the web app with a local daemon for a native desktop experience\n- **Factory Daemon (`apps/daemon`, `packages/daemon-core`)** — a background process (`factoryd`) that mediates between the frontend and the CLI process over WebSocket/JSON-RPC\n- **Backend API (`apps/backend`)** — a Next.js API providing REST endpoints for auth, sessions, billing, LLM proxying, integrations, and more\n\n## Repository map\n\n| Layer | Location | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| CLI | `apps/cli` | Terminal UI and AI agent loop |\n| Daemon | `apps/daemon` | Local background service (factoryd) |\n| Web app | `apps/web` | Browser-based session viewer |\n| Desktop | `apps/desktop` | Electron desktop wrapper |\n| Backend API | `apps/backend` | REST API and LLM proxy |\n| Admin | `apps/admin` | Internal admin dashboard |\n| Relay | `apps/relay` | Signal relay service |\n| Signal | `apps/signal` | Real-time signal layer |\n| VSCode ext | `apps/factory-vscode-extension` | IDE integration |\n| AI agent core | `packages/droid-core` | LLM integrations, tool definitions, streaming |\n| Design system | `packages/core-ui` | Shared component library (mandatory for UI) |\n| Shared features | `packages/frontend` | React features shared across web and desktop |\n| Shared types | `packages/common` | API contracts, enums, schemas |\n| Settings logic | `packages/services` | Business logic and external service integrations |\n| Infrastructure | `infra/` | OpenTofu (Terraform) IaC for AWS and GCP |\n| Internal tools | `internal/web` | Employee-only web app (internal.factory.ai) |\n\n## Quick links\n\n- [Architecture](architecture.md) — component diagram and data flow\n- [Getting started](getting-started.md) — how to build, test, and run locally\n- [Contributing](../how-to-contribute/index.md) — PR process and conventions\n- [CLI app](../apps/cli/index.md) — deep dive into the Droid CLI\n- [Daemon](../apps/daemon.md) — factoryd background service\n- [Packages](../packages/index.md) — shared library catalog\n",
