            "content": "# Architecture\n\nFactory is built as a three-tier system: a browser/desktop frontend, a local daemon, and a CLI agent process. All communication between tiers uses JSON-RPC 2.0.\n\n## Language breakdown\n\n```mermaid\npie title Source by language\n    \"TypeScript\" : 5108\n    \"Python (infra)\" : 40\n    \"HCL (infra)\" : 20\n```\n\nThe codebase is almost entirely TypeScript. Python and HCL appear only in `infra/` for infrastructure automation.\n\n## System components\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    subgraph \"User interfaces\"\n        WEB[\"apps/web\\n(Vite + React)\"]\n        DESKTOP[\"apps/desktop\\n(Electron)\"]\n        ADMIN[\"apps/admin\\n(Next.js)\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Local machine\"\n        DAEMON[\"apps/daemon\\n(factoryd, Bun)\"]\n        CLI[\"apps/cli\\n(Droid, Bun)\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Cloud\"\n        BACKEND[\"apps/backend\\n(Next.js API)\"]\n        RELAY[\"apps/relay\\n(Signal relay)\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"External services\"\n        LLM[\"LLM providers\\n(Anthropic, OpenAI, Google)\"]\n        GH[\"GitHub\"]\n        LINEAR[\"Linear\"]\n        FIREBASE[\"Firestore\"]\n    end\n\n    WEB -->|WebSocket JSON-RPC| DAEMON\n    DESKTOP -->|WebSocket JSON-RPC| DAEMON\n    DAEMON -->|stdin/stdout JSON-RPC| CLI\n    WEB -->|HTTPS REST| BACKEND\n    DESKTOP -->|HTTPS REST| BACKEND\n    BACKEND -->|proxy| LLM\n    BACKEND -->|integrations| GH\n    BACKEND -->|integrations| LINEAR\n    BACKEND -->|data| FIREBASE\n    CLI -->|HTTPS REST| BACKEND\n    RELAY -->|signal| WEB\n    RELAY -->|signal| DESKTOP\n```\n\n## Communication protocol\n\nThe three-tier communication is detailed in `docs/debugging-daemon.md`:\n\n```\nFrontend (DaemonSessionController.ts)\n    ↓ WebSocket JSON-RPC 2.0\nDaemon (droid-request-handler.ts)\n    ↓ stdin/stdout JSON-RPC 2.0\nCLI (streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts)\n```\n\nThe daemon spawns the CLI as a child process and acts as a broker:\n- Frontend sends requests (initialize session, add message, interrupt) to daemon\n- Daemon forwards them to the CLI process over stdin\n- CLI streams back notifications (tool calls, partial messages, status updates) over stdout\n- Daemon forwards these as notifications to the frontend\n\nSchemas and enums for this protocol live in `packages/common/src/droid/`.\n\n## Key architectural decisions\n\n**Daemon as broker:** The frontend never communicates with the CLI directly. The daemon (`factoryd`) mediates, tracks session state, and handles reconnection. This lets multiple clients (web, desktop) connect to the same running sessions and allows the daemon to restart the CLI on crash without losing the session.\n\n**Single executable CLI:** The CLI bundles into a single executable (SEA via Bun) for distribution. Native libraries (keytar, ripgrep, bun-pty) are embedded at build time in `embed-native-libs.ts`.\n\n**Monorepo with Turborepo:** All apps and packages are versioned together. Turborepo handles build ordering, caching, and parallel task execution. The `packages/common` package is the canonical home for all shared API types and enums.\n\n**Feature flags via Statsig:** All in-progress features are gated behind Statsig feature flags defined in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`. See [feature flags reference](../reference/configuration.md).\n\n## Data flow for a user message\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant Frontend\n    participant Daemon\n    participant CLI\n    participant LLM\n\n    User->>Frontend: types message\n    Frontend->>Daemon: addUserMessage (JSON-RPC)\n    Daemon->>CLI: addUserMessage (stdin)\n    CLI->>LLM: streaming request\n    LLM-->>CLI: token stream\n    CLI-->>Daemon: sessionNotification (stdout)\n    Daemon-->>Frontend: sessionNotification (WebSocket)\n    Frontend-->>User: renders assistant response\n```\n\n## Application ports\n\n| App | Default port | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `apps/backend` | 3000 | API and Next.js server |\n| `apps/admin` | 3001 | Admin dashboard |\n| `apps/web` | 3002 | Main web app |\n| `apps/daemon` (prod) | 37643 | factoryd WebSocket |\n| `apps/daemon` (dev) | 41723 | factoryd WebSocket dev |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Getting started](getting-started.md) — how to run the stack locally\n- [CLI app](../apps/cli/index.md) — agent loop and tool execution details\n- [Daemon app](../apps/daemon.md) — daemon lifecycle and request handling\n- [Droid-core package](../packages/droid-core.md) — LLM integrations and streaming\n",
