            "content": "# Getting started\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- **Node.js** 18.x (see `.nvmrc` — run `nvm use` if you use nvm)\n- **Bun** 1.3.10 (used for CLI and daemon)\n- **npm** 11.x (workspace management and most scripts)\n- **Git** 2.x\n\nOptional but recommended:\n- **nvm** for Node version management\n- **OpenTofu** for infrastructure changes (`infra/`)\n\n## Clone and install\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/Factory-AI/factory-mono.git\ncd factory-mono\nnpm install\n```\n\n`npm install` runs `postinstall`, which triggers `turbo run setup` across all packages.\n\n## Environment setup\n\nEach app has `.env` and `.env.local` files. Copy the examples and fill in credentials:\n\n```bash\n# Backend (required for API to start)\ncp apps/backend/.env.example apps/backend/.env.local\n\n# CLI\ncp apps/cli/.env.development apps/cli/.env.local\n```\n\nKey environment variables:\n\n| Variable | Where | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `WORKOS_CLIENT_ID` | `apps/backend/.env.local` | WorkOS authentication |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | `apps/backend/.env.local` | LLM proxy |\n| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | `apps/backend/.env.local` | LLM proxy |\n| `FACTORY_API_KEY_DEV` | `apps/cli/.env.local` | CLI auth for dev API |\n\n## Start the web stack\n\n```bash\n# Starts: backend (3000), web (3002), storybook, admin (3001), daemon (41723 dev)\nnpm run dev:web\n```\n\nThis streams logs to both the console and disk:\n\n| App | Log file |\n|---|---|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n\n## Run the CLI in dev mode\n\nAfter `npm run dev:web` is running:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup\ndroid-dev   # runs against hosted dev API\n# or\ndroid-localhost  # runs against local API (localhost:3000)\n```\n\n`droid-dev` and `droid-localhost` are wrapper scripts created by `npm run setup`. They run the CLI from source via Bun, so code changes are immediately available without rebuilding.\n\n## Build everything\n\n```bash\nnpm run build\n```\n\nBuild outputs go to `dist/` within each app/package. The CLI and daemon produce single-file executables.\n\n## Run tests\n\n```bash\n# All tests (WARNING: runs ~9 GB of tests — see filtering note below)\nnpm run test\n\n# Targeted: specific package(s)\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common --filter=@factory/daemon-core\n\n# Single test file\ncd apps/cli && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run path/to/file.test.ts\n```\n\n> **Important:** Always use `--` before `--filter` when running from the root. Without it, npm eats the flag and Turborepo runs all packages.\n\n## TypeScript checks\n\n```bash\nnpm run typecheck\n# or targeted:\nnpm run typecheck -- --filter=@factory/frontend\n```\n\n## Lint and format\n\n```bash\nnpm run fix        # lint + format (preferred)\nnpm run lint       # lint only\nnpm run format     # format only\n```\n\n## Storybook\n\n```bash\nnpm run storybook\n# or from the app:\ncd apps/storybook && npm run dev\n```\n\nView all `@factory/core-ui` components at http://localhost:6006.\n\n## Desktop app\n\n```bash\nnpm run dev:desktop   # starts web stack + Electron (local only, not over SSH)\n```\n\n## After modifying CLI or daemon code\n\n1. `cd apps/cli && npm run setup` — rebuild CLI wrappers\n2. Kill and restart the daemon process\n3. Start a new Droid session (old sessions won't pick up changes)\n\nSee [debugging](../how-to-contribute/debugging.md) for more on the development cycle.\n",
