            "content": "# Glossary\n\nTerms used throughout the Factory codebase and this wiki.\n\n## Core product\n\n**Droid** — the AI coding assistant. \"Droid\" refers both to the CLI binary (`droid`) and the AI agent it runs.\n\n**Session** — a single conversation between a user and Droid. Sessions have a unique ID, persist to disk (`.factory/sessions/`), and can be loaded, continued, or archived. The canonical type is in `packages/common/src/session/`.\n\n**factoryd** — the Factory daemon process (`apps/daemon`). It runs in the background on the user's machine (or on a remote CDE) and manages Droid agent processes over WebSocket/JSON-RPC.\n\n**CDE (Cloud Development Environment)** — a remote machine where Droid sessions run, managed by Factory infrastructure.\n\n**Mission** — a larger-scoped task decomposed into multiple sub-sessions. Missions are managed by a \"mission orchestrator\" and run parallel worker sessions.\n\n**Worker session** — a subordinate Droid session launched by a mission to handle a specific subtask.\n\n## Protocol terms\n\n**JSON-RPC 2.0** — the wire protocol used between all three tiers (frontend ↔ daemon ↔ CLI). Requests have a method name and params; responses contain result or error.\n\n**Notification** — a one-way JSON-RPC message (no response expected). The CLI sends notifications to the daemon to stream tool call results, partial messages, and status updates.\n\n**SessionNotification** — the specific notification type the CLI sends upstream for events within a session. Types are defined in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`.\n\n**Streaming JSON-RPC exec** — the mechanism by which the daemon runs a CLI process and streams its stdout as notifications. Implemented in `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts`.\n\n## Code concepts\n\n**Assembly** — the Redux state slice in `packages/frontend` that holds the current session's message tree. Named after \"assembly\" as in assembling a response.\n\n**Fragment** — a unit within a message (text, code block, tool call, etc.). Rendered by the CLI's `MessageList` component.\n\n**Tool executor** — a class that implements a specific tool (Read, Execute, Grep, etc.) callable by the AI agent. Client-side executors live in `apps/cli/src/tools/executors/client/`.\n\n**ACP (Agent Control Protocol)** — an internal protocol for managing agent lifecycle and task decomposition. Files in `apps/cli/src/acp/`.\n\n**Skill** — a user-defined or built-in Markdown instruction set that can be loaded into a Droid session to extend its capabilities. Skills live in `.factory/skills/`.\n\n**Hook** — a user-configurable script that runs at specific lifecycle points (e.g., before a session starts, after a tool runs). Configured in `.factory/hooks/`.\n\n**MCP (Model Context Protocol)** — an open protocol for connecting AI models to external tools and data sources. Factory supports MCP servers, managed via `apps/cli/src/mcp/McpHub.ts`.\n\n## Frontend/UI terms\n\n**core-ui** — the mandatory design system package (`@factory/core-ui`). All UI must use `Box`, `Button`, `Input`, and other primitives from this package rather than raw HTML elements.\n\n**Ink** — the React-for-terminals library used to render the CLI's TUI. Components use `Box`, `Text` from `ink` instead of HTML.\n\n**Storybook** — the component explorer at `apps/storybook`. All core-ui components are documented here.\n\n**Statsig** — the feature flag service used to gate in-progress features. Flag definitions are in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`.\n\n## Infrastructure terms\n\n**OpenTofu** — the open-source Terraform alternative used for IaC in `infra/`. Use `tofu` commands (not `terraform`) for infrastructure changes.\n\n**WorkOS** — the auth provider. Used for SSO (AuthKit) and user management across web, desktop, and internal apps.\n\n**Orb** — the billing provider used for subscription and usage tracking.\n\n**Firestore** — the primary database (Firebase/Cloud Firestore) for session data, user records, and org data.\n\n**E2B** — the cloud sandbox provider used for running Droid sessions in isolated environments.\n\n## Development terms\n\n**dev:web** — the root-level npm script (`npm run dev:web`) that starts backend, web, storybook, admin, and daemon together. The canonical way to start the dev stack.\n\n**droid-dev** — a wrapper binary created by `cd apps/cli && npm run setup` that runs the CLI from source against the hosted dev API.\n\n**droid-localhost** — same as droid-dev but routes to `localhost:3000`.\n\n**turborepo** — the build system orchestrating all packages. Most npm scripts (`build`, `test`, `lint`, `fix`) delegate to `turbo run <task>`.\n",
