            "content": "# How to contribute\n\nThis section covers the practical side of working in the Factory monorepo — from picking up tickets to getting code merged.\n\n## Quick orientation\n\n1. Read [getting started](../overview/getting-started.md) to get the dev stack running\n2. Check the [PR conventions](development-workflow.md#pr-conventions) before opening a pull request\n3. Every change needs a Linear ticket reference in the PR description\n4. Run `npm run fix` before pushing to avoid lint failures in CI\n\n## Sections\n\n- [Development workflow](development-workflow.md) — branch, code, test, PR, merge\n- [Testing](testing.md) — how to run, write, and mock tests\n- [Debugging](debugging.md) — logs, common errors, troubleshooting\n- [Patterns and conventions](patterns-and-conventions.md) — error handling, imports, component rules\n- [Tooling](tooling.md) — build system, linters, CI workflows\n\n## Definition of done\n\nA change is ready for review when:\n- All tests pass (`npm run test -- --filter=<affected-packages>`)\n- TypeScript checks pass (`npm run typecheck -- --filter=<affected-packages>`)\n- Lint is clean (`npm run fix`)\n- A Linear ticket is referenced in the PR description\n- You've self-reviewed the diff for regressions\n",
