            "content": "# Development workflow\n\n## Branch and PR flow\n\n1. Create a branch off `dev` (the default integration branch):\n   ```bash\n   git checkout dev\n   git pull\n   git checkout -b feat/fac-1234-my-feature\n   ```\n2. Write code and tests; run `npm run fix` often\n3. Open a PR against `dev`\n4. Get review and merge\n\nThe main branch (`main`) receives releases, not direct commits. All day-to-day development merges to `dev`.\n\n## PR conventions\n\n**Title format:** `type(scope): description`\n\n- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`\n- Scope: workspace name (e.g., `cli`, `backend`, `frontend`, `daemon`) or `monorepo`\n- Example: `feat(cli): add wiki upload command`\n\n**PR description** must include a Linear ticket reference:\n- `Closes FAC-1234` — closes the ticket on merge\n- `Part of FAC-1234` — links without closing\n\nFill out the PR template sections: description, related issue, risk/impact, and how you tested.\n\n## Commit style\n\nThe repo uses conventional commits. CI enforces the format via `.github/workflows/pr-conventions.yml`.\n\n```\nfeat(cli): add streaming progress indicator\nfix(daemon): handle session cleanup on crash\nchore(monorepo): bump turbo to 2.6.3\n```\n\n## Running targeted checks\n\nNever run `npm run test` from root without `--filter` — it consumes ~9 GB of RAM:\n\n```bash\n# Run tests for only the packages you changed\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/frontend --filter=@factory/common\n\n# TypeScript check\nnpm run typecheck -- --filter=@factory/frontend\n\n# Lint + format (fixes automatically)\nnpm run fix -- --filter=@factory/frontend\n```\n\nThe `--` is required to pass `--filter` through npm to Turborepo.\n\n## After changes to CLI or daemon\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup\n# Kill the running daemon, then restart with:\nnpm run dev:web\n# Start a new Droid session (old sessions don't reload)\n```\n\n## Hotfixes\n\nThe repo has a `hotfix-cut.yml` workflow for cutting hotfix releases. Hotfixes branch off `main`, not `dev`. See `.github/workflows/hotfix-cut.yml`.\n\n## Release process\n\nReleases are managed by a set of GitHub Actions workflows:\n- `release-cut.yml` — creates a release branch and bumps version\n- `release-bump-version.yml` — bumps version numbers\n- `cli-release.yml` — builds and publishes CLI binaries\n- `desktop-release.yml` — builds and signs desktop app\n\nSee [deployment](../deployment/index.md) for the full release pipeline.\n",
