            "content": "# Testing\n\n## Test frameworks\n\n| Context | Framework | Config |\n|---|---|---|\n| Backend, CLI, daemon, packages | Jest + ts-jest | `jest.config.cjs` per package |\n| Frontend (`packages/frontend`) | Vitest | `vitest.config.ts` |\n| CLI E2E (TUI) | `@microsoft/tui-test` | `tui-test.config.ts` |\n| Frontend E2E | Playwright | `packages/frontend/playwright.config.ts` |\n\n## Running tests\n\n```bash\n# All tests — only run if you want everything (~9 GB RAM)\nnpm run test\n\n# Targeted — pass --filter\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/daemon-core --filter=apps/cli\n\n# Single file (Jest)\ncd apps/cli && npx jest src/services/SessionService.test.ts\n\n# Single file (Vitest)\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run src/features/sessions/hooks/useSession.test.ts\n\n# Frontend E2E\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e\n# Visual/debug mode\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e -- --headed --debug\n\n# CLI TUI E2E\ncd apps/cli && npx tui-test run\n```\n\n## Unit test conventions\n\nUnit tests are 1:1 with a single source file. Test only the public API of the file under test; stub only heavy or non-deterministic cross-file calls.\n\n```ts\n// Standard mock pattern\njest.mock('./some-module', () => ({\n  ...jest.requireActual('./some-module'),\n  fetchData: jest.fn(),\n}));\n\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetAllMocks());\n```\n\n### jsdom for frontend tests\n\nAny test that uses React hooks, components, or browser APIs needs `jsdom`:\n\n```ts\n/**\n * @jest-environment jsdom\n */\nimport { renderHook } from '@testing-library/react';\n```\n\nWithout this pragma you'll get `ReferenceError: document is not defined`.\n\n### Singleton isolation\n\nWhen testing modules with singletons (services that initialize once), isolate modules per test:\n\n```ts\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetModules());\n\nit('initializes with correct config', async () => {\n  const { getService } = await import('./service');\n  // fresh instance for each test\n});\n```\n\n## What to test\n\n**Backend/CLI/daemon:** Jest integration-style tests. The session service (`SessionService.test.ts` at 5,116 lines) and daemon handler (`droid-request-handler.test.ts` at 11,857 lines) are good reference examples.\n\n**Frontend packages:** Vitest with Testing Library for hook and component tests. See `packages/frontend/src/features/` for examples.\n\n**CLI TUI:** Use `@microsoft/tui-test` for terminal UI interaction tests. Examples in `apps/cli/e2e-tests/`.\n\n**E2E:** Playwright tests in `packages/frontend`. See `docs/playwright-e2e-testing.md` for setup and patterns.\n\n## Coverage\n\nCoverage reports output to `coverage/` within each package. CI runs targeted tests on affected packages (see `.github/workflows/check-affected.yml`).\n",
