            "content": "# Debugging\n\n## Log locations\n\n| Environment | Directory | Key files |\n|---|---|---|\n| Development | `~/.factory-dev/logs/` | `factoryd.log`, `droid-log-single.log`, `console.log` |\n| Production | `~/.factory/logs/` | Same files |\n\nDev uses `~/.factory-dev/`, not `~/.factory/`. This is a common source of confusion when logs appear empty.\n\n```bash\n# Watch all dev logs in real time\ntail -f ~/.factory-dev/logs/*.log\n\n# Search for a specific feature\ngrep \"wiki\" ~/.factory-dev/logs/droid-log-single.log\n\n# Check daemon logs\ngrep \"error\" ~/.factory-dev/logs/factoryd.log\n```\n\n## Dev server logs\n\nWhen running `npm run dev:web`, each process streams to a file:\n\n| App | Log file |\n|---|---|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n| daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n\n```bash\ntail -f /tmp/factory-dev-backend.log\n```\n\n## Quick debug checklist\n\nWhen changes aren't showing up or behavior is unexpected:\n\n- [ ] Rebuilt CLI: `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`\n- [ ] Restarted daemon (kill process, restart `npm run dev:web`)\n- [ ] Started a new session (old sessions load cached state)\n- [ ] Checking the right log directory (`~/.factory-dev/` for dev)\n- [ ] Schema/enum changes are in `@factory/common` (not in a local package)\n- [ ] Frontend handler exists for any new notification type\n\n## Tracing message flow\n\nTo trace a message through the full stack:\n\n```bash\n# 1. Check CLI sent the notification\ngrep \"your-feature\" ~/.factory-dev/logs/droid-log-single.log\n\n# 2. Check daemon received it\ngrep \"your-feature\" ~/.factory-dev/logs/factoryd.log\n```\n\nThe three layers are:\n- **Frontend** — `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts`\n- **Daemon** — `apps/daemon/src/services/` and `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/droid-request-handler.ts`\n- **CLI** — `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts`\n\n## Common issues\n\n### Schema mismatches (notification not received)\n\n1. Is the notification type in `SessionNotificationType` enum? → `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`\n2. Is there a schema definition? → `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/cli.ts`\n3. Is there a frontend handler? → `DaemonSessionController.ts`\n\n### Timing: notification sent before session is ready\n\nNotifications sent before the session is registered with the daemon are silently dropped. Always emit notifications after session initialization completes, not during startup.\n\n### TypeScript errors after adding to common\n\nAfter adding a new type or enum to `packages/common`, rebuild the package:\n\n```bash\nnpm run build -- --filter=@factory/common\n```\n\nThen restart your dev server.\n\n## Adding debug logging\n\n```typescript\nimport { logInfo, logWarn } from '@factory/logging';\n\nlogInfo(`[Feature] Processing ${items.length} items`);\nlogWarn(`[Feature] Unexpected state: ${JSON.stringify(state)}`);\n```\n\nNever call `logError` — use `logException` when handling an error locally, or just rethrow. See [patterns and conventions](patterns-and-conventions.md) for the full error handling rules.\n\n## Infrastructure debugging\n\nFor `infra/` issues, use OpenTofu commands:\n\n```bash\ncd infra\ntofu init\ntofu validate\ntofu plan\n```\n\nDo not use `terraform` — the repo uses OpenTofu.\n",
