            "content": "# Patterns and conventions\n\n## Imports\n\n- Use absolute imports everywhere: `@factory/...`, `@/...` — never relative paths like `../../utils`\n- No `require()` — use ES6 `import`\n- ESLint enforces import order. Run `npm run fix` to auto-sort\n\n## File organization\n\nESLint rules enforce structure (see `packages/eslint-config/`):\n\n| Content | Where it goes |\n|---|---|\n| TypeScript enums | `enums.ts` in the relevant package |\n| TypeScript types | `types.ts` in the relevant package |\n| API types for an endpoint | `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts` |\n| UI components | Must use `@factory/core-ui` primitives |\n\nNever add an API endpoint without defining its request/response types in `@factory/common`.\n\n## Error handling\n\nFull rules in `docs/error-handling.md`. Key points:\n\n**Throw rich errors, not vanilla `Error`:**\n```typescript\nimport { MetaError, ResponseError404NotFound } from '@factory/logging/errors';\n\n// Internal unexpected failure\nthrow new MetaError('Expected session to exist', { sessionId });\n\n// HTTP 404\nthrow new ResponseError404NotFound('Session not found', { sessionId });\n```\n\n**Don't wrap with try/catch unless you have a reason.** Let errors bubble to middleware.\n\n**One or the other — log OR rethrow, never both:**\n```typescript\n// Handled locally: log, don't rethrow\ntry {\n  await riskyOperation();\n} catch (err) {\n  logException(err, 'Failed to run risky operation'); // handles it\n}\n\n// Not handled: don't log, just rethrow (or add logInfo breadcrumbs)\nconst result = await someCall(); // throws on failure\n```\n\n**Never call `logError`** — use `logInfo`/`logWarn` for breadcrumbs and `logException` for handled errors.\n\n## UI development\n\n**Mandatory:** All UI must use `@factory/core-ui` components. Never use raw HTML elements (`<div>`, `<button>`, `<input>`).\n\n```typescript\n// Wrong\n<div className=\"container\">\n  <button onClick={handleClick}>Submit</button>\n</div>\n\n// Right\nimport { Box, Button } from '@factory/core-ui';\n\n<Box>\n  <Button onClick={handleClick}>Submit</Button>\n</Box>\n```\n\n**Colors:** Use `colors.semantics` from `@factory/core-ui` — never hardcode hex values or CSS color names.\n\n**Component size:** Keep components under 200-300 lines. Extract subcomponents and custom hooks when a component grows.\n\n**CSS interactions:** Prefer CSS-driven show/hide and animations over component state (`isHovered`, `isVisible`).\n\n## State management (frontend)\n\nSelect Redux state precisely to avoid unnecessary re-renders:\n\n```typescript\n// Wrong — subscribes to the entire assembly slice\nconst { messageTree } = useSelector((state: RootState) => state.assembly);\n\n// Right — subscribes to only what's needed\nconst messageTree = useSelector(\n  (state: RootState) => state.assembly.messageTree\n);\n```\n\n## Feature flags\n\nGate new features with Statsig. Add a constant in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`, then use the appropriate hook or server-side check:\n\n```typescript\n// React component\nconst isEnabled = useFeatureFlagValue(FactoryFeatureFlags.MyFeature);\n\n// Backend\nconst featureFlags = await getFeatureFlagInstance();\nconst isEnabled = await featureFlags.checkFlag(FactoryFeatureFlags.MyFeature, orgId);\n```\n\nSee `docs/feature-flags.md` for full setup instructions including Statsig console steps.\n\n## CLI/Terminal UI\n\nThe CLI uses [Ink](https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink) (React for terminals). Components render to the terminal using `Box` and `Text` from `ink`, not HTML.\n\n```typescript\nimport { Box, Text } from 'ink';\n\nconst MyComponent = () => (\n  <Box flexDirection=\"column\">\n    <Text>Hello from terminal</Text>\n  </Box>\n);\n```\n\n## JSON-RPC protocol additions\n\nWhen adding a new notification type from CLI to frontend:\n\n1. Add the type to `SessionNotificationType` in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`\n2. Define the schema in `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/cli.ts`\n3. Add a handler in `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts`\n4. Emit the notification in the CLI after session initialization is complete\n",
