            "content": "# Tooling\n\n## Build system: Turborepo\n\n[Turborepo](https://turbo.build/) orchestrates builds, tests, and other tasks across all packages. Config is in `turbo.json`.\n\nAll root scripts delegate to turbo:\n\n```bash\nnpm run build       # turbo run build\nnpm run test        # turbo run test\nnpm run typecheck   # turbo run typecheck\nnpm run lint        # turbo run lint\nnpm run fix         # turbo run fix\n```\n\nTurborepo respects package dependencies — if `packages/common` changes, only dependent packages rebuild. Use `--filter` to target specific packages and avoid running all tests.\n\n## Package manager: npm workspaces\n\nAll workspaces are defined in `package.json`:\n```json\n\"workspaces\": [\n  \"apps/*\",\n  \"packages/*\",\n  \"internal/apps/*\",\n  \"internal/packages/*\",\n  \"internal/web\"\n]\n```\n\nInstall dependencies with `npm install` from root. Never add packages with `yarn` or `bun` — this repo uses npm for workspace management.\n\n## Linting: ESLint\n\nESLint config lives in `packages/eslint-config/`. Packages extend from it in their `.eslintrc.cjs`. Key rules enforced:\n\n- Enums must be in `enums.ts`\n- Types must be in `types.ts`\n- API types must be in `packages/common/src/api/`\n- Absolute imports required\n- No `require()` statements\n- No raw HTML elements in UI components (`no-restricted-imports` for `@factory/core-ui`)\n- `no-direct-process-env` — use `@factory/environment` typed constants instead of `process.env`\n\nRun `npm run fix` to auto-fix most lint issues.\n\n## Formatting: Prettier\n\nConfig in `.prettierrc.json`. Run with `npm run format` or `npm run fix` (which runs both lint and format).\n\n## Type checking: TypeScript\n\nEach package/app has its own `tsconfig.json` extending a root config. Run:\n\n```bash\nnpm run typecheck -- --filter=<package>\n```\n\n## Unused export detection: Knip\n\n[Knip](https://knip.dev) detects unused exports, types, and dependencies. Config is in `knip.json`.\n\n```bash\nnpm run knip\n```\n\nKnip runs in CI (`.github/workflows/knip.yml`) and will fail the build if unused exports are introduced.\n\n## Git hooks: Husky\n\n`.husky/` contains git hooks. The pre-commit hook runs lint checks. Husky is installed via `npm run prepare`.\n\n## Infrastructure: OpenTofu\n\n`infra/` uses [OpenTofu](https://opentofu.org/) (open-source Terraform fork) for AWS and GCP infrastructure. Always use `tofu`, not `terraform`:\n\n```bash\ncd infra\ntofu init\ntofu validate\ntofu fmt\ntofu plan\n```\n\nCI runs OpenTofu in `.github/workflows/opentofu.yml`.\n\n## CI/CD: GitHub Actions\n\n53 workflow files in `.github/workflows/`. Key workflows:\n\n| Workflow | Trigger | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `basic-checks.yml` | PR | Lint, format, typecheck |\n| `test.yml` | PR | Run unit tests |\n| `test-cli.yml` | PR | CLI-specific tests |\n| `cli-e2e-tests.yml` | PR | CLI TUI E2E tests |\n| `playwright-e2e.yml` | PR | Frontend E2E |\n| `release-cut.yml` | Manual | Cut a release |\n| `cli-release.yml` | Push to release branch | Publish CLI |\n| `desktop-release.yml` | Push to release branch | Build desktop |\n| `deploy-prod.yml` | Push to main | Deploy to production |\n| `deploy-dev-web.yml` | Push to dev | Deploy to dev |\n| `opentofu.yml` | `infra/` changes | Terraform plan/apply |\n| `semantic-diff.yml` | PR | AI-powered PR analysis |\n| `droid-daily-maintenance.yml` | Daily | Automated maintenance tasks |\n\n## Code generation\n\nThe CLI has some generated files in `apps/cli/src/generated/`. Regenerate with the relevant setup script (check `apps/cli/package.json` scripts).\n\n## Bug report downloader\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/download-bug-report.js <BUG_REPORT_ID>\n```\n\nDownloads and extracts CLI session bug reports from S3 into `~/Downloads/bug-reports/`. Requires AWS credentials in `apps/backend/.env.local`.\n",
