            "content": "# Apps\n\nFactory ships eight deployable applications, each with a distinct runtime and purpose.\n\n| App | Stack | Runtime | Description |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| [CLI](cli/index.md) | Bun + Ink (React) | Local | The Droid terminal agent |\n| [Daemon](daemon.md) | Bun | Local / CDE | factoryd background process |\n| [Web](web.md) | Vite + React | Browser | Web-based session viewer |\n| [Desktop](desktop.md) | Electron | macOS/Windows/Linux | Native desktop wrapper |\n| [Backend](backend.md) | Next.js 15 | Vercel/Node | REST API and LLM proxy |\n| [Admin](admin.md) | Next.js 15 | Vercel/Node | Admin dashboard |\n| [Relay](relay.md) | Bun | AWS | Real-time signal relay |\n| [Signal](signal.md) | Bun | AWS | Presence and event streaming |\n\nAdditionally, `apps/factory-vscode-extension` provides IDE integration and `apps/functions` contains Firebase Cloud Functions.\n\n## Tier assignments\n\n**Tier 1 (core product):** CLI, Daemon, Web, Desktop, Backend  \n**Tier 2 (important infrastructure):** Admin, Relay, Signal, VSCode Extension  \n**Tier 3 (support):** Firebase Functions, migrations, scripts, bridge utilities\n\n## Architecture relationship\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    WEB[\"Web / Desktop\"] -->|WebSocket| DAEMON[\"Daemon (factoryd)\"]\n    DAEMON -->|stdin/stdout| CLI[\"CLI (droid)\"]\n    WEB -->|HTTPS| BACKEND[\"Backend API\"]\n    CLI -->|HTTPS| BACKEND\n    RELAY[\"Relay\"] -->|signals| WEB\n    RELAY -->|signals| DESKTOP\n    SIGNAL[\"Signal\"] --> RELAY\n```\n\nSee [architecture](../overview/architecture.md) for the full system diagram.\n",
