            "content": "# CLI app (Droid)\n\nActive contributors: Arman Bolat, Luke Alvoeiro, Stepan, shashank-factory, theo\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe CLI is the primary user-facing product: a terminal UI (TUI) powered by Ink (React for terminals) that runs an AI agent capable of reading/writing files, executing shell commands, searching codebases, calling MCP tools, and producing streaming responses. Users interact through natural language; the agent plans and executes multi-step tasks.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/cli/\n├── src/\n│   ├── index.ts          # Entry point, Commander CLI setup\n│   ├── main.tsx          # Interactive TUI entry\n│   ├── app.tsx           # Root React component (~4,500 lines)\n│   ├── agent/            # Tool execution, confirmation, autonomy rules\n│   ├── acp/              # Agent Control Protocol (mission orchestration)\n│   ├── adapters/         # LLM provider adapters\n│   ├── commands/         # Slash commands (/help, /clear, /settings, etc.)\n│   ├── components/       # Ink UI components\n│   ├── contexts/         # React contexts\n│   ├── controllers/      # Session and file restoration controllers\n│   ├── core/             # AgentLoop\n│   ├── exec/             # Streaming JSON-RPC exec runner\n│   ├── feature-flags/    # Client-side feature flag initialization\n│   ├── hooks/            # React hooks (useAgent, useLLMStreaming, etc.)\n│   ├── i18n/             # Internationalization\n│   ├── llm-proxy/        # Local LLM proxy support\n│   ├── mcp/              # MCP hub for external tool servers\n│   ├── models/           # Session and message model types\n│   ├── prompt-tuning/    # Prompt optimization tooling\n│   ├── prompts/          # System prompt builders\n│   ├── services/         # SessionService, ConversationStateManager, etc.\n│   ├── skills/           # Built-in skill definitions and loader\n│   ├── task/             # Background task management\n│   ├── tools/            # Tool executors (file, shell, search, MCP)\n│   └── utils/            # Shared utilities (181 files)\n├── e2e-tests/            # TUI E2E tests using @microsoft/tui-test\n├── e2e-exec/             # Exec mode E2E tests\n├── e2e-stream-jsonrpc/   # JSON-RPC streaming tests\n└── scripts/              # Build and release scripts\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `src/index.ts` | Entry point; Commander CLI parsing; starts TUI or exec mode |\n| `src/app.tsx` | Root Ink component; renders the full TUI; orchestrates all overlays |\n| `src/core/AgentLoop.ts` | Agent execution loop; coordinates LLM calls and tool execution |\n| `src/hooks/useAgent.ts` | React hook managing agent state; owned by @factory-arman, @stepan-factory, @lukealvoeiro |\n| `src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` | Streaming LLM response handling |\n| `src/hooks/createLLMStreamingCore.ts` | Core LLM streaming implementation |\n| `src/hooks/useToolExecution.ts` | Tool call execution orchestration |\n| `src/services/SessionService.ts` | Session lifecycle (create, load, archive, resume) |\n| `src/services/ConversationStateManager.ts` | Maintains conversation history and TODO state |\n| `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` | Streams agent as JSON-RPC notifications over stdout |\n| `src/mcp/McpHub.ts` | Manages external MCP server connections |\n| `src/agent/tool-confirmation.ts` | Rules for when to ask user confirmation before tool execution |\n| `src/agent/autonomy.ts` | Autonomy level logic (auto-approve, ask, etc.) |\n\n## How it works\n\nThe CLI has two modes:\n\n**Interactive mode** (`droid` with no subcommand): Renders a full TUI via Ink. The `app.tsx` root component mounts and coordinates all UI panels. User input flows through `useChatKeyboardInput`, which triggers the agent via `useAgent`.\n\n**Exec mode** (`droid exec`): Non-interactive; runs the agent as a subprocess that communicates via JSON-RPC 2.0 over stdin/stdout. The daemon uses this mode to manage CLI processes. Implemented in `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts`.\n\n### Agent loop\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant useAgent\n    participant AgentLoop\n    participant LLM\n    participant Tools\n\n    User->>useAgent: submits message\n    useAgent->>AgentLoop: start loop\n    AgentLoop->>LLM: request with system prompt + history\n    LLM-->>AgentLoop: streaming response (text + tool calls)\n    AgentLoop->>Tools: execute tool calls\n    Tools-->>AgentLoop: tool results\n    AgentLoop->>LLM: continue with tool results\n    LLM-->>AgentLoop: final response\n    AgentLoop->>useAgent: done\n    useAgent->>User: renders response\n```\n\nTool calls may require user confirmation (controlled by `agent/tool-confirmation.ts` and autonomy settings). The agent loop runs until the LLM stops producing tool calls.\n\n### Skills system\n\nSkills are Markdown documents that extend the system prompt. Built-in skills live in `src/skills/builtin/constants.ts` (3,409 lines — the largest static file). User-defined skills live in `.factory/skills/`. The `McpHub` loads MCP tools on startup.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **Daemon:** The daemon spawns the CLI in exec mode (`streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts`). All session lifecycle calls (initialize, add message, interrupt) arrive as stdin JSON-RPC requests.\n- **Backend API:** The CLI calls `apps/backend` for session persistence, LLM proxying, and settings sync. Config is in `src/api/`.\n- **MCP servers:** External tool servers connect via `src/mcp/McpHub.ts`.\n- **IDE extensions:** `src/hooks/useVSCodeExtension.ts` and `useIdeContext.ts` manage IDE integration.\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\nTo add a new **tool**: create a tool executor in `src/tools/executors/client/`, register it in the tools index, and add the tool schema to `@factory/droid-core`.\n\nTo add a **slash command**: create a handler in `src/commands/` and register it in `src/commands/registry`.\n\nTo add a **new TUI panel or overlay**: create an Ink component in `src/components/` and mount it in `src/app.tsx`. Note that `app.tsx` is very large — consider whether the change belongs in a focused hook instead.\n\n## Active contributor stats\n\n| Scope | Top contributors (90 days) |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/` | Arman Bolat (44), shashank-factory (41), Luke Alvoeiro (38), theo (36), Stepan (34) |\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/index.ts` | CLI entry point and command routing |\n| `src/app.tsx` | Root TUI component |\n| `src/core/AgentLoop.ts` | Agent execution loop |\n| `src/hooks/useAgent.ts` | Agent state management hook |\n| `src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` | LLM streaming |\n| `src/services/SessionService.ts` | Session lifecycle |\n| `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` | Exec mode JSON-RPC runner |\n| `src/agent/tool-confirmation.ts` | Tool confirmation logic |\n| `src/mcp/McpHub.ts` | MCP server management |\n",
