            "content": "# CLI command structure\n\n## Entry point\n\n`apps/cli/src/index.ts` sets up a Commander.js CLI. The top-level `droid` binary has two modes:\n\n1. **Interactive TUI** — no subcommand; renders the Ink app via `src/main.tsx`\n2. **Subcommands** — `exec`, `wiki-upload`, `session`, and others\n\nKey Commander config:\n```\ndroid                        # interactive TUI\ndroid exec                   # exec mode (daemon-facing)\ndroid wiki-upload            # upload a wiki directory to Factory\ndroid session list           # list sessions\ndroid session load <id>      # load a session\n```\n\n## Slash commands (in-session)\n\nUsers can type `/` in the TUI to access commands. Command handlers live in `apps/cli/src/commands/`. The registry is in `apps/cli/src/commands/registry.ts`.\n\nCommon slash commands:\n- `/help` — show help\n- `/clear` — clear conversation\n- `/settings` — open settings overlay\n- `/model` — change LLM model\n- `/compact` — compact conversation history\n- `/skill` — manage skills\n\n## Exec mode\n\nWhen the daemon spawns the CLI as a subprocess, it uses exec mode. The daemon sends JSON-RPC requests on stdin and the CLI sends JSON-RPC notifications on stdout.\n\nEntry point: `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts`\n\nMethods the daemon can call:\n- `initialize` — start a new session\n- `load` — load an existing session\n- `addUserMessage` — add a user message and start the agent loop\n- `interrupt` — stop the current agent loop\n- `close` — shut down the session\n\nThe full method list mirrors the daemon's `DaemonDroidMethod` enum in `packages/common/src/daemon/enums.ts`.\n\n## Build and distribution\n\nThe CLI bundles to a single executable via Bun's SEA (Single Executable Application). Build script: `apps/cli/esbuild.config.js`. Native libraries (keytar, ripgrep, bun-pty) are embedded by `src/embed-native-libs.ts`.\n\nDevelopment wrappers created by `npm run setup`:\n- `droid-dev` — runs source via Bun against hosted dev API\n- `droid-localhost` — same but against `localhost:3000`\n- `droid-preprod` / `droid-staging` — other environment targets\n\nSee [apps/cli index](index.md) for the full CLI overview.\n",
