            "content": "# TUI rendering\n\n## Ink and React in the terminal\n\nThe CLI renders its interface using [Ink](https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink), which lets you write terminal UIs using React components. Ink components use `Box` and `Text` instead of HTML elements, and layout uses flexbox.\n\n```typescript\nimport { Box, Text } from 'ink';\n\nconst MyPanel = () => (\n  <Box flexDirection=\"column\" borderStyle=\"round\">\n    <Text bold>Session active</Text>\n    <Text color=\"green\">Ready</Text>\n  </Box>\n);\n```\n\n## Root component: app.tsx\n\n`apps/cli/src/app.tsx` (4,557 lines) is the root component. It manages:\n- All overlays and modals (settings, MCP manager, droids, missions, diagnostics)\n- The main message list (`MessageList`)\n- The chat input (`ChatInput`)\n- Footer status bars\n- Authentication checks\n- Keyboard shortcuts\n\nBecause `app.tsx` is so large and changes frequently, consider adding features via new hooks or subcomponents rather than directly in this file.\n\n## Component organization\n\nComponents live in `apps/cli/src/components/`. They are Ink components, not browser React components. Notable ones:\n\n| Component | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `AppLayout` | Top-level layout container |\n| `MessageList` | Renders conversation message list |\n| `ChatInput` | Text input with keyboard shortcuts |\n| `FooterPrimaryStatus` | Bottom status bar |\n| `McpManager` | MCP server management overlay |\n| `ModelSelector` | LLM model picker |\n| `DroidsOverlay` | Custom droids management |\n| `MissionControlOverlay` | Mission orchestration UI |\n| `DiagnosticsOverlay` | Dev/debug diagnostics panel |\n\n## Input handling\n\nKeyboard input for the chat box is handled by `apps/cli/src/hooks/useChatKeyboardInput.ts` (68,357 lines of code and tests — one of the largest files). It handles:\n- Multi-line input\n- Cursor movement (word/line navigation)\n- Copy/paste\n- IME (input method editor) shortcuts\n- Slash command detection\n\n## Layout primitives\n\nInk's `Box` component supports flexbox layout. The CLI uses it for all layout, with ANSI color codes for styling. Color constants are defined in `src/components/chat/themedColors.ts`.\n\n## TUI tests\n\nE2E tests for TUI interactions use `@microsoft/tui-test`. Tests live in `apps/cli/e2e-tests/` (78 test files). Run with:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npx tui-test run\n```\n\nConfig: `apps/cli/tui-test.config.ts`\n",
