            "content": "# Daemon (factoryd)\n\nActive contributors: factory-sherry, factory-jerry, factory-octavian, factory-daniel, Luke Alvoeiro\n\n## Purpose\n\n`factoryd` is the background daemon process that bridges the web/desktop frontends to the Droid CLI. It runs persistently on the user's machine (or on a remote CDE), manages CLI subprocess lifecycles, and exposes a WebSocket server for JSON-RPC 2.0 communication.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/daemon/\n├── src/\n│   ├── index.ts           # Entry point; Commander setup, auto-update, startup\n│   ├── environment.ts     # Environment variable loading\n│   ├── constants.ts       # Port constants\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   └── UpdateService.ts  # Daemon auto-update\n│   └── telemetry/         # OTEL tracing setup\npackages/daemon-core/\n├── src/\n│   ├── index.ts           # Exports DaemonCore\n│   ├── types.ts           # Core types\n│   ├── server/\n│   │   └── handlers/\n│   │       └── droid-request-handler.ts  # All RPC method handlers (~5000 lines)\n│   ├── droid/             # CLI process management\n│   ├── terminal/          # PTY terminal sessions\n│   ├── automations/       # Automation engine\n│   ├── relay/             # Relay integration\n│   └── services/          # Settings, file, search services\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/daemon/src/index.ts` | Entry; loads env, initializes telemetry, runs auto-update, starts server |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/index.ts` | Exports `DaemonCore` — the main server class |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/droid-request-handler.ts` | Handles all ~80 RPC methods |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/droid/` | CLI subprocess spawning and lifecycle |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/` | PTY-based terminal sessions |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/automations/` | Automation scheduling and execution |\n\n## How it works\n\nThe daemon starts a WebSocket server on port 37643 (production) or 41723 (development). Clients connect and send JSON-RPC 2.0 requests.\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    subgraph \"Clients\"\n        WEB[\"Web frontend\"]\n        DESKTOP[\"Desktop frontend\"]\n    end\n    subgraph \"factoryd\"\n        WS[\"WebSocket server\"]\n        HANDLER[\"droid-request-handler\"]\n        SESSIONS[\"CLI subprocess pool\"]\n    end\n    subgraph \"CLI\"\n        EXEC[\"exec runner (droid)\"]\n    end\n\n    WEB -->|WebSocket JSON-RPC| WS\n    DESKTOP -->|WebSocket JSON-RPC| WS\n    WS --> HANDLER\n    HANDLER --> SESSIONS\n    SESSIONS -->|stdin JSON-RPC| EXEC\n    EXEC -->|stdout JSON-RPC| SESSIONS\n    SESSIONS -->|notification| HANDLER\n    HANDLER -->|notification| WS\n```\n\n### Session lifecycle\n\n1. Frontend calls `initialize` → daemon spawns a new `droid exec` subprocess\n2. Each user message triggers `addUserMessage` → forwarded to CLI stdin\n3. CLI streams notifications back via stdout → daemon forwards to frontend WebSocket\n4. `interrupt` stops the agent loop; `close` terminates the subprocess\n\n### Terminal sessions\n\nThe daemon also manages interactive PTY sessions (not AI agent sessions). These are used for the embedded terminal in the web/desktop app. Implementation: `packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/`.\n\n### Auto-update\n\nOn startup, the daemon checks for and installs updates before starting the server (`apps/daemon/src/services/UpdateService.ts`). This is skipped when `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=true` (Electron bundles set this to preserve code signing).\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **Frontend:** `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` manages the WebSocket connection\n- **CLI:** Spawns via exec mode; all communication is JSON-RPC 2.0 over stdin/stdout\n- **Relay:** The daemon connects to the signal relay for remote CDE scenarios (`packages/daemon-core/src/relay/`)\n- **Protocol:** All method names and schemas defined in `packages/common/src/daemon/`\n\n## Default ports\n\n| Environment | Port |\n|---|---|\n| Production | 37643 |\n| Development | 41723 |\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/daemon/src/index.ts` | Entry point |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/index.ts` | DaemonCore export |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/droid-request-handler.ts` | All RPC method implementations |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/droid/` | CLI process management |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/` | PTY terminal sessions |\n| `packages/common/src/daemon/` | Protocol definitions |\n",
