            "content": "# Web app\n\nActive contributors: Jonathan Lucuix-Andre, Andrei Savin, factory-sherry, Ricky S, Alvin Sng\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/web` is the browser-based interface for Factory. Users can view and interact with Droid sessions, manage settings, and monitor session history. It is a thin host application that mounts components from `@factory/frontend`.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/web/\n├── src/\n│   ├── main.tsx           # App entry point\n│   ├── auth/              # WorkOS AuthKit setup\n│   ├── config/            # App configuration\n│   └── types/             # App-specific types\n├── public/\n├── index.html\n├── vite.config.ts\n└── package.json\n```\n\nMost of the logic lives in `@factory/frontend` — the web app itself is intentionally thin.\n\n## Tech stack\n\n- **Build tool:** Vite\n- **Framework:** React 19\n- **Auth:** WorkOS AuthKit (`@workos-inc/authkit-react`)\n- **Shared features:** `@factory/frontend`\n- **Design system:** `@factory/core-ui`\n- **E2E tests:** Playwright\n\n## How it works\n\nThe web app mounts the `@factory/frontend` feature modules, providing them with auth context and configuration. The frontend package handles:\n- Session list and detail views\n- Real-time session updates via WebSocket to the daemon\n- Settings management\n- Analytics pages\n\nAuthentication flows through WorkOS AuthKit. On load, the app checks for a valid session and redirects to WorkOS for SSO if unauthenticated.\n\n## Dev server\n\n```bash\n# Start from root (includes backend, daemon, storybook, admin)\nnpm run dev:web\n\n# Or directly\ncd apps/web && npm run dev\n```\n\nRuns on port 3002 by default.\n\n## E2E tests\n\nPlaywright E2E tests are in `packages/frontend`. Run from the `packages/frontend` directory:\n\n```bash\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e\n# Debug mode\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e -- --headed --debug\n```\n\nSee `docs/playwright-e2e-testing.md` for patterns and setup.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **Daemon:** Via `@factory/frontend`'s `DaemonSessionController`, connecting to factoryd WebSocket\n- **Backend:** REST API calls to `apps/backend` for auth, data fetching, and settings\n- **Frontend package:** All session UI, hooks, and business logic live in `@factory/frontend`\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/main.tsx` | App entry point and WorkOS auth setup |\n| `src/auth/` | Authentication configuration |\n| `vite.config.ts` | Build configuration |\n",
