            "content": "# Desktop app\n\nActive contributors: factory-sherry, Ricky S, Eno Reyes, Luke Alvoeiro\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe desktop app is an Electron wrapper around the web app. It bundles `factoryd` (the daemon) locally, so users don't need to install anything separately. It also provides OS-level integration: native window management, auto-update, and keychain access.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/desktop/\n├── src/\n│   ├── main/              # Electron main process\n│   ├── renderer/          # Renderer process (loads web app)\n│   ├── preload/           # Preload scripts (bridge main/renderer)\n│   ├── config/            # Build configuration\n│   └── types/             # Desktop-specific types\n├── electron-builder.config.ts\n└── package.json\n```\n\n## How it works\n\nElectron runs two processes:\n- **Main process** (`src/main/`): Node.js process managing the native window, daemon lifecycle, and auto-update\n- **Renderer process** (`src/renderer/`): Chromium window loading the web app (same code as `apps/web`)\n\nThe desktop app starts `factoryd` as a child process on launch and terminates it on quit. It sets `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=true` to prevent the daemon from self-updating while bundled (to preserve the code signature).\n\n### Auto-update\n\nThe desktop app uses a custom auto-updater backed by S3-hosted release artifacts. Config is in `packages/updater`. On launch, it checks for a newer version and offers to update.\n\n## Platforms\n\nBuilds target macOS, Windows, and Linux. macOS builds are signed and notarized via GitHub Actions (`desktop-release.yml`). The release workflow is in `.github/workflows/desktop-release.yml`.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **Daemon:** Spawned by the main process; communicates over the local WebSocket\n- **Web app:** The renderer loads the same web app code as `apps/web`\n- **Updater:** `packages/updater` provides version check and download logic\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/main/` | Electron main process |\n| `src/renderer/` | Renderer process (web app host) |\n| `src/preload/` | IPC bridge between main and renderer |\n| `electron-builder.config.ts` | Packaging configuration |\n",
