            "content": "# Backend API\n\nActive contributors: factory-octavian, Alvin Sng, factory-sherry, Nikita Lilichenko, Leo Tchourakov\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/backend` is the cloud API layer. It provides REST endpoints for authentication, session storage, billing, LLM proxying, integrations, and cron jobs. The Next.js web UI that originally lived here is deprecated; `apps/web` is the current frontend.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/backend/\n├── src/\n│   ├── constants.ts       # API constants and config\n│   ├── instrumentation.ts # OpenTelemetry setup\n│   ├── middleware.ts       # Route middleware (auth, error handling)\n│   ├── routes.ts          # API route definitions\n│   ├── app/               # Next.js App Router pages and API routes\n│   ├── features/          # Feature modules (feature flags, etc.)\n│   ├── services/          # Business logic services\n│   │   ├── sessions/      # Session management\n│   │   ├── billing/       # Orb billing integration\n│   │   ├── llm/           # LLM proxy service\n│   │   ├── github/        # GitHub integration\n│   │   ├── linear/        # Linear integration\n│   │   └── ...            # Other service integrations\n│   └── utils/             # Shared utilities\n└── package.json\n```\n\n## Tech stack\n\n- **Framework:** Next.js 15 with App Router\n- **Runtime:** Node.js (deployed on Vercel)\n- **Database:** Firebase Firestore\n- **Auth:** WorkOS\n- **Billing:** Orb\n- **Feature flags:** Statsig\n- **Observability:** Sentry, OTEL\n\n## Key services\n\n| Service | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| Session service | Create, load, update, archive sessions in Firestore |\n| LLM proxy | Proxy LLM requests to Anthropic, OpenAI, Google; handles streaming |\n| Auth service | WorkOS token validation and user context |\n| GitHub integration | GitHub App, webhooks, repo access |\n| Linear integration | Ticket linking and sync |\n| Billing service | Orb subscription management |\n| Feature flags | Statsig server-side evaluation |\n\n## API structure\n\nRoutes are defined in `src/routes.ts` and `src/app/`. The `middleware.ts` handles:\n- Authentication validation\n- Error formatting (catches `ResponseErrorXXX` instances and returns appropriate HTTP codes)\n- Request logging\n\nAll API types are in `packages/common/src/api/`.\n\n## Error handling\n\nThe backend follows the convention in `docs/error-handling.md`. Throw typed errors from `@factory/logging/errors`; middleware converts them to HTTP responses:\n\n```typescript\nthrow new ResponseError404NotFound('Session not found', { sessionId });\n// → 404 JSON response, no try/catch needed\n```\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **CLI:** CLI calls backend for session sync, LLM proxy, and settings\n- **Frontend:** REST calls for session data, settings, and analytics\n- **Firestore:** Primary data store for all persistent data\n- **External services:** GitHub, Linear, Slack, WorkOS, Orb, Statsig, E2B\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/middleware.ts` | Route middleware (auth, error handling) |\n| `src/routes.ts` | API route definitions |\n| `src/services/sessions/` | Session CRUD |\n| `src/services/llm/` | LLM proxy and streaming |\n| `src/features/feature-flags/server.ts` | Server-side feature flag evaluation |\n",
