            "content": "# @factory/frontend\n\nActive contributors: Jonathan Lucuix-Andre, Andrei Savin, factory-sherry, Ricky S, Alvin Sng\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/frontend` contains the shared React features, hooks, and services used by both `apps/web` and `apps/desktop`. This includes the session list, session detail view, settings, analytics, and the daemon communication layer.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/frontend/src/\n├── api/               # API client layer (REST calls to backend)\n├── app/               # App-level providers (Redux store, auth, theming)\n├── auth/              # Authentication utilities\n├── errors/            # Error boundaries\n├── features/          # Feature modules\n│   ├── sessions/      # Session list, detail, active session UI\n│   ├── settings/      # Settings pages and components\n│   ├── analytics/     # Analytics and metrics pages\n│   └── ...            # Other features\n├── hooks/             # Shared hooks\n├── layouts/           # Page layout components\n├── router/            # React Router configuration\n├── services/\n│   └── session/\n│       └── DaemonSessionController.ts  # WebSocket daemon client\n├── types/             # Frontend-specific types\n├── utils/             # Frontend utilities\n└── views/             # Top-level page views\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | Manages WebSocket connection to daemon; handles all session notifications |\n| `src/features/sessions/` | Session list, active session, new session UI |\n| `src/features/sessions/modules/NewSession.module.tsx` | New session creation flow (high churn file) |\n| `src/features/sessions/modules/ActiveSession.module.tsx` | Active session display (high churn) |\n| `src/app/` | Redux store configuration and root providers |\n\n## DaemonSessionController\n\n`DaemonSessionController.ts` (3,791 lines in the test file, ~40 changes in 90 days) is the most critical file in this package. It:\n\n1. Opens a WebSocket connection to `factoryd`\n2. Sends session lifecycle JSON-RPC requests (initialize, addUserMessage, interrupt)\n3. Handles incoming notifications (tool call results, partial messages, session status)\n4. Updates Redux state based on notifications\n\nWhen adding a new notification type from the CLI, the handler goes here.\n\n## State management\n\nThe package uses Redux Toolkit with entity adapters. The `assembly` slice holds the current session's message tree. Selectors must be specific (select individual properties, not the whole slice) to avoid unnecessary re-renders.\n\n## E2E tests\n\nPlaywright E2E tests are in `packages/frontend/` alongside the source code. Run:\n\n```bash\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e\n```\n\nConfiguration: `packages/frontend/playwright.config.ts`\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **Daemon:** `DaemonSessionController.ts` manages the WebSocket connection\n- **Backend:** `src/api/` layer makes REST calls\n- **core-ui:** All UI components use `@factory/core-ui`\n- **common:** Uses shared types and enums from `@factory/common`\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | Daemon WebSocket client |\n| `src/features/sessions/modules/ActiveSession.module.tsx` | Active session UI |\n| `src/features/sessions/modules/NewSession.module.tsx` | New session creation |\n| `src/app/` | Redux store and root providers |\n| `src/router/` | Route definitions |\n",
