            "content": "# @factory/core-ui\n\nActive contributors: Ricky S, Andrei Savin, Eno Reyes, Luke Alvoeiro, shashank-factory\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/core-ui` is the mandatory design system for all Factory UI. Every UI component in the codebase must use primitives from this package. Direct HTML elements (`<div>`, `<button>`, `<input>`) are banned by ESLint rules.\n\n## Components\n\nThe package provides:\n\n**Layout primitives:**\n- `Box` — flexible container with flexbox layout\n- `Flex` — shorthand for `Box` with `display: flex`\n- `Grid` — CSS grid layout\n\n**Form components:**\n- `Button` — styled button with variants\n- `Input` — text input\n- `Dropdown` — select/dropdown\n\n**Typography:**\n- `Header` — heading levels\n- `Text` — body text with semantic variants\n\n**Interactive:**\n- `Collapsible` — expand/collapse container\n- `Toast` — notification toasts\n\n**Color system:**\n- Semantic color tokens supporting light and dark modes\n- `colors.semantics` for all color references — never hardcode hex values\n\n## Storybook\n\nAll components are documented in Storybook at `apps/storybook`. Run with:\n\n```bash\nnpm run storybook\n# or\ncd apps/storybook && npm run dev\n```\n\nBrowse components at http://localhost:6006.\n\n## Usage rules\n\n```typescript\n// Always import from @factory/core-ui\nimport { Box, Button, Text } from '@factory/core-ui';\n\n// Never use raw HTML\n// ❌ <div className=\"...\">\n// ✓ <Box>\n\n// Never hardcode colors\n// ❌ color=\"#ff0000\"\n// ✓ color={colors.semantics.danger}\n```\n\nESLint enforces these rules via `no-restricted-imports` in `packages/eslint-config/`.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- Used by `apps/web`, `apps/desktop`, `apps/admin`, `packages/frontend`, `packages/component-library`\n- Themed via CSS variables, supporting light/dark mode\n- Components visible in `apps/storybook`\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/` | All component implementations |\n| `src/colors/` | Semantic color system |\n",
