            "content": "# @factory/common\n\nActive contributors: factory-octavian, Arman Bolat, l30t, factory-sherry, factory-davidgu\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/common` is the canonical location for all shared types, enums, API contracts, and feature flag definitions. Every API endpoint must have its request/response types defined here. It is imported by nearly every other package and app.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/common/src/\n├── agent/             # Agent readiness types\n├── agentReadiness/    # Agent readiness enums\n├── api/               # API type contracts (by service)\n├── automations/       # Automation types\n├── billing/           # Billing types\n├── cli/               # CLI-specific types and enums\n├── daemon/            # Daemon RPC protocol (methods, schemas, enums)\n├── desktop/           # Desktop-specific types\n├── documents/         # Document types\n├── droid/             # Droid protocol (SessionNotificationType, schemas)\n│   ├── enums.ts       # SessionNotificationType and other droid enums\n│   └── schemas/       # Zod schemas for protocol validation\n├── events/            # Event types\n├── feature-flags/\n│   └── constants.ts   # All feature flag definitions (78 changes in 90 days)\n├── images/            # Image handling types\n├── integrations/      # Third-party integration types\n├── llm/               # LLM model and provider enums\n├── memory/            # Memory management types\n├── node/              # Node environment types\n├── organization/      # Organization and team types\n├── policy/            # Policy and permission types\n├── relay/             # Relay protocol types\n├── repositories/      # Repository types\n├── security/          # Security policy types\n├── session/           # Session core types\n├── sessionV2/         # Session v2 message types\n├── settings/          # Settings schema (40 changes in 90 days)\n├── shared/            # Shared primitives (AutonomyLevel, DroidInteractionMode)\n├── tags/              # Tag types\n├── terminal/          # Terminal session types\n├── timeline/          # Timeline event types\n├── tools/             # Tool types\n├── ui/                # UI configuration types\n├── updater/           # Auto-update types\n├── usage/             # Usage tracking types\n├── wiki/              # Wiki types\n└── workspaces/        # Workspace types\n```\n\n## Key files\n\n| File | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `src/droid/enums.ts` | `SessionNotificationType` — all CLI→frontend notification types |\n| `src/droid/schemas/cli.ts` | Zod schemas for CLI notification payloads |\n| `src/daemon/` | All daemon RPC method names, request/response schemas |\n| `src/feature-flags/constants.ts` | Feature flag definitions (one of the most frequently changed files) |\n| `src/settings/types.ts` | Settings schema (frequently changed) |\n| `src/llm/` | LLM provider and model enums |\n| `src/session/` | Core session types |\n\n## Conventions\n\nAll API endpoints must have types here, organized as `src/api/{service}/types.ts`. This is enforced by ESLint.\n\nWhen adding a new notification type from CLI to frontend:\n1. Add to `SessionNotificationType` enum in `src/droid/enums.ts`\n2. Define the payload schema in `src/droid/schemas/cli.ts`\n\nWhen adding a new daemon RPC method:\n1. Add the method name to `DaemonDroidMethod` or `DaemonSettingsMethod` in `src/daemon/enums.ts`\n2. Define request/response types in `src/daemon/types.ts`\n\n## Integration points\n\nEvery app and package imports from `@factory/common`. It has no runtime dependencies — pure types and constants.\n",
