            "content": "# @factory/logging\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/logging` provides centralized logging utilities, error types, and metrics. All apps and packages import logging functions from here.\n\n## Key exports\n\n```typescript\nimport { logInfo, logWarn, logException, Metrics } from '@factory/logging';\nimport { MetaError, ResponseError404NotFound, ... } from '@factory/logging/errors';\nimport { Metric } from '@factory/logging/metrics/enums';\n```\n\n## Logging functions\n\n| Function | When to use |\n|---|---|\n| `logInfo(msg)` | Breadcrumbs and informational context |\n| `logWarn(msg)` | Unexpected but non-critical conditions |\n| `logException(err, msg)` | Handled errors — call when you catch and don't rethrow |\n\nNever use `logError` — it does not exist in this package by design.\n\n## Error types\n\n`@factory/logging/errors` exports typed HTTP error classes:\n\n| Class | HTTP status |\n|---|---|\n| `MetaError` | 500 (internal) |\n| `ResponseError400BadRequest` | 400 |\n| `ResponseError401Unauthorized` | 401 |\n| `ResponseError403Forbidden` | 403 |\n| `ResponseError404NotFound` | 404 |\n| `ResponseError409RetryConflict` | 409 |\n| `ResponseError422InvalidData` | 422 |\n| `ResponseError429RateLimitExceeded` | 429 |\n| `ResponseError503ServiceUnavailable` | 503 |\n\nThese are caught by `apps/backend`'s route middleware and converted to HTTP responses.\n\n## Metrics\n\n`Metrics` and `Metric` provide structured metric emission for observability.\n\n## Integration points\n\nUsed by every app and package that needs logging. The backend middleware in `apps/backend/src/middleware.ts` catches `ResponseErrorXXX` instances to format HTTP responses.\n",
