            "content": "# @factory/environment\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/environment` provides strongly-typed access to environment variables. Instead of reading `process.env.MY_VAR` directly (which is banned by the `no-direct-process-env` ESLint rule), code imports typed constants from this package.\n\n## Usage\n\n```typescript\nimport { EnvironmentVariable } from '@factory/environment';\n\nconst apiUrl = EnvironmentVariable.FACTORY_API_URL;\n```\n\nAll environment variable names are defined as an enum so they are type-checked and discoverable.\n\n## Why this exists\n\nDirect `process.env` access is banned by the `no-direct-process-env` lint rule. This ensures environment variable names are centralized and type-safe, rather than scattered as magic strings across the codebase.\n\n## Integration points\n\nUsed by CLI, daemon, and backend wherever environment configuration is needed.\n",
