            "content": "# Agent loop\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe agent loop is the core execution cycle that drives Droid's behavior. It manages the conversation between the user's instructions, the LLM's responses, and tool executions — looping until the LLM produces a final response with no pending tool calls.\n\n## Key files\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/core/AgentLoop.ts` | Orchestrates the loop |\n| `apps/cli/src/hooks/useAgent.ts` | React hook that owns agent state |\n| `apps/cli/src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` | Streaming LLM integration |\n| `apps/cli/src/hooks/createLLMStreamingCore.ts` | Core streaming implementation |\n| `apps/cli/src/hooks/useToolExecution.ts` | Tool call dispatch and result collection |\n| `apps/cli/src/agent/tool-confirmation.ts` | Rules for when to ask user confirmation |\n| `apps/cli/src/agent/autonomy.ts` | Autonomy level definitions |\n| `apps/cli/src/services/ConversationStateManager.ts` | Conversation history maintenance |\n\n## How it works\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant App as app.tsx\n    participant useAgent\n    participant LLMStreaming\n    participant ToolExecution\n    participant Tools\n\n    App->>useAgent: user message submitted\n    useAgent->>LLMStreaming: start stream (history + message)\n    LLMStreaming-->>useAgent: streaming tokens\n    LLMStreaming-->>useAgent: tool call detected\n    useAgent->>ToolExecution: execute tool\n    alt Confirmation required\n        ToolExecution-->>App: show confirmation UI\n        App-->>ToolExecution: user approves/rejects\n    end\n    ToolExecution->>Tools: run tool\n    Tools-->>ToolExecution: result\n    ToolExecution-->>useAgent: tool result\n    useAgent->>LLMStreaming: continue with tool results\n    LLMStreaming-->>useAgent: final response (no tool calls)\n    useAgent->>App: done\n```\n\n## Tool confirmation\n\nNot every tool call requires user confirmation. `agent/tool-confirmation.ts` (13,933 lines of logic and 44,887 lines of tests) encodes the rules:\n- Destructive operations (file writes, shell execution) may require confirmation\n- Read-only operations (file reads, search) generally auto-approve\n- The user's autonomy level setting overrides defaults\n- Confirmation can be batched for multiple simultaneous tool calls\n\nAutonomy levels are defined in `packages/common/src/shared/enums.ts` as `AutonomyLevel`.\n\n## Conversation state\n\n`ConversationStateManager.ts` tracks:\n- Message history for the current session\n- TODO state (the agent's internal task list)\n- Compaction state (context window management)\n\nWhen the context window fills up, conversation compaction is triggered via `hooks/compaction/`.\n\n## CODEOWNERS\n\nThe agent loop's core files (`useAgent.ts`, `useLLMStreaming.ts`, `createLLMStreamingCore.ts`, `useToolExecution.ts`, `ConversationStateManager.ts`) are owned by `@factory-arman`, `@stepan-factory`, and `@lukealvoeiro` per `.github/CODEOWNERS`.\n",
