            "content": "# Session management\n\n## Purpose\n\nA session is the core unit of user–Droid interaction. Session management spans the CLI (where sessions run), the daemon (which tracks active sessions), the backend (which persists them), and the frontend (which displays them).\n\n## Session lifecycle\n\n```mermaid\nstateDiagram-v2\n    [*] --> New: user starts Droid\n    New --> Active: initialize()\n    Active --> Active: addUserMessage()\n    Active --> Interrupted: interrupt()\n    Interrupted --> Active: resume\n    Active --> Closed: close()\n    Closed --> Loaded: load()\n    Loaded --> Active: addUserMessage()\n    Active --> Archived: archive()\n    Archived --> Unarchived: unarchive()\n```\n\n## Key files\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/services/SessionService.ts` | Session lifecycle in CLI (3,579 lines) |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/droid/` | Daemon-side CLI process pool |\n| `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | Frontend WebSocket client |\n| `packages/common/src/session/` | Session type definitions |\n| `packages/common/src/daemon/` | RPC method schemas for session operations |\n\n## Session storage\n\nSessions persist to `.factory/sessions/` on disk (one JSON file per session). The backend syncs session metadata to Firestore for cross-device access. Session files include:\n- Message history\n- Tool call results\n- Metadata (title, model, timestamps)\n\n## Daemon session pool\n\nThe daemon keeps a pool of active CLI subprocesses, one per open session. `droid-request-handler.ts` routes RPC calls to the appropriate subprocess based on session ID.\n\n## Frontend session state\n\n`DaemonSessionController.ts` in `packages/frontend` manages the WebSocket connection and updates the Redux `assembly` slice as notifications arrive. Key notification types (from `SessionNotificationType` in `packages/common`):\n- `agentMessage` — new message content\n- `toolCallStart` / `toolCallEnd` — tool execution events\n- `sessionStatus` — agent running/idle state changes\n- `todoWrite` — agent's task list updates\n\n## Related\n\n- [Agent loop](agent-loop.md) — what happens within an active session\n- [Daemon](../apps/daemon.md) — daemon-side session management\n- [DaemonSessionController](../packages/frontend.md) — frontend side\n",
