            "content": "# LLM streaming\n\n## Purpose\n\nLLM streaming is how Droid displays responses as they arrive — tokens appear in real time rather than waiting for the full response. It spans the LLM provider adapters, the agent hook, and the CLI rendering layer.\n\n## Key files\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` | Main streaming hook in CLI |\n| `apps/cli/src/hooks/createLLMStreamingCore.ts` | Core streaming logic (67,822 lines including inline tests) |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/` | Provider-specific streaming adapters |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/` | Shared streaming utilities |\n\n## How it works\n\nWhen the agent loop starts a new LLM request:\n\n1. `useLLMStreaming` opens a streaming request to the configured provider via the backend LLM proxy\n2. Tokens arrive as server-sent events (SSE)\n3. `createLLMStreamingCore` normalizes the provider's stream format into a common event stream\n4. The CLI renders partial text as it arrives via Ink components\n5. Tool calls embedded in the stream are extracted and dispatched to `useToolExecution`\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    useLLMStreaming -->|request| BackendProxy[\"Backend LLM proxy\"]\n    BackendProxy -->|SSE stream| useLLMStreaming\n    useLLMStreaming -->|tokens| createLLMStreamingCore\n    createLLMStreamingCore -->|text events| MessageList\n    createLLMStreamingCore -->|tool call events| useToolExecution\n```\n\n## Provider support\n\nSupported providers (adapters in `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/`):\n- **Anthropic** — Claude models (primary)\n- **OpenAI** — GPT and o-series models\n- **Google GenAI** — Gemini models\n\n## Backend proxy\n\nThe CLI does not call LLM providers directly. All requests go through `apps/backend`'s LLM proxy service, which handles authentication, rate limiting, and provider routing.\n\n## CODEOWNERS\n\n`useLLMStreaming.ts`, `createLLMStreamingCore.ts` are owned by `@factory-arman`, `@stepan-factory`, `@lukealvoeiro`.\n",
