            "content": "# MCP integration\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe Model Context Protocol (MCP) is an open standard for connecting AI models to external tools and data sources. Factory supports MCP servers, letting users extend Droid with custom tools.\n\n## Key files\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/mcp/McpHub.ts` | Manages all MCP server connections |\n| `packages/mcp/` | MCP protocol primitives |\n| `packages/common/src/daemon/` | MCP RPC methods (list, add, remove, toggle, authenticate) |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/droid-request-handler.ts` | Daemon-side MCP method handlers |\n\n## How it works\n\n1. User adds an MCP server via the `McpManager` overlay in the TUI (or via daemon RPC)\n2. `McpHub` connects to the server process and discovers available tools\n3. Discovered tools are registered with the agent's tool registry\n4. The agent can call these tools via the same tool execution pipeline as built-in tools\n5. MCP servers can require OAuth authentication (handled by `DaemonAuthenticateMcpServerRequest`)\n\n## MCP registry\n\nThe daemon maintains an MCP registry accessible via:\n- `listMcpRegistry` — lists available MCP servers\n- `listMcpTools` — lists tools from connected servers\n- `addMcpServer` / `removeMcpServer` — manage servers\n- `toggleMcpServer` / `toggleMcpTool` — enable/disable\n\n## Known issue\n\n`apps/cli/src/mcp/McpHub.ts` has a documented TODO: \"try/catch the MCP error -32603: Invalid URL if the resource doesn't exist.\"\n",
