            "content": "# Wiki generation\n\n## Purpose\n\nFactory's wiki skill generates structured documentation for any repository and uploads it to Factory's web app for browsing. This wiki was itself generated by this skill.\n\n## How it works\n\nThe wiki feature combines:\n1. A **skill** (`.factory/skills/wiki/SKILL.md`) that instructs Droid how to read a repo and generate documentation\n2. A **CLI command** (`droid wiki-upload`) that uploads the generated files to Factory\n\nWhen a user activates the wiki skill, Droid:\n1. Reads the repository structure, key files, git history\n2. Generates a `droid-wiki/` directory of Markdown pages\n3. Writes a `.wiki-meta.json` with page ordering\n4. Runs `droid wiki-upload` to send the pages to the Factory API\n\n## CLI command: wiki-upload\n\n```bash\ndroid wiki-upload \\\n  --session-id \"$SESSION_ID\" \\\n  --repo-url \"$REPO_URL\" \\\n  --wiki-dir ./droid-wiki \\\n  --cleanup    # optional: delete wiki-dir after upload\n```\n\nThe command reads all `.md` files from `--wiki-dir`, reads page order from `.wiki-meta.json`, and posts them to the Factory backend API.\n\n## API types\n\nWiki API types are defined in `packages/common/src/wiki/` (added to the common package in recent commits).\n\n## Frontend display\n\nWiki pages are displayed in `apps/web` via the wiki dashboard feature. The branch name `fac-16604-wiki-dashboard` indicates this feature is in active development.\n\n## Related\n\n- The wiki skill file at `.factory/skills/wiki/SKILL.md`\n- `packages/common/src/wiki/` — wiki types\n- `apps/cli/src/commands/` — wiki-upload command implementation\n",
