            "content": "# Session\n\n## Definition\n\nA session is a conversation thread between a user and the Droid AI agent. It has:\n- A unique ID\n- Message history (user messages, assistant responses, tool calls)\n- Metadata (title, model, created/updated timestamps, project directory)\n- Status (active, closed, archived)\n\n## Where it's defined\n\nCore session types are in `packages/common/src/session/` and `packages/common/src/sessionV2/`.\n\nThe `sessionV2` directory contains the newer message format (`FactoryDroidMessage`, `MessageVisibility`). The original `session/` types exist for backward compatibility.\n\n## How sessions are stored\n\n- **Disk:** `.factory/sessions/<session-id>.json` on the user's machine\n- **Backend:** Session metadata synced to Firestore for cross-device access and history\n\n## Session ID\n\nSession IDs are UUID v4 strings. They appear in daemon RPC calls, log files, file paths, and API routes. When debugging, always note the session ID to correlate logs across CLI, daemon, and frontend.\n\n## Related types\n\n| Type | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `FactoryDroidMessage` | `packages/common/src/sessionV2/types.ts` | A message in a session |\n| `MessageVisibility` | `packages/common/src/sessionV2/enums.ts` | Visible, hidden, or debug |\n| `SessionNotificationType` | `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` | CLI→frontend notification types |\n| `DaemonInitializeSessionRequest` | `packages/common/src/daemon/types.ts` | RPC init request |\n\n## Lifecycle\n\nSee [session management](../features/session-management.md) for the full lifecycle diagram.\n",
