            "content": "# Message\n\n## Definition\n\nA message is a single turn in a session's conversation. Messages have:\n- A role (`user`, `assistant`, or `tool`)\n- Content (text, code blocks, tool calls, tool results — called \"fragments\")\n- Visibility (`visible`, `hidden`, `debug`)\n- A timestamp and unique ID\n\n## Key types\n\n| Type | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `FactoryDroidMessage` | `packages/common/src/sessionV2/types.ts` | The canonical message type |\n| `MessageVisibility` | `packages/common/src/sessionV2/enums.ts` | Who can see the message |\n| `AssemblyFragmentType` | CLI types | Fragment types (code, text, tool use, etc.) |\n\n## Fragments\n\nMessages contain one or more \"fragments\" — granular content units. Fragment types include:\n- `TEXT` — plain text\n- `CODE` — code blocks\n- `TOOL_USE` — tool call made by the agent\n- `TOOL_RESULT` — result returned by a tool\n\nFragments are rendered individually by `apps/cli/src/components/MessageList` in the TUI.\n\n## Message tree\n\nThe frontend's Redux `assembly` slice maintains a \"message tree\" — a structured representation of all messages in the current session. The tree is updated in real time as the agent streams responses via `SessionNotification` events.\n\n## Related\n\n- [Session](session.md) — the container for messages\n- [Tool call](tool-call.md) — tool invocations within messages\n- `packages/common/src/sessionV2/` — type definitions\n",
