            "content": "# CLI releases\n\n## Release process\n\nCLI releases are managed by two GitHub Actions workflows:\n- `.github/workflows/release-cut.yml` — creates a release branch, bumps version\n- `.github/workflows/cli-release.yml` — builds and publishes the CLI binary\n- `.github/workflows/cli-release-npm.yml` — publishes to npm\n- `.github/workflows/binary-release-env.yml` — multi-platform binary builds\n\n## Distribution\n\nThe CLI is distributed as:\n1. **npm package** — `npm install -g @factory/cli`\n2. **Single executable** — macOS, Windows, Linux binaries on S3\n3. **Auto-update** — existing CLI installations self-update via `packages/updater`\n\n## Build process\n\nThe CLI bundles via Bun's Single Executable Application (SEA):\n1. `esbuild.config.js` bundles TypeScript to JavaScript\n2. Native libs (keytar, ripgrep, bun-pty) are embedded by `embed-native-libs.ts`\n3. Bun compiles to a platform-specific binary\n\n## Version checking\n\n`.github/workflows/cli-check-version.yml` verifies version consistency.  \n`.github/workflows/cli-auto-update-test.yml` tests the auto-update mechanism.\n\n## Release stages\n\n1. `release-cut.yml` creates a `release/x.y.z` branch\n2. `release-bump-version.yml` bumps version numbers across packages\n3. `cli-release.yml` builds and uploads binaries\n4. `post-release-validation.yml` validates the release\n",
