            "content": "# Configuration\n\n## Environment variables\n\nEnvironment variables are accessed via `@factory/environment` (not `process.env` directly — that's banned by ESLint). Variables are defined as the `EnvironmentVariable` enum in `packages/environment/src/`.\n\n### Backend\n\n| Variable | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `WORKOS_CLIENT_ID` | WorkOS authentication |\n| `WORKOS_API_KEY` | WorkOS server-side key |\n| `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` | Anthropic LLM proxy |\n| `OPENAI_API_KEY` | OpenAI LLM proxy |\n| `GOOGLE_AI_API_KEY` | Google GenAI LLM proxy |\n| `FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID` | Firestore project |\n| `STATSIG_SERVER_SDK_KEY` | Feature flags (server) |\n| `SENTRY_DSN` | Error tracking |\n| `ORB_API_KEY` | Billing |\n\n### CLI\n\n| Variable | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `FACTORY_API_KEY_DEV` | Dev API authentication |\n| `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE` | Skip daemon auto-update (desktop only) |\n| `FACTORY_OTEL_ENABLED` | Enable OTEL distributed tracing |\n\n### Daemon\n\n| Variable | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE` | Disable auto-update (set by Electron) |\n\nEach app has `.env`, `.env.development`, `.env.staging`, `.env.production` variants plus a `.env.local` (gitignored) for secrets.\n\n## Feature flags\n\nFeature flags use Statsig. All flags are defined in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts` (one of the most frequently changed files — 78 changes in 90 days).\n\nTo add a flag:\n1. Create it in the Statsig console at https://console.statsig.com/\n2. Add the definition to `FactoryFeatureFlags` in `constants.ts`\n3. Use in React with `useFeatureFlagValue(FactoryFeatureFlags.MyFlag)`\n4. Use on the backend with `featureFlags.checkFlag(FactoryFeatureFlags.MyFlag, orgId)`\n\n## Settings\n\nUser and organization settings are managed by `@factory/services`'s `SettingsManager`. The schema is in `packages/common/src/settings/types.ts`. Settings persist to `.factory/settings.json` on disk and sync to the backend.\n\n## Infrastructure\n\nOpenTofu (Terraform) configuration is in `infra/`. Environments are configured in `infra/env/`. Run `tofu init && tofu validate` from the `infra/` directory.\n\n## Ports\n\n| Service | Dev port | Prod port |\n|---|---|---|\n| Backend | 3000 | 443 |\n| Admin | 3001 | 443 |\n| Web | 3002 | 443 |\n| Daemon | 41723 | 37643 |\n| Storybook | 6006 | — |\n",
