            "content": "# Dependencies\n\n## Key runtime dependencies\n\n### Root workspace\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `turbo` | 2.6.3 | Monorepo build system |\n| `bun` | 1.3.10 | CLI and daemon runtime |\n| `typescript` | (per package) | Type safety |\n| `openai` | 6.25.0 | OpenAI API client |\n| `@google/genai` | 1.31.0 | Google GenAI client |\n| `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` | 1.26.0 | MCP protocol |\n| `@statsig/statsig-node-core` | 0.6.1 | Feature flags |\n| `@workos-inc/node` | 7.79.3 | WorkOS auth |\n| `e2b` | 2.14.0 | Cloud sandbox |\n| `orb-billing` | 4.33.0 | Billing |\n| `firebase-tools` | 14.4.0 | Firebase CLI |\n| `knip` | 5.81.0 | Unused export detection |\n\n### CLI (`apps/cli`)\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `ink` | 6.7.0 — React for terminals |\n| `commander` | CLI argument parsing |\n| `@microsoft/tui-test` | TUI E2E testing |\n| `@vscode/ripgrep` | 1.15.14 — code search |\n\n### Frontend (`packages/frontend`, `apps/web`)\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `react` | 19 — UI framework |\n| `@reduxjs/toolkit` | State management |\n| `styled-components` | 6.x — CSS-in-JS |\n| `@workos-inc/authkit-react` | WorkOS auth |\n| `recharts` | Charting |\n| `lucide-react` | Icons |\n\n### Backend (`apps/backend`)\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `next` | 15 — API framework |\n| `firebase-admin` | Firestore access |\n| `@sentry/nextjs` | Error tracking |\n\n## Security overrides\n\nThe root `package.json` has several `overrides` to force secure versions of transitive dependencies:\n\n```json\n\"overrides\": {\n  \"cookie@<0.7.0\": \"0.7.0\",\n  \"path-to-regexp@<0.1.10\": \"0.1.10\",\n  \"path-to-regexp@>=0.2.0 <1.9.0\": \"1.9.0\",\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nThese address known vulnerabilities in older versions of `cookie` and `path-to-regexp`.\n\n## Oldest dependency\n\n`ink` has been in the codebase since the early days of the CLI. Ink 6.7.0 is pinned across the monorepo via `overrides` to prevent version drift.\n\n## Dependency management\n\nRun `npm run knip` to detect unused dependencies. The `depcheck` script (`turbo run depcheck`) also checks for missing or unused packages per workspace.\n\nNode.js version: 18.x (see `.nvmrc`). Package manager: npm 11.2.0 (see `packageManager` in `package.json`).\n",
