            "content": "# Getting started\n\n> **Summary:** How to set up the monorepo for local development, run the key apps, and execute tests. Covers prerequisites, dev server commands, CLI setup, and targeted test execution.\n\n_Last verified: 2026-03-04 against commit `1cfbf04239`. Confidence: high._\n\n## Table of contents\n\n- [Prerequisites](#prerequisites)\n- [Install dependencies](#install-dependencies)\n- [Running the web stack](#running-the-web-stack)\n- [Running the CLI](#running-the-cli)\n- [Build](#build)\n- [Tests](#tests)\n- [Linting and formatting](#linting-and-formatting)\n- [Code references](#code-references)\n- [Related pages](#related-pages)\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- Node 18.x (see `.nvmrc` at the project root)\n- Bun 1.3.10 (specified in `package.json` `packageManager` field)\n- npm 11.x (workspace manager)\n\n## Install dependencies\n\n```bash\nnpm install\n```\n\nFact: The `postinstall` script in `package.json` runs `npm run setup` automatically, which executes `turbo run setup` to build per-workspace setup steps.\n\n## Running the web stack\n\n```bash\n# Start backend, web, storybook, admin, and daemon\nnpm run dev:web\n\n# Start backend, web, storybook, admin, and desktop (local only — requires Electron)\nnpm run dev:desktop\n```\n\nFact: `npm run dev` at the root is intentionally disabled and prints an error message (`package.json` scripts). Use `dev:web` or `dev:desktop`.\n\nDev server logs stream to disk as well as console:\n\n| App | Log file |\n|---|---|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n| daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n\nDefault ports: backend on 3000, admin on 3001, web on 3002.\n\n## Running the CLI\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli\nnpm run setup   # Build droid-dev and droid-localhost wrappers\n```\n\nAfter setup:\n- `droid-dev` — runs CLI from source against hosted dev API\n- `droid-localhost` — runs CLI from source against local API (`localhost:3000`)\n\nFact: After any CLI or daemon code change, you must run `cd apps/cli && npm run setup` and restart the daemon process for changes to take effect (`docs/debugging-daemon.md`).\n\n## Build\n\n```bash\nnpm run build              # Build all packages and apps\nnpm run build -- --filter=apps/web   # Build a single workspace\n```\n\nFact: The build script uses `turbo run build --force --continue` (`package.json`). The `--force` flag bypasses the Turborepo cache.\n\n## Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all tests (consumes ~9 GB RAM — use targeted runs instead)\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common\n\n# Run a specific Jest test file\ncd apps/backend && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts\n\n# Run a specific Vitest file (apps/web uses Vitest)\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run path/to/file.test.ts\n```\n\nFact: The `--filter` flag **must** follow `--` when passed via npm (`AGENTS.md`). Running without `--` causes npm to silently ignore the flag and Turborepo runs every workspace.\n\nFrontend tests that use DOM APIs require a `jsdom` environment annotation at the top of the file:\n\n```ts\n/** @jest-environment jsdom */\n```\n\n## Linting and formatting\n\n```bash\nnpm run fix        # Run ESLint + Prettier (preferred)\nnpm run lint       # ESLint only\nnpm run typecheck  # TypeScript type checking across all packages\nnpm run knip       # Detect unused exports\n```\n\nFact: `npm run fix` maps to `turbo run fix --continue --concurrency 2` (`package.json`).\n\n## Code references\n\n- `package.json` — root scripts and workspace configuration\n- `AGENTS.md` — canonical dev commands and conventions\n- `CLAUDE.md` — additional commands reference\n- `docs/debugging-daemon.md` — CLI + daemon rebuild checklist\n- `turbo.json` — Turborepo pipeline configuration\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Architecture](architecture.md)\n- [Configuration reference](reference/configuration.md)\n- [Droid CLI domain](domains/cli.md)\n- [Daemon domain](domains/daemon.md)\n",
