            "content": "# Domains\n\n> **Summary:** The Factory monorepo is organized into five primary functional domains. Each domain page covers the component's purpose, internal structure, key abstractions, and integration points with other domains.\n\n_Last verified: 2026-03-04 against commit `1cfbf04239`. Confidence: high._\n\n## Domain map\n\n| Domain | Description | Primary code location |\n|---|---|---|\n| [Droid CLI](cli.md) | The `droid` terminal application — TUI, commands, agent loop | `apps/cli/src/` |\n| [Daemon (factoryd)](daemon.md) | Background process managing sessions, terminals, and droid subprocesses | `apps/daemon/src/`, `packages/daemon-core/src/` |\n| [AI agent core](ai-agent.md) | Tool definitions, LLM providers, streaming, message handling | `packages/droid-core/src/` |\n| [Web frontend](web-frontend.md) | Browser and desktop session UI — React, Redux, DaemonSessionController | `apps/web/src/`, `packages/frontend/src/` |\n| [Backend API](backend-api.md) | REST API, LLM proxy, auth, billing, integrations | `apps/backend/src/` |\n\n## How the domains connect\n\nEach domain is a consumer and/or producer for the shared contracts in `packages/common/src/`. Changes to types in `@factory/common` affect multiple domains simultaneously.\n\nFact: `packages/common/src/` is organized by service area: `daemon/`, `droid/`, `llm/`, `session/`, `sessionV2/`, `settings/`, `tools/`, and others (`packages/common/src/` directory listing).\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Architecture](../architecture.md)\n- [Package catalog](../reference/packages.md)\n",
