            "content": "# Droid CLI\n\n> **Summary:** The `droid` CLI is the primary developer interface to the Factory AI agent. It runs as a Bun executable and supports both an interactive terminal UI (Ink/React) and a non-interactive `exec` mode for daemon-driven sessions. This page covers the CLI's internal structure, command set, and agent execution model.\n\n_Last verified: 2026-03-04 against commit `1cfbf04239`. Confidence: high._\n\n## Table of contents\n\n- [Overview](#overview)\n- [Entry point and startup sequence](#entry-point-and-startup-sequence)\n- [Interactive mode vs exec mode](#interactive-mode-vs-exec-mode)\n- [Command structure](#command-structure)\n- [Agent loop](#agent-loop)\n- [Tool execution](#tool-execution)\n- [MCP integration](#mcp-integration)\n- [Skills system](#skills-system)\n- [Code references](#code-references)\n- [Related pages](#related-pages)\n\n## Overview\n\nFact: The CLI binary is named `droid`. After running `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`, two wrapper scripts are created: `droid-dev` (targets hosted dev API) and `droid-localhost` (targets local backend at port 3000) (`docs/debugging-daemon.md`).\n\nFact: The CLI is built with Bun and uses the Single Executable Architecture (SEA) for distribution. The `apps/cli/package.json` declares it as an ESM module (`\"type\": \"module\"`).\n\n## Entry point and startup sequence\n\nFact: The CLI entry point is `apps/cli/src/index.ts`. At startup it:\n\n1. Patches `console.*` methods (`@/utils/patch-console` — must be the first import)\n2. Loads `.env` and `.env.local` via `dotenv`\n3. Configures credentials storage (`configureCredentialsStorage`) with an embedded `keytar` loader\n4. Initializes the API client (`@/api/init`)\n5. Initializes the telemetry client (`CliTelemetryClient.initializeSync()`)\n6. Loads system certificates\n7. Runs a conditional auto-update check (`runConditionalUpdate`)\n8. Registers the Commander.js root command and subcommands\n\nFact: Telemetry initialization is synchronous and happens before any subcommand imports, ensuring logging is available for `TaskToolManager` and other early-loading modules (`apps/cli/src/index.ts` lines 48–55).\n\n## Interactive mode vs exec mode\n\nThe CLI operates in two distinct modes:\n\n**Interactive (TUI) mode** — default when no sub-command is given. Renders a React/Ink terminal UI defined in `apps/cli/src/main.tsx`. The user interacts via a chat-style interface.\n\n**Exec mode** — entered via `droid exec`. The daemon spawns a `droid exec` subprocess and communicates with it over `stdin/stdout` JSON-RPC 2.0. The runner is `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts`.\n\nFact: `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` imports `ClientRequest`, `DroidServerMethod`, `SessionNotificationType`, and other JSON-RPC types from `@factory/common/droid`, showing the protocol contract is centralized in `packages/common`.\n\n## Command structure\n\nCommands are registered in `apps/cli/src/commands/index.ts` and individually defined in `apps/cli/src/commands/`. Major commands include:\n\n| Command | File | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `exec` | `exec.ts` | Daemon-managed agent session (primary agent mode) |\n| `daemon` | `daemon.ts` | Start/stop/status the local daemon |\n| `login` | `login.ts` | Authenticate with Factory |\n| `mcp` | `mcp/` | Manage MCP servers |\n| `missions` | `missions.ts` | Mission decomposition controls |\n| `skills` | `skills.ts` | List and manage skills |\n| `wiki-upload` | `wiki-upload.ts` | Upload generated wiki to Factory |\n| `ssh` | `ssh.ts` | SSH tunnel to remote session |\n| `bug` | `bug.ts` | File a bug report |\n| `update` | `update.ts` | Update the CLI |\n| `stats` | `stats/` | Usage statistics |\n| `computer` | `computer.ts` | Droid Computer (Sprites) management |\n\nFact: `apps/cli/src/commands/exec.ts` is 54 KB and contains the core logic for managing an `exec` session — option parsing, session initialization, message routing, and shutdown coordination.\n\n## Agent loop\n\nFact: When `droid exec` runs, the `streamingJsonRpcExecRunner` receives incoming JSON-RPC requests from the daemon and dispatches them through the agent. The agent loop (`apps/cli/src/agent/messaging.ts`) manages the message history and calls the LLM.\n\nFact: `apps/cli/src/agent/tools.ts` wires together all tool implementations. It imports tool definitions from `@factory/droid-core/tools/definitions` and adds CLI-specific implementations. The file checks `DroidMode` and `DecompSessionType` to gate which tools are available per session type (orchestrator vs worker vs standard).\n\nFact: Permission handling is in `apps/cli/src/agent/PermissionRequestHandler.ts`. Tool confirmations (prompting the user to approve a shell command, for example) are handled by `apps/cli/src/agent/tool-confirmation.ts`.\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant D as Daemon\n    participant R as streamingJsonRpcExecRunner\n    participant A as Agent (messaging.ts)\n    participant T as tools.ts\n    participant L as LLM provider\n\n    D->>R: stdin: addUserMessage (JSON-RPC)\n    R->>A: dispatch message\n    A->>L: LLM call with tools\n    L-->>A: response with tool_use\n    A->>T: execute tool\n    T-->>A: tool result\n    A->>L: next turn with tool_result\n    L-->>A: final text response\n    A-->>R: stream notifications\n    R-->>D: stdout notifications\n```\n\n## Tool execution\n\nFact: Tool definitions are split by category in `packages/droid-core/src/tools/definitions/`:\n\n- `cli/` — Read, LS, Execute, Edit, Create, Grep, Glob, Task, AskUser, ExitSpecMode, GenerateDroid, Skill\n- `file-tools/` — applyPatch, editFile, createFile (with Anthropic-specific variants)\n- `mission/` — proposeMission, startMissionRun, endFeatureRun, dismissHandoffItems\n- `slack/` — slackPostMessage\n- `todo/` — todoWrite\n- `web/` — fetchUrl, webSearch (via Exa)\n\nFact: `packages/droid-core/src/tools/definitions/index.ts` is the single re-export point for all tool definitions used by consumers like `apps/cli/src/agent/tools.ts`.\n\n## MCP integration\n\nFact: MCP (Model Context Protocol) server management is handled by `apps/cli/src/commands/mcp/`. The daemon-side handler is `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/` (which includes an MCP-related handler). MCP status is tracked in `apps/cli/src/exec/mcpStatusHandler.ts`.\n\nFact: The `toggleMcpServer`, `addMcpServer`, `removeMcpServer`, `authenticateMcpServer` JSON-RPC methods are part of the `ClientRequest` schema in `@factory/common/droid` (visible in `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` imports).\n\n## Skills system\n\nFact: Built-in skills are listed in `apps/cli/src/skills/builtin/` and accessed via `getAllSkills()` imported in `apps/cli/src/agent/tools.ts`. The `skillTool` from `@factory/droid-core/tools/definitions` exposes skill invocation to the LLM.\n\nFact: Custom droid configuration is managed by `PluginMarketplaceManager` from `@factory/services/settings`, imported in `apps/cli/src/index.ts`.\n\n## Code references\n\n- `apps/cli/src/index.ts` — CLI entry point and startup sequence\n- `apps/cli/src/main.tsx` — interactive TUI root component\n- `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` — exec mode runner\n- `apps/cli/src/agent/tools.ts` — tool registry wiring\n- `apps/cli/src/agent/messaging.ts` — agent message loop\n- `apps/cli/src/agent/tool-confirmation.ts` — user permission prompts\n- `apps/cli/src/commands/index.ts` — command registration\n- `apps/cli/src/commands/exec.ts` — exec command implementation\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Daemon domain](daemon.md)\n- [AI agent core domain](ai-agent.md)\n- [WebSocket JSON-RPC protocol](../api/websocket-protocol.md)\n- [Architecture](../architecture.md)\n",
