            "content": "# Daemon (factoryd)\n\n> **Summary:** `factoryd` is a Bun-based background process that runs on the user's machine or in a remote sandbox. It owns terminal sessions, spawns and monitors Droid CLI subprocesses, relays JSON-RPC messages between the frontend and the CLI, and manages automation scheduling. This page explains the daemon's structure, startup flow, and component responsibilities.\n\n_Last verified: 2026-03-04 against commit `1cfbf04239`. Confidence: high._\n\n## Table of contents\n\n- [Overview](#overview)\n- [Startup sequence](#startup-sequence)\n- [Core components](#core-components)\n- [WebSocket server and request routing](#websocket-server-and-request-routing)\n- [Terminal management](#terminal-management)\n- [Droid process registry](#droid-process-registry)\n- [Auto-update](#auto-update)\n- [Relay connection](#relay-connection)\n- [Code-server integration](#code-server-integration)\n- [Automation polling](#automation-polling)\n- [Code references](#code-references)\n- [Related pages](#related-pages)\n\n## Overview\n\nFact: The daemon entry point is `apps/daemon/src/index.ts`. It is a thin wrapper over `@factory/daemon-core` (`DaemonCore` from `packages/daemon-core/src/index.ts`). The wrapper adds:\n- Environment loading (`.env` files)\n- Telemetry and OpenTelemetry tracing initialization\n- Auto-update check\n- CLI argument parsing via Commander.js\n\nFact: Default ports are `37643` (production) and `41723` (development), configured via `WS_SERVER_CONFIG` in `packages/common/src/daemon/constants.ts`.\n\n## Startup sequence\n\nFact: `apps/daemon/src/index.ts` follows this order (lines 1–200):\n\n1. Load `.env` and `.env.local` via `dotenv`\n2. Embed native libraries (`@/embed-native-libs`) for `bun-pty`\n3. Initialize telemetry client (`DaemonTelemetryClient.initialize()`)\n4. Initialize OpenTelemetry tracing via `OtelTracing.initialize()`\n5. Run auto-update unless `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=true`\n6. Parse CLI arguments with Commander.js\n7. Load shell environment via `loadShellEnvironment()` to enrich PATH\n8. Build `DaemonCoreConfig` and call `new DaemonCore(config).start()`\n9. Start a `ParentHealthMonitor` to exit when the parent process dies\n\nFact: Auto-update is disabled automatically when `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=true`, which Electron sets when bundling the daemon to preserve code signing (`apps/daemon/src/index.ts` line 83).\n\n## Core components\n\nFact: `DaemonServer` in `packages/daemon-core/src/server/daemon-server.ts` composes the daemon's major subsystems at construction:\n\n| Component | Class | Responsibility |\n|---|---|---|\n| WebSocket server | `DaemonWebSocketServer` | Accept connections, route requests |\n| Terminal manager | `TerminalManager` | Create/manage PTY sessions |\n| Droid registry | `DroidRegistry` | Track spawned `droid exec` processes |\n| API client | `ApiClient` | HTTP client for backend calls |\n| Heartbeat service | `HeartbeatService` | Periodic ping to backend |\n| Due-run poller | `DueRunPoller` | Poll for scheduled automation runs |\n| Code-server manager | `CodeServerManager` | Optional code-server integration |\n| Relay connection | `RelayConnection` | Optional relay for remote access |\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    DS[\"DaemonServer\"]\n    DS --> WS[\"DaemonWebSocketServer\"]\n    DS --> TM[\"TerminalManager\"]\n    DS --> DR[\"DroidRegistry\"]\n    DS --> AC[\"ApiClient\"]\n    DS --> HS[\"HeartbeatService\"]\n    DS --> DRP[\"DueRunPoller\"]\n    DS --> CS[\"CodeServerManager (optional)\"]\n    DS --> RC[\"RelayConnection (optional)\"]\n```\n\n_Diagram represents `packages/daemon-core/src/server/daemon-server.ts` constructor._\n\n## WebSocket server and request routing\n\nFact: `DaemonWebSocketServer` in `packages/daemon-core/src/server/web-socket-server.ts` creates a Bun `Server` instance. It handles three WebSocket upgrade paths (checked via `ws.data.type`):\n\n- `JSONRPC` — Droid session management and terminal control messages\n- `TUNNEL` — raw TCP tunnel for remote access\n- `CODE_SERVER` — proxy WebSocket traffic to a code-server instance\n\nFact: The `WebSocketAuthAdapter` in `packages/daemon-core/src/server/websocket-auth-adapter.ts` sits in front of all JSON-RPC connections. It authenticates the connection and routes messages to the appropriate handler.\n\nFact: `packages/daemon-core/src/server/web-socket-request-router.ts` dispatches incoming JSON-RPC method calls to individual handlers in `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/`.\n\n## Terminal management\n\nFact: `TerminalManager` in `packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/terminal-manager.ts` creates pseudoterminal (PTY) sessions using `bun-pty`. It is configured with `shell`, `homeDir`, and `terminalEnv` from the daemon config.\n\n## Droid process registry\n\nFact: `DroidRegistry` in `packages/daemon-core/src/droid/droid-registry.ts` tracks all active `droid exec` subprocesses keyed by machine ID. It provides lifecycle methods to register, deregister, and look up processes.\n\n## Auto-update\n\nFact: The update service is `apps/daemon/src/services/UpdateService.ts`. It is called with `runAutoUpdate()` at daemon startup. The skip condition is the `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE` environment variable. Auto-update uses `@factory/updater` (in `packages/updater/`).\n\n## Relay connection\n\nFact: `RelayConnection` in `packages/daemon-core/src/relay/RelayConnection.ts` manages an optional persistent connection to the Factory relay service. This allows remote clients to reach the daemon without a direct network path.\n\n## Code-server integration\n\nFact: `CodeServerManager` in `packages/daemon-core/src/code-server/code-server-manager.ts` handles auto-installation and lifecycle of `code-server` (a browser-based VS Code). It is only instantiated when `--enable-code-server` is passed to `factoryd` (line 55 in `daemon-server.ts`).\n\n## Automation polling\n\nFact: `DueRunPoller` in `packages/daemon-core/src/automations/` polls every 60 seconds for scheduled automation runs (`packages/daemon-core/src/server/daemon-server.ts` line 63: `pollIntervalMs: 60_000`). When a run is due, it calls `webSocketServer.dispatchAutomationRun()`.\n\n## Code references\n\n- `apps/daemon/src/index.ts` — daemon entry point\n- `apps/daemon/src/environment.ts` — environment variable loading and validation\n- `packages/daemon-core/src/index.ts` — `DaemonCore` class\n- `packages/daemon-core/src/server/daemon-server.ts` — `DaemonServer` composition root\n- `packages/daemon-core/src/server/web-socket-server.ts` — `DaemonWebSocketServer`\n- `packages/daemon-core/src/server/websocket-auth-adapter.ts` — auth and request routing\n- `packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/terminal-manager.ts` — PTY session management\n- `packages/daemon-core/src/droid/droid-registry.ts` — process tracking\n- `packages/daemon-core/src/relay/RelayConnection.ts` — relay connectivity\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Architecture](../architecture.md)\n- [Droid CLI domain](cli.md)\n- [WebSocket JSON-RPC protocol](../api/websocket-protocol.md)\n- [Configuration reference](../reference/configuration.md)\n",
