            "content": "# AI agent core\n\n> **Summary:** `@factory/droid-core` is the model-agnostic AI agent library. It defines tools, LLM provider adapters, message structures, streaming protocols, and the automations runtime. The CLI and daemon-core both build on top of it. This page documents the library's organization and key abstractions.\n\n_Last verified: 2026-03-04 against commit `1cfbf04239`. Confidence: high._\n\n## Table of contents\n\n- [Overview](#overview)\n- [Package structure](#package-structure)\n- [Tool system](#tool-system)\n- [LLM providers](#llm-providers)\n- [Message handling](#message-handling)\n- [Streaming](#streaming)\n- [Mission decomposition](#mission-decomposition)\n- [Automations](#automations)\n- [Code references](#code-references)\n- [Related pages](#related-pages)\n\n## Overview\n\nFact: `packages/droid-core/package.json` declares `@factory/droid-core`. The `src/` directory contains 14 subdirectories: `api/`, `automations/`, `core/`, `droids/`, `feature-flags/`, `llms/`, `machine-connection/`, `messages/`, `prompts/`, `streaming/`, `test-utils/`, `tools/` (`packages/droid-core/src/` directory listing).\n\n## Package structure\n\n| Subdirectory | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `api/` | HTTP client for Factory API (`fetch.ts`, `droid.ts`, `readiness.ts`) |\n| `automations/` | Automation run dispatch and scheduling support |\n| `core/` | Core agent types and shared interfaces |\n| `droids/` | Droid configuration types and defaults |\n| `feature-flags/` | Client-side feature flag access |\n| `llms/` | LLM provider adapters (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, xAI) |\n| `machine-connection/` | Machine connection abstractions |\n| `messages/` | Message construction, validation, recovery |\n| `prompts/` | System prompt builders |\n| `streaming/` | SSE / streaming response handling |\n| `tools/` | Tool definitions, registry, execution types |\n\n## Tool system\n\nFact: `packages/droid-core/src/tools/definitions/index.ts` is the single export point for all tool definitions. It exports tools in these categories:\n\n- **CLI tools** — `readCliTool`, `lsCliTool`, `executeCliTool`, `editCliTool`, `grepSearchCliTool`, `globSearchCliTool`, `createCliTool`, `applyPatchCliTool`, `taskCliTool`, `skillTool`, `generateDroidCliTool`, `askUserTool`, `exitSpecModeTool`\n- **File tools** — `applyPatchTool`, `editFileTool`, `editFileAnthropicTool`, `createFileTool`, `createFileAnthropicTool`\n- **Web tools** — `webSearchTool`, `fetchUrlTool`\n- **Mission tools** — `proposeMissionTool`, `startMissionRunTool`, `endFeatureRunTool`, `dismissHandoffItemsTool`\n- **Slack tools** — `slackPostMessageTool`\n- **Todo tools** — `todoWriteTool`\n\nFact: Each tool is created via `packages/droid-core/src/tools/create-tool.ts`. A tool has an `id`, `description`, `inputSchema` (JSON Schema), and an `execute` function signature. The tool type is defined in `packages/droid-core/src/tools/types.ts`.\n\nFact: `packages/droid-core/src/tools/registry.ts` provides a `ToolRegistry` class that stores tools keyed by ID and supports lookup and listing.\n\n### Tool definitions directory\n\nFact: Individual tool files in `packages/droid-core/src/tools/definitions/` include:\n\n- `globSearch.ts` — file path glob search using ripgrep\n- `grepSearch.ts` — content search using ripgrep\n- `shell.ts` — shell command execution\n- `viewFile.ts` / `viewFolder.ts` — file and directory inspection\n- `cli/` — 21 CLI-specific tool files\n\n## LLM providers\n\nFact: LLM provider routing is in `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/router.ts`. Provider implementations are in subdirectories:\n\n- `anthropic/` — Anthropic Claude models\n- `openai/` — OpenAI GPT models\n- `google/` — Google Gemini models\n- `xai/` — xAI Grok models\n\nFact: `packages/droid-core/src/llms/index.ts` exports the provider types and `LLMModel` interfaces. Model pricing is tracked in `packages/droid-core/src/llms/price.ts`.\n\nFact: The `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/sanitize-json-schema.ts` file sanitizes tool JSON schemas before sending them to LLM APIs (different providers have different schema restrictions).\n\n## Message handling\n\nFact: `packages/droid-core/src/messages/` handles the conversation message lifecycle:\n\n- `create-xml-params.ts` — builds XML-formatted tool parameter strings\n- `fragment-to-string.ts` — converts streaming fragments to strings\n- `is-complete-assistant-message.ts` — validates message completeness\n- `recovery-message.ts` — generates recovery prompts for interrupted sessions\n- `utils.ts` — shared message utilities\n\nFact: `packages/droid-core/src/messages/enums.ts` defines `MessageRole` and `MessageContentBlockType`, which are core to the conversation data model.\n\n## Streaming\n\nFact: `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/schema.ts` (19 KB) defines the complete streaming event schema — all the event types that flow from LLM provider responses through the CLI to the frontend.\n\nFact: `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/enums.ts` enumerates streaming event types. `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/data-stream-parts.ts` provides helpers for constructing stream parts.\n\n## Mission decomposition\n\nFact: Mission tools in `packages/droid-core/src/tools/definitions/mission/` implement the multi-agent orchestration protocol:\n\n- `proposeMission.ts` — agent proposes a mission decomposition\n- `startMissionRun.ts` — starts a worker session for a sub-task\n- `endFeatureRun.ts` — marks a feature run as complete\n- `dismissHandoffItems.ts` — dismisses pending handoff items from a worker\n\nFact: Mission tools are gated by `DecompSessionType` in `apps/cli/src/agent/tools.ts`. Only orchestrator sessions get `proposeMissionTool` and `startMissionRunTool`; only worker sessions get `endFeatureRunTool`.\n\n## Automations\n\nFact: `packages/droid-core/src/automations/` handles the automation scheduling integration. The daemon-core's `DueRunPoller` calls into this subsystem to dispatch scheduled automation runs.\n\n## Code references\n\n- `packages/droid-core/src/tools/definitions/index.ts` — all tool exports\n- `packages/droid-core/src/tools/registry.ts` — `ToolRegistry` class\n- `packages/droid-core/src/tools/types.ts` — `FactoryTool`, `ToolImplementation`, `LLMToolSpec`\n- `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/router.ts` — LLM provider routing\n- `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/sanitize-json-schema.ts` — schema sanitization\n- `packages/droid-core/src/messages/` — message construction and validation\n- `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/schema.ts` — streaming event schema\n- `packages/droid-core/src/tools/definitions/mission/` — mission decomposition tools\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Architecture](../architecture.md)\n- [Droid CLI domain](cli.md)\n- [Data models reference](../reference/data-models.md)\n- [Package catalog](../reference/packages.md)\n",
