            "content": "# Web frontend\n\n> **Summary:** The web frontend spans three layers: `apps/web` (the Vite + React single-page app), `packages/frontend` (shared React features and services), and `packages/core-ui` (the mandatory design system). This page covers the session lifecycle, state management, UI architecture, and the design system rules.\n\n_Last verified: 2026-03-04 against commit `1cfbf04239`. Confidence: high._\n\n## Table of contents\n\n- [Overview](#overview)\n- [apps/web structure](#appsweb-structure)\n- [packages/frontend structure](#packagesfrontend-structure)\n- [DaemonSessionController](#daemonsessioncontroller)\n- [State management](#state-management)\n- [Design system (@factory/core-ui)](#design-system-factorycore-ui)\n- [Feature flags](#feature-flags)\n- [Authentication](#authentication)\n- [E2E testing](#e2e-testing)\n- [Code references](#code-references)\n- [Related pages](#related-pages)\n\n## Overview\n\nFact: `apps/web` is a Vite + React 19 single-page application that runs in the browser (`docs/repo-overview.md`). It mounts at port 3002 in development. The web app and the Electron desktop app (`apps/desktop`) share the same `packages/frontend` code.\n\nFact: `apps/web/src/main.tsx` is the SPA entry point. The source directory (`apps/web/src/`) contains `auth/`, `config/`, and `types/` subdirectories.\n\n## apps/web structure\n\nFact: The web app source directory is intentionally thin. The bulk of UI features live in `packages/frontend/src/features/` and are imported by the web app's router.\n\n```\napps/web/src/\n├── auth/         # WorkOS AuthKit integration\n├── config/       # App-level configuration\n├── main.tsx      # SPA entry point\n└── types/        # App-specific TypeScript types\n```\n\n## packages/frontend structure\n\nFact: `packages/frontend/src/` has these top-level directories: `api/`, `app/`, `auth/`, `errors/`, `features/`, `hooks/`, `index.ts`, `layouts/`, `router/`, `services/`, `types/`, `utils/`, `views/`.\n\nFact: The `features/` directory contains 23 feature modules (from `packages/frontend/src/features/` listing):\n\n| Feature | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `sessions/` | Session list, session chat view, mutations, queries |\n| `settings/` | User and org settings UI |\n| `automations/` | Automation builder and scheduler |\n| `missions/` | Mission decomposition UI |\n| `analytics/` | Usage analytics display |\n| `auth/` | Auth flow integration |\n| `feature-flags/` | Client-side flag access |\n| `onboarding/` | New user onboarding |\n| `wiki/` | Wiki viewing integration |\n\n## DaemonSessionController\n\nFact: `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` (81 KB) is the central class for managing the WebSocket connection to the daemon. It extends `EventEmitter` (line 1) and exposes methods for every JSON-RPC operation: `initializeSession`, `loadSession`, `addUserMessage`, `interruptSession`, `toggleMcpServer`, `runAutomation`, etc.\n\nFact: The controller imports every request/response type from `@factory/common/daemon` — `DaemonInitializeSessionRequestParams`, `DaemonLoadSessionRequestParams`, `DaemonListAutomationsResult`, and dozens more. All cross-layer type contracts flow through `@factory/common`.\n\nFact: `WorkerSessionRegistry` in `packages/frontend/src/services/session/WorkerSessionRegistry.ts` tracks active worker sessions for the mission decomposition system. It stores `WorkerStateInfo` by session ID.\n\n## State management\n\nFact: `packages/frontend` uses Redux Toolkit with entity adapters for session state (`docs/frontend.md` Technology Stack section). The `sessions/atoms/` directory in `packages/frontend/src/features/sessions/atoms/` holds Redux slice definitions.\n\nFact: Redux selectors must be precise rather than selecting entire slice objects. The convention (from `docs/frontend.md`) is:\n\n```typescript\n// Correct\nconst messageTree = useSelector(\n  (state: RootState) => state.assembly.messageTree\n);\n// Incorrect\nconst { messageTree } = useSelector((state: RootState) => state.assembly);\n```\n\n## Design system (@factory/core-ui)\n\nFact: All UI components must use primitives from `@factory/core-ui`. Direct use of HTML elements (`<div>`, `<button>`, `<input>`) is prohibited by ESLint rules enforced in `AGENTS.md`.\n\nFact: `packages/core-ui/` exports: layout primitives (`Box`, `Flex`, `Grid`), form components (`Button`, `Input`, `Dropdown`), typography (`Header`, `Text`), and interactive components (`Collapsible`, `Toast`) (`docs/repo-overview.md`).\n\nFact: Colors must use the semantic color system (`colors.semantics`). Hardcoded hex values are prohibited.\n\nFact: Storybook (`apps/storybook/`) is the live reference for all components. Start it via `npm run dev:web`.\n\n## Feature flags\n\nFact: Feature flags use Statsig. The flag definitions are in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts` as the `FactoryFeatureFlags` object. Each flag has a `displayName`, `statsigName`, and `defaultValue` (`docs/feature-flags.md`).\n\nFact: In React components, flags are checked via `useFeatureFlagValue(FactoryFeatureFlags.FlagName)` imported from `@/featureFlags`. Server-side checks use `getFeatureFlagInstance()` from `@/features/feature-flags/server`.\n\nFact: A DEV menu appears at the bottom-right of the app in non-production environments, allowing local flag overrides (`docs/feature-flags.md`).\n\n## Authentication\n\nFact: Authentication uses WorkOS AuthKit (`@workos-inc/authkit-react 0.5.1`). The auth integration lives in `apps/web/src/auth/` and `packages/frontend/src/features/auth/`.\n\n## E2E testing\n\nFact: `apps/web/e2e/` contains Playwright end-to-end tests. Configuration is in `apps/web/playwright.config.ts`. The `docs/playwright-e2e-testing.md` file documents conventions.\n\n## Code references\n\n- `apps/web/src/main.tsx` — SPA entry point\n- `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` — WebSocket session controller\n- `packages/frontend/src/services/session/WorkerSessionRegistry.ts` — worker session tracking\n- `packages/frontend/src/features/sessions/` — session UI feature\n- `packages/core-ui/` — design system primitives\n- `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts` — feature flag definitions\n- `docs/frontend.md` — comprehensive frontend conventions guide\n- `docs/feature-flags.md` — feature flag usage guide\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Architecture](../architecture.md)\n- [Backend API domain](backend-api.md)\n- [Daemon domain](daemon.md)\n- [Package catalog](../reference/packages.md)\n",
