            "content": "# Backend API\n\n> **Summary:** `apps/backend` is a Next.js 15 application that serves as the Factory platform's REST API. It handles authentication, session management, LLM proxying, billing, integrations (GitHub, Linear, Slack), cron jobs, and webhooks. This page describes its route structure, service layer, and key integration points.\n\n_Last verified: 2026-03-04 against commit `1cfbf04239`. Confidence: high._\n\n## Table of contents\n\n- [Overview](#overview)\n- [Route structure](#route-structure)\n- [Middleware and security](#middleware-and-security)\n- [Service layer](#service-layer)\n- [LLM proxy](#llm-proxy)\n- [Authentication](#authentication)\n- [Billing](#billing)\n- [Integrations](#integrations)\n- [Error handling](#error-handling)\n- [Cron jobs](#cron-jobs)\n- [Code references](#code-references)\n- [Related pages](#related-pages)\n\n## Overview\n\nFact: `apps/backend` runs on Next.js 15 with the App Router at port 3000. The web frontend in this app is deprecated; `apps/web` is the current web interface (`docs/repo-overview.md`).\n\nFact: The backend `src/app/api/` directory contains 35 route groups: `auth/`, `billing/`, `cron/`, `daemon/`, `github/`, `integrations/`, `llm/`, `organization/`, `sessions/`, `tools/`, `webhooks/`, `workspaces/`, and others (`apps/backend/src/app/api/` listing).\n\n## Route structure\n\nFact: Next.js App Router places API handlers under `apps/backend/src/app/api/`. Each leaf directory has a `route.ts` file with HTTP method handlers. Notable groups:\n\n| Route group | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `api/auth/` | WorkOS authentication flows |\n| `api/billing/` | Orb billing, subscriptions, usage |\n| `api/cron/` | 16 cron job endpoints for scheduled tasks |\n| `api/daemon/` | Daemon registration and health |\n| `api/github/` | GitHub App webhooks and API proxy |\n| `api/integrations/` | Third-party integrations (Linear, Slack, etc.) |\n| `api/llm/` | LLM API proxy and streaming |\n| `api/organization/` | Org management, members, settings |\n| `api/sessions/` | Session CRUD and retrieval |\n| `api/tools/` | Tool execution endpoints |\n| `api/webhooks/` | Inbound webhook handlers |\n| `api/feature-flags/` | Feature flag evaluation endpoint |\n| `api/admin/` | Internal admin-only endpoints |\n| `api/v0/` | Versioned API endpoints |\n\n## Middleware and security\n\nFact: `apps/backend/src/middleware.ts` runs on the Vercel Edge Network before any route handler. It enforces CORS against an `allowedOrigins` list (defined in `apps/backend/src/constants.ts`) and sets security headers on every response.\n\nFact: Security headers set by the middleware include: `X-Content-Type-Options`, `Content-Security-Policy`, `Referrer-Policy`, `Cross-Origin-Opener-Policy`, `Cross-Origin-Embedder-Policy`, `Permissions-Policy` (`apps/backend/src/middleware.ts` lines 28–44).\n\nFact: Allowed origins include `https://api.factory.ai`, `https://app.factory.ai`, Vercel preview URLs (`https://backend-*-factory-ai.vercel.app`, `https://web-*-factory-ai.vercel.app`), and localhost variants for development (`apps/backend/src/constants.ts`).\n\n## Service layer\n\nFact: `apps/backend/src/services/` contains these service directories: `bigquery/`, `cde/`, `computer/`, `e2b/`, `exa/`, `fraud/`, `integrations/`, `loops/`, `orb/`, `referrals/`, `remote-update/`, `segment/`, `stripe/`, `telemetry/`, `workos/`.\n\nFact: `apps/backend/src/features/` contains: `droids/`, `feature-flags/`, `integrations/`, `llm/`, `prompts/`, `workspace/`.\n\n## LLM proxy\n\nFact: The LLM proxy is at `apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/`. The backend's `apps/backend/src/features/llm/` directory holds the LLM provider integration logic that the API routes call into.\n\nInference: The backend proxies LLM calls so that API keys stay server-side. The CLI calls the backend LLM endpoint rather than provider APIs directly.\n\n## Authentication\n\nFact: Authentication is WorkOS-based. The `apps/backend/src/services/workos/` directory handles WorkOS API calls. Auth routes are in `apps/backend/src/app/api/auth/`.\n\nFact: `apps/backend/src/middleware.ts` imports `createOriginValidator` from `@factory/utils/security/csp-config` for pre-compiled CORS origin checks.\n\n## Billing\n\nFact: Billing uses Orb (`orb-billing` package, version 4.33.x per `package.json`). The billing service is in `apps/backend/src/services/orb/`. Stripe is also present in `apps/backend/src/services/stripe/` for some payment flows.\n\n## Integrations\n\nFact: `apps/backend/src/services/integrations/` has 26 subdirectories covering integrations with external services. `apps/backend/src/app/api/integrations/` provides the API routes that the frontend calls.\n\nFact: `apps/backend/src/common/src/integrations/` (inside `packages/common`) defines the API type contracts for each integration service.\n\n## Error handling\n\nFact: All error handling follows the patterns in `docs/error-handling.md`. The canonical error classes are imported from `@factory/logging/errors`:\n\n- `MetaError` — internal 500 errors\n- `ResponseError400BadRequest` through `ResponseError503ServiceUnavailable` — HTTP status errors\n\nFact: Route handlers wrap logic in `handleRouteMiddleware()` and throw these error classes. The middleware formats the `NextResponse`. Raw `new Error()` is never used (`docs/error-handling.md`).\n\n## Cron jobs\n\nFact: `apps/backend/src/app/api/cron/` contains 16 cron endpoint files (from directory listing). These are invoked on a schedule by Vercel Cron.\n\n## Code references\n\n- `apps/backend/src/app/api/` — all API route handlers\n- `apps/backend/src/middleware.ts` — CORS and security headers\n- `apps/backend/src/constants.ts` — allowed origins and CSP configuration\n- `apps/backend/src/services/` — external service integrations\n- `apps/backend/src/features/` — business logic features\n- `docs/error-handling.md` — error class and handling conventions\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Architecture](../architecture.md)\n- [REST endpoints reference](../api/rest-endpoints.md)\n- [Web frontend domain](web-frontend.md)\n- [Configuration reference](../reference/configuration.md)\n",
