            "content": "# API overview\n\n> **Summary:** The Factory platform exposes two API surfaces: a REST API served by `apps/backend` and a WebSocket JSON-RPC 2.0 protocol implemented by the daemon. This section documents both surfaces and their type contracts.\n\n_Last verified: 2026-03-04 against commit `1cfbf04239`. Confidence: high._\n\n## API surfaces\n\n| Surface | Protocol | Implemented in | Documentation |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| REST API | HTTP/HTTPS | `apps/backend/src/app/api/` | [REST endpoints](rest-endpoints.md) |\n| Daemon protocol | WebSocket JSON-RPC 2.0 | `packages/daemon-core/src/server/` | [WebSocket protocol](websocket-protocol.md) |\n\n## Type contracts\n\nFact: All API type definitions are centralized in `packages/common/src/`. The directory is organized by service domain: `agent/`, `api/`, `automations/`, `billing/`, `cli/`, `daemon/`, `droid/`, `events/`, `feature-flags/`, `integrations/`, `llm/`, `organization/`, `relay/`, `session/`, `sessionV2/`, `settings/`, `shared/`, `tools/`, etc. (`packages/common/src/` listing).\n\nFact: `AGENTS.md` mandates that new API endpoints must have types defined in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts`.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [REST endpoints](rest-endpoints.md)\n- [WebSocket JSON-RPC protocol](websocket-protocol.md)\n- [Backend API domain](../domains/backend-api.md)\n- [Daemon domain](../domains/daemon.md)\n",
