            "content": "# WebSocket JSON-RPC protocol\n\n> **Summary:** The daemon and CLI use a JSON-RPC 2.0 protocol over WebSocket (and stdin/stdout for the CLI exec subprocess). This page documents all request methods, notification types, and the message flow between client, daemon, and CLI process.\n\n_Last verified: 2026-03-04 against commit `1cfbf04239`. Confidence: high._\n\n## Table of contents\n\n- [Protocol framing](#protocol-framing)\n- [Client-to-daemon methods (DroidServerMethod)](#client-to-daemon-methods-droidservermethod)\n- [Daemon-to-client notifications (DroidClientMethod)](#daemon-to-client-notifications-droidclientmethod)\n- [Session notification types](#session-notification-types)\n- [Working states](#working-states)\n- [MCP methods](#mcp-methods)\n- [Terminal methods (DaemonSpecificNotificationType)](#terminal-methods)\n- [Code references](#code-references)\n- [Related pages](#related-pages)\n\n## Protocol framing\n\nFact: All messages use JSON-RPC 2.0 framing. The protocol version constants are `JSONRPC_VERSION` and `FACTORY_PROTOCOL_VERSION` imported from `@factory/common/droid` (`apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` line 33).\n\nFact: WebSocket connections to the daemon are authenticated via `WebSocketAuthAdapter` in `packages/daemon-core/src/server/websocket-auth-adapter.ts`.\n\n## Client-to-daemon methods (DroidServerMethod)\n\nFact: All client-to-daemon JSON-RPC method names are defined in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` as the `DroidServerMethod` enum:\n\n| Method | Value | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `INITIALIZE_SESSION` | `droid.initialize_session` | Start a new session |\n| `LOAD_SESSION` | `droid.load_session` | Resume an existing session |\n| `ADD_USER_MESSAGE` | `droid.add_user_message` | Send a user message to the agent |\n| `INTERRUPT_SESSION` | `droid.interrupt_session` | Interrupt the running agent |\n| `KILL_WORKER_SESSION` | `droid.kill_worker_session` | Terminate a worker session |\n| `UPDATE_SESSION_SETTINGS` | `droid.update_session_settings` | Update model/autonomy settings |\n| `TOGGLE_MCP_SERVER` | `droid.toggle_mcp_server` | Enable/disable an MCP server |\n| `AUTHENTICATE_MCP_SERVER` | `droid.authenticate_mcp_server` | Trigger MCP OAuth flow |\n| `CANCEL_MCP_AUTH` | `droid.cancel_mcp_auth` | Cancel an in-progress MCP auth |\n| `CLEAR_MCP_AUTH` | `droid.clear_mcp_auth` | Remove stored MCP credentials |\n| `ADD_MCP_SERVER` | `droid.add_mcp_server` | Register a new MCP server |\n| `REMOVE_MCP_SERVER` | `droid.remove_mcp_server` | Remove an MCP server |\n| `LIST_MCP_REGISTRY` | `droid.list_mcp_registry` | List available MCP servers |\n| `LIST_MCP_TOOLS` | `droid.list_mcp_tools` | List tools from connected MCP servers |\n| `TOGGLE_MCP_TOOL` | `droid.toggle_mcp_tool` | Enable/disable a specific MCP tool |\n| `LIST_SKILLS` | `droid.list_skills` | List available skills |\n| `SUBMIT_BUG_REPORT` | `droid.submit_bug_report` | Submit a bug report |\n\n## Daemon-to-client notifications (DroidClientMethod)\n\nFact: The daemon pushes three notification methods to clients (`packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`):\n\n| Method | Value | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `SESSION_NOTIFICATION` | `droid.session_notification` | Streaming session events (tool results, text deltas, state changes) |\n| `REQUEST_PERMISSION` | `droid.request_permission` | Ask the user to confirm a tool execution |\n| `ASK_USER` | `droid.ask_user` | Ask the user a question (AskUser tool) |\n\n## Session notification types\n\nFact: `SESSION_NOTIFICATION` carries a payload typed by `SessionNotificationType` in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`:\n\n| Type | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `TOOL_RESULT` | Result of a tool execution |\n| `TOOL_PROGRESS_UPDATE` | Progress update during a long tool call |\n| `CREATE_MESSAGE` | A new conversation message was created |\n| `ERROR` | An error notification |\n| `DROID_WORKING_STATE_CHANGED` | Agent working state changed |\n| `PERMISSION_RESOLVED` | User resolved a permission request |\n| `SETTINGS_UPDATED` | Session settings were updated |\n| `SESSION_TITLE_UPDATED` | The auto-generated session title changed |\n| `MCP_STATUS_CHANGED` | MCP server connection status changed |\n| `ASSISTANT_TEXT_DELTA` | Streaming text token from the LLM |\n| `THINKING_TEXT_DELTA` | Streaming thinking/reasoning token |\n| `SESSION_TOKEN_USAGE_CHANGED` | Token count updated |\n| `MISSION_STATE_CHANGED` | Mission orchestration state changed |\n| `MISSION_FEATURES_CHANGED` | Feature list in the mission changed |\n| `MISSION_PROGRESS_ENTRY` | A new mission progress log entry |\n| `MISSION_HEARTBEAT` | Periodic mission alive signal |\n| `MISSION_WORKER_STARTED` | A worker session started |\n| `MISSION_WORKER_COMPLETED` | A worker session completed |\n| `MCP_AUTH_REQUIRED` | MCP server requires OAuth |\n| `MCP_AUTH_COMPLETED` | MCP OAuth flow finished |\n\n## Working states\n\nFact: `DroidWorkingState` in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` tracks what the agent is doing at any moment:\n\n| State | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `Idle` | Agent waiting for user input |\n| `StreamingAssistantMessage` | LLM is generating a response |\n| `WaitingForToolConfirmation` | Waiting for user to approve a tool |\n| `ExecutingTool` | A tool is running |\n| `CompactingConversation` | Conversation history is being compacted |\n\n## MCP methods\n\nFact: MCP server statuses are tracked by `McpServerStatus` in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`: `Connecting`, `Connected`, `Disconnected`, `Failed`, `Disabled`.\n\nFact: MCP server transport types are `McpServerType.Stdio` and `McpServerType.Http`.\n\n## Terminal methods\n\nFact: In addition to session methods, the daemon WebSocket server handles terminal operations. The `DaemonSessionController` in `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` exposes `createTerminal`, `writeData`, `resize`, `closeTerminal`, `listTerminals` typed against `DaemonSpecificNotificationType` and related types from `@factory/common/daemon`.\n\n## Code references\n\n- `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` — all enum definitions: `DroidServerMethod`, `DroidClientMethod`, `SessionNotificationType`, `DroidWorkingState`, `DecompSessionType`, `MissionState`\n- `packages/common/src/droid/types.ts` — request and response type definitions\n- `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/` — Zod schemas for each message type\n- `packages/common/src/daemon/constants.ts` — port and connection constants\n- `packages/daemon-core/src/server/websocket-auth-adapter.ts` — connection authentication\n- `packages/daemon-core/src/server/web-socket-request-router.ts` — method dispatch\n- `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` — client-side implementation\n- `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` — CLI exec subprocess handler\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Daemon domain](../domains/daemon.md)\n- [Droid CLI domain](../domains/cli.md)\n- [REST endpoints](rest-endpoints.md)\n- [Architecture](../architecture.md)\n",
