            "content": "# REST endpoints\n\n> **Summary:** The `apps/backend` Next.js API serves REST endpoints under `/api/`. This page catalogs the major route groups, their purposes, and the key type contracts each group depends on.\n\n_Last verified: 2026-03-04 against commit `1cfbf04239`. Confidence: high._\n\n## Table of contents\n\n- [Base URL and versioning](#base-url-and-versioning)\n- [Endpoint groups](#endpoint-groups)\n- [Type contracts](#type-contracts)\n- [Error responses](#error-responses)\n- [Code references](#code-references)\n- [Related pages](#related-pages)\n\n## Base URL and versioning\n\nFact: The backend runs at port 3000. Production base URL is `https://api.factory.ai`. Development URL is `https://dev.api.factory.ai` (`apps/backend/src/constants.ts` `allowedOrigins`).\n\nFact: `apps/backend/src/app/api/v0/` and `apps/backend/src/app/api/v1/` provide versioned endpoints. Most feature endpoints are unversioned.\n\n## Endpoint groups\n\nFact: Route groups are directories under `apps/backend/src/app/api/` (full listing from directory traversal):\n\n| Group | Path prefix | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| Auth | `/api/auth/` | WorkOS SSO flows, token refresh |\n| Billing | `/api/billing/` | Orb subscriptions, usage metering |\n| Bug reports | `/api/bug-reports/` | Capture and store CLI/TUI bug reports |\n| CLI | `/api/cli/` | CLI-specific endpoints (version check, etc.) |\n| Cron | `/api/cron/` | 16 scheduled job handlers (Vercel Cron) |\n| Daemon | `/api/daemon/` | Daemon registration, heartbeat, health |\n| Desktop | `/api/desktop/` | Desktop app update and config |\n| E2E | `/api/e2e/` | End-to-end test helpers (non-production) |\n| Feature flags | `/api/feature-flags/` | Server-side Statsig evaluation |\n| Factory API keys | `/api/factory-api-key/` | API key management |\n| GitHub | `/api/github/` | GitHub App webhook handler, API proxy |\n| Health | `/api/health/` | Health check endpoint |\n| Integrations | `/api/integrations/` | GitHub, Linear, Slack, Jira, etc. |\n| LLM | `/api/llm/` | LLM proxy (streaming + non-streaming) |\n| Organization | `/api/organization/` | Org CRUD, members, invitations |\n| Promotions | `/api/promotions/` | Promotional codes |\n| Realtime | `/api/realtime/` | Realtime push events |\n| Referral | `/api/referral/` | Referral program |\n| Search | `/api/search/` | Session and content search |\n| Sessions | `/api/sessions/` | Session CRUD (REST layer) |\n| Telemetry | `/api/telemetry/` | Client telemetry collection |\n| Tools | `/api/tools/` | Tool execution results |\n| User | `/api/user/` | User profile |\n| Webhooks | `/api/webhooks/` | Inbound webhooks from external services |\n| Workspaces | `/api/workspaces/` | Workspace management |\n\n## Type contracts\n\nFact: Request and response types for every API group are defined in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts` (`AGENTS.md`). The `packages/common/src/api/` directory holds subdirectories for each service area: `admin/`, `agent/`, `automations/`, `billing/`, `cli/`, `daemon/`, `desktop/`, `droid/`, `integrations/`, `llm/`, `organization/`, `policy/`, `relay/`, `repositories/`, `session/`, `sessionV2/`, `settings/`, `tags/`, `terminal/`, `timeline/`, `tools/`, `usage/`, `wiki/`, `workspaces/`.\n\n## Error responses\n\nFact: Error responses are formatted by the `handleRouteMiddleware` helper in `apps/backend`. The error class hierarchy maps directly to HTTP status codes (`docs/error-handling.md`):\n\n| Class | HTTP status |\n|---|---|\n| `ResponseError400BadRequest` | 400 |\n| `ResponseError401Unauthorized` | 401 |\n| `ResponseError403Forbidden` | 403 |\n| `ResponseError404NotFound` | 404 |\n| `ResponseError409RetryConflict` | 409 |\n| `ResponseError410Gone` | 410 |\n| `ResponseError422InvalidData` | 422 |\n| `ResponseError429RateLimitExceeded` | 429 |\n| `ResponseError501NotImplemented` | 501 |\n| `ResponseError503ServiceUnavailable` | 503 |\n| `MetaError` | 500 |\n\nFact: All error classes are imported from `@factory/logging/errors` (`docs/error-handling.md` Canonical imports section).\n\n## Code references\n\n- `apps/backend/src/app/api/` — all route handler directories\n- `packages/common/src/api/` — API type contracts by service\n- `apps/backend/src/middleware.ts` — CORS and security headers applied to all routes\n- `docs/error-handling.md` — error class usage guide\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [WebSocket JSON-RPC protocol](websocket-protocol.md)\n- [Backend API domain](../domains/backend-api.md)\n- [Data models reference](../reference/data-models.md)\n",
