          "input": {
            "content": "# Configuration\n\n> **Summary:** Each app in the monorepo reads environment variables at startup. This page lists all known variables, their locations, and the `@factory/environment` package that centralizes environment access. It also explains how build-time defines work for compiled CLI and daemon binaries.\n\n_Last verified: 2026-03-04 against commit `1cfbf04239`. Confidence: high._\n\n## Table of contents\n\n- [@factory/environment package](#factoryenvironment-package)\n- [Core environment variables](#core-environment-variables)\n- [Daemon-specific variables](#daemon-specific-variables)\n- [CLI-specific variables](#cli-specific-variables)\n- [Backend variables](#backend-variables)\n- [Build-time defines](#build-time-defines)\n- [Environment tiers](#environment-tiers)\n- [.env file locations](#env-file-locations)\n- [Code references](#code-references)\n- [Related pages](#related-pages)\n\n## @factory/environment package\n\nFact: `packages/environment/src/constants.ts` defines `EnvironmentVariable` — an object of string constants for all known environment variable names. This is the canonical source for variable name strings.\n\nFact: `packages/environment/src/enums.ts` defines `FactoryEnv` (`Development` | `Production`) and `DeploymentEnv` (`Localhost` | `Development` | `Staging` | `Preprod` | `Production`).\n\nFact: The directory used for Factory config data is determined by `FactoryEnv`: `~/.factory-dev/` for Development, `~/.factory/` for Production (`packages/environment/src/constants.ts` `FACTORY_ENV_DIRS`).\n\n## Core environment variables\n\nThese variables apply to all apps (daemon, CLI, backend):\n\n| Variable | Purpose | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `FACTORY_ENV` | Runtime environment mode | `development` or `production` |\n| `FACTORY_DEPLOYMENT_ENV` | Deployment tier | `localhost`, `development`, `staging`, `preprod`, `production` |\n| `FACTORY_API_BASE_URL` | Base URL for the Factory backend API | Required |\n| `FACTORY_APP_BASE_URL` | Base URL for the web app | Required |\n| `FACTORY_DOWNLOADS_BUCKET` | S3 bucket for downloads | Required |\n| `FACTORY_DOWNLOADS_PREFIX` | Path prefix within the downloads bucket | Optional |\n| `FACTORY_API_KEY` | API key for service-to-service auth | Optional |\n| `FACTORY_LOG_FILE` | Override log file path | Optional |\n| `FACTORY_DISABLE_KEYRING` | Disable system keychain for auth storage | Optional, set `true` in CI |\n\n## Daemon-specific variables\n\n| Variable | Purpose | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `FACTORYD_VERSION` | Daemon version string | Set by build |\n| `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE` | Skip auto-update at startup | Set by Electron bundle to preserve code signing |\n| `FACTORY_OTEL_ENABLED` | Enable OpenTelemetry tracing | Defaults to `false` |\n| `ROLLBACK_ENABLED` | Enable rollback mechanism | Defaults to `true` |\n| `REMOTE_MACHINE_ID` | Machine ID for remote sandboxes | Set by E2B/CDE infrastructure |\n| `FACTORY_MACHINE_TYPE` | Override machine type (`local` / `ephemeral`) | Optional |\n| `MISSION_WORKER_INACTIVITY_TIMEOUT_MS` | Worker session inactivity timeout | Optional |\n| `TESTING_BYPASS_TOKEN_PASSWORD` | E2E test bypass token | Test-only, never in production |\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_PORT` | Relay server port | Optional |\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_HOST` | Relay server host | Optional |\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_DEBUG` | Enable relay debug logging | Optional |\n\n## CLI-specific variables\n\n| Variable | Purpose | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| `FACTORY_DROID_AUTO_UPDATE_ENABLED` | Control CLI auto-update | |\n| `FACTORY_WORKOS_BASE_URL` | Override WorkOS API base URL | For E2E tests with mock servers |\n| `FACTORY_DISABLE_DYNAMIC_CONFIG` | Disable runtime dynamic configuration | Test-only |\n\n## Backend variables\n\nFact: The backend reads `NEXT_PUBLIC_ENV` to determine the deployment tier and select Statsig's environment tier (`docs/feature-flags.md`). `NEXT_PUBLIC_ENV=production` selects the production tier; anything else uses development/staging.\n\nUnknown: A complete list of backend-specific environment variables was not found in a single location. The `apps/backend/.env.example` file and `apps/backend/.env` contain the definitive list.\n\n## Build-time defines\n\nFact: The CLI and daemon are compiled binaries (SEA — Single Executable Architecture). At build time, `scripts/build-sea.ts` injects values via `bun build --define`. The known defines are:\n\n| Define | Runtime fallback |\n|---|---|\n| `__FACTORY_ENV__` | `FACTORY_ENV` env var |\n| `__FACTORY_DEPLOYMENT_ENV__` | `FACTORY_DEPLOYMENT_ENV` env var |\n| `__FACTORY_API_BASE_URL__` | `FACTORY_API_BASE_URL` env var |\n| `__FACTORY_APP_BASE_URL__` | `FACTORY_APP_BASE_URL` env var |\n| `__FACTORY_DOWNLOADS_BUCKET__` | `FACTORY_DOWNLOADS_BUCKET` env var |\n| `__FACTORY_DOWNLOADS_PREFIX__` | `FACTORY_DOWNLOADS_PREFIX` env var |\n| `__FACTORYD_VERSION__` | `FACTORYD_VERSION` env var |\n| `__ROLLBACK_ENABLED__` | `ROLLBACK_ENABLED` env var |\n\nFact: Both `apps/daemon/src/environment.ts` and `apps/cli/src/environment.ts` use `typeof __DEFINE__ !== 'undefined'` guards before accessing build-time defines to avoid `ReferenceError` when running unbundled.\n\n## Environment tiers\n\n| `FACTORY_ENV` | `FACTORY_DEPLOYMENT_ENV` | Data dir | Default daemon port | Statsig tier |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| `development` | `localhost` | `~/.factory-dev/` | 41723 | development |\n| `development` | `development` | `~/.factory-dev/` | 41723 | staging |\n| `production` | `staging` | `~/.factory/` | 37643 | staging |\n| `production` | `preprod` | `~/.factory/` | 37643 | staging |\n| `production` | `production` | `~/.factory/` | 37643 | production |\n\n## .env file locations\n\nEach app loads `.env` and `.env.local` from its own directory at startup:\n\n| App | Primary .env | Override |\n|---|---|---|\n| `apps/daemon` | `apps/daemon/.env` | `apps/daemon/.env.local` |\n| `apps/cli` | `apps/cli/.env` | `apps/cli/.env.local` |\n| `apps/backend` | `apps/backend/.env` | — |\n\nFact: Daemon and CLI environment files are named `.env.development`, `.env.production`, `.env.staging`, `.env.preprod`, `.env.localhost` in their respective directories.\n\n## Code references\n\n- `packages/environment/src/constants.ts` — `EnvironmentVariable` object, all known variable names\n- `packages/environment/src/enums.ts` — `FactoryEnv`, `DeploymentEnv` enums\n- `apps/daemon/src/environment.ts` — daemon environment initialization\n- `apps/cli/src/environment.ts` — CLI environment initialization\n- `packages/environment/README.md` — package documentation\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Getting started](../getting-started.md)\n- [Architecture](../architecture.md)\n- [Daemon domain](../domains/daemon.md)\n",
