            "content": "# Data models\n\n> **Summary:** This page covers the core TypeScript types that flow through the system: sessions, messages, tools, agents, and the JSON-RPC protocol types. All canonical types live in `@factory/common`; this page maps the key interfaces to their source files.\n\n_Last verified: 2026-03-04 against commit `1cfbf04239`. Confidence: high._\n\n## Table of contents\n\n- [Session model](#session-model)\n- [Message model](#message-model)\n- [Tool types](#tool-types)\n- [Agent state types](#agent-state-types)\n- [Mission decomposition types](#mission-decomposition-types)\n- [Streaming event types](#streaming-event-types)\n- [Code references](#code-references)\n- [Related pages](#related-pages)\n\n## Session model\n\nFact: The primary session type is `FactoryDroidSession` in `packages/common/src/sessionV2/types.ts`:\n\n```typescript\ninterface FactoryDroidSession {\n  id: string;\n  isLegacy: boolean;\n  messages: FactoryDroidMessage[];\n  messagesCount?: number;\n  machineConnectionType?: MachineConnectionType;\n  workspaceSandboxId?: string | null;\n  computerId?: string;\n  title?: string;\n  createdAt: number;\n  updatedAt: number;\n  owner?: string;\n  privacyLevel?: SessionPrivacyLevel;\n  droidStatus?: DroidExecutionStatus | null;\n  callingSessionId?: string | null;   // set on worker sessions\n  callingToolUseId?: string | null;   // parent tool use that spawned this session\n  tags?: SessionTag[];\n  isPinned?: boolean;\n  archivedAt?: string;\n}\n```\n\nFact: `packages/common/src/session/enums.ts` defines enums used by the session model: `DroidExecutionStatus`, `MachineConnectionType`, `SessionCreatedLocation`, `SessionPrivacyLevel`.\n\n## Message model\n\nFact: `FactoryDroidMessage` is defined in `packages/common/src/sessionV2/messages/types.ts`. Messages contain `role` (`MessageRole` — user/assistant), a list of content blocks, and metadata.\n\nFact: `MessageRole` and `MessageContentBlockType` enums are defined in `packages/droid-core/src/messages/enums.ts` and re-exported from `@factory/common/sessionV2`.\n\nFact: Content blocks can be text, image, tool_use, or tool_result types, as enumerated in `MessageContentBlockType`.\n\n## Tool types\n\nFact: The tool interface is `FactoryTool` in `packages/droid-core/src/tools/types.ts`. A tool has:\n\n- `id` — unique string identifier\n- `description` — shown to the LLM\n- `inputSchema` — JSON Schema object for input validation\n- `execute` — async function taking input and returning a result\n\nFact: `LLMToolSpec` in `packages/droid-core/src/tools/types.ts` is the provider-agnostic representation sent to the LLM. The provider-specific adapters in `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/` convert `LLMToolSpec` to the format each API expects.\n\nFact: `ToolImplementation` in `packages/droid-core/src/tools/types.ts` wraps `FactoryTool` with runtime execution context (`ToolExecutionContext` from `apps/cli/src/agent/types.ts`).\n\n## Agent state types\n\nFact: `DroidWorkingState` in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` tracks the agent's current activity:\n- `Idle` — waiting for input\n- `StreamingAssistantMessage` — LLM generating\n- `WaitingForToolConfirmation` — user approval pending\n- `ExecutingTool` — tool running\n- `CompactingConversation` — history compaction in progress\n\nFact: `ToolConfirmationOutcome` in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` encodes all possible user responses to a permission prompt: `ProceedOnce`, `ProceedAlways`, `ProceedAutoRun`, `ProceedAutoRunLow`, `ProceedAutoRunMedium`, `ProceedAutoRunHigh`, `ProceedEdit`, `Cancel`.\n\nFact: `ToolConfirmationType` enumerates which tool categories require confirmation: `Edit`, `Execute`, `Create`, `AskUser`, `ExitSpecMode`, `ProposeMission`, `StartMissionRun`, `ApplyPatch`, `McpTool`.\n\n## Mission decomposition types\n\nFact: `DecompSessionType` in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` distinguishes `Orchestrator` (top-level) from `Worker` (sub-agent) sessions.\n\nFact: `MissionState` in `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` tracks orchestrator state: `AwaitingInput`, `Initializing`, `Running`, `Paused`, `OrchestratorTurn`, `Completed`.\n\nFact: `FeatureStatus` (`Pending`, `InProgress`, `Completed`, `Cancelled`) and `FeatureSuccessState` (`Success`, `Partial`, `Failure`) track the lifecycle of individual features within a mission.\n\nFact: `FactoryDroidSession.callingSessionId` and `callingToolUseId` link worker sessions back to their parent orchestrator session (`packages/common/src/sessionV2/types.ts`).\n\n## Streaming event types\n\nFact: `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/schema.ts` (19 KB) defines all streaming event schemas. Events travel from the LLM provider response → CLI agent → daemon → frontend.\n\nFact: `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/enums.ts` enumerates the streaming event types that the CLI sends as JSON-RPC notifications.\n\n## Code references\n\n- `packages/common/src/sessionV2/types.ts` — `FactoryDroidSession`, `PaginatedSessionsResponse`\n- `packages/common/src/session/enums.ts` — `DroidExecutionStatus`, `MachineConnectionType`, `SessionPrivacyLevel`\n- `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` — `DroidWorkingState`, `ToolConfirmationOutcome`, `ToolConfirmationType`, `DecompSessionType`, `MissionState`\n- `packages/droid-core/src/tools/types.ts` — `FactoryTool`, `LLMToolSpec`, `ToolImplementation`\n- `packages/droid-core/src/messages/enums.ts` — `MessageRole`, `MessageContentBlockType`\n- `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/schema.ts` — streaming event schema definitions\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [AI agent core domain](../domains/ai-agent.md)\n- [WebSocket JSON-RPC protocol](../api/websocket-protocol.md)\n- [Package catalog](packages.md)\n",
