            "content": "# Package catalog\n\n> **Summary:** Complete listing of every workspace in the monorepo — both apps and packages — with their primary purpose, tech stack, and key exports or entry points.\n\n_Last verified: 2026-03-04 against commit `1cfbf04239`. Confidence: high._\n\n## Table of contents\n\n- [Apps](#apps)\n- [Packages](#packages)\n- [Related pages](#related-pages)\n\n## Apps\n\n### apps/backend\n\nFact: Next.js 15 REST API at port 3000. Handles auth, billing, LLM proxy, cron jobs, GitHub/Linear/Slack integrations, and session data. The web frontend in this app is deprecated (`docs/repo-overview.md`).\n\n- Entry: `apps/backend/src/app/api/`\n- Config: `apps/backend/src/middleware.ts`, `apps/backend/next.config.mjs`\n\n### apps/admin\n\nFact: Next.js 15 admin dashboard at port 3001. Used for internal user management, analytics, billing operations, and feature flag management.\n\n- Stack: Redux Toolkit, styled-components\n\n### apps/web\n\nFact: Vite + React 19 SPA. The primary web interface for Droid chat sessions. Authenticated via WorkOS AuthKit. E2E tested with Playwright (`apps/web/playwright.config.ts`).\n\n- Entry: `apps/web/src/main.tsx`\n\n### apps/desktop\n\nFact: Electron application wrapping `apps/web`. Bundles the `factoryd` daemon, manages its lifecycle, and handles auto-updates via S3 distribution.\n\n### apps/daemon\n\nFact: Bun runtime background service (`factoryd`). WebSocket server on port 37643 (prod) / 41723 (dev). Manages terminal sessions, spawns `droid exec` subprocesses, and relays JSON-RPC messages.\n\n- Entry: `apps/daemon/src/index.ts`\n- Key dep: `@factory/daemon-core`\n\n### apps/cli\n\nFact: Bun-based `droid` CLI. Supports interactive TUI (Ink/React) and exec mode (JSON-RPC subprocess). ~90 commands, 90 tool definitions.\n\n- Entry: `apps/cli/src/index.ts`\n- Key deps: `@factory/droid-core`, `@factory/common`, `@factory/daemon-core`\n\n### apps/factory-vscode-extension\n\nFact: Visual Studio Code extension for Factory platform integration.\n\n### apps/functions\n\nFact: Firebase Cloud Functions for serverless backend tasks.\n\n### apps/scripts\n\nFact: Build, deployment, and maintenance utility scripts.\n\n### apps/storybook\n\nFact: Storybook instance for `@factory/core-ui` component documentation.\n\n### apps/relay\n\nFact: Relay service for routing connections to remote daemon instances.\n\n### apps/signal\n\nFact: Signal service. Unknown: exact purpose was not determined from available source files.\n\n### apps/droid-computer-worker\n\nFact: Worker for Droid Computer (Sprites) — persistent compute instances.\n\n---\n\n## Packages\n\n### @factory/core-ui (`packages/core-ui`)\n\nFact: Mandatory design system. All UI components must use this package. Provides `Box`, `Flex`, `Grid`, `Button`, `Input`, `Dropdown`, `Header`, `Text`, `Collapsible`, `Toast`, and a semantic color system (`docs/repo-overview.md`).\n\n### @factory/common (`packages/common`)\n\nFact: Shared type contracts, enums, and constants for all workspaces. Organized into 35+ subdirectories by service area. The canonical location for API types (`packages/common/src/`).\n\n### @factory/frontend (`packages/frontend`)\n\nFact: Shared React features and services used by both `apps/web` and `apps/desktop`. Contains `DaemonSessionController`, feature modules (sessions, settings, automations, missions), and the shared router.\n\n### @factory/droid-core (`packages/droid-core`)\n\nFact: AI agent core library. Provides tool definitions, LLM provider adapters (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, xAI), message handling, streaming schemas, and mission decomposition tools.\n\n### @factory/daemon-core (`packages/daemon-core`)\n\nFact: Environment-agnostic daemon implementation. `DaemonCore` class is the single entry point. Used by both `apps/daemon` and `apps/cli` (for in-process daemon mode).\n\n### @factory/services (`packages/services`)\n\nFact: Business logic and external service integrations shared across workspaces.\n\n### @factory/models (`packages/models`)\n\nFact: TypeScript data model schemas and type definitions.\n\n### @factory/logging (`packages/logging`)\n\nFact: Centralized logging utilities. Exports `logInfo`, `logWarn`, `logException`, `Metrics`, and the error class hierarchy (`MetaError`, `ResponseErrorXXX`). Used by all workspaces.\n\n### @factory/utils (`packages/utils`)\n\nFact: Shared utility functions — string formatting, date parsing, shell utilities, retry logic.\n\n### @factory/updater (`packages/updater`)\n\nFact: Auto-update logic for CLI and daemon. Handles version checking, download, and install.\n\n### @factory/environment (`packages/environment`)\n\nFact: Strongly-typed environment variable access. Defines `EnvironmentVariable` constants, `FactoryEnv`, `DeploymentEnv` enums, and `setEnvironmentProvider` / `getEnvironment` API. Replaces direct `process.env` access across the codebase.\n\n### @factory/runtime (`packages/runtime`)\n\nFact: Auth token storage and credential management. Provides `getAuthToken`, `configureCredentialsStorage`.\n\n### @factory/daemon-client (`packages/daemon-client`)\n\nFact: Client library for connecting to the daemon WebSocket server from external consumers.\n\n### @factory/signal-core (`packages/signal-core`)\n\nFact: Core library for the signal service.\n\n### @factory/mcp (`packages/mcp`)\n\nFact: Model Context Protocol shared types and utilities.\n\n### @factory/eslint-config (`packages/eslint-config`)\n\nFact: Shared ESLint configuration applied across all workspaces.\n\n### @factory/test-utils (`packages/test-utils`)\n\nFact: Shared test utilities, mocks, and helpers for Jest/Vitest tests.\n\n### @factory/component-library (`packages/component-library`)\n\nFact: Additional component library, separate from `@factory/core-ui`.\n\n---\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Architecture](../architecture.md)\n- [Domains overview](../domains/index.md)\n- [Configuration reference](configuration.md)\n",
