ta models** (`reference/data-models.md`)\nCore types, where the source of truth lives for each piece of data, what's cached vs live.\n\n**13. API surface** (`api/*.md`)\nEndpoints, protocols, contracts, backwards compatibility rules. Only if the repo exposes APIs.\n\n**14. External dependencies** (`reference/dependencies.md`)\nEvery third-party service, why we use it, where the integration code lives, what happens when it's down.\n\n**15. Why is it this way?** (`design-decisions.md`)\nThe 5-15 key architectural choices and their rationale. What was considered and rejected. What constraints forced the current design.\n\n**16. Where are the dragons?** (`pitfalls.md`)\nFragile areas, implicit contracts, things that look safe but aren't, common mistakes new contributors make, the file everyone is afraid of.\n\n**17. Technical debt and legacy context** (`migration-context.md`)\nWhy two systems exist for the same thing, which one to use for new code, what's being deprecated, active migration plans.\n\n**18. Deployment** (`deployment.md`)\nCommit to prod pipeline, environments, how to rollback, what's not rollback-safe, how to know your change is working in prod.\n\n**19. Security model** (`security.md`)\nTrust boundaries, what's authenticated, where secrets live, what should never be logged, input validation strategy.\n\n**20. Fun facts** (`fun-facts.md`)\nOrigin of the project name, oldest surviving code, easter eggs, the TODO from 2021. Makes the codebase human.\n\n---\n\nNot every repo needs all 20. A small CLI tool might collapse half of these into 5 pages. A large monorepo might expand domains into 15 sub-pages. The skill should list these as the *menu* and let the survey phase determine which ones the repo actually warrants.\n\nWant me to update the skill with this structure?",
