          "text": "\n\nI spent time on this earlier in our conversation and my answer hasn't changed. The current intent-driven groupings are:\n\n- **\"How to contribute\"** -- \"I want to submit code, what do I need to know?\"\n- **Overview** -- \"I just joined, orient me\"\n\nI proposed \"How it runs\" (ops/deployment/monitoring), \"How to extend\" (plugin patterns), \"How it's built\" (build tooling), \"How to debug\", and \"Data model\" earlier. I was critical of all of them and concluded none earn their place because engineers go to the source code or runbooks for those things, not a wiki.\n\nThat assessment still holds. The two groupings we have are the only ones that match how engineers actually use documentation.",
