            "content": "# Factory platform overview\n\nFactory is an AI software engineering platform built around Droid, an autonomous coding agent. Developers interact with Droid through a terminal CLI, a web app, or a native desktop app to get help writing, debugging, and shipping code.\n\nThe core loop: you describe a task, Droid reads your codebase, writes or edits files, runs tests, and reports back—all in a conversational interface backed by a streaming LLM pipeline.\n\n## What Factory does\n\n- **Droid CLI** (`droid` command) — a hybrid terminal app that runs a full TUI or accepts headless commands. This is the primary developer interface.\n- **Daemon** (`factoryd`) — a background process that manages agent sessions, terminal access, and the local WebSocket server that the web/desktop apps connect to.\n- **Web app** — a browser interface to the same agent experience, useful when working on remote machines.\n- **Desktop app** — an Electron wrapper that bundles the web app and the daemon together for a native install.\n- **Backend API** — a Next.js service that handles auth, LLM proxying, billing, integrations, and session persistence.\n\n## Key concepts\n\n- **Session** — a conversation between you and Droid. A session has a message history, tool calls, and a working directory.\n- **Droid** — an AI agent configured with a set of tools (file read/write, shell execution, search, etc.) and backed by an LLM.\n- **Mission** — a spec-first workflow where Droid drafts a plan before executing. You approve the plan, then Droid runs it.\n- **Tool** — a capability exposed to the LLM: `Read`, `Edit`, `Execute`, `Grep`, `Glob`, and more. Defined in `packages/droid-core/src/tools`.\n- **Relay** — a WebSocket relay service that lets browser clients reach a daemon running on a remote machine (BYOI/BYOK).\n- **Signal** — a GCP Cloud Function that analyzes sessions to find friction and delight moments.\n\n## Quick links\n\n- [Architecture](./architecture.md) — system components and how they connect\n- [Getting started](./getting-started.md) — prerequisites, install, and first run\n- [Glossary](./glossary.md) — all the project-specific terms\n- [CLI app](../apps/cli/index.md) — entry point for most developers\n- [Contributing](../contributing/index.md) — how to work in this codebase\n",
