            "content": "# Glossary\n\nProject-specific terms used across the codebase and documentation.\n\n| Term | Definition |\n|------|-----------|\n| **Droid** | The AI software engineering agent. Also the name of the CLI binary (`droid`). |\n| **Session** | A single conversation with Droid, including message history, tool call results, and working directory context. |\n| **Mission** | A spec-first workflow: Droid drafts a plan (the spec), you approve it, then Droid executes. Enabled via `droid --spec` or the `/mission` command. |\n| **Tool** | A capability exposed to the LLM (e.g., `Read`, `Edit`, `Execute`, `Grep`). Defined in `packages/droid-core/src/tools`. |\n| **TUI** | Terminal User Interface. The full-screen Ink/React app rendered in the terminal when you run `droid` interactively. |\n| **Headless mode** | Running the CLI without the TUI, via `droid exec` or other Commander subcommands. Useful for CI and scripting. |\n| **Daemon (factoryd)** | The background process that manages agent sessions and terminal access. Runs on the local machine or a CDE. |\n| **DaemonCore** | The `@factory/daemon-core` package — environment-agnostic daemon logic used by both `apps/daemon` and `apps/cli` (daemon mode). |\n| **Relay** | The `apps/relay` WebSocket relay service that bridges browser clients to daemons running on BYOI/BYOK machines. |\n| **BYOI / BYOK** | Bring Your Own Infrastructure / Bring Your Own Keys. A mode where the customer's own machine or API key is used instead of Factory's cloud. |\n| **CDE** | Cloud Development Environment — a remote machine (e.g., E2B sandbox) where the daemon and CLI run. |\n| **Signal** | The `apps/signal` analytics service. It processes sessions to detect friction and delight moments and stores results in BigQuery. |\n| **SEA** | Single Executable Application. The compiled `droid` binary built via Node.js SEA for distribution without a runtime dependency. |\n| **Assembly** | The Redux slice in `packages/frontend` that owns session state for the web/desktop apps. |\n| **ACP** | Agent Communication Protocol — the internal protocol used by the CLI's `apps/cli/src/acp` module. |\n| **Ink** | The React-based terminal rendering library used by the CLI TUI. |\n| **Statsig** | The feature flag service. Flag definitions live in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`. |\n| **WorkOS** | The authentication provider. Used for SSO, user management, and JWT token issuance. |\n| **Orb** | The billing platform integrated through `apps/backend/src/services/orb`. |\n| **Knip** | A tool that detects unused exports and dependencies in the monorepo. Run with `npm run knip`. |\n| **Turborepo** | The build orchestration tool. Runs tasks in parallel across workspaces and caches results. Config at `turbo.json`. |\n| **Workspace** | An npm workspace — one of the entries in the `workspaces` array in the root `package.json`. |\n| **MetaError** | The base error class from `@factory/logging/errors`. All internal 500-level errors must use this class. |\n| **JSON-RPC 2.0** | The protocol used for CLI↔daemon and daemon↔client communication. |\n| **PTY** | Pseudo-terminal. Used by the daemon to run shell commands with full terminal emulation (via `bun-pty`). |\n",
