            "content": "# Contributing\n\nThis section covers everything you need to work effectively in the Factory monorepo.\n\n## Before you start\n\nRead `AGENTS.md` at the repo root — it has the canonical command reference, architecture overview, and a list of things you must not do (like using `<div>` directly instead of `Box`, or hardcoding colors).\n\nRead `docs/ui-development.md` before touching any `packages/frontend` code. Design is the source of truth for all UI/UX decisions.\n\n## Pages in this section\n\n- [Development workflow](./development-workflow.md) — branch, code, test, PR, merge\n- [Testing](./testing.md) — test frameworks, patterns, how to run\n- [Debugging](./debugging.md) — logs, common issues, CLI/daemon debugging\n- [Patterns and conventions](./patterns-and-conventions.md) — error handling, file organization, coding style\n- [Tooling](./tooling.md) — Turborepo, ESLint config, code generators\n\n## Quick command reference\n\n```bash\nnpm run fix          # lint + format all packages (preferred over npm run lint)\nnpm run typecheck    # TypeScript check across all packages\nnpm run knip         # detect unused exports\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/frontend   # test one package\n```\n\nAlways pass `--filter` after `--` — without the `--`, npm eats the flag and Turborepo runs everything.\n\n## PR conventions\n\nTitle format: `type(scope): description`\n\n- Types: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`\n- Scope: the workspace name from `apps/*` or `packages/*`, or `monorepo`\n- Example: `feat(cli): add wiki-upload command`\n\nEvery PR description must include a Linear ticket reference (`Closes FAC-1234`). See `.github/pull_request_template.md` for the full template.\n",
