            "content": "# Development workflow\n\n## Branch and commit\n\nThe default branch is `dev`. Feature branches follow the Conventional Commits naming convention to match PR titles:\n\n```\nfeat/fac-1234-short-description\nfix/fac-5678-bug-description\n```\n\nCommits do not need to follow Conventional Commits format; only PR titles do.\n\n## Making changes\n\n1. Branch from `dev`.\n2. Make your changes, keeping the scope narrow.\n3. Run `npm run fix -- --filter=<your-package>` to lint and format.\n4. Run `npm run typecheck -- --filter=<your-package>` to check types.\n5. Run tests: `npm run test -- --filter=<your-package>`.\n6. Open a PR against `dev`.\n\nFor CLI/daemon changes, rebuild after every code change:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup   # creates droid-dev alias\n```\n\nThen start a new session — the old session caches the previous build.\n\n## Running the stack locally\n\n```bash\n# Start backend + web + admin + daemon\nnpm run dev:web\n\n# Or with Electron instead of daemon\nnpm run dev:desktop\n```\n\nEach app dual-streams output to console and a `/tmp/factory-dev-*.log` file.\n\n## Internal tooling\n\nThe `internal/` directory contains tools not part of the main product:\n\n- `internal/web` — internal dashboard (`dev:internal`)\n- `internal/apps/` and `internal/packages/` — supporting utilities\n\n## Release process\n\nSee [Deployment: release process](../deployment/release-process.md). Releases are cut from the `dev` branch by the CI pipeline.\n\n## Hotfixes\n\nHotfix branches target `main` and are cherry-picked forward to `dev`. The `hotfix-cut.yml` workflow in `.github/workflows/` orchestrates this.\n",
