            "content": "# Testing\n\n## Test frameworks by app/package\n\n| Location | Runner | Config file |\n|----------|--------|------------|\n| `apps/backend` | Jest | `apps/backend/jest.config.ts` |\n| `apps/cli` | Jest + TUI test | `apps/cli/jest.config.cjs` |\n| `apps/daemon` | Jest | `apps/daemon/jest.config.ts` |\n| `apps/relay` | Jest + Bun test | `apps/relay/` |\n| `packages/frontend` | Vitest (unit) + Playwright (E2E) | |\n| `packages/droid-core` | Jest | `packages/droid-core/jest.config.ts` |\n| `packages/daemon-core` | Jest | `packages/daemon-core/jest.config.ts` |\n\n## Running tests\n\n```bash\n# Run tests for a specific package (CORRECT — note the --)\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/cli\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common --filter=@factory/daemon-core\n\n# Run a single test file (backend)\ncd apps/backend && npx jest src/services/billing/billing.test.ts\n\n# Run a single test file (frontend package)\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run src/features/sessions/SessionList.test.tsx\n\n# Run a single test file (CLI)\ncd apps/cli && npx jest src/commands/exec.test.ts\n```\n\n## Frontend tests: jsdom environment\n\nAll frontend tests that use browser APIs must declare the jsdom environment at the top of the file:\n\n```ts\n/**\n * @jest-environment jsdom\n */\n```\n\nWithout this, you get `ReferenceError: document is not defined`.\n\n## Mocking pattern\n\nUse top-level `jest.mock` with `requireActual` to preserve unmocked exports:\n\n```ts\njest.mock('./module', () => ({\n  ...jest.requireActual('./module'),\n  functionToMock: jest.fn(),\n}));\n\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetAllMocks());\n```\n\n## Singleton isolation\n\nWhen testing modules with singletons (settings, services, etc.), use module isolation instead of reset functions:\n\n```ts\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetModules());\n\nit('test', async () => {\n  const { getService } = await import('./service');\n  // fresh module instance\n});\n```\n\n## E2E tests\n\n**Frontend (Playwright):**\n\n```bash\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e           # headless\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e -- --headed --debug\n```\n\n**CLI (TUI test):**\n\nThe CLI uses `@microsoft/tui-test` for end-to-end terminal interaction tests. Config is in `apps/cli/tui-test.config.ts`. These tests launch a real terminal and automate keystrokes.\n\n**CLI stream JSON-RPC tests:**\n\nA separate Jest config at `apps/cli/jest.e2e-stream-jsonrpc.config.cjs` runs integration tests against the streaming JSON-RPC exec mode.\n\n## CI test workflows\n\n- `test.yml` — runs `npm run test` across all packages\n- `test-backend.yml` — backend-specific tests\n- `test-cli.yml` — CLI tests\n- `cli-e2e-tests.yml` — full CLI E2E test suite on multiple platforms\n\n## Testing conventions\n\n- Colocate test files with the source file they test (e.g., `service.ts` → `service.test.ts`).\n- Test only the public API of a module.\n- Keep pure utility helpers real (don't mock `@factory/utils` functions unnecessarily).\n- Add `@jest-environment jsdom` to any test file that touches the DOM.\n\nSee `docs/unit-tests.md` for the full testing guide.\n",
