            "content": "# Debugging\n\n## Architecture overview\n\n```\nFrontend (DaemonSessionController.ts)\n    ↓ WebSocket JSON-RPC\nDaemon (droid-request-handler.ts)\n    ↓ stdin/stdout JSON-RPC\nCLI (streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.tsx)\n```\n\n## Log file locations\n\n| Environment | Directory | Key files |\n|-------------|-----------|-----------|\n| Production | `~/.factory/logs/` | `factoryd.log`, `droid-log-single.log`, `console.log` |\n| Development | `~/.factory-dev/logs/` | Same files, but for dev builds |\n\nDev builds write to `~/.factory-dev/`, not `~/.factory/`.\n\n## Development setup checklist\n\nAfter modifying CLI or daemon code:\n\n1. `cd apps/cli && npm run setup` — rebuilds `droid-dev` and `droid-localhost` wrappers\n2. Restart the daemon process\n3. Start a **new** session (old sessions cache the previous binary)\n\n## Watching logs in real time\n\n```bash\ntail -f ~/.factory-dev/logs/factoryd.log\ntail -f ~/.factory-dev/logs/droid-log-single.log\n\n# All logs at once\ntail -f ~/.factory-dev/logs/*.log\n```\n\nDev server logs (for `npm run dev:web`):\n\n```bash\ntail -f /tmp/factory-dev-backend.log\ntail -f /tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log\n```\n\n## Common issues\n\n**Daemon not starting**: Check if another daemon is already running on the default port (37643 for prod, 41723 for dev). Kill the old process or change the port.\n\n**CLI changes not taking effect**: You forgot to rebuild. Run `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`.\n\n**Session using old CLI**: You reused an existing session. Open a new session.\n\n**WebSocket connection refused**: The daemon is not running. Start it with `npm run dev:web` or `droid daemon start`.\n\n**Auth errors**: Check that your auth token is valid. Run `droid login` to re-authenticate.\n\n## Debugging the CLI entry point\n\nThe CLI entry point is `apps/cli/src/index.ts`. It detects the execution mode (interactive TUI vs exec mode) and routes accordingly. Run with the Node inspector:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run debug\n```\n\nOr add `--inspect` to the `tsx` invocation in `package.json` to step through in VS Code.\n\n## Debugging the daemon\n\nThe daemon entry point is `apps/daemon/src/index.ts`. It wraps `@factory/daemon-core` with environment loading, telemetry, and auto-update.\n\nThe daemon logs JSON-structured events. Use `jq` to filter:\n\n```bash\ntail -f ~/.factory-dev/logs/factoryd.log | jq 'select(.level == \"error\")'\n```\n\n## Bug report scripts\n\nDownload CLI bug reports from S3 (requires AWS credentials in `apps/backend/.env.local`):\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/download-bug-report.js <BUG_REPORT_ID>\n```\n\nReports extract to `~/Downloads/bug-reports/<BUG_REPORT_ID>/`.\n",
