            "content": "# CLI (apps/cli)\n\nThe `droid` command is the primary way developers interact with Factory. It is a hybrid app: running `droid` with no arguments opens the interactive TUI; running `droid exec` or other subcommands runs in headless mode.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/cli/\n├── src/\n│   ├── index.ts          # Entry point: mode detection, env loading, auth setup\n│   ├── main.tsx          # Interactive TUI bootstrap\n│   ├── app.tsx           # Root Ink component (~161 KB — the TUI shell)\n│   ├── commands/         # Commander commands (exec, wiki-upload, bug, etc.)\n│   ├── components/       # Ink/React TUI components\n│   ├── services/         # CLI-specific services (session, settings, update)\n│   ├── hooks/            # React hooks used by the TUI\n│   ├── agent/            # Agent lifecycle management\n│   ├── acp/              # Agent Communication Protocol\n│   ├── llm-proxy/        # Local LLM proxy (BYOK)\n│   ├── tools/            # CLI-specific tool overrides\n│   ├── utils/            # Helpers (keytarEmbedded, patchConsole, etc.)\n│   └── ...\n├── e2e-tests/            # TUI end-to-end tests (@microsoft/tui-test)\n├── e2e-stream-jsonrpc/   # Stream JSON-RPC integration tests\n└── scripts/              # Build and setup scripts\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/index.ts` | Entry point — loads env, sets up auth, detects exec vs. interactive mode |\n| `src/app.tsx` | Root Ink component — renders the TUI shell and routes to session views |\n| `src/commands/exec.ts` | The `exec` command — headless agent execution |\n| `src/commands/wiki-upload.ts` | The `wiki-upload` command — uploads wiki directories to Factory |\n| `src/services/SessionService.ts` | Manages the active session lifecycle |\n| `src/services/SettingsService.ts` | Reads and writes user settings |\n| `src/agent/` | Agent loop and streaming management |\n| `src/acp/` | ACP message format and transport |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Mode detection\n\n`src/index.ts` checks whether any positional arguments were provided:\n\n- **No args** → boots the interactive TUI via `src/main.tsx` and `src/app.tsx`\n- **`exec` subcommand** → routes to the Commander-based headless handler\n\n### Interactive TUI\n\nThe TUI renders in the terminal using [Ink](https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink), which runs React in a Node process and maps components to terminal output. `src/app.tsx` is the root — at ~161 KB, it is the largest file in the repo and owns the session view, command palette, and tool output display.\n\n### Exec mode\n\n`droid exec` accepts a prompt and runs a single agent session non-interactively. This mode is used by CI workflows and automation scripts. The streaming JSON-RPC runner at `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.tsx` handles communication with the daemon.\n\n### Agent communication\n\nThe CLI communicates with the daemon over `stdin/stdout` JSON-RPC 2.0. In daemon mode, the CLI spawns a local `factoryd` process. In hosted mode, it connects to a remote daemon. See [Systems: JSON-RPC communication](../../systems/json-rpc-communication.md).\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/index.ts` | Entry point and mode detection |\n| `src/app.tsx` | TUI root component |\n| `src/commands/exec.ts` | Headless exec command (~60 KB) |\n| `src/commands/wiki-upload.ts` | Wiki upload command |\n| `src/commands/bug.ts` | Bug report command |\n| `src/commands/mcp/` | MCP (Model Context Protocol) integration |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Command structure](./command-structure.md) — all CLI commands and their flags\n- [TUI rendering](./tui-rendering.md) — Ink components and the render pipeline\n- [Daemon](../daemon.md) — the process the CLI communicates with\n- [Systems: JSON-RPC communication](../../systems/json-rpc-communication.md)\n",
