            "content": "# Command structure\n\nThe CLI has two execution modes and a large set of commands. The entry point at `src/index.ts` detects which mode applies based on whether subcommand arguments are present.\n\n## Mode detection\n\n```\ndroid                    → Interactive TUI (default)\ndroid exec               → Headless agent execution\ndroid <other subcommand> → Commander-based headless command\n```\n\n## Interactive TUI commands\n\nWhen inside the TUI, you interact via keyboard. Key slash-commands (defined in `src/commands/`):\n\n| Command | File | Purpose |\n|---------|------|---------|\n| `/exec` | `exec.ts` | Run a single agent turn |\n| `/mission` | `mission.ts` | Enter spec/mission mode |\n| `/fork` | `fork.ts` | Fork the current session |\n| `/rewind` | `rewind.ts` | Rewind to a previous state |\n| `/compact` | `compact.ts` | Compact message history |\n| `/search` | `search.ts` | Search session history |\n| `/copy` | `copy.ts` | Copy output to clipboard |\n| `/settings` | `settings.ts` | Open settings |\n| `/model` | `model.ts` | Switch LLM model |\n| `/language` | `language.ts` | Switch language |\n| `/ssh` | `ssh.ts` | SSH connection management |\n| `/ide` | `ide.ts` | IDE integration |\n| `/share` | `share.ts` | Share a session |\n\n## Headless (Commander) commands\n\nRun as `droid <command> [options]`:\n\n| Command | File | Purpose |\n|---------|------|---------|\n| `exec` | `exec.ts` | Non-interactive agent execution with a prompt |\n| `wiki-upload` | `wiki-upload.ts` | Upload a wiki directory to Factory |\n| `bug` | `bug.ts` | Submit a bug report |\n| `login` | `loginCommand.ts` | Authenticate with Factory |\n| `logout` | `logoutCommand.ts` | Remove stored credentials |\n| `daemon` | `daemon.ts` | Manage the local daemon process |\n| `ssh` | `ssh.ts` | Configure SSH connections |\n| `mcp` | `mcp/` | Model Context Protocol management |\n| `update` | `update.ts` | Update the CLI binary |\n| `sessions` | `sessions.ts` | List and manage sessions |\n| `missions` | `missions.ts` | List and manage missions |\n| `status` | `status.ts` | Show platform status |\n| `diagnostics` | `diagnostics.ts` | Run diagnostic checks |\n| `computer` | `computer.ts` | Computer use / BYOI management |\n| `enter-mission` / `exit-mission` | respective files | Mission lifecycle |\n\n## The `exec` command in detail\n\n`droid exec` is used by CI and automation. Key flags:\n\n```\ndroid exec \"Describe the task\"\n  --worktree          run in a separate git worktree\n  --spec              start in spec/mission mode\n  --byok              use bring-your-own-keys mode\n  --skip-permissions  skip tool permission prompts (unsafe)\n  --stream-jsonrpc    output events as JSON-RPC stream\n```\n\n`exec.ts` is ~60 KB and covers option validation, session setup, streaming, and error handling for all exec variations.\n\n## `wiki-upload` command\n\n`wiki-upload.ts` implements `droid wiki-upload`:\n\n```\ndroid wiki-upload\n  --session-id <id>   current session ID\n  --repo-url <url>    repository URL (remote origin)\n  --wiki-dir <path>   path to the wiki directory\n  --cleanup           delete wiki-dir after successful upload\n```\n\nIt reads all `.md` files in `--wiki-dir`, parses the `.wiki-meta.json` for page ordering, and uploads pages to the Factory API. Test coverage in `wiki-upload.test.ts`.\n\n## MCP (Model Context Protocol)\n\n`src/commands/mcp/` implements the `droid mcp` subcommand group for managing MCP server integrations. The CLI can connect to external MCP servers to provide additional tools to the agent.\n\n## Plugin system\n\n`src/commands/plugin/` handles the `droid plugin` subcommand group for managing CLI plugins from the Factory marketplace.\n\n## Skills\n\n`src/commands/skills/` and `src/skills/` implement the skill system — packaged instruction files that activate specific agent behaviors. Skills can be project-level (`.factory/skills/`) or personal (`~/.factory/skills/`).\n",
