            "content": "# Web app (apps/web)\n\n`apps/web` is the browser-based Droid interface. It gives developers the same agent experience as the CLI but accessible from any browser, without installing anything locally.\n\n## Tech stack\n\n- **Vite** — dev server and production bundler (`apps/web/vite.config.ts`)\n- **React 19** — UI framework\n- **TypeScript** — type safety\n- **WorkOS AuthKit** — authentication (`@workos-inc/authkit-react`)\n- **Playwright** — E2E testing (`apps/web/playwright.config.ts`)\n- **Vitest** — unit tests\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/web/\n├── src/\n│   ├── main.tsx       # React entry point\n│   ├── App.tsx        # Root component and routing\n├── e2e/               # Playwright E2E tests\n├── public/            # Static assets\n├── index.html         # HTML entry point\n├── vite.config.ts     # Vite configuration\n└── playwright.config.ts\n```\n\n## How it works\n\nThe web app shares almost all of its logic with the desktop app through `packages/frontend`. The app itself is a thin shell that:\n\n1. Authenticates the user via WorkOS AuthKit\n2. Connects to the Factory backend to load session data\n3. Establishes a WebSocket connection to the local daemon (or via the relay for BYOI setups)\n4. Renders the shared session UI from `packages/frontend`\n\n## Authentication\n\nUsers authenticate with WorkOS. On the first visit, they are redirected to the WorkOS-hosted login page. After auth, WorkOS returns a JWT that the web app includes in all API requests.\n\n## Relay and BYOI\n\nWhen connecting to a daemon on a remote machine, the web app connects through `apps/relay` rather than directly. The relay URL is configured via environment variables and the Factory platform settings.\n\n## E2E tests\n\nPlaywright tests in `apps/web/e2e/` cover the critical user paths:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/web && npm run test:e2e         # headless\ncd apps/web && npm run test:e2e -- --headed\n```\n\nThe Playwright configuration uses `apps/web/playwright.config.ts`.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Frontend package](../packages/frontend.md) — shared React features used by web and desktop\n- [Desktop app](./desktop.md) — the Electron wrapper around this web app\n- [Relay](./relay.md) — the BYOI WebSocket relay\n",
