            "content": "# Desktop app (apps/desktop)\n\nThe desktop app is an Electron wrapper around `apps/web`. It adds native OS integration, bundles `factoryd` so users get a single installable binary, and handles auto-updates via S3.\n\n## Tech stack\n\n- **Electron** — native wrapper\n- **Vite** — builds both the Electron main process and the renderer (the web app)\n- **React 19** — renderer UI (same as `apps/web`)\n- **TypeScript**\n\n## What it adds over the web app\n\n- **Bundled daemon**: The desktop app ships `factoryd` inside the Electron package. When you launch the app, it starts the daemon automatically. You don't need to install or run `factoryd` separately.\n- **Auto-updater**: The app checks for new versions on startup and can install them in the background. Update distribution uses S3.\n- **Native OS integration**: File system access, system tray, native dialogs.\n- **Local credentials**: Secrets are stored in the OS keychain via `keytar`.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/desktop/\n├── src/\n│   ├── main/           # Electron main process\n│   ├── renderer/       # Electron renderer (loads apps/web)\n│   ├── preload/        # Preload scripts (context bridge)\n│   └── shared/         # Shared types between main and renderer\n├── scripts/            # Build and packaging scripts\n└── ...\n```\n\n## Build\n\n```bash\nnpm run build -- --filter=desktop   # build Electron app\nnpm run dev:desktop                  # start in development mode\n```\n\nThe build produces platform-specific installers (`dist-electron/`).\n\n## Auto-update\n\n`packages/updater` provides the auto-update logic. The desktop app uses it to check S3 for new versions and download them in the background. The `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=true` env var prevents the bundled daemon from trying to update itself (the app manages its own lifecycle).\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Web app](./web.md) — the web app rendered inside Electron\n- [Daemon](./daemon.md) — the factoryd process bundled inside the desktop app\n- [packages/updater](../packages/index.md) — auto-update utilities\n",
