            "content": "# droid-core package\n\n`@factory/droid-core` is the AI agent core library. It owns tool definitions, LLM provider integrations, message handling, and streaming utilities. Both the CLI and the daemon import from this package to run agent logic.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/droid-core/src/\n├── api/              # API client for communicating with the Factory backend\n├── automations/      # Automation trigger definitions\n├── core/             # Agent core loop and message processing\n├── droids/           # Droid configuration and loading\n├── feature-flags/    # Agent-side feature flag integration\n├── llms/             # LLM provider clients and model registry\n│   ├── index.ts      # Provider exports\n│   ├── price.ts      # Token pricing by model\n│   ├── types.ts      # LLM request/response types\n│   ├── errors/       # LLM-specific error classes\n│   └── provider/     # Per-provider implementations (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google)\n├── machine-connection/  # Daemon connection management\n├── messages/         # Message type definitions and builders\n├── prompts/          # System prompt construction\n├── streaming/        # Streaming response processing\n├── test-utils/       # Shared test helpers for agent tests\n└── tools/            # Tool definitions (the main extension point)\n    ├── create-tool.ts\n    ├── registry.ts\n    ├── types.ts\n    ├── definitions/  # One file per tool (Read, Edit, Execute, Grep, etc.)\n    ├── legacy/       # Deprecated tool implementations\n    └── utils/        # Tool execution helpers\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/tools/registry.ts` | Global tool registry — registers and looks up tools by name |\n| `src/tools/types.ts` | `Tool`, `ToolCall`, `ToolResult` type definitions |\n| `src/tools/create-tool.ts` | Factory function for defining a new tool |\n| `src/llms/index.ts` | LLM provider registry and model selection |\n| `src/llms/types.ts` | `LLMRequest`, `LLMResponse`, `LLMStreamEvent` types |\n| `src/streaming/` | Streaming response parsing and event dispatch |\n| `src/messages/` | Message builders for user, assistant, and tool messages |\n| `src/prompts/` | System prompt assembly from template parts |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Tool system\n\nTools are the primary extension point. Each tool is an object with a name, description (shown to the LLM), JSON Schema input definition, and an execute function:\n\n```ts\nconst ReadTool = createTool({\n  name: 'Read',\n  description: 'Read the contents of a file',\n  inputSchema: { /* JSON Schema */ },\n  execute: async ({ file_path }) => { /* ... */ },\n});\n```\n\nTools are registered in the registry at `src/tools/registry.ts`. The agent assembles a list of tools for each LLM request based on the session context and feature flags.\n\n### LLM integration\n\n`src/llms/provider/` contains per-provider implementations. Each provider implements a common interface for streaming completions. The backend LLM proxy routes requests to the correct provider; `droid-core` handles the stream events on the client side.\n\n### Streaming\n\n`src/streaming/` parses the server-sent event stream from the LLM proxy. It converts raw SSE chunks into structured events (token deltas, tool calls, stop reasons) and emits them to the caller.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/tools/registry.ts` | Tool registry |\n| `src/tools/types.ts` | Tool type contracts |\n| `src/tools/definitions/` | Individual tool implementations |\n| `src/llms/index.ts` | LLM provider setup |\n| `src/llms/provider/` | Anthropic, OpenAI, Google implementations |\n| `src/streaming/` | SSE stream parsing |\n| `src/messages/` | Message construction |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Tools deep-dive](./tools.md) — all built-in tools\n- [LLMs](./llms.md) — provider integrations and model registry\n- [CLI](../apps/cli/index.md) — the main consumer of droid-core\n",
