            "content": "# LLM integrations\n\n`packages/droid-core/src/llms/` contains the LLM provider layer. It abstracts over Anthropic, OpenAI, and Google to give the agent a uniform interface for streaming completions.\n\n## Provider implementations\n\nEach provider lives in `src/llms/provider/<name>/`:\n\n| Provider | Directory | Models |\n|----------|-----------|--------|\n| Anthropic | `provider/anthropic/` | Claude 3.5 Sonnet, Claude 3.7, etc. |\n| OpenAI | `provider/openai/` | GPT-4o, o1, o3, etc. |\n| Google | `provider/google/` | Gemini 2.0 Flash, Gemini 2.5 Pro, etc. |\n\n## Key files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/llms/index.ts` | Provider registry and model lookup |\n| `src/llms/types.ts` | `LLMRequest`, `LLMResponse`, streaming event types |\n| `src/llms/price.ts` | Token pricing by model (used for cost tracking) |\n| `src/llms/errors/` | Provider-specific error classes |\n| `src/llms/provider/sanitize-json-schema.ts` | Normalizes tool JSON schemas for each provider's requirements |\n\n## Request flow\n\nLLM requests go through the Factory backend proxy rather than directly to providers. This lets the backend add authentication, usage tracking, and rate limiting:\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Agent as droid-core\n    participant Backend as apps/backend (proxy)\n    participant LLM as LLM provider\n\n    Agent->>Backend: POST /api/llm/stream (streaming request)\n    Backend->>LLM: provider-specific API call\n    LLM-->>Backend: token stream (SSE)\n    Backend-->>Agent: forwarded SSE stream\n    Agent->>Agent: parse events via src/streaming/\n```\n\n## Schema sanitization\n\nDifferent LLM providers have different requirements for JSON Schema in tool definitions. `sanitize-json-schema.ts` normalizes schemas before sending them to each provider — removing unsupported keywords, converting types, and handling edge cases like `anyOf` combinations.\n\n## Model registry\n\nThe model registry in `src/llms/index.ts` maps model identifiers (e.g., `claude-sonnet-4-5`) to provider configurations. This is the place to add new models.\n\n## Error handling\n\n`src/llms/errors/` defines provider-specific error classes that map upstream API errors to the project's error hierarchy. Rate limit errors, context length exceeded, and invalid request errors each have a typed class.\n\n## Pricing\n\n`src/llms/price.ts` contains token price tables per model. The agent uses these to compute cost estimates displayed in the TUI and stored in session records.\n",
