            "content": "# daemon-core package\n\n`@factory/daemon-core` is the environment-agnostic implementation of the daemon. Both `apps/daemon` (the standalone `factoryd` binary) and `apps/cli` (when running in daemon mode) import from this package and provide their own environment configuration.\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe separation between `apps/daemon` and `packages/daemon-core` means the daemon logic can run in two contexts:\n\n1. **Standalone**: `apps/daemon` wraps `daemon-core` with env loading, auto-update, and process management.\n2. **Inline in CLI**: `apps/cli` can spin up a daemon-core instance directly when operating without a separately running `factoryd`.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/daemon-core/src/\n├── index.ts            # DaemonCore class — public entry point\n├── constants.ts        # Default ports and timeouts\n├── types.ts            # DaemonCoreConfig and related types\n├── server/             # WebSocket server and request handling\n│   ├── daemon-server.ts       # WebSocket server setup\n│   ├── droid-request-handler.ts  # Incoming JSON-RPC request dispatcher\n│   └── types.ts\n├── automations/        # Automation session management\n├── code-server/        # Code server (VS Code server) integration\n├── droid/              # Droid session lifecycle\n├── relay/              # Relay client (for BYOI connections)\n├── services/           # Internal daemon services\n├── terminal/           # PTY-based terminal session management\n└── utils/              # Helpers\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/index.ts` | `DaemonCore` class — start/stop lifecycle |\n| `src/server/daemon-server.ts` | Bun WebSocket server — accepts connections and routes messages |\n| `src/server/droid-request-handler.ts` | Dispatches JSON-RPC requests to the appropriate handler |\n| `src/terminal/` | PTY session management — spawns shells and forwards I/O |\n| `src/droid/` | Droid agent session lifecycle (initialize, load, interrupt, execute) |\n| `src/relay/` | Connects to the relay service for BYOI sessions |\n\n## How it works\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    Client[\"WebSocket client (web/desktop)\"] -->|\"JSON-RPC\"| DaemonServer\n    CLI[\"CLI (stdin/stdout)\"] -->|\"JSON-RPC\"| DaemonServer\n    DaemonServer --> RequestHandler[\"droid-request-handler.ts\"]\n    RequestHandler --> DroidSession[\"Droid session (src/droid/)\"]\n    RequestHandler --> TerminalSession[\"Terminal session (src/terminal/)\"]\n    DroidSession -->|\"HTTPS\"| Backend[\"Factory backend\"]\n```\n\n1. A client (browser or CLI) sends a JSON-RPC 2.0 request over WebSocket (or stdin/stdout).\n2. `daemon-server.ts` receives the WebSocket frame and passes it to `droid-request-handler.ts`.\n3. The request handler dispatches to the appropriate service:\n   - `droid/` for agent session operations (send message, interrupt, get history)\n   - `terminal/` for terminal session operations (spawn, resize, write)\n4. Results are sent back as JSON-RPC responses or notifications.\n\n## Terminal (PTY)\n\n`src/terminal/` manages pseudo-terminal sessions using `bun-pty`. When a client requests a terminal, the daemon spawns a shell process with a PTY and forwards I/O. This is what powers the terminal panel in the web/desktop apps.\n\n## DaemonCoreConfig\n\n```ts\ninterface DaemonCoreConfig {\n  port: number;\n  host: string;\n  shell: string;           // e.g., '/bin/zsh'\n  homeDir: string;\n  apiBaseUrl: string;      // Factory backend URL\n  deploymentEnv: string;   // 'production' | 'development' | 'staging'\n  isProductionTier: boolean;\n}\n```\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Daemon app](../apps/daemon.md) — the wrapper that runs daemon-core as factoryd\n- [Systems: session management](../systems/session-management.md)\n- [Systems: JSON-RPC communication](../systems/json-rpc-communication.md)\n",
