            "content": "# frontend package\n\n`@factory/frontend` is the shared React feature library used by both `apps/web` and `apps/desktop`. It contains the session UI, auth flows, settings pages, and other features that are identical across both apps.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/frontend/src/\n├── index.ts          # Public exports\n├── api/              # API client hooks and fetchers\n├── app/              # App-level setup (store, providers)\n├── auth/             # Authentication hooks and WorkOS AuthKit integration\n├── errors/           # Error boundary components\n├── features/         # Feature modules\n│   ├── analytics/    # Usage analytics UI\n│   ├── automations/  # Automation management\n│   ├── banner/       # System banners\n│   ├── feature-flags/ # Client-side Statsig integration\n│   ├── missions/     # Mission workflow UI\n│   ├── onboarding/   # New user onboarding\n│   ├── sessions/     # Session list and chat UI (the main view)\n│   ├── settings/     # User and org settings pages\n│   ├── terminal/     # Terminal panel\n│   ├── wiki/         # Wiki browsing UI\n│   └── ...\n├── hooks/            # Shared React hooks\n├── layouts/          # Page layout components\n├── router/           # React Router setup and route definitions\n├── services/         # Frontend service layer (DaemonSessionController, etc.)\n├── types/            # Frontend-specific TypeScript types\n├── utils/            # Helper functions\n└── views/            # Page-level view components\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File/Directory | Purpose |\n|----------------|---------|\n| `src/features/sessions/` | Session list, chat view, message rendering — the core UI |\n| `src/services/DaemonSessionController.ts` | Manages the WebSocket connection to the daemon |\n| `src/app/` | Redux store setup, React context providers |\n| `src/auth/` | WorkOS AuthKit hooks, auth state management |\n| `src/features/feature-flags/` | `useFeatureFlagValue` hook and Statsig client |\n| `src/features/settings/` | User preferences, API keys, integrations |\n| `src/router/` | Route definitions shared across web and desktop |\n\n## State management\n\nThe package uses Redux Toolkit. The main slice is the `assembly` slice (historical name — it manages the active session state including message tree, tool call status, and connection state).\n\nKey Redux patterns:\n- Entity adapters for collections (sessions, messages)\n- Precise selector usage (never destructure the whole slice — see [patterns](../contributing/patterns-and-conventions.md))\n- Async thunks for API calls\n\n## Daemon connection\n\n`src/services/DaemonSessionController.ts` owns the WebSocket connection to `factoryd`. It:\n1. Establishes the WebSocket connection on mount\n2. Sends JSON-RPC 2.0 requests for session operations\n3. Receives notifications and dispatches them to the Redux store\n4. Handles reconnection on connection loss\n\n## Feature flag integration\n\nThe `useFeatureFlagValue` hook from `src/features/feature-flags/` integrates with Statsig. Flags are defined in `@factory/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`. New flags must be created in the Statsig console first.\n\n## Testing\n\nUnit tests use Vitest. E2E tests use Playwright:\n\n```bash\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run path/to/test.ts\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e\n```\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [core-ui package](./core-ui.md) — UI primitives used by frontend components\n- [common package](./common.md) — shared types imported by frontend\n- [Web app](../apps/web.md) — one of the two consumers\n- [Desktop app](../apps/desktop.md) — the other consumer\n",
