            "content": "# core-ui package\n\n`@factory/core-ui` is the design system for all Factory web UIs. Using it is mandatory — no `<div>`, `<button>`, or `<input>` elements directly in application code.\n\n## Purpose\n\nA single component library ensures visual consistency, accessibility, and theming across `apps/web`, `apps/desktop`, `apps/admin`, and `internal/web`. It also prevents ad-hoc styling decisions from fragmenting the UI.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/core-ui/src/\n├── components/\n│   ├── layout/         # Box, Flex, Grid\n│   ├── form/           # Button, Input, Dropdown, Select\n│   ├── typography/     # Header, Text\n│   ├── interactive/    # Collapsible, Toast, Tooltip, Modal\n│   ├── media/          # Icon, Avatar, Badge\n│   └── ...\n├── colors.ts           # Semantic color system\n├── theme.ts            # Theme variables\n└── index.ts            # Public exports\n```\n\n## Core components\n\n| Component | Replaces | Notes |\n|-----------|---------|-------|\n| `Box` | `<div>` | Layout container with style props |\n| `Flex` | `<div style=\"display:flex\">` | Flex container |\n| `Grid` | `<div style=\"display:grid\">` | Grid container |\n| `Button` | `<button>` | Handles variants (primary, secondary, ghost) |\n| `Input` | `<input>` | Text input with validation states |\n| `Dropdown` | `<select>` | Styled select/dropdown |\n| `Text` | `<p>`, `<span>` | Inline and block text |\n| `Header` | `<h1>`–`<h6>` | Heading levels |\n| `Collapsible` | custom | Expandable sections |\n| `Toast` | custom | Notification toasts |\n\n## Color system\n\nColors are accessed through `colors.semantics.*`, not hardcoded hex values:\n\n```ts\nimport { colors } from '@factory/core-ui';\n\n// Correct\nconst style = { backgroundColor: colors.semantics.background.primary };\n\n// Wrong\nconst style = { backgroundColor: '#1a1a2e' };\n```\n\nThe semantic system supports light and dark modes. All components handle theming internally.\n\n## Using in Storybook\n\nAll components are documented and previewed in Storybook:\n\n```bash\nnpm run storybook   # starts Storybook at localhost\n```\n\nCheck Storybook before implementing any UI change to find the right component.\n\n## ESLint enforcement\n\n`packages/eslint-config` contains `no-restricted-elements` rules that ban bare HTML elements in application code. A lint error will appear if you use `<div>` instead of `<Box>`.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [frontend package](./frontend.md) — uses core-ui throughout\n- [Contributing: patterns](../contributing/patterns-and-conventions.md) — UI rules\n",
