            "content": "# JSON-RPC communication\n\nAll communication between the CLI, daemon, and browser clients uses [JSON-RPC 2.0](https://www.jsonrpc.org/specification). This applies to two distinct transport paths:\n\n1. **CLI → daemon**: stdin/stdout JSON-RPC (the CLI spawns the daemon process)\n2. **Browser/desktop → daemon**: WebSocket JSON-RPC\n\n## The communication stack\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    subgraph \"CLI path\"\n        CLI[\"apps/cli\"] -->|\"JSON-RPC\\nstdin/stdout\"| Daemon[\"apps/daemon\\n(daemon-core)\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Web/Desktop path\"\n        Web[\"apps/web\\n(DaemonSessionController)\"] -->|\"JSON-RPC\\nWebSocket\"| Daemon\n        Desktop[\"apps/desktop\"] -->|\"JSON-RPC\\nWebSocket\"| Daemon\n    end\n\n    Daemon -->|\"HTTPS\\n(JSON-RPC over HTTP)\"| Backend[\"apps/backend\"]\n```\n\n## Request/response format\n\nStandard JSON-RPC 2.0. Requests:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"method\": \"session.sendMessage\",\n  \"params\": { \"sessionId\": \"abc123\", \"content\": \"Fix the bug\" },\n  \"id\": 1\n}\n```\n\nResponses:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"result\": { \"messageId\": \"msg_456\" },\n  \"id\": 1\n}\n```\n\nNotifications (no `id`, no response expected):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\n  \"method\": \"session.tokenReceived\",\n  \"params\": { \"delta\": \"Hello\" }\n}\n```\n\n## Key methods\n\n| Method | Direction | Purpose |\n|--------|-----------|---------|\n| `session.initialize` | Client → Daemon | Create or load a session |\n| `session.sendMessage` | Client → Daemon | Send a user message |\n| `session.interrupt` | Client → Daemon | Stop the running agent |\n| `session.tokenReceived` | Daemon → Client | Streaming token notification |\n| `session.toolCallStarted` | Daemon → Client | Tool execution starting |\n| `session.toolCallCompleted` | Daemon → Client | Tool execution result |\n| `terminal.create` | Client → Daemon | Create a PTY session |\n| `terminal.write` | Client → Daemon | Send input to the terminal |\n| `terminal.output` | Daemon → Client | Terminal output notification |\n\n## CLI streaming exec mode\n\nFor headless exec mode (`droid exec`), the CLI can also operate in a \"stream JSON-RPC\" mode where it outputs JSON-RPC events to stdout. This lets external processes (CI systems, other tools) consume the agent's output as a machine-readable event stream.\n\nThe streaming exec runner lives in `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.tsx`. Tests for this mode are in `apps/cli/e2e-stream-jsonrpc/`.\n\n## Relay envelope protocol\n\nWhen a browser client connects through the relay service, messages are wrapped in an envelope that includes a `clientId` and `computerId`. The relay uses these to route messages to the correct daemon connection.\n\nEnvelope schemas are defined in `packages/common/src/relay`. Codec functions live in `packages/utils/src/relay`.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [CLI app](../apps/cli/index.md) — the CLI-side sender\n- [daemon-core](../packages/daemon-core.md) — the server-side receiver (`droid-request-handler.ts`)\n- [Relay](../apps/relay.md) — the WebSocket relay for remote connections\n- [Session management](./session-management.md) — the operations that go over JSON-RPC\n",
