            "content": "# Architecture\n\nFactory's architecture has three tiers: client surfaces (CLI, web, desktop), a local coordination layer (daemon), and a cloud backend. The most important data path is the chain from user input in the terminal all the way through the daemon to the CLI's agent loop and back.\n\n## Language breakdown\n\nThe codebase is predominantly TypeScript. Bun handles CLI and daemon runtimes; Next.js and Vite handle the web surfaces. A small Python component exists in `infra/` for infrastructure tooling.\n\n```mermaid\npie title Source language breakdown (approx.)\n    \"TypeScript / TSX\" : 92\n    \"JavaScript\" : 4\n    \"Python (infra)\" : 2\n    \"Other (HCL, YAML, JSON)\" : 2\n```\n\n## System components\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    subgraph \"Client surfaces\"\n        CLI[\"Droid CLI\\n(apps/cli)\"]\n        WEB[\"Web app\\n(apps/web)\"]\n        DESKTOP[\"Desktop app\\n(apps/desktop)\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Local layer\"\n        DAEMON[\"factoryd daemon\\n(apps/daemon)\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"Cloud\"\n        BACKEND[\"Backend API\\n(apps/backend)\"]\n        FIREBASE[\"Firebase\\nFirestore\"]\n        FUNCTIONS[\"Cloud Functions\\n(apps/functions)\"]\n        SIGNAL[\"Signal service\\n(apps/signal)\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph \"External\"\n        LLM[\"LLM providers\\n(OpenAI / Anthropic / Google)\"]\n        WORKOS[\"WorkOS\\n(auth)\"]\n        E2B[\"E2B sandboxes\\n(remote CDEs)\"]\n    end\n\n    CLI -- \"stdin/stdout JSON-RPC\" --> DAEMON\n    WEB -- \"WebSocket JSON-RPC\" --> DAEMON\n    DESKTOP -- \"WebSocket JSON-RPC\" --> DAEMON\n    DAEMON -- \"REST / WebSocket\" --> BACKEND\n    BACKEND -- \"Firestore SDK\" --> FIREBASE\n    BACKEND -- \"HTTP\" --> LLM\n    BACKEND -- \"WorkOS SDK\" --> WORKOS\n    BACKEND -- \"E2B SDK\" --> E2B\n    FUNCTIONS -- \"Firestore\" --> FIREBASE\n    SIGNAL -- \"WebSocket (SSE)\" --> WEB\n    SIGNAL -- \"WebSocket (SSE)\" --> DESKTOP\n```\n\n## Primary data flow: a user task\n\nThis is the sequence for a user typing a task in the Droid CLI:\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant CLI as Droid CLI (Ink TUI)\n    participant Daemon as factoryd daemon\n    participant Backend as Backend API\n    participant LLM as LLM provider\n\n    User->>CLI: Types task + Enter\n    CLI->>Daemon: daemon.add_user_message (JSON-RPC)\n    Daemon->>CLI: Spawns droid agent process\n    CLI->>Backend: POST /api/llm/stream (with messages)\n    Backend->>LLM: Chat completion request (streaming)\n    LLM-->>Backend: Token stream\n    Backend-->>CLI: Server-sent event stream\n    CLI-->>Daemon: Tool call results (JSON-RPC)\n    Daemon-->>CLI: Acknowledgement\n    CLI-->>User: Streamed output in TUI\n```\n\n## Daemon session lifecycle\n\nThe daemon (`apps/daemon`, using `@factory/daemon-core`) is the central coordinator for agent processes:\n\n```mermaid\nstateDiagram-v2\n    [*] --> Idle\n    Idle --> Initializing: daemon.initialize_session\n    Initializing --> Running: Agent process spawned\n    Running --> Interrupted: daemon.interrupt_session\n    Interrupted --> Running: daemon.add_user_message\n    Running --> Idle: Session completes\n    Idle --> Running: daemon.load_session\n```\n\n## Package dependency graph\n\nKey import relationships between packages:\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    CLI[\"apps/cli\"] --> DC[\"@factory/droid-core\"]\n    CLI --> FE[\"@factory/frontend\"]\n    CLI --> SVC[\"@factory/services\"]\n    DAEMON[\"apps/daemon\"] --> DCC[\"@factory/daemon-core\"]\n    DAEMON --> LOG[\"@factory/logging\"]\n    WEB[\"apps/web\"] --> FE\n    FE --> CUI[\"@factory/core-ui\"]\n    FE --> CMN[\"@factory/common\"]\n    DC --> CMN\n    DC --> LOG\n    DCC --> LOG\n    SVC --> CMN\n    BACKEND[\"apps/backend\"] --> SVC\n    BACKEND --> LOG\n    BACKEND --> CMN\n```\n\n## Environments\n\n| Environment | CLI binary | Daemon port | API base URL |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Production | `droid` | 37643 | `https://api.factory.ai` |\n| Development | `droid-dev` | 41723 | `https://api-dev.factory.ai` |\n| Localhost | `droid-localhost` | 41723 | `http://localhost:3000` |\n\n## Key design decisions\n\n- **Daemon as the coordination layer** — the daemon keeps agent processes alive independent of UI state. If the web app disconnects and reconnects, the agent is still running. See [background/design-decisions.md](../background/design-decisions.md).\n- **JSON-RPC 2.0 over WebSocket** — a standard protocol lets multiple client surfaces (web, desktop, CLI) use the same daemon API.\n- **Single Executable Application (SEA)** — the CLI and daemon each compile to a self-contained binary for distribution without requiring Node.js on the target machine.\n- **Bun runtime** — chosen for fast startup and native TypeScript support in the CLI and daemon.\n",
