            "content": "# Getting started\n\nThis page gets you from a fresh clone to a running development environment.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- Node.js 18.x (see `.nvmrc`)\n- npm 11.x (specified in `package.json` `packageManager` field)\n- Bun 1.3.x — required for CLI and daemon development\n- Git 2.x\n- macOS is the primary developer platform; Linux also works; Windows support is partial\n\nOptional but useful:\n\n- `nvm` for Node version management\n- Firebase CLI for Cloud Functions development\n\n## Install dependencies\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/Factory-AI/factory-mono.git\ncd factory-mono\nnpm install\n```\n\n`npm install` automatically runs `npm run setup` (via the `postinstall` hook), which builds and links packages.\n\n## Start the web stack\n\nThe recommended development mode for most contributors:\n\n```bash\nnpm run dev:web\n```\n\nThis starts: backend API (port 3000), web app (port 3002), Storybook, admin app (port 3001), and the daemon. Each app streams logs to both console and a file:\n\n| App | Log file |\n|---|---|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n\nFor local desktop development (requires display):\n\n```bash\nnpm run dev:desktop\n```\n\n**Do not run `npm run dev`** — it is intentionally disabled at the root.\n\n## CLI development\n\nThe CLI has its own setup step:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup\n```\n\nThis creates `droid-dev` and `droid-localhost` shell wrappers. After setup, `droid-dev` runs the CLI from source against the hosted dev API; `droid-localhost` runs against your local backend.\n\nWhen you make code changes to the CLI:\n1. Run `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`\n2. Restart the daemon\n3. Start a new session (do not reuse an old one)\n\n## Build\n\n```bash\nnpm run build                        # Build all packages\nnpm run build -- --filter=apps/web   # Build a single app\n```\n\n## Run tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all tests (caution: ~9 GB RAM)\nnpm run test\n\n# Run tests for specific packages (correct way)\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common --filter=@factory/frontend\n\n# Run a single test file\ncd apps/backend && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run path/to/file.test.ts\n```\n\n## Lint and format\n\n```bash\nnpm run fix        # Lint + auto-format (preferred)\nnpm run lint       # Lint only\nnpm run typecheck  # TypeScript type-checking\n```\n\n## Infrastructure (infra/)\n\nThe `infra/` directory uses OpenTofu (Terraform-compatible):\n\n```bash\ncd infra\ntofu init\ntofu validate\ntofu fmt\n```\n\n## Where to go next\n\n- [Development workflow](../how-to-contribute/development-workflow.md) — branch strategy, PR process\n- [Testing](../how-to-contribute/testing.md) — test frameworks and patterns\n- [Debugging](../how-to-contribute/debugging.md) — logs, common errors, troubleshooting\n- [Architecture](architecture.md) — how the system fits together\n",
