            "content": "# Glossary\n\nProject-specific terms and concepts you will encounter across the codebase.\n\n## Core concepts\n\n**Droid** — the AI agent that performs coding tasks. Also the name of the CLI binary (`droid`). Context determines which meaning applies.\n\n**Session** — a unit of agentic work. A session has an ID, a message history, a working repository, and a lifecycle (initializing → running → completed/interrupted). Sessions persist in Firestore and can be resumed.\n\n**factoryd** — the Factory daemon process (stylised lowercase). Runs on the user's machine or CDE, manages droid agent processes, and exposes a WebSocket/JSON-RPC API. Source is in `apps/daemon/`.\n\n**CDE** — Cloud Development Environment. A remote sandbox (typically an E2B-hosted container) where the daemon and agent run instead of the developer's local machine.\n\n**SEA** — Single Executable Application. A Node.js/Bun feature that compiles a TypeScript project into a self-contained binary with no external runtime dependencies. Both the CLI and daemon distribute as SEAs.\n\n**Agent loop** — the inner loop inside the Droid CLI where the LLM is called, tool calls are executed, and results are fed back. Implemented in `apps/cli/src/agent/`.\n\n**Tool call** — an action the LLM requests, such as reading a file, running a shell command, or calling a web search. The tool system in `packages/droid-core/src/tools/` defines and validates these.\n\n**ACP** — Agent Communication Protocol. The internal protocol for structured communication between agent and operator (the CLI). See `apps/cli/src/acp/`.\n\n## Infrastructure / services\n\n**Relay** — the relay service (`apps/relay/`) is an AWS-hosted proxy that forwards WebSocket connections from the web app to remote CDEs, avoiding direct browser-to-CDE connectivity requirements.\n\n**Signal** — the real-time notification service (`apps/signal/`) that pushes session and system events to connected web/desktop clients over WebSocket.\n\n**Core-UI** — the mandatory internal design system (`packages/core-ui/`). All UI code must use primitives from this package. Do not create custom `<div>`, `<button>`, `<input>` elements directly.\n\n## Code organisation\n\n**@factory/common** — the shared API contract package. Every backend API endpoint must have its request/response types defined here in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts`.\n\n**@factory/droid-core** — the AI agent core library (`packages/droid-core/`). Contains LLM integration, tool definitions, message formatting, and streaming utilities shared between CLI and other consumers.\n\n**@factory/frontend** — shared React features, hooks, and services used by both `apps/web` and `apps/desktop` (`packages/frontend/`).\n\n**@factory/daemon-core** — the daemon business logic (`packages/daemon-core/`), separate from the entry-point in `apps/daemon/`.\n\n**@factory/services** — the service layer for backend business logic, shared between `apps/backend` and other packages.\n\n## Developer tooling\n\n**droid-dev** — a shell alias / script created by `cd apps/cli && npm run setup` that runs the CLI from source code against the hosted dev API. Use this during CLI development.\n\n**droid-localhost** — like `droid-dev` but points at `http://localhost:3000`. Use this when developing backend changes alongside CLI changes.\n\n**Turborepo** (`turbo`) — the build orchestrator. It runs tasks across the monorepo in dependency order and caches outputs. Most scripts (`build`, `test`, `lint`, `fix`) are turbo tasks.\n\n**Knip** — the unused-exports checker. `npm run knip` finds TypeScript exports that nothing imports. Run before submitting a PR.\n\n**Statsig** — the feature flag service. Feature flags are defined in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts` and checked with Statsig SDKs on both client and server.\n\n## Protocols\n\n**JSON-RPC 2.0** — the protocol used for all communication between daemon and clients (web/desktop over WebSocket, CLI over stdin/stdout).\n\n**LLM proxy** — the backend endpoint in `apps/cli/src/llm-proxy/` (and corresponding backend route) that forwards LLM requests to providers, handles streaming, applies rate limiting, and strips secrets.\n\n## Patterns\n\n**MetaError** — the base error class (`packages/logging/errors`). All non-HTTP errors in the codebase must be `MetaError` instances; never throw vanilla `Error`. See [patterns and conventions](../how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md).\n\n**ResponseError4xx** — HTTP-semantic error classes in `@factory/logging/errors` (e.g. `ResponseError404NotFound`). Used in API routes to produce well-structured error responses.\n\n**Entity adapter** — Redux Toolkit's `createEntityAdapter`. Used throughout `packages/frontend/` to manage collections of typed domain objects in Redux slices.\n",
