            "content": "# How to contribute\n\nThis section covers everything you need to work effectively in the Factory monorepo: how to pick up work, write and test code, submit PRs, and understand project conventions.\n\n## Pages in this section\n\n| Page | What it covers |\n|---|---|\n| [Development workflow](development-workflow.md) | Branch strategy, PR process, commit conventions, definition of done |\n| [Testing](testing.md) | Test frameworks, patterns, mocking, how to run tests |\n| [Debugging](debugging.md) | Log locations, message tracing, common errors, troubleshooting |\n| [Patterns and conventions](patterns-and-conventions.md) | Error handling, coding style, state management, cross-cutting concerns |\n| [Tooling](tooling.md) | Build system, linters, code generators, CI tooling |\n\n## Core rules (the short version)\n\n1. **Use `@factory/core-ui` for all UI.** Never create custom `<div>`, `<button>`, or `<input>` elements. Use `Box`, `Button`, `Input`, and the other primitives from the design system.\n\n2. **API types go in `@factory/common`.** Every new endpoint needs its request/response types defined in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts` before you write the implementation.\n\n3. **Never use `npm run dev` at the root.** Use `npm run dev:web` (or `dev:desktop`).\n\n4. **Filter turbo tasks correctly.** Use `--` before `--filter`: `npm run test -- --filter=@factory/frontend`. Without `--`, turbo runs all packages and consumes ~9 GB of RAM.\n\n5. **PR title follows Conventional Commits:** `type(scope): description`. Types are `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`. Include your Linear ticket in the PR description.\n\n6. **After changing CLI/daemon code**, always run `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`, restart the daemon, and start a new session.\n\n## Getting help\n\n- For the frontend/UI system, read [`docs/frontend.md`](../../docs/frontend.md)\n- For error handling, read [`docs/error-handling.md`](../../docs/error-handling.md)\n- For