            "content": "# Development workflow\n\n## Branch strategy\n\n- **`dev`** is the main development branch and the default integration target\n- **`main`** is the production branch; only release commits merge here\n- Feature branches cut from `dev` and PR back to `dev`\n- Hotfix branches cut from `main` with `hotfix-cut.yml` workflow\n\nBranch names follow the Linear ticket format: `fac-{ticket-number}-{slug}`.\n\n## Starting work\n\n1. Pull latest `dev`: `git pull origin dev`\n2. Create a branch: `git checkout -b fac-12345-my-feature`\n3. Install if needed: `npm install`\n4. Run the dev stack: `npm run dev:web`\n\n## Commit conventions\n\nCommits follow [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/):\n\n```\ntype(scope): short description\n\nLonger body if needed.\n\nCloses FAC-1234\n```\n\n**Types:** `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`\n\n**Scope:** the workspace name (e.g. `cli`, `frontend`, `backend`, `daemon-core`, `common`, `monorepo`)\n\nExamples:\n- `feat(cli): add --no-stream flag to exec mode`\n- `fix(backend): handle missing session ID in relay endpoint`\n- `chore(monorepo): upgrade turbo to 2.6`\n\n## PR process\n\n1. Push your branch and open a PR against `dev`\n2. The PR title must be a valid Conventional Commits message (enforced by `pr-conventions.yml`)\n3. Include the Linear ticket: `Closes FAC-1234`\n4. Fill out the PR template (`.github/pull_request_template.md`)\n5. CI runs automatically: lint, typecheck, unit tests, affected-change detection, E2E tests for critical paths\n\nPRs require at least one approving review before merge.\n\n## Definition of done\n\nA PR is ready to merge when:\n- All CI checks pass\n- At least one reviewer has approved\n- Any requested changes are addressed\n- The Linear ticket is linked in the description\n- No new TypeScript errors (`npm run typecheck -- --filter=<scope>`)\n- No new lint errors (`npm run fix -- --filter=<scope>`)\n\n## Release process\n\nReleases are managed through GitHub Actions:\n- `release-cut.yml` — cuts a release branch from `dev`, bumps version, creates a PR to `main`\n- `cli-release.yml` and `factoryd-release.yml` — build and publish the CLI and daemon binaries\n- `desktop-release.yml` — builds and publishes the Electron app\n- `release-bump-version.yml` — handles version coordination across packages\n\nCLI releases also publish to npm via `cli-release-npm.yml`. The CLI binary is also distributed as a SEA (Single Executable Application) through `binary-release-env.yml`.\n\n## Semantic diff\n\nThe `semantic-diff.yml` workflow runs on PRs and summarises code changes in plain English using an LLM. This is an automated review aid, not a replacement for human review.\n\n## After merging\n\nAfter a PR merges to `dev`:\n- The dev web environment deploys automatically via `deploy-dev-web.yml`\n- The relay deploys to AWS via `deploy-relay-aws.yml` when relay code changes\n- Signal service deploys via `signal-deploy.yml`\n",
