            "content": "# Testing\n\n## Test frameworks\n\n| App / package | Framework | Runner |\n|---|---|---|\n| `apps/backend` | Jest | `npx jest` |\n| `apps/cli` | Jest + `@microsoft/tui-test` | `npm test` |\n| `packages/daemon-core` | Jest | `npm test` |\n| `packages/frontend` | Vitest + Playwright (E2E) | `npx vitest run` |\n| Other packages | Jest or Vitest (varies) | `npm test` |\n\n## Running tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all tests — uses ~9 GB RAM, prefer targeted\nnpm run test\n\n# Target specific packages (the correct syntax)\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/frontend --filter=@factory/daemon-core\n\n# Run a single test file (backend)\ncd apps/backend && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts\n\n# Run a single test file (frontend package)\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run path/to/file.test.ts\n```\n\n## Frontend test setup\n\nFrontend tests require the jsdom environment. Add this at the top of the test file:\n\n```ts\n/** @jest-environment jsdom */\n```\n\n## Mocking patterns\n\nUse top-level `jest.mock` with `requireActual` to mock modules while preserving the real implementation for everything you don't override:\n\n```ts\njest.mock('./module', () => ({\n  ...jest.requireActual('./module'),\n  functionToMock: jest.fn(),\n}));\n\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetAllMocks());\n```\n\nFor singleton services that hold internal state, use module isolation instead of reset functions. This avoids state leaking between tests:\n\n```ts\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetModules());\n\nit('test', async () => {\n  const { getService } = await import('./service');\n  // fresh module with no prior state\n});\n```\n\n## Playwright E2E tests\n\nPlaywright tests live in `packages/frontend/` and cover critical user paths in the web app:\n\n```bash\n# Run all E2E tests\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e\n\n# Run with browser visible (for debugging)\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e -- --headed --debug\n```\n\nThe `playwright-e2e-critical.yml` workflow runs a subset of E2E tests on every PR. The full suite runs on the `playwright-e2e.yml` schedule.\n\nSee [`docs/playwright-e2e-testing.md`](../../docs/playwright-e2e-testing.md) for detailed conventions.\n\n## CLI TUI tests\n\nThe CLI uses `@microsoft/tui-test` for terminal interaction testing. TUI tests launch the CLI process and automate terminal inputs/outputs. Configuration is in `apps/cli/tui-test.config.ts`.\n\nCLI E2E tests run on the `cli-e2e-tests.yml` workflow.\n\n## Test file conventions\n\n- Test files live next to the file they test: `foo.ts` → `foo.test.ts`\n- The one exception is the `e2e-tests/` directory in `apps/cli/` for full integration tests\n- Test utilities shared between test files in a package go in `test-utils/` subdirectories\n- The `packages/test-utils/` package provides shared test helpers across the monorepo\n\n## Test coverage\n\nThe CLI has a `coverage/` directory with lcov reports. Coverage is not currently enforced as a PR gate, but the data is available.\n\n## What to test\n\nFor UI components:\n- User interactions (clicks, keyboard events)\n- State transitions visible to the user\n- Error states\n\nFor service functions:\n- Happy path with realistic inputs\n- Error cases (network failures, invalid data)\n- Edge cases mentioned in comments\n\nFor API routes:\n- Input validation (missing/invalid fields)\n- Authorization checks\n- Correct response shapes\n",
