            "content": "# Debugging\n\n## Log locations\n\n| Environment | Directory | Key files |\n|---|---|---|\n| Production | `~/.factory/logs/` | `factoryd.log`, `droid-log-single.log`, `console.log` |\n| Development | `~/.factory-dev/logs/` | Same files, `dev` suffix in directory |\n\nDev server logs (when running `npm run dev:web` or `dev:desktop`) also stream to disk:\n\n| App | Log file |\n|---|---|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n| daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n\nLive-tail all daemon logs:\n```bash\ntail -f ~/.factory-dev/logs/*.log\n```\n\n## Message flow tracing\n\nThe full chain from user input to agent and back:\n\n```\nFrontend (DaemonSessionController.ts)\n    ↓ WebSocket JSON-RPC\nDaemon (droid-request-handler.ts)\n    ↓ stdin/stdout JSON-RPC\nCLI (streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.tsx)\n```\n\nTo trace a message at each layer:\n\n```bash\n# 1. Check the CLI processed the message\ngrep \"your-feature\" ~/.factory-dev/logs/droid-log-single.log\n\n# 2. Check the daemon received and forwarded it\ngrep \"your-feature\" ~/.factory-dev/logs/factoryd.log\n\n# 3. Check the backend API received the LLM request\ngrep \"your-feature\" /tmp/factory-dev-backend.log\n```\n\n## Development setup for CLI/daemon changes\n\n```bash\n# Build CLI for development (creates droid-dev and droid-localhost wrappers)\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup\n\n# Start the web stack (includes daemon)\nnpm run dev:web\n```\n\nAfter any CLI or daemon code change:\n1. `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`\n2. Restart the daemon (Ctrl+C the dev:web stack, restart)\n3. Start a **new** session — old sessions can have stale process state\n\n`droid-dev` runs against hosted dev API; `droid-localhost` runs against local backend (port 3000).\n\n## Common issues\n\n**Daemon not responding / WebSocket errors**\n- Check daemon is running: `ps aux | grep factoryd`\n- Tail daemon log: `tail -f ~/.factory-dev/logs/factoryd.log`\n- Restart via `npm run dev:web`\n\n**CLI changes not taking effect**\n- Run `cd apps/cli && npm run setup` again\n- Confirm you're using `droid-dev`, not the installed production `droid`\n\n**TypeScript errors after pulling changes**\n- Run `npm install` to pick up any new dependencies\n- Run `npm run build -- --filter=<changed-package>` to rebuild\n\n**Session stuck / agent not responding**\n- Look for errors in `~/.factory-dev/logs/droid-log-single.log`\n- Check if the LLM request is timing out in backend logs\n- Try interrupting the session from the web UI\n\n## Backend / API debugging\n\nThe backend runs in Next.js dev mode. Check `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` for route errors and Firestore issues.\n\nEnvironment variables for local backend:\n- `.env.local` in `apps/backend/` overrides `.env`\n- Firestore emulator configuration: check `firebase.json`\n\n## Sentry error tracking\n\nProduction and staging errors are captured in Sentry. Both the CLI (`apps/cli/src/sentry.config.ts`) and daemon (`apps/daemon/src/sentry.config.ts`) initialise Sentry on startup. Check the Factory Sentry organization for production error details.\n",
