            "content": "# Tooling\n\n## Build system\n\nThe repo uses **Turborepo** + **npm workspaces**. Turborepo runs tasks across packages in dependency order and caches outputs.\n\nKey scripts at the root:\n\n| Script | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| `npm run build` | Build all packages (Turborepo, with output caching) |\n| `npm run dev:web` | Start backend, web, storybook, admin, daemon |\n| `npm run dev:desktop` | Start backend, web, storybook, admin, desktop |\n| `npm run test` | Run all tests |\n| `npm run fix` | Lint + auto-format (preferred over `lint` alone) |\n| `npm run typecheck` | TypeScript type-checking across all packages |\n| `npm run knip` | Detect unused exports |\n| `npm run clean` | Clear all build caches (next, vite, turbo, dist, tsconfig) |\n\n**Always use `--` before `--filter`:**\n```bash\n# Correct\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/frontend\n\n# Wrong - turbo gets no filter and runs everything\nnpm run test --filter=@factory/frontend\n```\n\n## Linting and formatting\n\n`packages/eslint-config/` provides the shared ESLint configuration used by all apps and packages. Conventions enforced include:\n\n- No `require()` — ES6 imports only\n- Absolute imports (`@factory/...`, `@/...`)\n- Enums in `enums.ts`, types in `types.ts`\n- No direct `process.env` access\n- No `as` type assertions (where enforced)\n\nPrettier handles formatting. Configuration is in `.prettierrc.json` at the repo root.\n\nStylelint handles CSS-in-JS via `stylelint-config-standard`. Run with `npm run stylelint`.\n\n## Runtime: Bun vs Node\n\n- **CLI** and **daemon** use [Bun](https://bun.sh/) as the runtime — fast startup, native TypeScript support\n- **Backend**, **admin**, **web** use Node.js via Next.js / Vite\n- Package manager is `npm` (Bun's lock format isn't used; `bun.lock` exists but `npm` is the workspace manager)\n\n## SEA builds (Single Executable Application)\n\nBoth the CLI and daemon distribute as Node.js/Bun SEA binaries — self-contained executables that include the runtime:\n\n```bash\n# Build CLI SEA for current platform\ncd apps/cli && npm run build\n\n# Platform-specific\nnpm run build:sea:mac:arm64\nnpm run build:sea:mac:x64\nnpm run build:sea:linux:arm64\n```\n\nThe esbuild config (`apps/cli/esbuild.config.js`) bundles the source; the SEA config wraps the bundle into a binary.\n\n## CI/CD\n\n53 GitHub Actions workflows in `.github/workflows/`. Key ones:\n\n| Workflow | Trigger | What it does |\n|---|---|---|\n| `test.yml` | Push / PR | Runs unit tests |\n| `typecheck.yml` | Push / PR | TypeScript type-check |\n| `eslint.yml` / `format.yml` | Push / PR | Lint and format checks |\n| `cli-e2e-tests.yml` | Push / PR | CLI TUI end-to-end tests |\n| `playwright-e2e-critical.yml` | Push / PR | Critical web E2E tests |\n| `pr-conventions.yml` | PR | Enforces Conventional Commits PR title |\n| `check-affected.yml` | PR | Identifies changed packages |\n| `semantic-diff.yml` | PR | LLM-generated code diff summary |\n| `cli-release.yml` | Tag push | Build and publish CLI binary |\n| `desktop-release.yml` | Tag push | Build and publish Electron app |\n| `deploy-dev-web.yml` | Merge to dev | Deploy web stack to dev environment |\n| `opentofu.yml` | Infra changes | Run OpenTofu plan/apply |\n\n## Husky git hooks\n\nPre-commit and pre-push hooks are configured via Husky (`.husky/`). They run lint and formatting checks before commits complete.\n\n## Knip (unused exports)\n\n```bash\nnpm run knip\n```\n\nKnip finds TypeScript exports that nothing in the codebase imports. Run it before submitting a PR to avoid accumulating dead code. Configuration is in `knip.json`.\n\n## Storybook\n\n```bash\nnpm run storybook\n# or from apps/storybook:\ncd apps/storybook && npm run dev\n```\n\nStorybook documents and visually tests `@factory/core-ui` components. All design system components should have a corresponding story.\n\n## Infra tooling\n\n`infra/` uses OpenTofu (a Terraform-compatible open-source fork). Validation:\n\n```bash\ncd infra\ntofu init\ntofu validate\ntofu fmt\n```\n\nInfra changes are planned and applied via the `opentofu.yml` GitHub Actions workflow.\n",
