            "content": "# Apps\n\nThis section documents each deployable application in the Factory monorepo.\n\n| App | Stack | Purpose | Page |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `apps/cli` | Bun, TypeScript, Ink/React | Droid CLI — interactive TUI + headless exec | [CLI](cli/index.md) |\n| `apps/daemon` | Bun, TypeScript, WebSocket | factoryd background daemon | [Daemon](daemon.md) |\n| `apps/backend` | Next.js 15, TypeScript | REST API for all product surfaces | [Backend](backend.md) |\n| `apps/web` | Vite, React 19, TypeScript | Main web application | [Web](web.md) |\n| `apps/desktop` | Electron, Vite, React 19 | Native desktop wrapper + local daemon | [Desktop](desktop.md) |\n| `apps/admin` | Next.js 15, React 19 | Internal admin dashboard | [Admin](admin.md) |\n| `apps/signal` | Bun, TypeScript, WebSocket | Real-time event notification service | [Signal](signal.md) |\n| `apps/relay` | TypeScript, AWS Lambda | WebSocket relay for remote CDEs | (see [deployment](../deployment/index.md)) |\n| `apps/functions` | Firebase Cloud Functions | Serverless background jobs | — |\n| `apps/scripts` | Node.js | Build and maintenance automation | — |\n\n## How the apps relate\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    WEB[\"web (Vite)\"]\n    DESKTOP[\"desktop (Electron)\"]\n    CLI[\"cli (Bun TUI)\"]\n    DAEMON[\"daemon (factoryd)\"]\n    BACKEND[\"backend (Next.js)\"]\n    SIGNAL[\"signal\"]\n    RELAY[\"relay (AWS)\"]\n    ADMIN[\"admin\"]\n\n    WEB -- \"WebSocket (local)\" --> DAEMON\n    DESKTOP -- \"WebSocket (local)\" --> DAEMON\n    CLI -- \"stdin/stdout\" --> DAEMON\n    WEB -- \"WebSocket (remote)\" --> RELAY\n    RELAY -- \"WebSocket\" --> DAEMON\n    DAEMON -- \"REST\" --> BACKEND\n    BACKEND -- \"REST\" --> WEB\n    SIGNAL -- \"WebSocket push\" --> WEB\n    SIGNAL -- \"WebSocket push\" --> DESKTOP\n    ADMIN -- \"REST\" --> BACKEND\n```\n\nThe web and desktop apps communicate with the daemon over WebSocket/JSON-RPC 2.0. Remote CDEs use the relay service to bridge the connection. The daemon calls the backend API for session persistence and LLM proxying. Signal pushes real-time events to connected clients.\n",
