            "content": "# CLI (apps/cli)\n\nActive contributors: arman, tchourakov, alvinsng, sherry, shashank\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe Droid CLI is the primary interface for engineers using Factory. It runs either as a full-screen interactive TUI (the default) or in headless exec mode for automation. The CLI spawns an AI agent loop, calls LLM APIs through the backend, executes tool calls (shell, file system, web search, etc.), and streams results to the user.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/cli/src/\n├── index.ts          # Entry point: mode detection, telemetry init, auth setup\n├── app.tsx           # Root React/Ink component for the interactive TUI (4,556 lines)\n├── main.tsx          # Re-export of app.tsx entry for Ink rendering\n│\n├── agent/            # Agent loop: tool dispatch, confirmation, autonomy\n├── commands/         # ~96 slash-commands (exec, wiki-upload, bug, ssh, mcp, ...)\n├── components/       # ~123 Ink/React UI components\n├── hooks/            # React hooks (useAgent.ts, useLLMStreaming.ts, ...)\n├── services/         # SessionService, SettingsService, UpdateService, ...\n├── tools/            # Tool definitions specific to CLI (beyond droid-core tools)\n├── exec/             # Headless exec mode entry and streaming JSON-RPC runner\n├── acp/              # Agent Communication Protocol implementation\n├── llm-proxy/        # Client-side LLM proxy (streams from backend)\n├── mcp/              # MCP (Model Context Protocol) client\n├── adapters/         # LLM provider adapters\n├── models/           # Message and content converters for different providers\n├── i18n/             # Internationalisation strings\n├── feature-flags/    # Statsig feature flag hooks\n├── skills/           # Skills system (built-in and user-defined skill loading)\n├── task/             # Task (sub-agent) tool management\n├── telemetry/        # CLI telemetry client\n└── utils/            # ~197 utility modules\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Type / File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/agent/tools.ts` | Dispatches tool calls; manages tool confirmation workflow |\n| `src/agent/autonomy.ts` | Autonomy level logic (ask/auto/full) |\n| `src/services/SessionService.ts` | Session lifecycle, message history, persist/resume |\n| `src/hooks/useAgent.ts` | React hook wiring the agent loop into the TUI |\n| `src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` | Streams LLM tokens from the backend proxy |\n| `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` | Exec mode: runs sessions as non-interactive JSON-RPC |\n| `src/acp/` | ACP protocol for structured agent-operator communication |\n| `src/llm-proxy/` | Client-side proxy forwarding chat requests to `apps/backend` |\n| `src/commands/exec.ts` | The `exec` command (headless execution, 60,778 lines of tests) |\n| `src/commands/wiki-upload.ts` | Wiki upload command (uploads generated docs to Factory) |\n| `src/mcp/` | MCP (Model Context Protocol) integration for external tool providers |\n| `src/skills/` | Skills loading, built-in skills, user-defined skill discovery |\n| `src/task/` | Dynamic task tool registration (spawning sub-agents from the CLI) |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Mode detection\n\n`src/index.ts` reads `process.argv` at startup. No positional arguments → interactive TUI mode (launches `app.tsx`). A `exec` subcommand → headless exec mode (routes through `src/commands/exec.ts` → `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts`).\n\n### Interactive TUI\n\nThe TUI is built with [Ink](https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink) — React rendering for the terminal. `app.tsx` is the root component. Key hooks:\n\n- `useAgent` orchestrates the full agent lifecycle\n- `useLLMStreaming` streams LLM completions and handles SSE chunks\n- Components in `src/components/` render the message list, tool call outputs, file diffs, and status bar\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    A[\"src/index.ts\\n(entry)\"] --> B[\"app.tsx\\n(Ink root)\"]\n    B --> C[\"useAgent hook\"]\n    C --> D[\"useLLMStreaming\"]\n    C --> E[\"agent/tools.ts\\n(tool dispatch)\"]\n    D --> F[\"llm-proxy/\\n(backend stream)\"]\n    E --> G[\"@factory/droid-core\\ntools\"]\n    C --> H[\"SessionService\\n(persist)\"]\n```\n\n### Exec mode\n\nExec mode runs a session without a TUI. The `streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` reads commands from stdin as JSON-RPC messages and writes results to stdout. This mode is used for automation, CI integration, and the daemon's agent process management.\n\n### Tool calling\n\nThe agent loop in `src/agent/tools.ts` receives tool calls from the LLM, validates them, optionally prompts the user for confirmation (`src/agent/tool-confirmation.ts`), executes them, and returns results. Most tools come from `@factory/droid-core`; CLI-specific tools are in `src/tools/`.\n\n### Skills\n\nSkills are markdown files that provide additional context and instructions to the agent for specific tasks. Built-in skills live in `src/skills/builtin/constants.ts` (3,409 lines). User-defined skills are loaded from `.factory/skills/` in the repository root.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- Imports `@factory/droid-core` for tool definitions, LLM integrations, and message types\n- Imports `@factory/frontend` for shared React components used in some CLI views\n- Communicates with `apps/daemon` over stdin/stdout JSON-RPC (when running in daemon-managed mode)\n- Calls `apps/backend` REST API for session persistence and LLM proxying\n- Uses `@factory/services` for settings management and plugin marketplace\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n- **Add a new command:** create `src/commands/my-command.ts` and register it in `src/commands/index.ts`\n- **Add a new tool:** define it in `@factory/droid-core/src/tools/` or `src/tools/` for CLI-specific tools\n- **Change TUI layout:** start in `app.tsx` and follow the component tree through `src/components/`\n- **Modify exec mode behaviour:** start at `src/commands/exec.ts` and `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts`\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/index.ts` | Entry point, mode detection, telemetry and auth init (710 lines) |\n| `src/app.tsx` | Interactive TUI root component (4,556 lines) |\n| `src/agent/tools.ts` | Tool dispatch and confirmation logic (21,468 lines total with tests) |\n| `src/services/SessionService.ts` | Session lifecycle management (3,579 lines) |\n| `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` | Headless exec mode runner |\n| `src/commands/exec.ts` | The `droid exec` command implementation (60,778 lines test) |\n| `src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` | LLM token streaming hook |\n| `src/hooks/useAgent.ts` | Agent loop React hook |\n",
