            "content": "# Features\n\nCross-cutting capabilities that span multiple apps and packages. Features are things you would explain to a new user: \"here's what you can do with Factory.\"\n\n| Feature | Description | Page |\n|---|---|---|\n| AI agent sessions | The core product: starting, running, and managing Droid sessions | [AI agent sessions](ai-agent-sessions.md) |\n| LLM integration | How Factory connects to LLM providers and proxies requests | [LLM integration](llm-integration.md) |\n| Wiki generation | Automated documentation generation for repositories | [Wiki generation](wiki-generation.md) |\n| Third-party integrations | GitHub, Linear, Slack, Sentry, PagerDuty, Notion, Jira | [Integrations](integrations.md) |\n| Missions | Large-scale multi-agent task decomposition (Colossus/AGI mode) | [Missions](missions.md) |\n| Skills | User-defined and built-in instruction sets for the agent | [Skills](skills.md) |\n| MCP (Model Context Protocol) | External tool provider protocol integration | [MCP](mcp.md) |\n\n## What makes something a \"feature\"\n\nA feature is a user-visible or developer-visible capability that you understand by tracing through multiple systems. If understanding it requires following code across `apps/cli` → `packages/droid-core` → `apps/backend`, it belongs here.\n\nIndividual subsystem documentation lives in [apps/](../apps/index.md) and [packages/](../packages/index.md).\n",
