            "content": "# AI agent sessions\n\nActive contributors: arman, tchourakov, alvinsng, sherry, shashank\n\n## Purpose\n\nA session is the fundamental unit of work in Factory. The user gives a task; a session tracks the full message history, coordinates the agent loop, persists state to the cloud, and can be paused and resumed. Sessions run on both local machines and remote CDEs.\n\n## How a session starts\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant CLI\n    participant Daemon as factoryd daemon\n    participant Backend\n\n    User->>CLI: droid (start TUI)\n    CLI->>Backend: GET /api/session (or POST to create)\n    Backend-->>CLI: Session ID + history\n    CLI->>Daemon: daemon.initialize_session (JSON-RPC)\n    Daemon-->>CLI: Session process spawned\n    User->>CLI: Types task\n    CLI->>Daemon: daemon.add_user_message\n    Daemon-->>CLI: Agent loop starts\n```\n\nWhen no session is active, the CLI shows an empty prompt. The user types a task and the CLI creates a session via the backend API, then initialises it with the daemon.\n\n## Session lifecycle\n\n```mermaid\nstateDiagram-v2\n    [*] --> Creating\n    Creating --> Active: daemon.initialize_session OK\n    Active --> Running: daemon.add_user_message\n    Running --> Paused: daemon.interrupt_session\n    Paused --> Running: daemon.add_user_message (resume)\n    Running --> Completed: Agent loop finishes\n    Completed --> [*]\n    Paused --> [*]: User closes session\n```\n\n## Where session data lives\n\n| Layer | What it stores |\n|---|---|\n| Firestore (`apps/backend`) | Session metadata, message history, agent state |\n| Local `~/.factory/` (CLI) | Settings, credentials, cached session data |\n| In-memory (daemon) | Active process handles, WebSocket connections |\n\nThe backend API (`apps/backend/src/services/`) manages Firestore reads and writes. `packages/common/src/session/` defines the shared session types.\n\n## The agent loop\n\nInside a running session, the CLI executes the agent loop:\n\n1. Build the prompt from the session's message history\n2. Send to the LLM via the backend proxy (streaming)\n3. Parse tool calls from the LLM response\n4. Confirm dangerous tool calls with the user (if confirmation is required)\n5. Execute tool calls (shell, file read/write, search, etc.)\n6. Append tool results to message history\n7. Repeat from step 1 until the LLM says it's done\n\nThe agent loop lives in `apps/cli/src/agent/tools.ts` and `apps/cli/src/hooks/useAgent.ts`.\n\n## Autonomy levels\n\nThe confirmation behaviour is controlled by the autonomy setting:\n\n| Level | Description |\n|---|---|\n| Ask | Confirm every tool call before executing |\n| Auto | Confirm only potentially destructive operations |\n| Full | Execute all tool calls without confirmation |\n\nAutonomy logic is in `apps/cli/src/agent/autonomy.ts` and `apps/cli/src/agent/shouldConfirmExecution.ts`.\n\n## Session resumption\n\nSessions are persistent. A user can:\n- Close the terminal and reopen it — the CLI reconnects to the in-progress session\n- View past sessions in the web app and review the message history\n- Fork a session to create a branch from a previous state\n- Rewind to an earlier point in the session\n\nFork logic: `apps/cli/src/commands/fork.ts`. Rewind: `apps/cli/src/commands/rewind.ts`.\n\n## Spec mode\n\nBefore executing a large task, the agent can enter spec mode — it writes a structured plan and waits for user approval before proceeding. This is surfaced as a TUI confirmation step and controlled by a feature flag. See `apps/cli/src/commands/exec-spec-mode.test.ts` for detailed test coverage.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **Session state**: persisted via `apps/backend` → Firestore\n- **Agent process**: managed by `apps/daemon` / `packages/daemon-core`\n- **LLM calls**: proxied through `apps/backend/src/features/llm/` \n- **Frontend state**: managed in `packages/frontend/src/features/sessions/`\n- **Session types**: defined in `packages/common/src/session/`\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/services/SessionService.ts` | Session lifecycle in the CLI (3,579 lines) |\n| `apps/cli/src/hooks/useAgent.ts` | React hook wiring the agent loop |\n| `apps/cli/src/agent/tools.ts` | Tool dispatch and confirmation |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/droid-request-handler.ts` | Daemon session management (4,994 lines) |\n| `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | WebSocket/JSON-RPC bridge in the web frontend |\n| `packages/common/src/session/` | Shared session types |\n| `apps/backend/src/services/` | Backend session persistence |\n",
