            "content": "# LLM integration\n\nActive contributors: arman, shashank, davidgu, ricky\n\n## Purpose\n\nFactory supports multiple LLM providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google Gemini) through a unified proxy layer. The CLI never calls LLM APIs directly — it sends requests to the Factory backend, which handles provider routing, streaming, rate limiting, secret management, and usage tracking.\n\n## Request flow\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant CLI as CLI (useLLMStreaming)\n    participant Proxy as CLI LLM proxy\n    participant Backend as Backend /api/llm/stream\n    participant Provider as LLM provider\n\n    CLI->>Proxy: Chat request (messages, model, tools)\n    Proxy->>Backend: POST /api/llm/stream (bearer token)\n    Backend->>Backend: Route to provider, strip secrets\n    Backend->>Provider: API call (streaming)\n    Provider-->>Backend: Token stream (SSE)\n    Backend-->>Proxy: Forwarded SSE stream\n    Proxy-->>CLI: Parsed token chunks\n```\n\n## Provider adapters\n\nEach LLM provider has an adapter in `packages/droid-core/src/llms/`. The adapter translates the Factory message format to the provider's expected format and vice versa.\n\nSupported providers:\n- **Anthropic** (Claude models) — via Anthropic SDK\n- **OpenAI** (GPT models, o-series reasoning models) — via OpenAI SDK  \n- **Google Gemini** — via `@google/genai` SDK\n\nModel registry and capabilities: `packages/utils/src/llm/model-registry.ts` (52 lines, high-churn file).\n\n## Message conversion\n\nMessages flow through converters in `apps/cli/src/models/converters.test.ts` (2,828 lines). The converters handle:\n- Mapping between Factory's internal message format and provider-specific formats\n- Tool call serialization and result formatting\n- Token counting and context window management\n\n## Streaming\n\nLLM responses stream as server-sent events (SSE). The pipeline:\n\n1. `apps/cli/src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` — React hook that opens an SSE connection\n2. `apps/cli/src/llm-proxy/` — client-side proxy, adds auth token to requests\n3. `apps/backend/src/features/llm/` — backend route that proxies to the provider\n4. `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/` — shared streaming utilities (chunk parsing, tool call accumulation)\n\n## Model selection\n\nThe user can change models with the `/model` command (`apps/cli/src/commands/model.ts`). Available models come from `packages/utils/src/llm/model-registry.ts`. EAP (early access preview) models may require feature flags.\n\n## Tool calling\n\nLLMs request tool invocations by name. The tool registry in `packages/droid-core/src/tools/` defines each tool's name, input schema, and handler. The CLI tool dispatch layer (`apps/cli/src/agent/tools.ts`) receives tool call objects from the streaming response, validates inputs against the schema, and invokes the correct handler.\n\n## BYOK (Bring Your Own Key)\n\nUsers can configure their own LLM API keys. This routes requests directly from the CLI to the provider, bypassing the Factory proxy. BYOK handling is in `apps/cli/src/commands/exec-byok.test.ts` and associated implementation.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/droid-core/src/llms/` | Provider adapters |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/` | Streaming utilities |\n| `apps/cli/src/llm-proxy/` | Client-side LLM proxy |\n| `apps/cli/src/hooks/useLLMStreaming.ts` | Streaming hook |\n| `apps/cli/src/models/` | Message format converters |\n| `apps/backend/src/features/llm/` | Backend proxy route |\n| `packages/utils/src/llm/model-registry.ts` | Model registry |\n",
