            "content": "# Wiki generation\n\nActive contributors: jonathan, arman, alvinsng\n\n## Purpose\n\nFactory's wiki generation capability produces structured documentation for any repository. The agent reads a codebase, generates a set of interconnected markdown pages, and uploads them to Factory for browsing in the web app. This documentation you're reading was generated using this same system.\n\n## How it works\n\nWiki generation is implemented as a skill — a markdown file with detailed instructions that the agent follows when activated. The skill lives at `.factory/skills/wiki/SKILL.md` (696 lines).\n\nThe workflow:\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    A[\"User runs: droid wiki or\\napplies wiki skill\"] --> B[\"Agent surveys repo\\n(README, package.json, docs/, etc.)\"]\n    B --> C[\"Agent plans table of contents\"]\n    C --> D[\"Agent writes overview/ pages\\n(serial)\"]\n    D --> E[\"Sub-agents write by-the-numbers,\\nlore, fun-facts (parallel)\"]\n    D --> F[\"Agent writes how-to-contribute/\\n(serial)\"]\n    E --> G[\"Agent writes lens pages\\napps/, packages/, features/ (serial)\"]\n    F --> G\n    G --> H[\"Sub-agents write conditional sections\\n(api/, deployment, security, etc.) (parallel)\"]\n    H --> I[\"droid wiki-upload command\\nuploads to Factory\"]\n    I --> J[\"Wiki visible in web app\"]\n```\n\n## The upload command\n\nAfter generating pages, the `droid wiki-upload` command (`apps/cli/src/commands/wiki-upload.ts`, 16,541 lines including tests) uploads the wiki to Factory:\n\n```bash\ndroid wiki-upload \\\n  --session-id \"$SESSION_ID\" \\\n  --repo-url \"https://github.com/org/repo\" \\\n  --wiki-dir ./droid-wiki\n```\n\nThe command reads all `.md` files in the wiki directory and posts them to the backend API. The `.wiki-meta.json` file controls page ordering in the sidebar.\n\n## Backend support\n\nThe backend API has endpoints for wiki management in `packages/common/src/wiki/` (types) and `apps/backend/src/services/` (persistence). The web frontend renders wikis in `packages/frontend/src/features/wiki/`.\n\n## Sub-agent parallelization\n\nThe wiki skill leverages Factory's own task tool to spawn parallel sub-agents for independent sections. This is a meta-use of the platform: the agent documenting a repo uses the repo's own agent infrastructure to do the work faster.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `.factory/skills/wiki/SKILL.md` | The wiki generation skill (696 lines of instructions) |\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/wiki-upload.ts` | The upload command implementation |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/wiki/` | Web frontend wiki viewer |\n| `packages/common/src/wiki/` | Shared wiki types |\n",
