            "content": "# Skills\n\nActive contributors: arman, tchourakov, sherry\n\n## Purpose\n\nSkills are markdown files that provide additional context, instructions, and domain knowledge to the Droid agent for specific tasks. A skill is activated when the user invokes it or when the agent selects it automatically based on the task context. They let teams encode repeatable workflows, coding conventions, and task-specific guidance without modifying the core agent.\n\n## How skills work\n\nA skill is a `.md` file with structured sections describing what the skill does, when to use it, and step-by-step instructions. The agent reads the skill content and follows the instructions as part of its task.\n\n**Built-in skills** are shipped with the CLI in `apps/cli/src/skills/builtin/constants.ts` (3,409 lines). These cover common tasks like creating PRs, running CI, searching code, and more — including the wiki generation skill.\n\n**User-defined skills** live in `.factory/skills/` in the repository root. Any team can add custom skills for their workflow. The agent discovers and loads them at session start.\n\n**Personal skills** can also be stored in `~/.factory/skills/` for skills you want available across all projects.\n\n## Creating a skill\n\n```bash\n# Interactive skill creation wizard\ndroid create-skill\n```\n\nThe `create-skill` command (`apps/cli/src/commands/create-skill.ts`, 14,163 lines) walks the user through defining a skill's purpose, trigger conditions, and step-by-step instructions.\n\n## Skill invocation\n\nFrom within the CLI TUI, type the skill name or use the skill picker. The `droid skills` command (`apps/cli/src/commands/skills.ts`) lists available skills.\n\n## Relationship to droids\n\nDroids (`.factory/droids/`) are a related but distinct concept — they define sub-agent configurations with specific capabilities. Skills define _what to do_; droids define _who does it_ (capabilities, tools, model). Both are file-based configurations in `.factory/`.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/skills/builtin/constants.ts` | Built-in skill definitions (3,409 lines) |\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/create-skill.ts` | Interactive skill creation |\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/skills.ts` | List skills command |\n| `.factory/skills/` | User/project-level skills directory |\n",
