            "content": "# Environments\n\nFactory has four named runtime environments that span the CLI binary, daemon port, API URL, and Vercel deployment tier.\n\n## CLI and daemon environments\n\n| Environment | CLI binary | Daemon port | API URL | Notes |\n|-------------|-----------|-------------|---------|-------|\n| Production | `droid` | 37643 | `https://api.factory.ai` | Released from `main` branch |\n| Development | `droid-dev` | 41723 | `https://dev.api.factory.ai` | Released from `dev` branch |\n| Staging | `droid` (staging build) | 41723 | `https://staging.api.factory.ai` | Released from `dev` branch alongside development |\n| Pre-production | `droid` (preprod build) | 41723 | `https://preprod.api.factory.ai` | Released when a PR targets `main` |\n| Localhost | `droid-localhost` | 41723 | `http://localhost:3000` | Local dev wrapper; points at your running backend |\n\n`droid-dev` and `droid-localhost` are shell wrapper scripts created by running `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`. They are not distributed binaries — they run the CLI from TypeScript source via Bun so changes are immediately available without rebuilding.\n\nThe environment is controlled by `FACTORY_ENV` (used by the daemon) and the `.env.<environment>` files in `apps/daemon/` and `apps/desktop/`. The daemon reads `FACTORY_API_BASE_URL` from these files; the CLI reads the environment from `@factory/environment`.\n\n## Web app environments\n\nThe web app (`apps/web`) and backend (`apps/backend`) are deployed to Vercel:\n\n| Vercel environment | Triggered by | App URL |\n|-------------------|-------------|---------|\n| Production | Push to `main` | `app.factory.ai` |\n| Development (dev) | Push to `dev` | `dev.app.factory.ai` |\n| Preview | Every pull request | Unique Vercel preview URL |\n| Pre-production (preprod) | PR targeting `main` | `preprod.app.factory.ai` |\n\n## Firebase environments\n\nFirebase (Firestore, Cloud Functions) does not have environment-specific projects in the same way. Functions are deployed as part of the production release workflow. Separate Firebase projects are used for dev and production; the relevant project is selected via the `FIREBASE_PROJECT` variable in the deploy workflows.\n\n## Feature flag environments (Statsig)\n\nStatsig uses its own environment tiers, which map to Factory environments as follows:\n\n| Factory environment | Statsig tier |\n|--------------------|-------------|\n| localhost | development |\n| development (dev) | staging |\n| production | production |\n\nNote: Statsig's `staging` tier corresponds to Factory's `development` (the `dev` branch), not to Factory's `staging` environment. This mapping is defined in `apps/backend/src/features/feature-flags/server.ts`.\n",
            "file_path": "/Users/jonathanlucuix-andre/Documents/test-repos/factory-mono/droid-wiki/deployment/environments.md"
          },
          "timestamp": "2026-03-11T09:02:49.184Z"
