            "content": "# Infrastructure\n\nFactory's infrastructure spans AWS, Firebase, and Vercel. The AWS resources are managed with OpenTofu (an open-source Terraform fork). Firebase and Vercel are configured through their respective consoles and CI workflows.\n\n## Components\n\n### AWS (us-west-1)\n\n- **Relay Lambda** — A Lambda function (`@factory/relay`) that proxies connections between the CLI/daemon and the Factory backend. Deployed by `.github/workflows/deploy-relay-aws.yml` on push to `dev` (→ dev) or `main` (→ prod). Uses OIDC-based IAM role assumption (no long-lived credentials).\n- **S3** — Stores CLI and daemon release artifacts at `downloads.factory.ai`. Also used for Terraform/OpenTofu remote state (bucket `zlr-use1-terraform-state`, DynamoDB lock table `terraform-lock-dynamo`).\n- **IAM** — Roles for Lambda execution and CI pipeline access. The backend S3 bucket and DynamoDB lock table for OpenTofu state are bootstrapped separately in `infra/backend/`.\n\n### Firebase\n\n- **Firestore** — Primary database. Rules live in `firestore.rules`; indexes in `firestore.indexes.json`.\n- **Cloud Functions** — Serverless function handlers in `apps/functions/`. Deployed as part of `deploy-prod.yml`.\n- **Firebase Hosting** — Not the primary hosting mechanism (Vercel is used for the web app), but Firebase configuration is in `firebase.json` and `storage.rules`.\n\n### Vercel\n\n- Web app (`apps/web`) and backend API (`apps/backend`) are hosted on Vercel.\n- Each Vercel project is identified by `VERCEL_PROJECT_ID` and `VERCEL_ORG_ID` secrets.\n- Preview deployments are created automatically on every pull request.\n\n## OpenTofu\n\n**Workflow:** `.github/workflows/opentofu.yml`  \n**Version:** OpenTofu 1.11.5  \n**Region:** us-west-1\n\nThe `opentofu.yml` workflow runs on pull requests that touch `infra/**`. It runs plan on open PRs and apply on merge (when the PR closes with `merged == true`).\n\n### Directory layout\n\n```\ninfra/\n├── backend/          # S3 + DynamoDB for OpenTofu state, IAM roles\n├── common/           # Shared OpenTofu modules\n├── env/              # Per-environment variable files\n├── lambda_code/      # Source for Lambda functions managed by OpenTofu\n├── lambda_layers/    # Lambda layer source\n├── modules/          # Reusable Terraform modules\n├── ansible/          # Ansible playbooks for node configuration\n└── scripts/          # Helper scripts\n```\n\n### Working with OpenTofu locally\n\n```bash\n# Validate the infra directory (use OpenTofu, not Terraform)\ncd infra\ntofu init\ntofu validate\ntofu fmt\n```\n\nThe `infra/README.md` has setup instructions including how to configure the S3 backend and IAM role ARN.\n\n### CI authentication\n\nThe workflow uses `id-token: write` permissions and AWS OIDC to assume an IAM role — no AWS access keys are stored as secrets. The role ARN is defined in the workflow file itself.\n\n## Key secrets\n\n| Secret | Used by |\n|--------|---------|\n| `VERCEL_TOKEN` | All Vercel deploy workflows |\n| `VERCEL_ORG_ID` | All Vercel deploy workflows |\n| `VERCEL_PROJECT_ID` (various) | Per-project Vercel deploys |\n| AWS OIDC | `opentofu.yml`, `deploy-relay-aws.yml` |\n| Firebase service account | `deploy-prod.yml` |\n",
            "file_path": "/Users/jonathanlucuix-andre/Documents/test-repos/factory-mono/droid-wiki/deployment/infra.md"
          },
          "timestamp": "2026-03-11T09:03:11.509Z"
