            "content": "# How to monitor\n\nFactory's observability stack has three layers:\n\n1. **Logging** — structured log output from every component (CLI, daemon, backend, web), stored in files locally and forwarded to Axiom in production.\n2. **Metrics** — counters, gauges, and histograms recorded with `Metrics.addToCounter` / `Metrics.setGauge` / `Metrics.recordHistogram`, visible in Axiom and Datadog.\n3. **Alerting** — Sentry for application errors (CLI, daemon, backend all initialise Sentry); Datadog for infrastructure metrics; GitHub Actions for CI failures.\n\n## Sub-pages\n\n- [Logging](./logging.md) — log functions, log file locations, structured metadata, secret scrubbing\n- [Metrics](./metrics.md) — how to record metrics, metric naming conventions, Axiom and Datadog\n- [Alerting](./alerting.md) — Sentry setup, Datadog monitors, CI failure alerts, how to triage\n",
