            "content": "# Logging\n\nThe logging system lives in `packages/logging/src/`. It provides structured logging with automatic secret scrubbing and optional Sentry integration.\n\n## Log file locations\n\n| Environment | Directory | Key files |\n|-------------|-----------|-----------|\n| Production | `~/.factory/logs/` | `factoryd.log`, `droid-log-single.log`, `console.log` |\n| Development | `~/.factory-dev/logs/` | Same names, different directory |\n\nThe dev directory is `~/.factory-dev/`, not `~/.factory/`. Checking the wrong one is a common source of confusion — see `docs/debugging-daemon.md`.\n\nDev server processes also stream to disk:\n\n| Process | Log file |\n|---------|----------|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n| daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n\nIn interactive TUI mode the CLI writes per-session timestamped files: `~/.factory/logs/droid-log-<timestamp>.log`.\n\n## Logging functions\n\nImport from `@factory/logging`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { logInfo, logWarn, logException, LogOnce } from '@factory/logging';\n```\n\n### `logInfo(message, metadata?)`\n\nFor normal operations and debugging context. Use freely — secrets are scrubbed automatically.\n\n```typescript\nlogInfo('Session started', { sessionId, userId });\n```\n\n### `logWarn(message, metadata?)`\n\nFor conditions that don't break functionality but indicate something worth monitoring.\n\n```typescript\nlogWarn('API rate limit approaching', { currentUsage: 950, limit: 1000 });\n```\n\n### `logException(error, message, metadata?)`\n\nFor errors that are swallowed locally (no rethrow). If you call `logException` you must not re-throw — doing both creates duplicate Sentry issues.\n\n```typescript\ntry {\n  await riskyOp();\n} catch (error) {\n  logException(error, 'riskyOp failed', { context: 'startup' });\n  // do NOT throw here\n}\n```\n\n### `LogOnce`\n\nPrevents log spam in frequently-called code by ensuring a given message is only emitted once per session.\n\n```typescript\nif (configMissing) {\n  LogOnce.logError('API key not configured', { service: 'openai' });\n}\n```\n\n## Log levels\n\n| Function | Level | When to use |\n|----------|-------|-------------|\n| `logInfo` | INFO | Normal flow, debugging breadcrumbs |\n| `logWarn` | WARN | Degraded state, approaching limits |\n| `logException` | ERROR | Handled errors (no rethrow) |\n\nThere is no `logError` function — do not use it. Use `logWarn` for breadcrumbs before a rethrow, and `logException` only when swallowing the error.\n\n## Structured logging with metadata\n\nAlways pass a metadata object for context. Metadata is attached as Sentry tags (truncated at 200 characters) and included in log output.\n\n```typescript\nlogInfo('Processing file', {\n  fileName: 'example.ts',\n  fileSize: 1024,\n  userId: '123',\n});\n```\n\nThe implementation is in `packages/logging/src/log.ts`. Metadata is passed through `withSentryScope` which sets each key as a Sentry tag.\n\n## Secret scrubbing\n\nSecrets are scrubbed automatically — you do not need to redact them manually. The scrubber (imported from `@factory/utils/secretScrubber`) runs on `message` and `metadata` before anything is written to logs or Sentry.\n\nMetadata keys `body`, `error`, `errorMessage`, `messages`, and `headers` are specifically scrubbed because they commonly contain sensitive content. The scrubbing logic is in `packages/logging/src/log.ts` → `redactMetadata`.\n",
