            "content": "# Metrics\n\nThe metrics system records performance and usage data. It lives in `packages/logging/src/metrics.ts` with supporting types in `packages/logging/src/metrics/`.\n\n## How to record metrics\n\nImport `Metrics` from `@factory/logging`:\n\n```typescript\nimport { Metrics } from '@factory/logging';\n```\n\nThree methods cover all cases:\n\n### Counter — things that increment\n\n```typescript\nMetrics.addToCounter('llm_completion_count', 1, { model: 'claude-3-5-sonnet', status: 'success' });\n```\n\n### Gauge — current state\n\n```typescript\nMetrics.setGauge('active_sessions_count', 42);\n```\n\n### Histogram — distributions (latency, sizes)\n\n```typescript\nMetrics.recordHistogram('session_initialize_latency_ms', 1250, { provider: 'anthropic' });\n```\n\n## Metric naming conventions\n\n- Use `snake_case`\n- Include the unit as a suffix when it matters: `_ms`, `_bytes`, `_count`\n- Be specific: `llm_completion_success_count` rather than `success`\n\nGood examples:\n```\nsession_initialize_latency_ms\nfile_size_bytes\nllm_completion_count\nactive_sessions_count\n```\n\n## How metrics flow\n\nIn server-side code (backend, daemon), `Metrics.addLog` calls `logInfo` with a `METRICS_PREFIX` so the metric appears as a structured log entry. In browser/client contexts it goes to `TelemetryClient` which batches events and flushes them every 2 seconds.\n\nThe `METRICS_PREFIX` constant is defined in `packages/logging/src/constants.ts`. Axiom parses these structured log lines and makes them queryable.\n\n## Labels (tags)\n\nLabels let you slice metrics in Axiom. The available label keys are defined in `packages/logging/src/metrics/types.ts` (`MetricLabels`). Common ones:\n\n```typescript\nconst labels = {\n  model: 'claude-3-5-sonnet',\n  provider: 'anthropic',\n  status: 'success',\n  integrationType: 'github',\n};\n```\n\n## Instrumenting external calls\n\nTwo helpers in `apps/backend/src/app/api/_utils/metrics/` wrap outbound calls with automatic latency and error recording:\n\n### `fetchWithMetrics` — HTTP calls\n\n```typescript\nimport { fetchWithMetrics } from '@/app/api/_utils/metrics';\nimport { ExternalDependency } from '@/app/api/_utils/metrics/enums';\n\nconst response = await fetchWithMetrics(\n  fetch,\n  ExternalDependency.OPENAI,\n  { labels: { model: 'gpt-4' } },\n  'https://api.openai.com/v1/chat/completions',\n  { method: 'POST', body: JSON.stringify(payload) }\n);\n```\n\n### `callWithMetrics` — any function\n\n```typescript\nimport { callWithMetrics } from '@/app/api/_utils/metrics';\n\nconst result = await callWithMetrics(\n  processDocument,\n  ExternalDependency.WEAVIATE,\n  { isUserError: (err) => err.status < 500 },\n  documentId\n);\n```\n\nWhen adding a new external service, add it to the `ExternalDependency` enum in `apps/backend/src/app/api/_utils/metrics/enums.ts`.\n\n## Where to view metrics\n\n- **Axiom** — primary destination for structured log-based metrics. Query by metric name (e.g., `llm_completion_count`).\n- **Datadog** — infrastructure and system-level metrics. See [Alerting](./alerting.md) for Datadog monitor setup.\n- **TelemetryClient** — client-side events are batched and sent to the Factory backend telemetry endpoint before reaching Axiom.\n",
