            "content": "# Getting started\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- Node.js 18.x (see `.nvmrc` at the repo root)\n- npm 11.x (`packageManager: \"npm@11.2.0\"` in `package.json`)\n- Bun 1.3.x (used by `apps/cli` and `apps/daemon`)\n\nOptional but recommended:\n- [nvm](https://github.com/nvm-sh/nvm) for managing Node versions\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/Factory-AI/factory-mono.git\ncd factory-mono\nnvm use        # switches to the Node version in .nvmrc\nnpm install    # installs all workspace dependencies\n```\n\n`npm install` automatically runs `npm run setup` via the `postinstall` hook, which builds necessary local packages.\n\n## Running the web stack\n\nTo start the backend, web app, admin, storybook, and daemon together:\n\n```bash\nnpm run dev:web\n```\n\nThis streams logs to the console and to log files:\n\n| App | Log file |\n|---|---|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n\nFor desktop development (requires macOS):\n\n```bash\nnpm run dev:desktop\n```\n\n**Do not run `npm run dev` at the root** — it is intentionally disabled.\n\n## Running the CLI\n\nAfter starting the daemon, set up the CLI alias:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup\n```\n\nThis creates a `droid-dev` alias (points to hosted dev environment) and `droid-localhost` alias (points to local API). Start a new terminal session after running setup, then launch the TUI:\n\n```bash\ndroid-dev\n```\n\n## Building\n\n```bash\nnpm run build           # builds all packages and apps\nnpm run build --filter=apps/web   # builds a specific workspace\n```\n\nTo build the CLI as a standalone binary:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run build\n```\n\nThis produces `dist/{platform}/{arch}/droid` (or `droid.exe` on Windows).\n\n## Running tests\n\n```bash\n# All tests (memory-intensive — uses ~9 GB RAM)\nnpm run test\n\n# Targeted (CORRECT syntax — note the -- before --filter)\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common --filter=@factory/droid-core\n\n# Single file\ncd apps/backend && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run path/to/file.test.ts\n```\n\n## Type checking and linting\n\n```bash\nnpm run typecheck              # TypeScript across all packages\nnpm run fix                    # lint + auto-format (preferred over npm run lint)\nnpm run knip                   # detect unused exports\n```\n\nTo target a specific package:\n\n```bash\nnpm run typecheck -- --filter=apps/cli\nnpm run fix -- --filter=packages/droid-core\n```\n\n## Storybook\n\n```bash\nnpm run storybook\n```\n\nStorybook documents `@factory/core-ui` and `@factory/component-library` components.\n\n## Environment variables\n\nEach app has `.env`, `.env.development`, `.env.staging`, `.env.production` files. For local development, create `.env.local` files (git-ignored) to override values. The `@factory/environment` package provides typed access to environment variables — never read `process.env` directly.\n\nSee [configuration reference](../reference/configuration.md) for the full list of environment variables.\n",
