            "content": "# Tooling\n\n## Build system\n\nThe repo uses **Turborepo** (`turbo`) with npm workspaces. Turborepo caches build outputs and runs tasks in dependency order. The root `turbo.json` configures pipeline relationships between packages.\n\nKey turbo scripts:\n\n| Script | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| `npm run build` | Builds all packages in dependency order |\n| `npm run fix` | Runs lint + format across all packages |\n| `npm run test` | Runs all tests |\n| `npm run typecheck` | TypeScript checking |\n| `npm run clean` | Removes `.turbo`, `.next`, `dist`, `vite` caches |\n\n**Always use `--` before `--filter` when targeting packages:**\n```bash\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common   # correct\nnpm run test --filter=@factory/common       # wrong — npm eats the flag\n```\n\n## ESLint\n\nEach package has its own `.eslintrc` or `.eslintrc.cjs`. The shared base config is in `packages/eslint-config/`. Custom rules enforced across all packages:\n\n- `no-direct-process-env` — require use of `@factory/environment` instead of `process.env`\n- File organization rules: enums in `enums.ts`, types in `types.ts`\n- No raw HTML elements in UI code (Box, Button, Input, etc.)\n- No relative cross-package imports\n\nRun lint and auto-fix:\n```bash\nnpm run fix -- --filter=apps/cli\n```\n\n## TypeScript\n\nAll packages use TypeScript with strict settings. The root `tsconfig.json` is extended by each package. Key conventions:\n\n- No `as` type assertions in most packages — use proper type narrowing\n- API types in `@factory/common` are the source of truth for cross-boundary data\n\n## Testing tools\n\n| Tool | Used by |\n|---|---|\n| Jest | Most packages |\n| Vitest | `packages/frontend` |\n| `@microsoft/tui-test` | `apps/cli` E2E tests |\n| Playwright | `apps/web` E2E tests |\n| `@testing-library/react` | React component/hook tests |\n\n## Storybook\n\nStorybook documents `@factory/core-ui` and `@factory/component-library`. Run it with:\n```bash\nnpm run storybook\n```\nor from the workspace: `cd apps/storybook && npm run dev`.\n\n## Knip\n\n`knip` detects unused exports, dead code, and dependency issues. Run before finalizing a PR:\n```bash\nnpm run knip -- --filter=<your-package>\n```\n\n## Husky and git hooks\n\nThe repo uses Husky (configured in `package.json` `prepare` hook) for pre-commit linting. The git hook runs automatically on `git commit`.\n\n## CI/CD\n\nGitHub Actions workflows are in `.github/workflows/`. Key workflows:\n\n| Workflow | Trigger |\n|---|---|\n| `basic-checks.yml` | Every PR — lint, typecheck |\n| `test.yml` | Every PR — unit tests |\n| `typecheck.yml` | Every PR — TypeScript |\n| `cli-e2e-tests.yml` | CLI changes — TUI E2E |\n| `playwright-e2e-critical.yml` | Web changes — browser E2E |\n| `cli-release.yml` | Tagged release — CLI binary distribution |\n| `factoryd-release.yml` | Tagged release — daemon binary |\n| `desktop-release.yml` | Tagged release — Electron app |\n| `deploy-prod.yml` | Merge to main — backend + web deployment |\n| `opentofu.yml` | Infrastructure changes — OpenTofu (Terraform fork) |\n\nThe `droid.yml` workflow runs an automated code review using the Droid agent itself on each PR.\n\n## Bun\n\n`apps/cli` and `apps/daemon` use Bun as the runtime and build tool. Bun is declared in `package.json` as a dev dependency (`bun@1.3.10`) and is required for building CLI and daemon.\n\n## Infrastructure\n\nInfrastructure is managed with [OpenTofu](https://opentofu.org/) (an open-source Terraform fork). Config lives in `infra/`. Run infrastructure validation with:\n```bash\ntofu init\ntofu validate\ntofu fmt\n```\nNever use the `terraform` CLI — use `tofu`.\n",
