            "content": "# Apps\n\nThe `apps/` directory contains six deployable applications. Each has its own `package.json`, build config, and deployment target.\n\n## Overview\n\n| App | Port | Runtime | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `apps/backend` | 3000 | Next.js 15 | REST API, LLM proxy, billing, integrations |\n| `apps/admin` | 3001 | Next.js 15 | Platform admin dashboard |\n| `apps/web` | 3002 | Vite + React | Main web interface for Droid |\n| `apps/desktop` | — | Electron | Native desktop app |\n| `apps/daemon` | 37643/41723 | Bun | `factoryd` background daemon |\n| `apps/cli` | — | Bun | `droid` CLI tool |\n\nAlso in `apps/` but with limited active development:\n\n| App | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/storybook` | Component documentation |\n| `apps/factory-vscode-extension` | VSCode integration |\n| `apps/factory-jetbrains-plugin` | JetBrains IDE integration |\n| `apps/functions` | Firebase Cloud Functions |\n| `apps/scripts` | Build and maintenance scripts |\n| `apps/signal` | Notification/signal service |\n| `apps/relay` | WebSocket relay for remote CDEs |\n\n## Relationship between apps\n\nThe web and desktop apps are user-facing interfaces that connect to the daemon over WebSocket. The daemon manages droid (CLI) processes. The backend provides the API layer for auth, session persistence, billing, and LLM proxying.\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    WEB[\"apps/web\"] -->|WebSocket| DAEMON[\"apps/daemon\"]\n    DESKTOP[\"apps/desktop\"] -->|WebSocket| DAEMON\n    DAEMON -->|stdin/stdout| CLI[\"apps/cli\"]\n    WEB -->|HTTP| BACKEND[\"apps/backend\"]\n    DESKTOP -->|HTTP| BACKEND\n```\n\n## Detailed pages\n\n- [CLI (droid)](cli/index.md)\n- [Daemon (factoryd)](daemon/index.md)\n- [Backend](backend/index.md)\n- [Web](web.md)\n- [Desktop](desktop.md)\n- [Admin](admin.md)\n",
