            "content": "# TUI rendering\n\nThe Droid CLI renders a full-screen terminal UI using [Ink](https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink) — a React renderer that outputs to a terminal instead of the DOM. Components are written in TSX and rendered using React's reconciler, but the output is terminal control codes.\n\n## How Ink works\n\nInk replaces the terminal UI with a React component tree. Each component renders text and boxes using terminal-compatible layout (`flexbox` mapped to terminal columns). Updates re-render only the changed cells, making the TUI feel responsive.\n\nThe root component is `apps/cli/src/app.tsx`. It is a 160k+ line file that manages the entire TUI state tree.\n\n## Main layout\n\nThe TUI has three primary regions:\n\n```\n┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  Header (session name, model, status)              │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                    │\n│  Message list                                      │\n│  (AssistantMessages, ToolResults, UserMessages)    │\n│                                                    │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  Active region                                     │\n│  (input box, confirmation dialogs, tool views)     │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  Status line / footer                              │\n└────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Key components\n\n| Component | File | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `AppLayout` | `components/AppLayout.tsx` | Root layout wrapper |\n| `MessageItem` | `components/MessageItem.tsx` | Single message display |\n| `BatchToolConfirmationMessage` | `components/BatchToolConfirmationMessage.tsx` | Tool confirmation dialogs |\n| `DiffRenderer` | `components/DiffRenderer.tsx` | File diff display |\n| `SettingsList` | `components/SettingsList.tsx` | Settings panel |\n| `SessionList` | `components/SessionList.tsx` | Session browser |\n| `ModelSelector` | `components/ModelSelector.tsx` | Model picker |\n| `ThinkingDisplay` | `components/ThinkingDisplay.tsx` | Extended thinking rendering |\n| `renderMarkdown` | `components/renderMarkdown.tsx` | Markdown → Ink output |\n| `MissionsList` | `components/MissionsList.tsx` | Mission status overview |\n\n## State management\n\nThe TUI manages state through a combination of React `useState`/`useReducer` hooks and a controller pattern. The `SessionController` (`apps/cli/src/controllers/SessionController.ts`) holds the live session state and connects the WebSocket (daemon) protocol to the React component tree.\n\nKey hooks in `apps/cli/src/hooks/`:\n\n- State for the active session, message list, working state\n- Keyboard shortcut handling\n- Daemon connection status\n\n## Rendering modes within the TUI\n\nThe TUI adapts its active region based on context:\n\n- **Chat input** — default state when agent is idle\n- **Tool confirmation** — shown when agent requests permission to run a tool\n- **Spec mode** — structured proposal mode where the agent presents a plan before acting\n- **Mission control** — mission status panel showing orchestrator/worker state\n- **Settings panel** — when user presses the settings hotkey\n- **Session list** — session browser\n\n## Sound and notifications\n\nThe CLI plays audio cues on key events (agent idle, agent starting, etc.) via sound files in `apps/cli/src/sounds/`. Users can configure or disable sounds in settings.\n\n## Terminal compatibility\n\nInk handles most terminal differences. The CLI targets standard ANSI terminals (iTerm2, Terminal.app, VS Code integrated terminal, common Linux terminals). Windows Terminal is supported via the SEA build.\n",
