            "content": "# Packages\n\nThe `packages/` directory contains shared libraries used across the apps. All packages are npm workspaces managed by Turborepo.\n\n## Overview\n\n| Package | Scope | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `@factory/core-ui` | UI | Design system — mandatory for all web UI |\n| `@factory/frontend` | UI | Shared React features (sessions, settings, analytics) |\n| `@factory/component-library` | UI | Additional UI components (beyond core-ui) |\n| `@factory/droid-core` | Agent | AI agent core — tools, LLMs, streaming |\n| `@factory/daemon-core` | Infrastructure | Daemon WebSocket server and session management |\n| `@factory/common` | Shared | Types, enums, API contracts |\n| `@factory/services` | Backend | Business logic and external service clients |\n| `@factory/models` | Shared | TypeScript type definitions |\n| `@factory/environment` | Shared | Typed environment variable access |\n| `@factory/runtime` | Shared | Auth storage, runtime utilities |\n| `@factory/logging` | Shared | Logging, metrics, error classes |\n| `@factory/utils` | Shared | Common utility functions |\n| `@factory/updater` | Shared | Auto-update checking |\n| `@factory/eslint-config` | Dev | Shared ESLint configuration |\n| `@factory/test-utils` | Dev | Shared test utilities and mocks |\n| `@factory/signal-core` | Infrastructure | Signal/notification infrastructure |\n| `@factory/daemon-client` | Infrastructure | TypeScript client for daemon WebSocket API |\n\n## Package dependency rules\n\n- All web UI code must use `@factory/core-ui` — no raw HTML elements\n- Cross-boundary data shapes must be defined in `@factory/common`\n- Environment variables must be accessed through `@factory/environment`\n- Logging must use `@factory/logging` — no `console.error` or direct Sentry calls\n\n## Detailed pages\n\n- [`@factory/droid-core`](droid-core/index.md)\n- [`@factory/core-ui`](core-ui/index.md)\n- [`@factory/frontend`](frontend/index.md)\n- [`@factory/common`](common.md)\n- [`@factory/daemon-core`](daemon-core.md)\n- [Other packages](other-packages.md)\n",
