            "content": "# LLM integration\n\n`@factory/droid-core` supports three LLM provider families and routes requests through the Factory backend proxy or directly to providers (BYOK).\n\n## Provider adapters\n\nEach provider adapter handles the translation between the canonical internal message format (`FactoryDroidMessage`) and the provider's specific API format.\n\n### Anthropic (`llms/provider/anthropic/`)\n\nSupports all Claude models. Uses the Anthropic Messages API with streaming via Server-Sent Events. The adapter handles:\n\n- Message role mapping (user, assistant, tool_use, tool_result)\n- Extended thinking block processing (reasoning tokens)\n- Token counting and context window management\n- Rate limit error handling and retries\n\n### OpenAI (`llms/provider/openai/`)\n\nSupports GPT models and the o-series reasoning models. Uses the OpenAI Chat Completions API with streaming. The adapter handles:\n\n- Function calling / tool use format conversion\n- Reasoning effort parameter (for o1, o3, o4 models)\n- Response format and finish reason mapping\n\n### Google (`llms/provider/google/`)\n\nSupports Gemini models. Uses the Google GenAI SDK. The adapter handles:\n\n- Content part mapping (text, function call, function response)\n- Safety settings and blocked content handling\n- Extended context window models (Gemini 1.5 Pro)\n\n## LLM proxy\n\nBy default, all LLM requests route through the Factory backend's LLM proxy at `apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/`. The proxy:\n\n1. Validates the user's entitlements and usage limits\n2. Records usage metrics for billing\n3. Forwards the request to the provider\n4. Streams the response back\n\nThe CLI sends requests to the proxy using the Factory API base URL from environment config.\n\n## BYOK (Bring Your Own Key)\n\nWith `--byok`, the CLI sends requests directly to the provider using the user's own API key, bypassing the Factory proxy:\n\n```bash\ndroid exec --prompt \"...\" --byok --api-key sk-ant-...\n```\n\nBYOK skips the Factory usage tracking and billing. The CLI configures the provider adapter to use the supplied key directly.\n\n## Streaming\n\nLLM responses stream as Server-Sent Events. The streaming layer in `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/` processes the event stream:\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    LLM[\"LLM provider\\n(via proxy or direct)\"] -->|\"SSE stream\"| SCHEMA[\"StreamingSchema\\nvalidation\"]\n    SCHEMA --> PARTS[\"DataStreamPart\\nprocessing\"]\n    PARTS --> RUNNER[\"ExecRunner\\n(CLI)\"]\n    RUNNER -->|\"Notifications\"| DAEMON[\"Daemon → Frontend\"]\n```\n\nEvent types in `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/enums.ts`:\n\n- Text delta (streaming text chunks)\n- Thinking delta (extended thinking chunks)\n- Tool call start/delta/end\n- Usage update (token counts)\n- Finish reason\n\n## Error handling\n\nLLM errors are classified in `packages/droid-core/src/llms/errors/`:\n\n- Rate limit errors → retry with backoff\n- Context window exceeded → trigger compaction\n- Provider errors → surface to user with context\n- Network errors → retry with exponential backoff\n\n## Model selection\n\nAvailable models are defined and filtered in `apps/cli/src/models/availability.ts`. The set of available models can vary by org tier, feature flags, and the command being run (exec vs. TUI, missions vs. standard).\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/anthropic/` | Anthropic adapter |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/openai/` | OpenAI adapter |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/google/` | Google adapter |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/schema.ts` | SSE event schema |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/streaming/data-stream-parts.ts` | Event part types |\n| `apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/` | Backend LLM proxy |\n| `apps/cli/src/models/availability.ts` | Available model list |\n",
