            "content": "# Session management in @factory/frontend\n\nThe `packages/frontend/src/services/session/` and `features/sessions/` directories handle all live session state in the web and desktop UIs.\n\n## DaemonSessionController\n\n`DaemonSessionController.ts` is the central coordinator for a live droid session. It manages the WebSocket connection to the daemon and translates incoming protocol messages into Redux state updates.\n\n### Initialization\n\nWhen a user opens a session, the frontend:\n\n1. Creates a WebSocket connection to the daemon\n2. Sends `daemon.initialize_session` or `daemon.load_session` with the session ID and settings\n3. `DaemonSessionController` starts listening for notifications on this connection\n\n### Handling notifications\n\nEach `droid.session_notification` carries a `SessionNotificationType`. The controller dispatches Redux actions based on the notification type:\n\n| Notification | Redux action |\n|---|---|\n| `create_message` | Add message to session state |\n| `tool_result` | Update tool execution in message |\n| `assistant_text_delta` | Append streaming text to current message |\n| `droid_working_state_changed` | Update working state indicator |\n| `session_token_usage_changed` | Update token usage counter |\n| `mission_state_changed` | Update mission run state |\n\n### Permission handling\n\nWhen the CLI sends `droid.request_permission`, the controller renders a confirmation dialog component. The user's response is sent back to the daemon (and forwarded to the CLI) as the JSON-RPC response.\n\n### Disconnection and reconnection\n\nThe controller monitors WebSocket health. On disconnection, it attempts reconnection with exponential backoff. Session state is preserved in Redux during reconnect.\n\n## Session features\n\n### `features/sessions/`\n\nThe sessions feature module handles:\n\n- **Session list** — browsing, searching, and selecting sessions\n- **Session creation** — new session flow with initial message\n- **Session metadata** — title, tags, settings\n\n### Session state in Redux\n\nThe Redux slice for sessions holds:\n\n- `currentSession` — the active session ID and metadata\n- `messageTree` — ordered list of messages with tool calls\n- `workingState` — current agent activity (`DroidWorkingState`)\n- `tokenUsage` — running token count for the session\n- `settings` — session-level settings (model, autonomy mode, etc.)\n\n## Settings panel\n\nThe settings feature (`features/settings/`) provides UI for:\n\n- Integration configuration (GitHub, Linear, Slack)\n- API key management (BYOK)\n- Model preferences\n- Notification preferences\n- Billing and subscription management\n\nSettings are persisted to the backend and fetched on session initialization.\n\n## Terminal feature\n\n`features/terminal/` provides the embedded terminal component. It connects to the daemon's terminal management endpoints (`daemon.create_terminal`, `daemon.write_terminal_data`) and renders a PTY-based terminal using [xterm.js](https://xtermjs.org/).\n",
