            "content": "# Other packages\n\nSmaller shared packages used across the monorepo.\n\n## @factory/logging\n\n`packages/logging` provides structured logging, metrics, error classes, and Sentry integration.\n\n**Key exports:**\n- `logInfo(message, metadata?)` — informational breadcrumbs\n- `logWarn(message, metadata?)` — potential issues\n- `logException(error, message, metadata?)` — handled errors (do not rethrow after calling)\n- `Metrics` — counter, gauge, and histogram recording\n- `MetaError` — base error class (use instead of `Error`)\n- `ResponseErrorXXX` — HTTP-status-typed error classes\n\n**Usage:**\n```typescript\nimport { logInfo, logException, Metrics } from '@factory/logging';\nimport { MetaError } from '@factory/logging/errors';\n```\n\nSee `docs/error-handling.md` and `docs/metrics-logging.md` for rules and patterns.\n\n## @factory/environment\n\n`packages/environment` provides typed access to environment variables. Prevents direct `process.env` access, which is banned by ESLint.\n\n**Usage:**\n```typescript\nimport { EnvironmentVariable } from '@factory/environment';\nconst apiUrl = EnvironmentVariable.FACTORY_API_URL;\n```\n\nEnvironment variables are declared and typed in `packages/environment/src/`.\n\n## @factory/utils\n\n`packages/utils` contains common utility functions shared across packages:\n- String manipulation\n- Date formatting\n- Shell utility functions (`expandTilde`, `loadShellEnvironment`)\n- LLM utility functions (`getModelConfig`, `getAuthedUser`)\n- Retry helpers\n\n## @factory/runtime\n\n`packages/runtime` handles cross-platform credential storage and auth token management. Used by the CLI for storing WorkOS session tokens via the OS keychain (keytar).\n\n**Key exports:**\n- `getAuthToken()` — retrieve the stored auth token\n- `configureCredentialsStorage({ keytarLoader })` — configure the keychain backend\n\n## @factory/updater\n\n`packages/updater` provides version checking and update download utilities used by both the CLI and daemon for auto-update:\n\n- Version comparison\n- Update manifest fetching from `downloads.factory.ai`\n- Binary download and replacement\n\n## @factory/services\n\n`packages/services` contains shared business logic and external service clients that are used across multiple apps:\n\n- `settings/` — settings management utilities\n- Other service utilities\n\n## @factory/models\n\n`packages/models` contains TypeScript type definitions and data model schemas for domain entities (not Firestore schemas, which live in the backend).\n\n## @factory/daemon-client\n\n`packages/daemon-client` provides a typed TypeScript client for the daemon WebSocket API. Used by the frontend packages to send requests and receive notifications in a type-safe way.\n\n## @factory/signal-core\n\n`packages/signal-core` contains core logic for the `apps/signal` notification service.\n\n## @factory/test-utils\n\n`packages/test-utils` provides shared test utilities:\n- Common mock factories\n- Test wrappers for Redux store\n- Shared Firestore mock helpers\n\n## @factory/eslint-config\n\n`packages/eslint-config` is the shared ESLint configuration base. All packages extend from this. It enforces:\n\n- File organization rules (enums.ts, types.ts)\n- No direct process.env access\n- No raw HTML elements in UI\n- Absolute imports only\n- No unused variables\n",
