            "content": "# Features\n\nCross-cutting capabilities that span multiple apps and packages.\n\n## Feature catalog\n\n| Feature | Description |\n|---|---|\n| [Agent execution](agent-execution/index.md) | The core agent loop — tools, confirmation, streaming |\n| [Missions](missions.md) | Autonomous task decomposition with orchestrator/worker sessions |\n| [MCP integration](mcp-integration.md) | Model Context Protocol server support |\n| [Wiki generation](wiki-generation.md) | Documentation generation and upload |\n\n## How features span the stack\n\nEach feature below touches multiple components in the architecture:\n\n**Agent execution** — the CLI (`apps/cli`), droid-core (`packages/droid-core`), daemon (`apps/daemon`), and frontend (`packages/frontend`) all participate in a single agent session.\n\n**Missions** — additionally involves the backend for mission metadata and the orchestrator/worker session coordination in the CLI and daemon.\n\n**MCP** — primarily in the CLI (`apps/cli/src/mcp/`), droid-core tool registry, and daemon (which manages MCP server state across sessions).\n\n**Wiki** — the CLI command (`apps/cli/src/commands/wiki-upload.ts`) generates and uploads documentation to the Factory platform via the backend.\n",
