            "content": "# Wiki generation\n\nWiki generation is the `droid wiki-upload` command that generates documentation for a repository and uploads it to the Factory platform for browsing in the web app. This wiki was itself generated using this feature.\n\n## Overview\n\nThe workflow is:\n\n1. A Droid session reads the repository structure and source files\n2. The agent writes a set of interconnected markdown pages to a local directory (default `./droid-wiki/`)\n3. `droid wiki-upload` uploads all pages to the Factory platform\n4. The wiki is accessible at `app.factory.ai` under the repository's wiki section\n\n## The `wiki-upload` command\n\n```bash\ndroid wiki-upload \\\n  --session-id \"$SESSION_ID\" \\\n  --repo-url \"https://github.com/org/repo\" \\\n  --wiki-dir ./droid-wiki\n\n# With cleanup (removes local files after successful upload)\ndroid wiki-upload \\\n  --session-id \"$SESSION_ID\" \\\n  --repo-url \"https://github.com/org/repo\" \\\n  --wiki-dir ./droid-wiki \\\n  --cleanup\n```\n\nThe command is implemented in `apps/cli/src/commands/wiki-upload.ts`.\n\n## What `wiki-upload` does\n\n1. Validates the wiki directory and its `.wiki-meta.json` file\n2. Reads all `.md` files recursively from the wiki directory\n3. Parses each file's title from the first `# Heading`\n4. Uploads the pages to the Factory backend via the wiki API\n5. Associates the wiki with the provided session ID and repo URL\n\n## Wiki directory structure\n\nThe generated wiki follows a standard structure:\n\n```\ndroid-wiki/\n├── .wiki-meta.json          # Page order and metadata\n├── overview/                # Project overview pages\n├── how-to-contribute/       # Contributor guides\n├── apps/                    # Per-application documentation\n├── packages/                # Per-package documentation\n├── features/                # Cross-cutting feature documentation\n├── api/                     # API reference\n├── reference/               # Configuration and data model reference\n└── fun-facts.md             # Optional trivia\n```\n\n## The .wiki-meta.json file\n\nThe `.wiki-meta.json` file controls the sidebar order in the wiki browser:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"generatedAt\": \"2025-01-15T10:30:00Z\",\n  \"pageCount\": 42,\n  \"topLevelSections\": [\"overview\", \"how-to-contribute\", \"apps\"],\n  \"pageOrder\": [\n    \"overview/index.md\",\n    \"overview/architecture.md\",\n    ...\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nWithout this file, pages display in alphabetical order.\n\n## Backend API\n\nThe upload sends pages to the backend wiki API at `apps/backend/src/app/api/v0/` (wiki endpoints). The backend stores wiki content in Firestore, keyed by organization, repository, and session.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/wiki-upload.ts` | `droid wiki-upload` command implementation |\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/wiki-upload.test.ts` | Tests for upload command |\n| `apps/backend/src/app/api/v0/` | Backend wiki API endpoints |\n| `packages/common/src/api/wiki/` | Wiki API types |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/wiki/` | Wiki browser UI |\n",
