            "content": "# API\n\nThe Factory platform exposes two API surfaces:\n\n1. **Backend REST API** (`apps/backend`) — HTTP endpoints for all platform operations\n2. **Daemon WebSocket API** (`apps/daemon`) — JSON-RPC 2.0 over WebSocket for live session management\n\n## Backend REST API base URL\n\n| Environment | URL |\n|---|---|\n| Production | `https://api.factory.ai` |\n| Development | `http://localhost:3000` |\n\nAll endpoints are under `/api/`. Authentication uses WorkOS session tokens sent as cookies or the `Authorization` header.\n\n## Daemon WebSocket API base URL\n\n| Environment | Port |\n|---|---|\n| Production | `37643` |\n| Development | `41723` |\n\nThe daemon WebSocket server runs locally on the user's machine or on a CDE.\n\n## API type contracts\n\nAll request and response types are defined in `packages/common/src/api/`. This is the canonical source — both frontend and backend import from here.\n\n## See also\n\n- [REST endpoints](rest-endpoints.md)\n- [LLM proxy](llm-proxy.md)\n- [Daemon JSON-RPC protocol](../apps/daemon/json-rpc-protocol.md)\n",
