            "content": "# LLM proxy\n\nThe Factory backend includes an LLM proxy at `apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/` that routes LLM requests from the CLI through the backend. This centralizes usage tracking, rate limiting, and billing.\n\n## Why the proxy exists\n\n1. **Usage tracking** — every token used is recorded and reported to Orb for billing\n2. **Rate limiting** — org-level rate limits are enforced before forwarding to providers\n3. **Entitlement checks** — verifies the user's plan allows the requested model\n4. **Secrets management** — API keys for Anthropic/OpenAI/Google are stored server-side; clients never need them\n5. **Audit trail** — LLM calls are logged for debugging and compliance\n\n## Request format\n\nThe proxy accepts the standard provider-native format (Anthropic Messages API, OpenAI Chat Completions API, etc.) with a Factory authentication header:\n\n```http\nPOST /api/llm/stream\nAuthorization: Bearer <factory-token>\nContent-Type: application/json\n\n{\n  \"provider\": \"anthropic\",\n  \"model\": \"claude-3-5-sonnet-20241022\",\n  \"messages\": [...],\n  \"stream\": true,\n  \"tools\": [...]\n}\n```\n\n## Streaming response\n\nStreaming responses use Server-Sent Events (SSE). The proxy forwards events from the upstream provider as-is, with additional Factory-specific events for usage tracking:\n\n```\ndata: {\"type\":\"content_block_start\",\"index\":0,\"content_block\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\"}}\n\ndata: {\"type\":\"content_block_delta\",\"index\":0,\"delta\":{\"type\":\"text_delta\",\"text\":\"Hello\"}}\n\ndata: {\"type\":\"message_delta\",\"delta\":{\"stop_reason\":\"end_turn\"},\"usage\":{\"output_tokens\":142}}\n```\n\n## BYOK (Bring Your Own Key)\n\nWhen the CLI is configured with `--byok`, requests bypass the proxy and go directly to the provider using the user's own API key. The proxy is not involved, and no usage is tracked through Factory.\n\nBYOK is configured in `apps/cli/src/commands/exec.ts` and `apps/cli/src/commands/assertValidOptions.ts`.\n\n## Provider routing\n\nThe proxy determines the upstream provider from the `provider` field in the request:\n\n| Provider | Upstream |\n|---|---|\n| `anthropic` | `api.anthropic.com` |\n| `openai` | `api.openai.com` |\n| `google` | Google GenAI API |\n\nThe proxy injects the appropriate API key for the selected provider from server-side environment variables.\n\n## Usage reporting\n\nAfter each streaming response completes, the proxy records token usage to Orb. This is done asynchronously to avoid blocking the response.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/backend/src/app/api/llm/` | LLM proxy route handlers |\n| `apps/backend/src/features/llm/` | LLM feature logic (model validation, rate limiting) |\n| `packages/common/src/llm/` | LLM model types and constants |\n| `packages/droid-core/src/llms/provider/` | Client-side provider adapters |\n",
