            "content": "# Data models\n\nCore domain entities and their structure. Persistent data is stored in Firestore. TypeScript types are defined in `packages/common/`.\n\n## Session\n\nA session represents a single conversation between a user and the Droid agent.\n\nKey fields:\n- `id` — unique session ID (Firestore document ID)\n- `orgId` — organization that owns the session\n- `userId` — user who created the session\n- `title` — auto-generated or user-set title\n- `model` — LLM model used in the session\n- `createdAt`, `updatedAt` — timestamps\n- `settings` — session-level settings (autonomy mode, enabled tools, etc.)\n- `tokenUsage` — cumulative token counts\n\nTypes: `packages/common/src/session/`, `packages/common/src/sessionV2/`\n\n## Message\n\nMessages in a session form a tree (not a flat list) to support branching.\n\nKey fields:\n- `id` — message ID\n- `sessionId` — parent session\n- `role` — `user` | `assistant`\n- `content` — array of content blocks (text, tool_use, tool_result, thinking)\n- `parentId` — for tree structure\n- `createdAt`\n\nThe main message type is `FactoryDroidMessage` in `packages/common/src/sessionV2/`.\n\nContent block types are in `MessageContentBlockType` enum in `packages/common/src/sessionV2/`.\n\n## Organization\n\nAn organization groups users and sessions.\n\nKey fields:\n- `id` — Firestore org ID\n- `name` — display name\n- `workosOrgId` — WorkOS organization ID for auth\n- `plan` — subscription plan\n- `settings` — org-level settings (default model, integrations, etc.)\n\n## User\n\nA user belongs to one or more organizations.\n\nKey fields:\n- `id` — Firestore user ID\n- `workosUserId` — WorkOS user ID\n- `email`\n- `name`\n- `defaultOrgId` — preferred organization\n\n## Integration\n\nAn integration connects a Factory org to a third-party service.\n\nKey fields:\n- `orgId` — owner org\n- `type` — `github` | `linear` | `slack` | `jira`\n- `accessToken` — OAuth token (encrypted at rest)\n- `scope` — granted permissions\n- `installedAt`\n\n## Droid settings\n\nPer-session and per-org settings controlling agent behavior.\n\nKey fields:\n- `model` — selected LLM model\n- `autonomyMode` — default confirmation behavior\n- `enabledTools` — list of enabled/disabled tools\n- `mcpServers` — configured MCP server list\n- `byokConfig` — BYOK API key configuration\n\nTypes: `packages/common/src/settings/`\n\n## Mission\n\nA mission tracks an autonomous task decomposition run.\n\nKey fields:\n- `id` — mission ID\n- `sessionId` — orchestrator session\n- `state` — `MissionState` enum\n- `features` — array of feature tasks\n- `progressLog` — chronological list of events\n\nFeature fields:\n- `id`\n- `title`, `description`\n- `status` — `FeatureStatus` enum\n- `successState` — `FeatureSuccessState` enum\n- `workerSessionId` — assigned worker session\n\nTypes: `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` (enums), `packages/common/src/droid/types.ts`\n\n## Firestore collections\n\n| Collection | Documents |\n|---|---|\n| `organizations` | Org documents |\n| `users` | User documents |\n| `sessions` | Session documents |\n| `sessions/{id}/messages` | Messages subcollection |\n| `integrations` | Integration documents |\n",
