        {
          "type": "tool_use",
          "name": "Create",
          "input": {
            "content": "# Fun facts\n\n## The daemon is named factoryd\n\nFollowing the Unix tradition of naming background daemons with a `d` suffix (`sshd`, `httpd`, `crond`), the Factory daemon is called `factoryd`. The CLI binary keeps the product name: `droid`.\n\n## The TUI is 160k+ lines\n\n`apps/cli/src/app.tsx` — the root TUI component — is over 161,000 lines. It is the largest single file in the monorepo by a wide margin. It manages the entire interactive terminal interface state tree, from the message list to the settings panel to tool confirmation dialogs.\n\n## The CLI has two lives: one file, two modes\n\n`apps/cli/src/index.ts` starts as a humble 710-line entry point that decides the CLI's entire personality: if you run `droid` with no arguments, you get a full-screen Ink/React terminal app; if you run `droid exec`, you get Commander. The same binary, two completely different user experiences.\n\n## The wiki was written by the tool it documents\n\nThis wiki was generated by Droid, the AI agent described on every page. The `droid wiki-upload` command documented in [wiki generation](features/wiki-generation.md) was used to upload these very pages.\n\n## Missions mode has a bureaucracy of enums\n\nThe missions feature defines eight enums in a single file (`packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`): `MissionState`, `FeatureStatus`, `FeatureSuccessState`, `IssueSeverity`, `DismissalType`, `ProgressLogEntryType`, `DecompSessionType`, and more. It takes a village.\n\n## The LLM proxy predates BYOK\n\nThe Factory backend LLM proxy was the original and only way to call LLMs. BYOK (Bring Your Own Key) was added later to let users route requests directly to providers, bypassing the proxy entirely. The exec command supports both modes with a single flag: `--byok`.\n\n## Ink is pinned to a specific patch version\n\nThe root `package.json` has an override pinning `ink` to exactly `6.7.0`. Ink's terminal layout engine has subtle behavior differences between minor versions, and the TUI's 160k-line component tree is sensitive to them.\n\n## The repo has 50+ CI workflows\n\nThere are over 50 GitHub Actions workflows in `.github/workflows/`. Some are triggered on every PR (`basic-checks.yml`, `typecheck.yml`, `test.yml`). Others are for specific events: releases, cron jobs, infra changes, and automated droid code reviews. One workflow (`droid.yml`) runs the Droid agent itself to review pull requests.\n",
