            "content": "# Architecture\n\nFactory's architecture centers on one interaction loop: a user starts a Droid session (via CLI, web, or desktop), the daemon manages that session's lifecycle, and the backend provides API services for auth, billing, integrations, and LLM proxying.\n\n## High-level system diagram\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    User -->|terminal| CLI\n    User -->|browser| Web\n    User -->|native app| Desktop\n\n    Desktop -->|embeds| Daemon\n    Web -->|WebSocket JSON-RPC| Daemon\n    CLI <-->|stdin/stdout JSON-RPC| Daemon\n\n    Daemon -->|HTTP| Backend\n    Backend -->|REST| GitHub[GitHub/Linear/Slack]\n    Backend -->|streaming| LLM[LLM Providers]\n    Backend -->|Firestore| DB[(Firebase)]\n    Backend -->|billing| Orb\n\n    CLI -->|direct| LLM\n```\n\n## The session lifecycle\n\nA \"session\" is a single conversation between a user and the Droid agent. The daemon is responsible for the full lifecycle:\n\n1. **Initialize** -- the frontend (web or desktop) sends a `session/initialize` JSON-RPC request to the daemon\n2. **Spawn CLI** -- the daemon spawns a Droid CLI process as a child, communicating over stdin/stdout JSON-RPC\n3. **Run agent loop** -- the CLI runs the AI agent, calling tools, streaming responses, and sending notifications back through the daemon to the frontend\n4. **Interrupt/end** -- the user can interrupt or end the session; the daemon kills the CLI process\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant FE as Frontend\n    participant D as Daemon\n    participant CLI as Droid CLI\n    participant LLM as LLM Provider\n\n    FE->>D: session/initialize (WebSocket JSON-RPC)\n    D->>CLI: spawn process\n    D->>CLI: initialize (stdin JSON-RPC)\n    CLI->>LLM: streaming request\n    LLM-->>CLI: token stream\n    CLI-->>D: notifications (stdout JSON-RPC)\n    D-->>FE: notifications (WebSocket)\n    FE->>D: session/interrupt\n    D->>CLI: SIGINT\n```\n\n## Communication protocols\n\nAll inter-process communication in Factory uses JSON-RPC 2.0.\n\n| Link | Transport | Direction |\n|---|---|---|\n| Frontend to daemon | WebSocket | Bidirectional |\n| Daemon to CLI | stdin/stdout pipes | Bidirectional |\n| CLI to LLM providers | HTTPS | Request/streaming response |\n| CLI to backend API | HTTPS | Request/response |\n\nProtocol schemas (notification types, request/response shapes) are defined in `packages/common/src/droid/`.\n\n## App boundaries\n\n- **Backend** (`apps/backend`) -- stateless API server. Handles auth, billing, integrations, LLM proxy endpoints. Deployed on Vercel.\n- **Web** (`apps/web`) -- static SPA. Talks to the backend for data and to the daemon over WebSocket for sessions.\n- **Desktop** (`apps/desktop`) -- Electron shell. Bundles the daemon, renders the same frontend as web.\n- **Daemon** (`apps/daemon`) -- long-running local process. Manages CLI child processes, PTY sessions, and WebSocket connections.\n- **CLI** (`apps/cli`) -- the Droid agent. Runs inside Bun, uses Ink for TUI rendering, calls LLMs directly or via the backend proxy.\n\n## Package dependency graph\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    CLI[apps/cli] --> DC[packages/droid-core]\n    CLI --> Common[packages/common]\n    CLI --> Utils[packages/utils]\n    CLI --> Logging[packages/logging]\n    CLI --> Models[packages/models]\n\n    Daemon[apps/daemon] --> DC\n    Daemon --> Common\n    Daemon --> DaemonCore[packages/daemon-core]\n\n    Web[apps/web] --> FE[packages/frontend]\n    Web --> CoreUI[packages/core-ui]\n\n    Desktop[apps/desktop] --> FE\n    Desktop --> CoreUI\n    Desktop --> DaemonClient[packages/daemon-client]\n\n    FE --> CoreUI\n    FE --> Common\n    FE --> Services[packages/services]\n\n    Backend[apps/backend] --> Common\n    Backend --> Services\n    Backend --> Logging\n\n    DC --> Common\n    DC --> Models\n```\n\n## Key data stores\n\n| Store | Technology | What it holds |\n|---|---|---|\n| User data, orgs, sessions | Firebase Firestore | Core application state |\n| Session messages | Firestore | Conversation history |\n| Billing | Orb | Subscription and usage data |\n| Auth | WorkOS | User identities, SSO, organizations |\n| Feature flags | Statsig | Gate definitions and targeting rules |\n| Error tracking | Sentry | Exceptions and breadcrumbs |\n| Metrics/logs | Axiom | Structured logs and time-series metrics |\n\n## Infrastructure\n\nThe `infra/` directory contains OpenTofu (Terraform) modules for AWS and GCP resources, Ansible playbooks for VM provisioning, and Lambda functions for background jobs. See [Deployment](../deployment.md) for details.\n",
