            "content": "# Getting started\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- Node.js 18.x (see `.nvmrc`)\n- npm 11.x (specified in `package.json` `packageManager` field)\n- Bun 1.3.x (for CLI and daemon development)\n- Git\n\n## Initial setup\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/Factory-AI/factory-mono.git\ncd factory-mono\nnpm install\n```\n\n`npm install` runs the `postinstall` script, which calls `npm run setup` to run workspace-level setup tasks via Turborepo.\n\n## Running the dev environment\n\nThe root `npm run dev` command is intentionally disabled. Use one of these instead:\n\n| Command | What it starts | When to use |\n|---|---|---|\n| `npm run dev:web` | backend, web, storybook, admin, daemon | Remote/SSH development |\n| `npm run dev:desktop` | backend, web, storybook, admin, desktop | Local development with Electron |\n| `npm run dev:internal` | backend, internal web | Internal tooling work |\n\nEach app streams its output to both the console and a log file:\n\n| App | Log file |\n|---|---|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n| daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n\n## CLI development\n\nThe Droid CLI has its own setup step:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup\n```\n\nThis builds the CLI and creates wrapper scripts. After setup, use:\n\n- `droid-dev` -- runs CLI from source via Bun against the hosted dev API\n- `droid-localhost` -- runs CLI from source against a local API\n\nChanges to CLI source files are immediately available through `droid-dev` without rebuilding.\n\n## Common commands\n\n```bash\nnpm run fix           # Lint + auto-format (preferred over npm run lint)\nnpm run test          # Run all tests\nnpm run typecheck     # TypeScript type checking\nnpm run build         # Build all packages\nnpm run knip          # Detect unused exports\nnpm run clean         # Clear caches (turbo, vite, next, dist, tsbuildinfo)\n```\n\n## Filtering to specific packages\n\nTurborepo commands require `--` before `--filter`, otherwise npm swallows the flag:\n\n```bash\n# Correct\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common\n\n# Wrong -- npm eats --filter, turbo runs everything\nnpm run test --filter=@factory/common\n```\n\nA full unfiltered `npm run test` consumes around 9 GB of RAM, so always filter when possible.\n\n## Storybook\n\nRun Storybook to browse and develop `@factory/core-ui` components:\n\n```bash\nnpm run storybook\n```\n\n## Playwright E2E tests\n\n```bash\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e -- --headed --debug  # visual debugging\n```\n\n## Bug report downloader\n\nDownload and extract CLI bug reports from S3 for debugging:\n\n```bash\nnode scripts/download-bug-report.js <BUG_REPORT_ID>\n```\n\nRequires AWS credentials in `apps/backend/.env.local` or environment variables. Reports extract to `~/Downloads/bug-reports/<BUG_REPORT_ID>/`.\n",
