            "content": "# Glossary\n\n| Term | Definition |\n|---|---|\n| **Droid** | The AI coding agent. Refers to both the CLI tool (`droid` command) and the agent behavior. |\n| **Session** | A single conversation between a user and the Droid agent. Has a lifecycle: initialize, run, interrupt/end. |\n| **Daemon (factoryd)** | Background process that manages Droid sessions. Spawns CLI processes, handles WebSocket connections from frontends. |\n| **CLI** | The command-line interface for Droid (`apps/cli`). Runs inside Bun, uses Ink for terminal UI. |\n| **JSON-RPC 2.0** | The wire protocol used for all inter-process communication (daemon-to-CLI, frontend-to-daemon). |\n| **Tool** | A capability the Droid agent can invoke (e.g., Read, Edit, Grep, Execute). Defined in `packages/droid-core/src/tools/`. |\n| **MCP (Model Context Protocol)** | Protocol for connecting AI agents to external tool servers. The CLI can discover and use MCP tools. |\n| **Skill** | A predefined prompt/workflow that the Droid agent can activate to handle specific tasks (e.g., wiki generation, PR creation). |\n| **core-ui** | The mandatory design system package (`packages/core-ui`). All UI must use its primitives. |\n| **Frontend package** | `packages/frontend` -- shared React features, hooks, and services used by both web and desktop apps. |\n| **common package** | `packages/common` -- shared types, enums, API type definitions, and protocol schemas. |\n| **droid-core** | `packages/droid-core` -- AI agent core: tool definitions, LLM integrations, message handling, streaming. |\n| **Signal** | A backend service (`apps/signal`) for real-time event routing and notifications. |\n| **Relay** | A proxy service (`apps/relay`) deployed on AWS for routing traffic between clients and backend services. |\n| **SEA** | Single Executable Application. The CLI is distributed as a standalone binary using Bun's SEA feature. |\n| **CDE** | Cloud Development Environment. The daemon can run remotely in a cloud environment. |\n| **WorkOS** | Third-party auth provider used for SSO, user management, and organization management. |\n| **Statsig** | Feature flag service. Gates are defined in the Statsig console and referenced via `@factory/common/feature-flags`. |\n| **Orb** | Billing provider for subscription and usage-based billing. |\n| **Axiom** | Log aggregation and metrics platform. Used alongside Sentry for observability. |\n| **MetaError** | The custom error class (`@factory/logging/errors`) used for internal 500-level errors. All code should throw `MetaError` instead of `Error`. |\n| **ResponseErrorXXX** | Custom error classes for HTTP status codes (400, 401, 403, 404, etc.) thrown from API routes. |\n| **Turbo** | Turborepo, the build system that orchestrates workspace tasks (build, test, lint). |\n| **knip** | Tool for detecting unused exports across the monorepo. Run with `npm run knip`. |\n",
