            "content": "# How to contribute\n\nThis section covers everything you need to work effectively in the Factory monorepo: the development workflow, testing conventions, debugging techniques, coding patterns, and build tooling.\n\n## Pages in this section\n\n- [Development workflow](./development-workflow.md) -- branch, code, test, PR, merge\n- [Testing](./testing.md) -- frameworks, patterns, how to run and write tests\n- [Debugging](./debugging.md) -- logs, common errors, troubleshooting\n- [Patterns and conventions](./patterns-and-conventions.md) -- error handling, file organization, coding style\n- [Tooling](./tooling.md) -- build system, linters, code generators, CI\n\n## PR process at a glance\n\n1. Create a branch from `dev`\n2. Make changes, run `npm run fix` to auto-format\n3. Run targeted tests: `npm run test -- --filter=@factory/<package>`\n4. Open a PR with a Conventional Commits title: `type(scope): description`\n5. Include the Linear ticket reference (e.g., `Closes FAC-1234`)\n6. Get review, address feedback, merge\n",
