            "content": "# Development workflow\n\n## Branch strategy\n\nThe default branch is `dev`. Production releases are cut from `dev` to `main`. Feature work branches off `dev` and merges back into `dev`.\n\n## Day-to-day cycle\n\n1. **Branch** -- create a feature branch from `dev`\n2. **Code** -- make changes, following [patterns and conventions](./patterns-and-conventions.md)\n3. **Lint/format** -- run `npm run fix` (this runs ESLint with auto-fix and Prettier)\n4. **Test** -- run tests for affected packages: `npm run test -- --filter=@factory/<package>`\n5. **Typecheck** -- run `npm run typecheck -- --filter=@factory/<package>`\n6. **PR** -- open a pull request against `dev`\n\n## PR conventions\n\n**Title format:** `type(scope): description`\n\n- **Types:** `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`\n- **Scope:** workspace name from `apps/*` or `packages/*`, or `monorepo` for cross-cutting changes\n- **Examples:** `feat(cli): add wiki upload command`, `fix(frontend): correct session state race`\n\n**Description:** Must include a Linear ticket reference (e.g., `Closes FAC-1234`). Follow the template in `.github/pull_request_template.md`.\n\n## After modifying CLI or daemon code\n\nChanges to the CLI or daemon require extra steps before testing:\n\n1. Rebuild the CLI: `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`\n2. Restart the daemon process\n3. Start a new session (old sessions will not pick up changes)\n\nThe `droid-dev` wrapper runs CLI source directly via Bun, so source changes are available without rebuilding for non-binary distribution testing.\n\n## Environment setup\n\nSee [Getting started](../overview/getting-started.md) for full setup instructions. The short version:\n\n```bash\nnpm install\nnpm run dev:web    # or dev:desktop for local Electron\n```\n",
