            "content": "# Testing\n\n## Test runners\n\n| Runner | Used by | Config file |\n|---|---|---|\n| Jest | Backend, CLI, daemon, most packages | `jest.config.ts` or `jest.config.cjs` per workspace |\n| Vitest | Web app, desktop app | `vitest.config.mts` per workspace |\n| Playwright | Frontend E2E tests | `playwright.config.ts` in `apps/web` |\n| `@microsoft/tui-test` | CLI E2E tests | `tui-test.config.ts` in `apps/cli` |\n\n## Running tests\n\n```bash\n# All tests (uses ~9 GB RAM, prefer filtering)\nnpm run test\n\n# Specific package\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common\n\n# Single file (Jest)\ncd apps/backend && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts\n\n# Single file (Vitest)\ncd apps/web && npx vitest run path/to/file.test.ts\n\n# Playwright E2E\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e\n```\n\nAlways use `--` before `--filter` when running from the root, otherwise npm swallows the flag.\n\n## Writing tests\n\n### Frontend tests need jsdom\n\nAny test that uses browser APIs (`document`, `window`, React hooks) must declare the jsdom environment:\n\n```ts\n/**\n * @jest-environment jsdom\n */\n```\n\n### Mock pattern\n\nUse top-level `jest.mock()` with `jest.requireActual()`. Only mock the functions you need:\n\n```ts\nimport { fetchTeamId } from './linearApi';\nimport { getItems } from './todoList';\n\njest.mock('./linearApi', () => ({\n  ...jest.requireActual('./linearApi'),\n  fetchTeamId: jest.fn(),\n}));\n\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetAllMocks());\n```\n\nSet behavior per test with `mockResolvedValue` or `mockImplementation`:\n\n```ts\nit('maps tickets', async () => {\n  (fetchTeamId as jest.Mock).mockResolvedValue({ id: 'team-123' });\n  const result = await getItems('org-123');\n  expect(result).toEqual([...]);\n});\n```\n\n### What to mock vs. keep real\n\nMock: network/HTTP clients, database access, filesystem, external APIs, non-deterministic calls.\n\nKeep real: pure helpers, formatters, utilities, logging calls, date helpers (unless determinism is needed).\n\n### Singleton testing\n\nFor singletons and cached instances, use Jest module isolation instead of exported reset functions:\n\n```ts\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetModules());\n\nit('test', async () => {\n  const { getService } = await import('./service');\n  // Fresh instance each time\n});\n```\n\nThis keeps production code clean and avoids `knip` warnings about unused exports.\n\n### Fixtures\n\nUse factory functions that accept `Partial<T>` overrides:\n\n```ts\nexport const subscriptionFixture = (\n  overrides: Partial<Subscription> = {}\n): Subscription => ({\n  id: 'sub_123',\n  status: 'active',\n  ...overrides,\n});\n```\n\n### Rules to remember\n\n- Never mock `@factory/logging` for assertions -- test behavior, not logging side effects\n- Never use `jest.doMock` or dynamic `import()` for mocking -- use static top-level `jest.mock()`\n- Never put `expect()` inside conditionals or try/catch (violates `jest/no-conditional-expect`)\n- Use ES6 `import` syntax, not `require()`\n- Use pragmatic typing in tests (`as any` for fakes is acceptable)\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `docs/unit-tests.md` | Full testing guidelines |\n| `docs/testing-react-hooks.md` | React hook testing patterns |\n| `docs/playwright-e2e-testing.md` | E2E test guide for `apps/web` |\n",
