            "content": "# Patterns and conventions\n\n## Error handling\n\nFactory uses a structured error system defined in `@factory/logging/errors`.\n\n### Core principles\n\n1. **Bubble by default** -- do not catch errors unless you have a concrete fallback\n2. **Use metadata-rich errors** -- throw `MetaError` for internal errors, `ResponseErrorXXX` for HTTP status codes\n3. **Never throw vanilla `Error`**\n4. **One or the other** -- if you call `logException`, handle the error locally (no rethrow). Otherwise, do not log, just rethrow.\n\n### Error class selection\n\n| Situation | Class |\n|---|---|\n| Internal bug / unexpected failure | `MetaError` |\n| Bad request / validation | `ResponseError400BadRequest` |\n| Unauthenticated | `ResponseError401Unauthorized` |\n| Permission denied | `ResponseError403Forbidden` |\n| Resource not found | `ResponseError404NotFound` |\n| Rate limited | `ResponseError429RateLimitExceeded` |\n| Service unavailable | `ResponseError503ServiceUnavailable` |\n\n### Logging rules\n\n- Use `logInfo` and `logWarn` for breadcrumbs before risky calls\n- Never call `logError` (it does not exist in the codebase)\n- Use `logException` only when swallowing an error with a fallback\n- Let middleware (`handleRouteMiddleware`) format HTTP responses from thrown errors\n\n## File organization\n\nESLint enforces strict file placement rules:\n\n| Content | Must live in |\n|---|---|\n| Enums | `enums.ts` |\n| Types and interfaces | `types.ts` |\n| Exported constants | `constants.ts` |\n| Error classes | `errors.ts` |\n\nThese files have import restrictions: `types.ts` can import from `enums.ts` and `schema.ts`; `constants.ts` can import from `types.ts`, `enums.ts`, `schema.ts`; and so on. Regular source files can import from any of them.\n\nNon-exported (private) types, enums, and constants can live anywhere.\n\n## Import conventions\n\n- Use absolute imports: `@factory/...` for packages, `@/...` for app-internal paths\n- No `require()` -- use ES6 `import` syntax\n- ESLint enforces these rules project-wide\n\n## UI conventions\n\nAll UI must use `@factory/core-ui` primitives. See [core-ui package](../packages/core-ui.md).\n\n- Use `Box`, `Flex`, `Grid` for layout (never raw `<div>`)\n- Use `Button`, `Input`, `Dropdown` for forms\n- Use `Header`, `Text` for typography\n- Use `colors.semantics` for colors (never hardcode hex values)\n\n## API type conventions\n\nAPI request/response types live in `packages/common/src/api/{service}/types.ts`. See `docs/examples/api-type-conventions.md` for the full pattern.\n\n## Feature flags\n\nFeature flags use Statsig. Definitions live in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`. See [Feature flags](../features/feature-flags.md) for usage patterns.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `docs/error-handling.md` | Full error handling guide |\n| `docs/file-organization.md` | ESLint file organization rules |\n| `docs/ui-development.md` | UI component rules |\n| `docs/frontend.md` | Frontend engineering conventions |\n| `packages/eslint-config/` | Custom ESLint rules implementation |\n",
