            "content": "# Tooling\n\n## Build system\n\nFactory uses npm workspaces with Turborepo for task orchestration. Turbo config lives in `turbo.json` at the repo root.\n\n### Key commands\n\n| Command | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| `npm run build` | Build all packages (outputs to `dist/`, `.next/`) |\n| `npm run fix` | ESLint auto-fix + Prettier formatting (preferred over `npm run lint`) |\n| `npm run lint` | ESLint only, no auto-fix |\n| `npm run typecheck` | TypeScript type checking across all packages |\n| `npm run test` | Run all test suites |\n| `npm run knip` | Detect unused exports |\n| `npm run clean` | Clear all caches (turbo, vite, next, dist, tsbuildinfo) |\n\n### Filtering\n\nAlways use `--` before `--filter` when running from the root:\n\n```bash\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common --filter=@factory/daemon-core\n```\n\nWithout `--`, npm eats the `--filter` flag and turbo runs everything.\n\n## Linting\n\n### ESLint\n\nThe shared configuration lives in `packages/eslint-config/`. It includes custom Factory rules:\n\n- `factory/enum-file-organization` -- enums must live in `enums.ts`\n- `factory/types-file-organization` -- exported types must live in `types.ts`\n- `factory/constants-file-organization` -- exported constants must live in `constants.ts`\n- `factory/errors-file-organization` -- error classes must live in `errors.ts`\n\nEach workspace can extend the shared config and add workspace-specific rules via its own `.eslintrc.js`.\n\n### Prettier\n\nConfig at the repo root (`.prettierrc`). Runs as part of `npm run fix`.\n\n### Stylelint\n\nFor CSS-in-JS validation: `npm run stylelint`. Config uses `postcss-styled-syntax`.\n\n## Husky (git hooks)\n\nHusky is configured via the `prepare` script. Pre-commit hooks run linting on staged files.\n\n## CI/CD workflows\n\nGitHub Actions workflows live in `.github/workflows/`. The main ones:\n\n| Workflow | Trigger | What it does |\n|---|---|---|\n| `basic-checks.yml` | PR | Runs lint, format, typecheck |\n| `test.yml` | PR | Runs unit tests |\n| `test-backend.yml` | PR | Backend-specific tests |\n| `test-cli.yml` | PR | CLI tests |\n| `playwright-e2e.yml` | PR | Playwright E2E tests |\n| `cli-e2e-tests.yml` | PR | CLI TUI E2E tests |\n| `eslint.yml` | PR | Targeted ESLint checks |\n| `typecheck.yml` | PR | TypeScript checks |\n| `knip.yml` | PR | Unused export detection |\n| `cli-release.yml` | release | Build and publish CLI binary |\n| `desktop-release.yml` | release | Build and publish desktop app |\n| `deploy-prod.yml` | merge to main | Deploy backend + web |\n| `release-cut.yml` | manual | Cut a release from dev to main |\n\n## Package management\n\nnpm 11.x is the package manager. The `bun.lock` file coexists for Bun-based apps (CLI, daemon), but `npm install` from the root handles all workspace dependencies.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `turbo.json` | Turborepo task definitions |\n| `package.json` (root) | Workspace definitions, shared scripts, dependency overrides |\n| `packages/eslint-config/` | Shared ESLint rules and custom Factory plugins |\n| `.github/workflows/` | CI/CD pipeline definitions |\n| `knip.json` | Unused export detection config |\n",
