            "content": "# Droid CLI\n\nThe Droid CLI (`apps/cli`) is the primary AI coding agent. Users type `droid` in their terminal to start an interactive session where the agent can read code, edit files, run commands, search the web, and use external tools through MCP.\n\n## Hybrid architecture\n\nThe CLI runs in two modes:\n\n1. **Interactive TUI** -- a full-screen React/Ink terminal application (the default when no arguments are given)\n2. **Headless commands** -- traditional subcommands via Commander.js (e.g., `droid exec`, `droid login`, `droid wiki-upload`)\n\nThe entry point (`src/index.ts`) detects how it was invoked and routes to the right mode.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/cli/src/\n├── index.ts              # Entry point, mode detection\n├── app.tsx               # React/Ink TUI root (~160KB, the largest file in the repo)\n├── main.tsx              # TUI initialization\n├── commands/             # Commander.js command definitions (~95 commands)\n├── components/           # Ink React components for TUI rendering\n├── hooks/                # React hooks for CLI state and side effects\n├── services/             # Business logic (auth, sessions, settings, etc.)\n├── agent/                # Agent loop and orchestration\n├── exec/                 # Execution runner (JSON-RPC streaming)\n├── tools/                # Tool definitions and implementations\n├── llm-proxy/            # Direct LLM provider integration\n├── mcp/                  # MCP client and tool discovery\n├── models/               # Data models\n├── i18n/                 # Internationalization\n├── prompt-tuning/        # Prompt optimization utilities\n├── utils/                # Utility functions (~197 files)\n├── acp/                  # Agent Control Protocol\n└── e2e-tests/            # TUI E2E test suites\n```\n\n## How sessions work\n\nWhen a user starts an interactive session:\n\n1. The CLI authenticates and initializes a session via the backend API\n2. In daemon mode, the CLI communicates over stdin/stdout JSON-RPC with the daemon\n3. In direct mode, the CLI connects directly to LLM providers\n4. The agent loop sends user messages to the LLM, receives tool calls, executes them, and streams results back\n\nSee [Architecture](../../overview/architecture.md) for the full session lifecycle.\n\n## Commands\n\nThe `src/commands/` directory has around 95 command files. Key commands:\n\n| Command | File | What it does |\n|---|---|---|\n| `exec` | `exec.ts` | Run the AI agent (main interactive loop) |\n| `login` / `logout` | `loginCommand.ts` / `logoutCommand.ts` | Auth management |\n| `sessions` | `sessions.ts` | List and manage sessions |\n| `wiki-upload` | `wiki-upload.ts` | Upload generated wiki to Factory |\n| `bug` | `bug.ts` | File bug reports with session context |\n| `update` | `update.ts` | Self-update the CLI binary |\n| `ssh` | `ssh.ts` | SSH into remote CDEs |\n| `mcp` | `mcp/` | MCP server management |\n| `model` | `model.ts` | Model selection and configuration |\n| `settings` | `settings.ts` | CLI configuration |\n\n## Distribution\n\nThe CLI is distributed as a Single Executable Application (SEA) built with Bun:\n\n- `npm run build` builds for the current platform\n- Platform-specific builds: `npm run build:sea:mac:arm64`, `npm run build:sea:linux:arm64`, etc.\n- Release pipeline: `.github/workflows/cli-release.yml`\n\n## Development\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup   # Build CLI and create dev wrappers\ndroid-dev                       # Run from source against hosted dev API\ndroid-localhost                  # Run from source against local API\n```\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/index.ts` | Entry point and mode routing |\n| `src/app.tsx` | TUI React root component |\n| `src/commands/exec.ts` | Main agent execution command |\n| `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.tsx` | JSON-RPC communication with daemon |\n| `src/agent/` | Agent loop and orchestration |\n| `src/tools/` | Tool definitions |\n| `src/mcp/` | MCP client integration |\n",
