            "content": "# Daemon (factoryd)\n\nThe Factory daemon (`apps/daemon`) is a long-running background process that manages Droid sessions and terminal access. It acts as a coordinator between the web/desktop frontend and the CLI processes running the agent loop.\n\n## What it does\n\n- Spawns and manages Droid CLI child processes (one per session)\n- Provides a WebSocket server with JSON-RPC 2.0 protocol\n- Routes messages between frontends and CLI processes\n- Manages terminal (PTY) sessions for remote command execution\n- Auto-updates itself on remote CDEs\n\n## Where it runs\n\n- **Local**: bundled with the Electron desktop app\n- **Remote**: downloaded from `downloads.factory.ai` onto cloud development environments (CDEs)\n- **Development**: started via `npm run dev:web` or `npm run dev:desktop` from the repo root\n\nDefault ports: 37643 (production), 41723 (development).\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/daemon/src/\n├── index.ts              # Entry point\n├── environment.ts        # Environment detection and config\n├── types.ts              # Type definitions\n├── services/\n│   └── UpdateService.ts  # Auto-update mechanism\n├── utils/                # Utility functions\n└── telemetry/            # Metrics and logging\n```\n\nThe daemon is thin. Most session management logic lives in `packages/daemon-core/`, and the JSON-RPC protocol schemas live in `packages/common/src/droid/`.\n\n## JSON-RPC API\n\n### Droid management\n\n| Method | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `daemon.initialize_session` | Initialize a new session and spawn its CLI process |\n| `daemon.load_session` | Load an existing session |\n| `daemon.add_user_message` | Send user messages to an active CLI process |\n| `daemon.interrupt_session` | Interrupt the agent execution (SIGINT to CLI) |\n\n### Terminal access\n\n| Method | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `daemon.create_terminal` | Create a new PTY session |\n| `daemon.write_terminal_data` | Send input to a terminal |\n| `daemon.resize_terminal` | Handle terminal window resizing |\n| `daemon.close_terminal` | Close a terminal session |\n| `daemon.list_terminals` | List active terminal sessions |\n\n### Health endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `GET /health` | Basic health check (uptime, session counts) |\n| `GET /status` | Detailed status (daemon info, terminals, WebSocket connections) |\n\n## Communication flow\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant FE as Frontend (Web/Desktop)\n    participant D as Daemon\n    participant CLI as Droid CLI Process\n\n    FE->>D: WebSocket connect\n    FE->>D: daemon.initialize_session\n    D->>CLI: spawn child process\n    D->>CLI: initialize (stdin JSON-RPC)\n    CLI-->>D: ready notification (stdout)\n    D-->>FE: session ready (WebSocket)\n    FE->>D: daemon.add_user_message\n    D->>CLI: forward message (stdin)\n    CLI-->>D: agent notifications (stdout)\n    D-->>FE: forward notifications (WebSocket)\n```\n\n## Development\n\n```bash\nnpm run dev:web    # Starts daemon alongside other services\n```\n\nDev logs go to `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` and `~/.factory-dev/logs/factoryd.log`.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/daemon/src/index.ts` | Daemon entry point |\n| `apps/daemon/src/services/UpdateService.ts` | Auto-update logic |\n| `packages/daemon-core/` | Core session management logic |\n| `packages/common/src/droid/` | JSON-RPC protocol schemas |\n",
