            "content": "# Signal\n\nSignal (`apps/signal`) is a GCP Cloud Function that analyzes Factory chat sessions for quality signals: friction points, delight moments, and session metadata. It uses OpenAI's Batch API to process sessions at scale, stores results in BigQuery, and sends daily reports to Slack.\n\n## Operating modes\n\n| Mode | What it does |\n|---|---|\n| `submit_batch` | Streams sessions from BigQuery, submits them to OpenAI Batch API |\n| `process_results` | Polls completed batches, validates results, inserts into BigQuery |\n| `daily_report` | Queries aggregated stats and sends a Slack summary |\n| `analyze_and_ticket` | Runs a Droid to find recurring friction patterns and create Linear tickets |\n\n## Signal types\n\n### Friction\n\nDetects obstacles users encounter: model errors, tool failures, repeated rephrasing (3+ messages restating the same request), escalation tone, platform confusion, abandoned tool flows, backtracking, and context churn. Each friction event has a severity (High/Medium/Low) and citations from the session.\n\n### Delight\n\nIdentifies positive moments: positive exclamations, first-attempt success (task completed in 2 or fewer turns), rapid tool confirmation, adoption milestones, and efficiency gain mentions. Each delight event has a confidence level.\n\n### Facets\n\nSession metadata extracted through a hybrid approach:\n- **LLM-derived**: language, intent categories, task description, outcome\n- **Computed**: turn count, duration, tool call stats\n- **From OTEL**: file extensions mapped to programming languages\n\n## Architecture\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    Scheduler[Cloud Scheduler] --> CF[Cloud Function]\n    CF --> OpenAI[OpenAI Batch API]\n    CF --> BQ[(BigQuery)]\n    CF --> Slack[Slack]\n    CF --> Linear[Linear]\n```\n\nCore signal definitions (prompts, schemas, mappers) are extracted to `packages/signal-core/` for shared use by `apps/admin`.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/signal/src/` | Cloud Function entry points and processing logic |\n| `packages/signal-core/` | Shared signal definitions, prompts, and schemas |\n| `apps/signal/deploy.sh` | Deployment script for GCP |\n| `apps/signal/DEPLOY.md` | Deployment documentation |\n",
