            "content": "# Relay\n\nRelay (`apps/relay`) is a WebSocket proxy that bridges browser clients to BYOI (Bring Your Own Infrastructure) computers. It multiplexes multiple client connections onto a single computer connection per `computerId`.\n\n## Routes\n\n| Endpoint | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `WS /v0/computer/:computerId/agent` | Daemon connects here (one per computer) |\n| `WS /v0/computer/:computerId/client` | Browser clients connect here (N per computer) |\n| `GET /health` | Health check |\n\nClients receive a 503 if the target computer is not connected. `computerId` must be a valid UUID.\n\n## How it works\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    C1[Browser Client 1] --> R[Relay]\n    C2[Browser Client 2] --> R\n    R --> D[Daemon on BYOI Computer]\n```\n\nThe relay uses a channel-based architecture:\n- `ChannelSession` -- manages a single computer-to-clients mapping\n- `ChannelRegistry` -- tracks all active channels\n\n## Testing\n\n```bash\n# All tests (unit + integration)\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/relay\n\n# Unit tests (Jest, mock sockets)\nnpm run test:unit -- --filter=@factory/relay\n\n# Integration tests (Bun test runner, real WebSocket connections)\nnpm run test:integration -- --filter=@factory/relay\n\n# E2E smoke test (spawns real processes)\ncd apps/relay && bun scripts/smoke.ts\n```\n\n## Environment variables\n\n| Variable | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_PORT` | `8080` | Listen port |\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_HOST` | `0.0.0.0` | Bind host |\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_DEBUG` | `false` | Debug logging |\n\n## Deployment\n\nDeployed to AWS via `.github/workflows/deploy-relay-aws.yml`.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/relay/src/` | Relay server implementation |\n| `apps/relay/scripts/` | Mock client/computer scripts for testing |\n",
