            "content": "# droid-core\n\n`@factory/droid-core` (`packages/droid-core`) is the AI agent's core library. It defines how the Droid agent interacts with LLM providers, processes tool calls, manages message streams, and orchestrates the agent loop. Both the CLI (`apps/cli`) and the daemon (`apps/daemon`) depend on it.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/droid-core/src/\n├── api/              # API client utilities\n├── automations/      # Automation workflows\n├── core/             # Core agent abstractions\n├── droids/           # Droid configuration and management\n├── feature-flags/    # Feature flag integration\n├── llms/             # LLM provider adapters\n├── machine-connection/ # Remote machine connectivity\n├── messages/         # Message types and processing\n├── prompts/          # System prompts and prompt templates\n├── streaming/        # Response streaming utilities\n├── tools/            # Tool definitions and execution\n└── test-utils/       # Test helpers\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Abstraction | Location | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| LLM adapters | `src/llms/` | Adapter layer for different LLM providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, etc.) |\n| Tool definitions | `src/tools/` | Schema and implementation of tools the agent can call |\n| Message handling | `src/messages/` | Message type definitions, serialization, and processing |\n| Streaming | `src/streaming/` | Streaming response handling for LLM outputs |\n| Prompt management | `src/prompts/` | System prompts, prompt templates, and prompt construction |\n| Droid configuration | `src/droids/` | Custom droid definitions and configuration loading |\n| Automations | `src/automations/` | Pre-defined automation workflows |\n\n## How the agent loop works\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    UserMessage[User Message] --> BuildPrompt[Build Prompt]\n    BuildPrompt --> LLMCall[LLM API Call]\n    LLMCall --> StreamResponse[Stream Response]\n    StreamResponse --> ParseToolCalls{Tool Calls?}\n    ParseToolCalls -->|Yes| ExecuteTools[Execute Tools]\n    ExecuteTools --> AppendResults[Append Tool Results]\n    AppendResults --> LLMCall\n    ParseToolCalls -->|No| ReturnResponse[Return Final Response]\n```\n\nThe agent loop is iterative: send messages to the LLM, parse the response for tool calls, execute them, append results, and loop until the LLM returns a final text response with no tool calls.\n\n## LLM provider integration\n\nThe `src/llms/` directory contains adapters for multiple LLM providers. Each adapter normalizes the provider's API into a common interface that the agent loop consumes. The CLI can call LLM providers directly or route through the backend's LLM proxy endpoints.\n\n## Tool system\n\nTools are the agent's capabilities (Read, Edit, Execute, Grep, etc.). Each tool has:\n\n- A JSON schema defining its parameters\n- An execution function that performs the action\n- Metadata (name, description) that the LLM uses to decide when to call it\n\nTool definitions in `src/tools/` are the canonical source. The CLI's `src/tools/` directory extends these with CLI-specific implementations.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/llms/` | LLM provider adapters |\n| `src/tools/` | Tool definitions and schemas |\n| `src/messages/` | Message types and processing |\n| `src/streaming/` | Response streaming |\n| `src/prompts/` | System prompts and templates |\n",
