            "content": "# frontend\n\n`@factory/frontend` (`packages/frontend`) contains the shared React code used by both the web and desktop applications. It is the primary location for frontend features, hooks, services, and views.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/frontend/src/\n├── api/              # API client functions\n├── app/              # App-level setup and providers\n├── auth/             # Authentication (WorkOS AuthKit)\n├── errors/           # Error boundary and error handling\n├── features/         # Feature modules (the bulk of the code)\n├── hooks/            # Shared React hooks\n├── layouts/          # Page layout components\n├── router/           # Routing configuration\n├── services/         # Service layer (session management, etc.)\n├── types/            # Shared TypeScript types\n├── utils/            # Utility functions\n└── views/            # Page-level view components\n```\n\n## Feature modules\n\nThe `src/features/` directory contains most of the frontend business logic, organized by domain:\n\n| Feature | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `session/` | Session management, message display, chat interface |\n| `integrations/` | GitHub, Linear, Slack integration UIs |\n| `settings/` | User and org settings |\n| `wiki/` | Wiki viewer |\n| `billing/` | Billing and usage display |\n| `agent/` | Agent-related UI (readiness, tools) |\n| `terminal/` | Terminal UI component |\n| `tags/` | Tagging system |\n| `timeline/` | Timeline display |\n| `usage/` | Usage tracking display |\n| `updater/` | Update notification UI |\n| `documents/` | Document management |\n\n## Session management\n\nThe session service layer (`src/services/session/`) contains `DaemonSessionController.ts`, which manages the WebSocket connection to the daemon and handles all session lifecycle events. This is one of the most critical files in the frontend codebase.\n\n## State management\n\nThe frontend uses Redux Toolkit for state management:\n\n- Select state precisely: `useSelector((state: RootState) => state.assembly.messageTree)`, not the whole slice\n- Prefer local state (`useState`, router params) over Redux when possible\n- Top-level page components can delegate state from Redux\n\n## UI rules\n\nAll components must use `@factory/core-ui` primitives. See [core-ui](./core-ui.md) and [Patterns and conventions](../how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md).\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | WebSocket session management |\n| `src/features/` | Feature modules (session, integrations, settings, etc.) |\n| `src/auth/` | WorkOS authentication |\n| `src/router/` | Route definitions |\n| `src/index.ts` | Package entry point and exports |\n",
