            "content": "# common\n\n`@factory/common` (`packages/common`) is the shared type library used across the entire monorepo. It defines API contracts, protocol schemas, enums, and constants that all apps and packages import.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/common/src/\n├── agent/            # Agent-related types\n├── agentReadiness/   # Readiness check types\n├── api/              # API request/response types (organized by service)\n├── automations/      # Automation types\n├── billing/          # Billing types\n├── cli/              # CLI-specific types\n├── daemon/           # Daemon protocol types and schemas\n├── desktop/          # Desktop app types\n├── documents/        # Document types\n├── droid/            # Droid protocol (enums, schemas, notifications)\n├── events/           # Event types\n├── feature-flags/    # Feature flag constants and types\n├── images/           # Image-related types\n├── integrations/     # Integration types (GitHub, Linear, etc.)\n├── llm/              # LLM-related types\n├── memory/           # Memory types\n├── node/             # Node types\n├── organization/     # Organization types\n├── policy/           # Policy types\n├── relay/            # Relay protocol types\n├── repositories/     # Repository types\n├── security/         # Security types\n├── session/          # Session types (the largest subdirectory)\n├── sessionV2/        # Session v2 types\n├── settings/         # Settings types\n├── shared/           # Shared utilities\n├── tags/             # Tag types\n├── terminal/         # Terminal types\n├── timeline/         # Timeline types\n├── tools/            # Tool types\n├── ui/               # UI types\n├── updater/          # Updater types\n├── usage/            # Usage types\n├── wiki/             # Wiki types\n└── workspaces/       # Workspace types\n```\n\n## API type conventions\n\nAPI types follow a strict convention. For each backend service, types live in `src/api/{service}/types.ts`:\n\n```ts\n// packages/common/src/api/sessions/types.ts\nexport interface CreateSessionRequest {\n  name: string;\n  repositoryId: string;\n}\n\nexport interface CreateSessionResponse {\n  sessionId: string;\n}\n```\n\nSee `docs/examples/api-type-conventions.md` for the full pattern.\n\n## Droid protocol schemas\n\nThe `src/droid/` directory is critical for the daemon-CLI communication protocol:\n\n- `enums.ts` -- `SessionNotificationType` and other protocol enums\n- `schemas/` -- JSON-RPC message schemas for CLI notifications and daemon requests\n\nWhen adding a new notification type, you must update both the enum and the schema here, then add a handler in the frontend's `DaemonSessionController.ts`.\n\n## Feature flag constants\n\nFeature flag definitions live in `src/feature-flags/constants.ts`. Each flag has a display name, Statsig name, and default value. See [Feature flags](../features/feature-flags.md).\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/droid/enums.ts` | Protocol notification type enums |\n| `src/droid/schemas/` | JSON-RPC message schemas |\n| `src/session/` | Session type definitions |\n| `src/api/` | API request/response types |\n| `src/feature-flags/constants.ts` | Feature flag definitions |\n",
