            "content": "# Feature flags\n\nFactory uses Statsig for feature flag management. Flags gate new features for gradual rollout, A/B testing, and organization-level targeting.\n\n## Adding a new flag\n\n1. Create the gate in the Statsig console (https://console.statsig.com/), using `snake_case` naming\n2. Add the definition to `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`:\n\n```ts\nexport const FactoryFeatureFlags = {\n  NewFeature: {\n    displayName: 'My New Feature',\n    statsigName: 'my_new_feature',\n    defaultValue: false,\n  },\n};\n```\n\n## Using flags in React\n\n```ts\nimport { useFeatureFlagValue } from '@/featureFlags';\nimport { FactoryFeatureFlags } from '@factory/common/feature-flags';\n\nfunction MyComponent() {\n  const isEnabled = useFeatureFlagValue(FactoryFeatureFlags.NewFeature);\n  return isEnabled ? <NewFeature /> : null;\n}\n```\n\n## Using flags on the server\n\n```ts\nimport { getFeatureFlagInstance } from '@/features/feature-flags/server';\nimport { FactoryFeatureFlags } from '@factory/common/feature-flags';\n\nconst featureFlags = await getFeatureFlagInstance();\nconst isEnabled = await featureFlags.checkFlag(\n  FactoryFeatureFlags.NewFeature,\n  firestoreOrgId\n);\n```\n\nThe server-side client uses a singleton pattern (`once()` wrapper) and has a 5-second initialization timeout. On failure, it falls back to the flag's `defaultValue`.\n\n## Environment tiers\n\n| Factory env | Statsig tier |\n|---|---|\n| localhost | development |\n| development | staging |\n| production | production |\n\n## Dev menu\n\nWhen running locally or in dev, a \"DEV\" menu at the bottom-right of the screen lets you view and override feature flags for your browser session.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts` | Flag definitions |\n| `apps/backend/src/features/feature-flags/server.ts` | Server-side flag evaluation |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/` | Frontend flag hooks |\n",
