            "content": "# Integrations\n\nFactory connects to several third-party services. Integration logic is split between the backend (API endpoints and webhooks) and the frontend (UI for connecting and managing integrations).\n\n## Supported integrations\n\n| Service | Purpose | Backend location | Frontend location |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| GitHub | Repository access, PR management, webhooks | `apps/backend/src/app/api/integrations/` | `packages/frontend/src/features/integrations/` |\n| Linear | Issue tracking, ticket creation | `apps/backend/src/services/` | `packages/frontend/src/features/integrations/` |\n| Slack | Notifications, daily reports | `apps/backend/src/services/` | `packages/frontend/src/features/integrations/` |\n| WorkOS | Authentication, SSO, organizations | `apps/backend/src/services/` | `packages/frontend/src/auth/` |\n| Orb | Billing, subscriptions, usage metering | `apps/backend/src/services/` | `packages/frontend/src/features/billing/` |\n\n## Integration types in common\n\nIntegration-related types live in `packages/common/src/integrations/`. Each integration has its own subdirectory with type definitions that both the backend and frontend import.\n\n## Webhook handling\n\nIncoming webhooks from GitHub, Linear, and other services hit endpoints in `apps/backend/src/app/api/webhooks/`. The backend validates signatures, processes events, and updates Firestore accordingly.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/common/src/integrations/` | Integration type definitions |\n| `apps/backend/src/app/api/integrations/` | Backend integration endpoints |\n| `apps/backend/src/app/api/webhooks/` | Webhook handlers |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/integrations/` | Integration UI |\n| `packages/services/src/integrations/` | Integration service layer |\n",
