            "content": "# Observability\n\nFactory uses a layered observability stack: structured logging via `@factory/logging`, metrics via Axiom, error tracking via Sentry, and call instrumentation for external dependencies.\n\n## Logging\n\nAll logging goes through `@factory/logging`:\n\n```ts\nimport { logInfo, logWarn, logException } from '@factory/logging';\n\nlogInfo('Processing file', { fileName, fileSize });\nlogWarn('Rate limit approaching', { currentUsage, limit });\nlogException(error, 'Failed to process request', { userId });\n```\n\nRules:\n- `logInfo` for informational breadcrumbs\n- `logWarn` for non-breaking issues\n- `logException` for errors you are handling locally (never followed by `throw`)\n- `LogOnce` class to prevent log spam in loops\n- No `logError` function exists; do not look for one\n- Secrets are scrubbed automatically\n\n## Metrics\n\n```ts\nimport { Metrics } from '@factory/logging';\n\nMetrics.addToCounter('feature_usage_count', 1, { feature: 'code_generation' });\nMetrics.setGauge('active_sessions_count', 42);\nMetrics.recordHistogram('file_processing_time_ms', 1250, { fileType: 'typescript' });\n```\n\nInclude the base unit in metric names (e.g., `_ms`, `_bytes`, `_count`).\n\n## External call instrumentation\n\nFor HTTP requests to external services:\n\n```ts\nimport { fetchWithMetrics } from '@/app/api/_utils/metrics';\nimport { ExternalDependency } from '@/app/api/_utils/metrics/enums';\n\nconst response = await fetchWithMetrics(fetch, ExternalDependency.OPENAI, { labels: { model } }, url, options);\n```\n\nFor non-HTTP calls:\n\n```ts\nimport { callWithMetrics } from '@/app/api/_utils/metrics';\n\nconst result = await callWithMetrics(processDocument, ExternalDependency.WEAVIATE, { labels }, docId);\n```\n\nNew external services must be added to the `ExternalDependency` enum in `apps/backend/src/app/api/_utils/metrics/enums.ts`.\n\n## Error tracking (Sentry)\n\nSentry is configured in each app:\n- `apps/backend/src/sentry.*.config.ts`\n- `apps/cli/src/sentry.config.ts`\n- `apps/daemon/src/sentry.config.ts`\n\nThe Sentry 0 policy means all exceptions should be resolved promptly. Use `MetaError` and `ResponseErrorXXX` classes for proper categorization.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/logging/` | Logging, metrics, and error class implementations |\n| `apps/backend/src/app/api/_utils/metrics/` | Call instrumentation utilities |\n| `docs/metrics-logging.md` | Full metrics and logging guide |\n| `docs/error-handling.md` | Error handling conventions |\n",
