            "content": "# MCP and tools\n\nThe Droid agent's capabilities come from its tool system. Tools are actions the agent can take: reading files, editing code, executing commands, searching, and more. MCP (Model Context Protocol) extends this system by letting external servers provide additional tools.\n\n## Built-in tools\n\nTool definitions live in `packages/droid-core/src/tools/`. The CLI extends these with implementations in `apps/cli/src/tools/`. Core built-in tools include:\n\n| Tool | Description |\n|---|---|\n| Read | Read file contents |\n| Edit | Find-and-replace text in files |\n| Create | Create new files |\n| Execute | Run shell commands |\n| Grep | Search file contents with ripgrep |\n| Glob | Search for files by path pattern |\n| LS | List directory contents |\n| WebSearch | Search the web |\n| FetchUrl | Fetch and parse web pages |\n| Task | Spawn a subagent for parallel work |\n| TodoWrite | Manage a structured task list |\n| AskUser | Ask the user structured questions |\n\nEach tool has:\n- A JSON schema defining its parameters (used by the LLM to understand what the tool accepts)\n- An execution function\n- Metadata (name, description, risk level)\n\n## MCP (Model Context Protocol)\n\nMCP lets the CLI discover and use tools from external servers. The CLI acts as an MCP client that connects to MCP servers (local processes or remote endpoints).\n\nMCP integration code lives in:\n- `apps/cli/src/mcp/` -- MCP client implementation\n- `packages/droid-core/src/tools/` -- Tool integration layer\n- `packages/mcp/` -- MCP protocol utilities\n\nUsers manage MCP servers through the `droid mcp` command group:\n\n```bash\ndroid mcp install <server>   # Install an MCP server\ndroid mcp list               # List installed servers\ndroid mcp configure          # Configure server settings\n```\n\n## Tool execution flow\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    LLM[LLM Response] --> Parse[Parse Tool Calls]\n    Parse --> Builtin{Built-in Tool?}\n    Builtin -->|Yes| ExecBuiltin[Execute Built-in]\n    Builtin -->|No| MCP{MCP Tool?}\n    MCP -->|Yes| ExecMCP[Call MCP Server]\n    MCP -->|No| Error[Unknown Tool Error]\n    ExecBuiltin --> Result[Tool Result]\n    ExecMCP --> Result\n    Result --> AppendToMessages[Append to Messages]\n```\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/droid-core/src/tools/` | Tool definitions and schemas |\n| `apps/cli/src/tools/` | CLI-specific tool implementations |\n| `apps/cli/src/mcp/` | MCP client |\n| `apps/cli/src/commands/mcp/` | MCP management commands |\n| `packages/mcp/` | MCP protocol utilities |\n",
