            "content": "# Sessions\n\nA session is the core unit of interaction in Factory. It represents a single conversation between a user and the Droid agent. Sessions span all three layers: frontend, daemon, and CLI.\n\n## Session lifecycle\n\n```mermaid\nstateDiagram-v2\n    [*] --> Initializing: User starts session\n    Initializing --> Active: CLI spawned and ready\n    Active --> Active: User sends message / Agent responds\n    Active --> Interrupted: User interrupts\n    Interrupted --> Active: User sends new message\n    Active --> Ended: User ends session / Agent completes\n    Ended --> [*]\n```\n\n## How it works across layers\n\n### Frontend (web/desktop)\n\nThe `DaemonSessionController` in `packages/frontend/src/services/session/` manages:\n- WebSocket connection to the daemon\n- Sending JSON-RPC requests (initialize, add message, interrupt)\n- Receiving and processing notifications (agent messages, tool calls, status updates)\n- Redux state updates for the UI\n\n### Daemon\n\nThe daemon (`apps/daemon` + `packages/daemon-core`) handles:\n- Spawning a CLI child process for each session\n- Routing messages between the frontend WebSocket and the CLI stdin/stdout\n- Session lifecycle management (initialize, load, interrupt, cleanup)\n- Terminal (PTY) session management\n\n### CLI\n\nThe CLI (`apps/cli`) handles:\n- Running the agent loop (send messages to LLM, execute tool calls, loop)\n- Communicating with the daemon via stdin/stdout JSON-RPC\n- Direct LLM provider calls (or proxied through the backend)\n- Tool execution in the local filesystem\n\n## Session storage\n\nSessions and their messages are stored in Firebase Firestore. The backend provides CRUD endpoints, and the frontend fetches session data through the services layer.\n\nSession types are defined in `packages/common/src/session/`, which is the largest subdirectory in the common package.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | Frontend session management |\n| `packages/daemon-core/` | Daemon session lifecycle |\n| `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.tsx` | CLI JSON-RPC execution |\n| `packages/common/src/session/` | Session type definitions |\n| `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` | Session notification types |\n| `packages/services/src/session/` | Session service layer |\n",
