            "content": "# Security\n\n## Authentication\n\nFactory uses WorkOS AuthKit for authentication:\n- SSO support via WorkOS\n- Organization-based multi-tenancy\n- Token validation in backend middleware (`apps/backend/src/middleware.ts`)\n- Frontend auth handled by `packages/frontend/src/auth/`\n\n## Authorization\n\n- Backend routes are protected by middleware that validates auth tokens and checks organization membership\n- API routes check user permissions before performing operations\n- Feature flags can gate access to features at the organization level\n\n## Secrets management\n\n- Environment variables are stored in `.env` files (not committed) and deployed via platform-specific mechanisms (Vercel, GCP, AWS)\n- The `@factory/logging` package automatically scrubs secrets from log output\n- The `@factory/environment` package provides strongly-typed access to env vars, replacing raw `process.env` usage\n\n## Tool execution safety\n\nThe Droid CLI's Execute tool has a risk-level system:\n- **Low risk**: read-only commands (ls, cat, git status)\n- **Medium risk**: file modifications, package installs\n- **High risk**: destructive operations, remote access, sudo\n\nUsers can configure approval behavior through CLI settings.\n\n## Firebase security\n\nFirestore security rules are defined in `firestore.rules` at the repo root. Storage rules are in `storage.rules`.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/backend/src/middleware.ts` | Auth middleware |\n| `packages/frontend/src/auth/` | Frontend auth integration |\n| `packages/common/src/security/` | Security type definitions |\n| `packages/environment/` | Typed environment variable access |\n| `firestore.rules` | Firestore security rules |\n| `storage.rules` | Firebase Storage rules |\n",
