          "input": {
            "content": "# Configuration\n\n## Root config files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `package.json` | Workspace definitions, shared scripts, dependency overrides |\n| `turbo.json` | Turborepo task configuration |\n| `tsconfig.json` | Root TypeScript config |\n| `knip.json` | Unused export detection config |\n| `firebase.json` | Firebase project configuration |\n| `firestore.rules` | Firestore security rules |\n| `firestore.indexes.json` | Firestore index definitions |\n| `storage.rules` | Firebase Storage security rules |\n| `.nvmrc` | Node.js version (18.x) |\n\n## Per-app environment variables\n\nEach app has environment files per deployment target:\n\n| File | Environment |\n|---|---|\n| `.env.production` | Production |\n| `.env.development` | Dev/staging |\n| `.env.localhost` | Local development |\n| `.env.staging` | Staging |\n| `.env` | Default/shared |\n\nThe backend's `.env.example` lists required variables. Sensitive values are not committed.\n\n## ESLint configuration\n\n- Root config: each workspace has its own `.eslintrc.js` or `.eslintrc.cjs`\n- Shared base: `packages/eslint-config/`\n- Custom rules: `factory/enum-file-organization`, `factory/types-file-organization`, etc.\n\n## TypeScript configuration\n\n- Root `tsconfig.json` with shared compiler options\n- Each workspace extends it with `tsconfig.json`\n- Some workspaces have `tsconfig.build.json` for production builds\n\n## Daemon ports\n\n| Environment | Port |\n|---|---|\n| Production | 37643 |\n| Development | 41723 |\n\n## CLI environment detection\n\nThe CLI detects its environment from the binary name and environment variables:\n- `droid` -- production\n- `droid-dev` -- development (uses hosted dev API)\n- `droid-localhost` -- local (uses local API at localhost:3000)\n\nConfiguration is in `apps/cli/src/environment.ts` and `apps/daemon/src/environment.ts`.\n",
