            "content": "# Dependencies\n\nMajor external dependencies used across the Factory monorepo.\n\n## Runtime and build\n\n| Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| Node.js | 18.x | Primary runtime for backend, web, desktop |\n| Bun | 1.3.x | Runtime for CLI and daemon |\n| npm | 11.x | Package manager |\n| Turborepo | 2.6.x | Monorepo build orchestration |\n| TypeScript | -- | Type system (used everywhere) |\n\n## Frontend\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| React 19 | UI framework (web, desktop, CLI via Ink) |\n| Vite | Build tool for web and desktop |\n| Next.js 15 | Framework for backend and admin |\n| Electron | Desktop app shell |\n| Electron Forge | Desktop app packaging |\n| styled-components | CSS-in-JS styling |\n| Redux Toolkit | State management (frontend) |\n| Ink 6.7 | React renderer for terminal (CLI) |\n| Commander.js | CLI command parsing |\n| Recharts | Charting library |\n| CodeMirror | Code editor components |\n| Lucide React | Icon library |\n\n## Auth and billing\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| WorkOS AuthKit | Authentication, SSO, organizations |\n| Orb Billing | Subscription and usage-based billing |\n| Statsig | Feature flag management |\n\n## AI and LLM\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| OpenAI SDK | OpenAI API client |\n| `@google/genai` | Google AI (Gemini) client |\n| `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` | MCP protocol implementation |\n\n## Infrastructure\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| Firebase/Firestore | Primary data store |\n| Sentry | Error tracking |\n| Axiom | Log aggregation and metrics |\n| AWS (via OpenTofu) | Cloud infrastructure |\n| GCP | Cloud Functions (Signal), BigQuery |\n| Vercel | Backend and web hosting |\n| E2B | Cloud development environments |\n\n## Testing\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| Jest | Unit testing (backend, CLI, packages) |\n| Vitest | Unit testing (web, desktop) |\n| Playwright | Browser E2E testing |\n| `@microsoft/tui-test` | Terminal UI E2E testing |\n\n## Dev tooling\n\n| Dependency | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| ESLint | Linting with custom Factory rules |\n| Prettier | Code formatting |\n| Husky | Git hooks |\n| knip | Unused export detection |\n| Stylelint | CSS-in-JS validation |\n",
