            "content": "# Daemon (apps/daemon)\n\nActive contributors: factory-sherry, factory-jerry, Luke Alvoeiro, David Vendrow, factory-daniel, shashank-factory, Alvin Sng, Arman Bolat\n\n## Purpose\n\nfactoryd is the background daemon that manages droid agent processes and provides terminal access across all user sessions. It runs on both local machines (bundled inside the Electron desktop app) and remote cloud development environments. The daemon acts as the coordination layer between the Factory web/desktop clients and the per-session droid CLI processes, bridging WebSocket JSON-RPC from the frontend to stdin/stdout JSON-RPC on each spawned droid process.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/daemon/\n├── src/\n│   ├── index.ts              # Entry point: arg parsing, env init, auto-update, DaemonCore startup\n│   ├── constants.ts          # Default host binding\n│   ├── environment.ts        # Env var loading and DaemonEnvironment type\n│   ├── types.ts              # App-level types\n│   ├── embed-native-libs.ts  # Embeds bun-pty native bindings into the SEA bundle\n│   ├── sentry.config.ts      # Sentry error reporting setup\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   └── UpdateService.ts  # Auto-update logic (downloads + installs new daemon builds)\n│   ├── telemetry/\n│   │   └── DaemonOtelTracingClient.ts  # OpenTelemetry tracing adapter\n│   └── utils/\n│       ├── command-wrapper.ts        # SIGINT/SIGTERM handling\n│       ├── daemon-telemetry-client.ts # Analytics/telemetry helpers\n│       ├── exit-with-code.ts\n│       └── parent-health-monitor.ts  # Detects parent process death (desktop crash)\n\npackages/daemon-core/src/\n├── index.ts              # DaemonCore class: start() / stop() / isRunning()\n├── types.ts              # DaemonCoreConfig\n├── constants.ts\n├── server/\n│   ├── daemon-server.ts           # Starts HTTP + WebSocket server\n│   ├── web-socket-server.ts       # WebSocket server, connection lifecycle\n│   ├── web-socket-request-router.ts # Routes JSON-RPC method names to handlers\n│   ├── websocket-auth-adapter.ts  # Authenticates WS connections against backend\n│   ├── tunnel-handler.ts          # Relay/tunnel support for remote CDEs\n│   ├── code-server-proxy.ts       # code-server (VS Code) HTTP proxy\n│   └── handlers/                  # Per-method JSON-RPC handler modules\n├── droid/\n│   └── droid-registry.ts          # Spawns/tracks droid CLI child processes per session\n├── terminal/                       # PTY-based terminal session management\n├── relay/                          # WebSocket relay protocol for remote machines\n├── automations/                    # Automation-related handlers\n├── services/                       # Shared services (auth token cache, etc.)\n└── utils/\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Type / File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/index.ts` → `DaemonCore` | Top-level class; owns start/stop lifecycle of the daemon server |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/daemon-server.ts` → `DaemonServer` | Combines HTTP health endpoints and WebSocket server into one process |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/web-socket-server.ts` → `WebSocketServer` | Accepts WS connections, reads JSON-RPC frames, dispatches to router |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/web-socket-request-router.ts` | Routes `daemon.*` method names to handler functions |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/websocket-auth-adapter.ts` | Validates JWT tokens on each new WS connection |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/droid/droid-registry.ts` → `DroidRegistry` | Spawns droid CLI processes, wires up stdin/stdout JSON-RPC bridge |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/` | PTY session management (create, write, resize, close) |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/relay/` | Relay protocol for remote machine connectivity |\n| `apps/daemon/src/services/UpdateService.ts` → `UpdateService` | Checks `downloads.factory.ai` for new daemon builds and self-updates |\n| `apps/daemon/src/utils/parent-health-monitor.ts` → `ParentHealthMonitor` | Polls parent PID; shuts down daemon if Electron/launcher dies |\n| `apps/daemon/src/environment.ts` → `DaemonEnvironment` | Resolves environment variables into strongly typed config |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Session lifecycle\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Client as Web/Desktop Client\n    participant WS as WebSocket Server\n    participant Router as Request Router\n    participant Registry as DroidRegistry\n    participant Droid as droid CLI process\n\n    Client->>WS: WebSocket connect + JWT token\n    WS->>WS: Authenticate token (websocket-auth-adapter)\n    Client->>WS: daemon.initialize_session {cwd, mcpServers}\n    WS->>Router: route method\n    Router->>Registry: spawnDroid(sessionId, config)\n    Registry->>Droid: spawn() via stdin/stdout JSON-RPC\n\n    Client->>WS: daemon.add_user_message {sessionId, text}\n    WS->>Router: route\n    Router->>Registry: forwardToSession(sessionId, message)\n    Registry->>Droid: write to stdin\n\n    Droid->>Registry: JSON-RPC notification (tool result, message, etc.)\n    Registry->>WS: daemon.session_notification\n    WS->>Client: forward notification\n\n    Client->>WS: daemon.interrupt_session\n    WS->>Registry: interruptSession(sessionId)\n    Registry->>Droid: SIGINT\n\n    Client->>WS: disconnect\n    WS->>Registry: cleanup sessions for connection\n```\n\n### Startup sequence\n\n1. `apps/daemon/src/index.ts` loads `.env` files and initialises environment\n2. Telemetry (`DaemonTelemetryClient`) is set up first so errors during update can be captured\n3. `UpdateService.runAutoUpdate()` checks `downloads.factory.ai` and replaces the binary if a newer version is available (skipped when `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=true`)\n4. Commander parses CLI args (`--port`, `--host`, `--unix`, `--droid-path`, `--debug`)\n5. Shell environment is loaded with `loadShellEnvironment()` to resolve `PATH` and shell init paths\n6. `DaemonCore` is instantiated with the merged config and `start()` is called\n7. `ParentHealthMonitor` begins polling the parent PID; kills daemon if parent dies\n\n### Port binding\n\nProduction port: **37643**. Dev port: **41723**. Binding the port prevents multiple instances. The `--unix` flag switches to a Unix domain socket, which enables zero-downtime restarts via a systemd socket proxy.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **Web/Desktop clients** — connect over WebSocket JSON-RPC 2.0 (see `daemon.*` methods in README)\n- **Backend API** — daemon-core calls `apps/backend` REST API to validate session tokens and persist session data\n- **droid CLI** — daemon spawns `droid` (or `droid-dev` in development) as a child process and bridges JSON-RPC via stdin/stdout\n- **Relay** (`apps/relay`) — for remote CDEs the frontend connects to the relay which proxies traffic to the daemon\n- **Factory downloads** — `UpdateService` fetches new daemon builds from `downloads.factory.ai`\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n- **Add a new JSON-RPC method:** add a handler in `packages/daemon-core/src/server/handlers/` and register it in the router\n- **Change session spawning behaviour:** `packages/daemon-core/src/droid/droid-registry.ts`\n- **Change terminal behaviour:** `packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/`\n- **Change auto-update logic:** `apps/daemon/src/services/UpdateService.ts`\n- **Add new environment variables:** `apps/daemon/src/environment.ts` → `DaemonEnvironment`\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/daemon/src/index.ts` | Entry point — init, auto-update, CLI args, DaemonCore wiring |\n| `apps/daemon/src/environment.ts` | Environment variable resolution |\n| `apps/daemon/src/services/UpdateService.ts` | Self-update mechanism |\n| `apps/daemon/src/utils/parent-health-monitor.ts` | Parent process death detection |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/index.ts` | `DaemonCore` class — start/stop lifecycle |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/daemon-server.ts` | HTTP + WebSocket server setup |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/web-socket-server.ts` | WS connection handling |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/web-socket-request-router.ts` | JSON-RPC method routing |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/websocket-auth-adapter.ts` | JWT auth on WS connections |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/droid/droid-registry.ts` | Droid process spawning and tracking |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/` | PTY-based terminal sessions |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/tunnel-handler.ts` | Relay tunnel for remote CDEs |\n",
