            "content": "# Backend (apps/backend)\n\nActive contributors: Alvin Sng, factory-octavian, factory-sherry, Nikita Lilichenko, Leo Tchourakov, jonathan-factory, factory-jerry, Andrei Savin\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/backend` is the central REST API for the Factory platform, built on Next.js 15 App Router. All product surfaces — web, desktop, CLI, admin, and IDE extensions — talk to this service for session management, authentication, billing, LLM proxying, and integrations. It is hosted on Vercel and connected to a Firebase/Firestore database and a set of third-party services.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/backend/src/\n├── app/\n│   ├── api/                    # Next.js route handlers (REST endpoints)\n│   │   ├── admin/              # Admin-only endpoints\n│   │   ├── auth/               # Auth callback, session tokens\n│   │   ├── billing/            # Billing portal, plan info\n│   │   ├── bug-reports/        # Bug report ingestion\n│   │   ├── cli/                # CLI download + update manifest\n│   │   ├── cron/               # Scheduled background jobs\n│   │   ├── daemon/             # Daemon download + update manifest\n│   │   ├── desktop/            # Desktop update manifest\n│   │   ├── e2e/                # E2E test helpers\n│   │   ├── feature-flags/      # Statsig flag evaluation\n│   │   ├── github/             # GitHub OAuth + webhooks\n│   │   ├── integrations/       # Third-party integration management\n│   │   ├── llm/                # LLM proxy (streaming chat completions)\n│   │   ├── organization/       # Org CRUD, members, invitations\n│   │   ├── sessions/           # Session CRUD, history, search\n│   │   ├── telemetry/          # Client telemetry ingestion\n│   │   ├── tools/              # Tool call result storage\n│   │   ├── user/               # User profile\n│   │   ├── webhooks/           # Stripe + Orb webhooks\n│   │   └── workspaces/         # CDE workspace management\n│   ├── layout.tsx\n│   └── page.tsx\n├── features/\n│   ├── llm/                    # LLM model IDs, streaming helpers\n│   ├── droids/                 # Droid (AI agent) configuration\n│   ├── feature-flags/          # Server-side Statsig helpers\n│   ├── integrations/           # Integration-specific business logic\n│   ├── prompts/                # Prompt templates\n│   └── workspace/              # CDE workspace provisioning logic\n├── services/\n│   ├── billing/                # Orb usage metering\n│   ├── bigquery/               # BigQuery analytics writes\n│   ├── cde/                    # CDE lifecycle management\n│   ├── computer/               # Computer-use agent sessions\n│   ├── e2b/                    # E2B sandbox integration\n│   ├── exa/                    # Exa search integration\n│   ├── fraud/                  # Fraud detection rules\n│   ├── integrations/           # GitHub, GitLab, etc. API wrappers\n│   ├── loops/                  # Loops email automation\n│   ├── orb/                    # Orb billing SDK wrapper\n│   ├── referrals/              # Referral code logic\n│   ├── remote-update/          # Remote daemon/CLI push updates\n│   ├── segment/                # Segment analytics\n│   ├── stripe/                 # Stripe payment processing\n│   ├── telemetry/              # Internal telemetry pipeline\n│   └── workos/                 # WorkOS SSO + user management\n├── data/                       # Firestore data models and query helpers\n├── env/                        # Environment variable types and validation\n├── middleware.ts               # Auth middleware (validates tokens on all routes)\n├── routes.ts                   # Client-side route constants (AppRoutes)\n├── constants.ts                # Shared backend constants\n└── utils/                      # Shared utility functions\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Type / File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/app/api/llm/` | LLM proxy — forwards streaming chat completions to Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, etc. |\n| `src/features/llm/streaming/` | Streaming helpers: SSE framing, provider adapters, token counting |\n| `src/features/llm/model-ids.ts` | Canonical model identifier mapping for all supported providers |\n| `src/middleware.ts` | Next.js middleware — validates WorkOS tokens on every request |\n| `src/services/workos/` | WorkOS user auth, org management, token refresh |\n| `src/services/orb/` | Orb billing integration for usage-based billing |\n| `src/services/integrations/` | GitHub/GitLab/Linear API wrappers used by sessions |\n| `src/data/` | Firestore model classes and typed query helpers |\n| `src/services/cde/` | Cloud development environment provisioning (E2B, custom CDEs) |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Request flow\n\nAll inbound requests pass through `src/middleware.ts`, which validates the bearer token against WorkOS. The token is decoded and the user/org context is attached to the request before it reaches the route handler.\n\n### LLM proxy\n\nThe LLM proxy at `src/app/api/llm/` is the most traffic-sensitive endpoint. The CLI and web clients send chat completion requests here instead of directly to LLM providers. The backend:\n\n1. Validates the user's subscription entitlements\n2. Selects the appropriate provider adapter (`src/features/llm/streaming/`)\n3. Streams the response back to the client via Server-Sent Events\n4. Meters usage against Orb for billing\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant CLI as CLI / Web\n    participant API as /api/llm\n    participant MW as middleware.ts\n    participant LLM as LLM Provider\n    participant Orb as Orb Billing\n\n    CLI->>API: POST /api/llm/stream {model, messages}\n    API->>MW: validate token\n    MW-->>API: user + org context\n    API->>LLM: streaming chat completion\n    LLM-->>API: SSE tokens\n    API-->>CLI: SSE tokens (proxied)\n    API->>Orb: record token usage\n```\n\n### Session management\n\n`src/app/api/sessions/` exposes CRUD endpoints for agent sessions. Sessions are stored in Firestore via `src/data/`. The CLI and web clients use these endpoints to create, load, list, and search sessions.\n\n### Cron jobs\n\n`src/app/api/cron/` contains scheduled Next.js route handlers that run via Vercel Cron. Jobs include billing reconciliation, stale workspace cleanup, and analytics aggregation.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **WorkOS** — authentication provider for users and organizations (`src/services/workos/`)\n- **Firebase / Firestore** — primary datastore for sessions, users, orgs (`src/data/`)\n- **LLM providers** — Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, etc. proxied through `src/app/api/llm/`\n- **Orb** — usage-based billing; records token consumption per session (`src/services/orb/`)\n- **Stripe** — payment processing for subscriptions (`src/services/stripe/`)\n- **GitHub** — OAuth flow and repository API access for integrations (`src/services/integrations/`)\n- **E2B** — cloud sandbox provisioning for remote CDEs (`src/services/e2b/`)\n- **Segment** — product analytics events (`src/services/segment/`)\n- **BigQuery** — analytical write path for session data (`src/services/bigquery/`)\n- **Statsig** — server-side feature flag evaluation (`src/features/feature-flags/`)\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n- **Add a new API route:** create a `route.ts` under `src/app/api/<name>/`\n- **Add a new LLM provider:** add an adapter in `src/features/llm/streaming/` and register in `model-ids.ts`\n- **Add a new integration:** implement the API wrapper in `src/services/integrations/` and expose a route in `src/app/api/integrations/`\n- **Change billing logic:** `src/services/orb/` and `src/services/billing/`\n- **Change auth rules:** `src/middleware.ts`\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/middleware.ts` | Token validation on every request |\n| `src/app/api/llm/` | LLM streaming proxy |\n| `src/features/llm/model-ids.ts` | Supported model identifiers |\n| `src/features/llm/streaming/` | SSE streaming helpers per provider |\n| `src/app/api/sessions/` | Session CRUD endpoints |\n| `src/app/api/organization/` | Organization and membership management |\n| `src/services/workos/` | WorkOS auth service |\n| `src/services/orb/` | Orb billing service |\n| `src/services/integrations/` | Third-party integration wrappers |\n| `src/data/` | Firestore data models |\n| `src/routes.ts` | Client-side route constants |\n",
