            "content": "# Web app (apps/web)\n\nActive contributors: Andrei Savin, factory-sherry, Alvin Sng, Ricky S, Nikita Lilichenko, factory-octavian, David Vendrow, Eno Reyes\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/web` is the main web application for the Factory platform. Users access it at `app.factory.ai` to start and manage Droid agent sessions, configure integrations, view session history, and manage billing. It is a Vite + React 19 SPA that connects to the daemon over WebSocket for live session interaction and to `apps/backend` for persistence and LLM proxying.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/web/\n├── src/\n│   ├── main.tsx              # Entry point — mounts WebAuthProvider\n│   ├── auth/\n│   │   ├── WebAuth.provider.tsx  # WorkOS AuthKit wrapper, routes to RootApp\n│   │   └── utils.ts              # Redirect URL validation helpers\n│   ├── config/               # App-level configuration (feature flags, environment)\n│   └── types/                # App-level TypeScript types\n├── e2e/                      # Playwright end-to-end tests\n├── index.html                # HTML shell\n└── vite.config.ts            # Vite build configuration\n\npackages/frontend/src/\n├── features/\n│   ├── sessions/             # Session list, session view, agent chat UI\n│   ├── settings/             # User settings, integrations, billing, API keys\n│   ├── onboarding/           # First-run flow\n│   ├── analytics/            # Internal product analytics hooks\n│   ├── auth/                 # Shared auth context and helpers\n│   ├── automations/          # Automation configuration UI\n│   ├── feature-flags/        # Statsig client-side flag hooks\n│   ├── missions/             # AGI Mode / large task decomposition UI\n│   ├── terminal/             # Embedded terminal component\n│   ├── wiki/                 # Wiki dashboard feature\n│   └── ...                   # (banner, debug, e2e, error, ga-analytics, health, ...)\n├── services/                 # Shared frontend services (DaemonSessionController, etc.)\n└── ...\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Type / File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/web/src/auth/WebAuth.provider.tsx` | Wraps the app in WorkOS `AuthKitProvider`; bridges WorkOS auth state into `RootApp` |\n| `packages/frontend/src/` → `RootApp` | Root React component; sets up router, auth context, daemon connection |\n| `packages/frontend/src/` → `initRouter` | Creates the Vite/React Router instance |\n| `packages/frontend/src/services/DaemonSessionController` | Manages the WebSocket connection to the daemon and session JSON-RPC lifecycle |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/sessions/` | Session list page, session detail view, agent message thread |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/settings/` | Settings pages (integrations, billing, API keys, security) |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/feature-flags/` | Statsig client-side flag hooks |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/terminal/` | Integrated PTY terminal component backed by daemon `daemon.create_terminal` |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Authentication flow\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant App as apps/web (browser)\n    participant WorkOS as WorkOS AuthKit\n    participant Backend as apps/backend\n\n    User->>App: navigate to app.factory.ai\n    App->>WorkOS: AuthKitProvider init\n    WorkOS-->>App: user + access token (cookie-based)\n    App->>App: WebAuthProviderInner renders RootApp\n    App->>Backend: API calls with Bearer token\n    Backend->>WorkOS: validate token\n    WorkOS-->>Backend: user context\n```\n\nOn first load, `WebAuth.provider.tsx` checks whether WorkOS has an active session. If not authenticated, WorkOS handles the redirect to the login page. After a successful OAuth callback, the access token is stored by AuthKit and the app renders `RootApp`.\n\nThe `RootApp` component (from `@factory/frontend`) sets up React Router, the global auth context, and the daemon connection.\n\n### Daemon connection\n\nThe web app connects to the local daemon (or remote relay) via WebSocket from `packages/frontend/src/services/DaemonSessionController`. It uses JSON-RPC 2.0 to:\n\n- Initialize or resume sessions (`daemon.initialize_session` / `daemon.load_session`)\n- Send user messages (`daemon.add_user_message`)\n- Receive streaming notifications (`daemon.session_notification`)\n- Create and interact with embedded terminals (`daemon.create_terminal`)\n\n### React rendering\n\nThe SPA uses React 19 with React Router. All pages live in `packages/frontend/src/features/`. The web app's `src/` directory is intentionally thin — it only provides the auth wrapper and mounts the shared `@factory/frontend` feature tree.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **WorkOS AuthKit** — handles browser-side OAuth login, token storage, and refresh (`@workos-inc/authkit-react`)\n- **`apps/backend`** — REST calls for sessions, organizations, billing, LLM proxying\n- **`apps/daemon`** — WebSocket JSON-RPC for live session interaction\n- **Statsig** — client-side feature flags via `packages/frontend/src/features/feature-flags/`\n- **`apps/signal`** — real-time push events for session status updates (see the Signal app)\n- **Sentry** — client-side error tracking\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n- **Auth flow changes:** `apps/web/src/auth/WebAuth.provider.tsx`\n- **Add a new page:** create a feature directory in `packages/frontend/src/features/` and register a route\n- **Daemon interaction:** `packages/frontend/src/services/DaemonSessionController`\n- **Session UI:** `packages/frontend/src/features/sessions/`\n- **Settings UI:** `packages/frontend/src/features/settings/`\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/web/src/main.tsx` | Entry point — mounts `WebAuthProvider` |\n| `apps/web/src/auth/WebAuth.provider.tsx` | WorkOS auth wrapper |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/sessions/` | Core session UI |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/settings/` | Settings pages |\n| `packages/frontend/src/services/DaemonSessionController` | WebSocket session management |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/feature-flags/` | Client-side Statsig flag hooks |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/terminal/` | Embedded terminal component |\n| `packages/frontend/src/features/wiki/` | Wiki dashboard feature |\n",
