            "content": "# Desktop app (apps/desktop)\n\nActive contributors: factory-jerry, factory-sherry, David Vendrow, Alvin Sng, Arman Bolat, Luke Alvoeiro, Kirk Strauser, factory-daniel\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/desktop` is the Electron-based native desktop application for Factory. It wraps the same React UI used by the web app, adds local file system access and native OS integration, and bundles the `factoryd` daemon so the daemon starts automatically alongside the app. This allows Factory to work entirely offline and gives the agent direct access to the user's local machine without requiring a cloud development environment.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/desktop/\n├── src/\n│   ├── main/                     # Electron main process\n│   │   ├── index.ts              # Main process entry point\n│   │   ├── initLifecycle.ts      # App lifecycle: setup, daemon start, auto-updater\n│   │   ├── ipc.ts                # IPC handlers exposed to renderer\n│   │   ├── window.ts             # BrowserWindow creation and management\n│   │   ├── menu.ts               # Application menu\n│   │   ├── deeplink.ts           # factory:// deep link handling\n│   │   ├── checkVersionSupported.ts  # Version gate (min supported version check)\n│   │   ├── desktopTelemetryClient.ts # Telemetry client for the main process\n│   │   ├── auth/                 # WorkOS OAuth flow in main process\n│   │   │   ├── workos.ts         # Initiates OAuth, handles callback\n│   │   │   ├── legacyElectronStorage.ts  # Legacy safeStorage migration helpers\n│   │   │   └── migrateLegacyElectronAuth.ts  # One-shot migration on startup\n│   │   ├── factoryd/             # Daemon process management\n│   │   │   ├── manager.ts        # FactorydManager: spawn, health-check, restart\n│   │   │   └── enums.ts          # FactorydState enum\n│   │   ├── droid/                # CLI setup helpers (symlinks, PATH)\n│   │   └── bootstrap.ts          # Early init (Sentry, logging)\n│   ├── renderer/                 # Electron renderer process (browser context)\n│   │   ├── main.tsx              # Renderer entry — mounts DesktopAuthProvider\n│   │   ├── auth/\n│   │   │   └── DesktopAuth.provider.tsx  # Auth via Electron IPC instead of WorkOS AuthKit\n│   │   └── automations/          # Automation-specific renderer helpers\n│   ├── preload/                  # Electron preload script (exposes window.electronAPI)\n│   ├── config/                   # Build-time constants (release channel, etc.)\n│   └── types/                    # Shared TypeScript types (window.electronAPI shape)\n├── forge.config.ts               # Electron Forge packaging configuration\n├── vite.main.config.ts           # Vite config for main process\n├── vite.renderer.config.ts       # Vite config for renderer\n└── VERSIONING.md                 # Version numbering policy\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Type / File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/main/initLifecycle.ts` | Orchestrates full app startup: auto-updater, single-instance lock, shell env, IPC setup, daemon start, window creation |\n| `src/main/factoryd/manager.ts` → `FactorydManager` | Spawns `factoryd` (or `factoryd-dev`), polls health endpoint, handles restarts on crash |\n| `src/main/ipc.ts` | All `ipcMain.handle` registrations: auth, app version, dialog, notifications, badge counts |\n| `src/main/auth/workos.ts` | Handles the OAuth redirect URI via the `factory://` custom protocol |\n| `src/renderer/auth/DesktopAuth.provider.tsx` | Renderer-side auth: fetches auth data from main via `window.electronAPI`, renders `RootApp` |\n| `src/preload/` | Preload script that safely exposes `window.electronAPI` (ipcRenderer wrappers) to the renderer |\n| `src/main/window.ts` | Creates and configures the main `BrowserWindow` |\n| `src/main/deeplink.ts` | Handles `factory://` deep links for OAuth callbacks and in-app navigation |\n\n## How it works\n\n### Startup sequence\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant OS as Operating System\n    participant Main as Electron main process\n    participant Daemon as factoryd (child process)\n    participant Renderer as Electron renderer\n\n    OS->>Main: app launches\n    Main->>Main: initLifecycle()\n    Main->>Main: auto-updater init (production only)\n    Main->>Main: ensureSingleInstance()\n    Main->>Main: loadShellEnvironment() — resolve PATH\n    Main->>Main: ipc() — register IPC handlers\n    Main->>Main: migrateLegacyElectronAuth()\n    Main->>Daemon: FactorydManager.start() — spawn factoryd binary\n    Daemon-->>Main: health check passes\n    Main->>Renderer: createWindow() — load renderer URL\n    Renderer->>Main: auth:getAuthData (IPC)\n    Main-->>Renderer: user + access token\n    Renderer->>Renderer: RootApp renders (router, daemon WS connection)\n```\n\n### Daemon bundling\n\nWhen the app is packaged, `factoryd` and `droid` binaries are bundled into `resources/bin/`. The `FactorydManager` detects `app.isPackaged` to choose between the bundled binary and the development alias (`factoryd-dev` / `droid-dev`). Auto-update for the bundled daemon is disabled (`FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE=true`) to preserve the code signature; the desktop app updates as a whole unit instead.\n\n`FactorydManager` periodically polls `http://127.0.0.1:<port>/health` and restarts the daemon on unexpected exits, up to 3 times with exponential backoff.\n\n### Auth flow\n\nThe desktop app cannot use the WorkOS browser AuthKit widget directly since the main process does not run in a browser context. Instead:\n\n1. The renderer calls `window.electronAPI.auth.signIn()` over IPC\n2. The main process opens the WorkOS OAuth URL in the system browser\n3. WorkOS redirects to the `factory://` custom protocol URI\n4. The main process intercepts the deep link, exchanges the code for tokens, and emits `auth:success` to the renderer via IPC\n5. The renderer updates its auth state and renders the authenticated UI\n\n### Auto-update\n\nProduction builds check for new versions at `https://downloads.factory.ai/factory-desktop/updates/<platform>/<arch>` using `update-electron-app`. The update interval is 10 minutes for production/preprod and 2 hours for staging.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **`apps/daemon` / `packages/daemon-core`** — desktop starts and manages the daemon process; renderer connects over WebSocket\n- **WorkOS** — OAuth flow through system browser + `factory://` deep links\n- **`packages/frontend`** — same `RootApp` and feature tree used by `apps/web`\n- **`@factory/runtime/auth`** — shared credential storage layer used by the main process\n- **Electron auto-updater** — `update-electron-app` for OTA app updates\n- **Factory downloads CDN** — update manifests and binary hosting at `downloads.factory.ai`\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\n- **App startup / lifecycle:** `src/main/initLifecycle.ts`\n- **Daemon management:** `src/main/factoryd/manager.ts`\n- **Add/change IPC handlers:** `src/main/ipc.ts`\n- **Auth flow:** `src/main/auth/workos.ts` and `src/renderer/auth/DesktopAuth.provider.tsx`\n- **Deep link handling:** `src/main/deeplink.ts`\n- **Packaging / build:** `forge.config.ts`\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/main/initLifecycle.ts` | Full app startup orchestration |\n| `src/main/factoryd/manager.ts` | Daemon process management and health polling |\n| `src/main/ipc.ts` | All IPC handler registrations |\n| `src/main/auth/workos.ts` | WorkOS OAuth flow in main process |\n| `src/renderer/main.tsx` | Renderer entry point |\n| `src/renderer/auth/DesktopAuth.provider.tsx` | Renderer auth via IPC |\n| `src/main/window.ts` | BrowserWindow setup |\n| `src/main/deeplink.ts` | `factory://` deep link handling |\n| `forge.config.ts` | Packaging, signing, and release configuration |\n| `VERSIONING.md` | Version number policy |\n",
