            "content": "# Signal (apps/signal)\n\nActive contributors: Abhay Singhal, factory-jerry\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/signal` is a GCP Cloud Function that analyses Factory chat sessions using OpenAI's Batch API. It runs on a schedule via Cloud Scheduler, detects friction points and delight moments in sessions, extracts structured session metadata, and stores results in BigQuery. It also generates daily Slack summaries and, in `analyze_and_ticket` mode, spawns a Droid to identify recurring friction patterns and create Linear tickets automatically.\n\n> **Note:** Despite the name \"Signal,\" this app is a batch analytics pipeline — not a real-time WebSocket notification service. Real-time event push to clients is handled by `apps/relay` and the daemon's WebSocket server.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/signal/\n├── src/\n│   ├── index.ts              # Cloud Function HTTP handler; mode dispatch\n│   ├── config.ts             # App config (BigQuery dataset, Slack channels, etc.)\n│   ├── droid-analysis.ts     # analyze_and_ticket mode: spawns Droid to find friction patterns\n│   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── bigquery.ts       # BigQuery read/write helpers\n│   │   ├── runner.ts         # BatchRunner: orchestrates batch submission and polling\n│   │   ├── session-transform.ts  # Transforms raw session data for batch input\n│   │   ├── thread.ts         # Session thread utilities\n│   │   ├── structured-facets.ts  # Computes structured facets (turn count, tool calls, etc.)\n│   │   ├── openai.ts         # OpenAI Batch API client helpers\n│   │   └── schemas.ts        # Zod schemas for batch outputs\n│   ├── signals/              # Signal type definitions and processors\n│   └── utils/                # Shared utilities\n├── deploy.sh                 # Deploy script (bundles skills, builds, deploys to GCP)\n└── DEPLOY.md                 # Deployment and operations guide\n\npackages/signal-core/         # Shared signal definitions used by apps/signal and apps/admin\n├── prompts/                  # LLM prompt templates for each signal type\n├── schemas/                  # Zod schemas (friction, delight, facets)\n└── mappers/                  # Result mappers (raw batch output → typed results)\n```\n\n## How it works\n\n### Operating modes\n\nThe Cloud Function dispatches on a `mode` field in the request body:\n\n| Mode | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `submit_batch` | Streams sessions from BigQuery and submits them to the OpenAI Batch API |\n| `process_results` | Polls completed batches, validates outputs, and inserts results into BigQuery |\n| `daily_report` | Queries aggregated stats and sends a Slack summary |\n| `analyze_and_ticket` | Spawns a Droid with BigQuery access to find recurring friction patterns and create Linear tickets |\n\n### Processing pipeline\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    Scheduler[\"Cloud Scheduler\"] --> CF[\"Cloud Function\\n(apps/signal)\"]\n    CF --> BQ1[\"BigQuery\\n(read sessions)\"]\n    BQ1 --> Runner[\"BatchRunner\\n(core/runner.ts)\"]\n    Runner --> OpenAI[\"OpenAI Batch API\"]\n    OpenAI --> Runner\n    Runner --> BQ2[\"BigQuery\\n(write results)\"]\n    Runner --> Slack[\"Slack\\n(daily report)\"]\n    Runner --> Linear[\"Linear\\n(friction tickets)\"]\n```\n\n### Signal types\n\n**Friction** — detects obstacles: model errors, repeated rephrasing, escalation tone, platform confusion, abandoned tool flows, backtracking, and context churn. Each friction event has a severity (High/Medium/Low) and citations.\n\n**Delight** — identifies positive moments: exclamations, first-attempt successes, rapid tool confirmation, adoption milestones, and efficiency gain mentions.\n\n**Facets** — structured session metadata extracted per session: intent categories, task description, outcome (Success/PartialSuccess/Abandoned/Error/Unknown), turn count, tool calls confirmed, droid used, file extensions.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **BigQuery** — primary data source (session data) and write target (signal results in `analytics` dataset tables: `friction_session_results`, `delight_session_results`, `session_facets`, `batch_summaries`)\n- **OpenAI Batch API** — bulk LLM inference for signal extraction\n- **Cloud Scheduler** — triggers the function on a daily schedule\n- **Slack** — daily summary reports via webhook\n- **Linear** — creates sub-issue tickets under the friction analysis epic when patterns are found\n- **`packages/signal-core`** — shared prompt templates, schemas, and result mappers also used by `apps/admin` for display\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/index.ts` | Cloud Function entry point; request parsing and mode dispatch |\n| `src/core/runner.ts` | `BatchRunner` — orchestrates the full batch submit → poll → store cycle |\n| `src/core/bigquery.ts` | BigQuery helpers for reading sessions and writing signal results |\n| `src/core/session-transform.ts` | Prepares session data as batch API input |\n| `src/droid-analysis.ts` | Friction pattern analysis via Droid + Linear ticket creation |\n| `src/config.ts` | App configuration (dataset names, Slack channels, etc.) |\n| `packages/signal-core/` | Shared prompt templates, schemas, and mappers |\n| `deploy.sh` | Bundles skills and deploys to GCP Cloud Functions |\n",
