            "content": "# Configuration\n\n## Environment variables\n\nAll three runtimes (CLI, daemon, backend) share a core set of `FACTORY_*` variables. The CLI and daemon read them through `@factory/environment`; the backend uses its own typed lookup in `apps/backend/src/env/constants.ts`.\n\n### CLI and daemon (`apps/cli`, `apps/daemon`)\n\nManaged via `packages/environment/src/constants.ts`. The `EnvironmentVariable` object is the canonical list of names.\n\n| Variable | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `FACTORY_ENV` | Runtime tier: `development` or `production` |\n| `FACTORY_DEPLOYMENT_ENV` | Deployment target: `development`, `localhost`, `staging`, `preprod`, or `production` |\n| `FACTORY_API_BASE_URL` | Base URL for the backend API |\n| `FACTORY_APP_BASE_URL` | Base URL for the web app |\n| `FACTORY_DOWNLOADS_BUCKET` | S3/GCS bucket for CLI update downloads |\n| `FACTORY_DOWNLOADS_PREFIX` | Path prefix inside the downloads bucket |\n| `FACTORY_DROID_AUTO_UPDATE_ENABLED` | Enable or disable CLI auto-update checks |\n| `FACTORY_RUNTIME_SETTINGS_PATH` | Override path for runtime settings JSON |\n| `FACTORY_API_KEY` | API key auth (alternative to WorkOS token) |\n| `FACTORY_WORKOS_BASE_URL` | Override WorkOS API base URL (testing only) |\n| `FACTORY_DISABLE_KEYRING` | Disable OS keyring for credential storage |\n| `FACTORY_LOG_FILE` | Override the log file path |\n| `FACTORYD_VERSION` | Daemon version string |\n| `FACTORYD_DISABLE_AUTO_UPDATE` | Disable daemon auto-update |\n| `FACTORY_OTEL_ENABLED` | Enable OpenTelemetry tracing in daemon |\n| `ROLLBACK_ENABLED` | Enable rollback on failed daemon update |\n| `REMOTE_MACHINE_ID` | ID for remote machine sessions |\n| `FACTORY_MACHINE_TYPE` | Machine type identifier |\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_PORT` | WebSocket relay port |\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_HOST` | WebSocket relay host |\n| `FACTORY_RELAY_DEBUG` | Enable relay debug logging |\n| `MISSION_WORKER_INACTIVITY_TIMEOUT_MS` | Inactivity timeout for mission worker sessions |\n\n### Backend (`apps/backend`)\n\nThe backend uses a typed `env` object in `apps/backend/src/env/constants.ts`. Key variables:\n\n| Variable | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_ENV` | App environment (used client-side) |\n| `FACTORY_FIRESTORE_ORG_ID` | Firestore org ID for the Factory org itself |\n| `CORS_ALLOWED_ORIGINS` | Comma-separated list of allowed CORS origins |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_*` | Firebase project config (API key, project ID, etc.) |\n| `GITHUB_APP_ID` / `GITHUB_APP_ID_INTERNAL` | GitHub App integration credentials |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_WORKOS_CLIENT_ID` | WorkOS OAuth client ID |\n| `NEXT_PUBLIC_STATSIG_SDK_KEY` | Statsig client SDK key for feature flags |\n| `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID` / `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY` | AWS credentials (falls back to credential chain) |\n| `AWS_DROID_EXECUTE_QUEUE_URL` | SQS queue URL for droid execution jobs |\n| `PROXY_FUNCTION_URL` | GCP proxy function for LLM requests |\n| `GCP_VERTEX_ANTHROPIC_REGION` | GCP region for Vertex AI Anthropic models |\n| `LOOPS_API_KEY` | Loops transactional email API key |\n| `VOYAGE_API_KEY` | Voyage AI API key (embeddings) |\n| `WEAVIATE_URL` / `WEAVIATE_API_KEY` | Weaviate vector database connection |\n| `TESTING_BYPASS_TOKEN_PASSWORD` | Shared secret for bypassing auth in tests |\n\n## Using `@factory/environment`\n\nIn CLI and daemon code, read environment variables through the typed `@factory/environment` package rather than `process.env` directly. This is enforced by the `no-direct-process-env` ESLint rule.\n\n```ts\nimport { getEnvironment } from '@factory/environment';\n\nconst env = getEnvironment();\nenv.apiBaseUrl; // typed string\nenv.factoryEnv; // typed FactoryEnv enum\n```\n\nSource: `packages/environment/src/`.\n\n## Local overrides\n\nEach app has `.env` files for different environments. To override locally without committing:\n\n- Create `.env.local` in the app directory (`apps/cli/.env.local`, `apps/daemon/.env.local`, `apps/backend/.env.local`)\n- `.env.local` is git-ignored and takes precedence over `.env` and `.env.development`\n\n## Secrets\n\n| Secret | Where it lives |\n|---|---|\n| WorkOS client secret and API key | Vercel environment (backend) / CI secrets |\n| LLM provider API keys (Anthropic, OpenAI) | GCP Secret Manager, accessed via LLM proxy |\n| Firebase service account | CI secrets; not stored in repo |\n| GitHub App private key | CI secrets |\n| Statsig server-side SDK key | CI secrets / Vercel environment |\n| `TESTING_BYPASS_TOKEN_PASSWORD` | Shared across CLI, daemon, and backend — stored in CI secrets |\n\nSecrets are never committed to the repo. The `.env` files in each app contain only non-sensitive defaults (URLs, flag names, bucket names).\n",
