            "content": "# Data models\n\nDomain types are split between two packages:\n\n- **`@factory/common`** (`packages/common/src/`) — shared types consumed by CLI, daemon, backend, and frontend. No runtime logic.\n- **`@factory/models`** (`packages/models/src/`) — Firestore data models with handlers, validation, and business logic. Backend and daemon only.\n\n## Key types by area\n\n### Session\n\nThe session is the central entity. A session has a list of messages and tracks the progress of a droid execution.\n\n| Type | Package | Location |\n|---|---|---|\n| `Session` | `@factory/common` | `src/session/types.ts` |\n| `SessionV2` | `@factory/common` | `src/sessionV2/types.ts` |\n| `SessionSummary` | `@factory/common` | `src/session/summary/` |\n| Session messages | `@factory/common` | `src/session/messages/` |\n| Firestore session model | `@factory/models` | `src/session/` |\n\n`SessionV2` is the current schema; `Session` is kept for backward compatibility during the migration.\n\n### Message and tool calls\n\n| Type | Package | Location |\n|---|---|---|\n| `Message` (LLM message) | `@factory/common` | `src/session/messages/` |\n| Tool definitions (schemas) | `@factory/common` | `src/tools/` |\n| Tool result types | `@factory/common` | `src/session/tools/` |\n| LLM provider types | `@factory/common` | `src/llm/` |\n\n### Integrations\n\nIntegrations (GitHub, GitLab, Linear, Slack, Jira, Notion, Confluence, Sentry, PagerDuty) share a common structure in `@factory/common/src/integrations/`. Each integration has its own subdirectory with `types.ts` and `enums.ts`. Firestore models live in `@factory/models/src/integrations/`.\n\n### User and organization\n\n| Type | Package | Location |\n|---|---|---|\n| `Organization` | `@factory/models` | `src/organization/types.ts` |\n| `UserProfile` | `@factory/models` | `src/organization/user/` |\n| Subscription | `@factory/models` | `src/organization/subscription/` |\n| Organization settings | `@factory/models` | `src/organization/managedSettings/` |\n| Members | `@factory/models` | `src/organization/members/` |\n| Factory API keys | `@factory/models` | `src/factoryApiKeys/` |\n\nOrganization types that are referenced by both frontend and backend are also mirrored in `@factory/common/src/organization/`.\n\n### Settings\n\nUser-facing settings (model preferences, privacy, UI options) are stored in two places:\n\n- **Daemon/CLI settings**: `@factory/services/src/settings/SettingsManager.ts` — local JSON file at `~/.factory/settings.json`\n- **Org-level managed settings**: `@factory/models/src/organization/managedSettings/` — Firestore, set by org admins\n\n### Feature flags\n\nFlag names are defined as string constants in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`. This file changes frequently (78 times in the last 90 days) because every new flag is added here first.\n\n## Firestore data structure\n\nThe Firestore database is organized under `organizations/{organizationId}`:\n\n```\norganizations/{orgId}\n  integrations/{integrationId}\n  userProfiles/{userId}\n  sessions/{sessionId}\n    messages/{messageId}\n    plans/{planId}\n    localProcesses/{processId}\n  wiki/{...}\n  ...\n```\n\nTop-level collections outside of `organizations/` include `factoryApiKeys/`, `referrals/`, `promotions/`, and `memory/`. The full list is in `firestore.rules` and `firestore.indexes.json` at the monorepo root.\n\nAccess rules are defined in `firestore.rules`. Sessions are visible to the owner, or to any org member if `privacyLevel == \"organization\"`.\n",
