            "content": "# Factory platform overview\n\nFactory is an AI-powered coding assistant built around the **Droid CLI** — a terminal application that runs an AI agent loop locally and communicates with Factory's cloud services. Engineers interact with Droid through the CLI, a desktop Electron app, or a web interface.\n\n## What Factory does\n\nFactory provides AI-assisted software development by running autonomous agent sessions. The agent can read and write files, run shell commands, interact with external services (GitHub, Linear, Slack), and stream results back to the user in real time. Sessions are managed by a local daemon process (`factoryd`) that spawns and supervises individual agent processes.\n\n## Who uses it\n\nFactory is used by software engineers at companies that have connected their codebases to the Factory platform. The CLI is the primary interface; the web and desktop apps provide a browser-based or native wrapper around the same experience.\n\n## Key components\n\n| Component | Description |\n|---|---|\n| **Droid CLI** (`apps/cli`) | Terminal UI and headless runner. The primary user interface. |\n| **factoryd daemon** (`apps/daemon`) | Background process that manages agent sessions and terminal access. |\n| **Backend API** (`apps/backend`) | Next.js REST API for auth, billing, sessions, LLM proxying, and integrations. |\n| **Web app** (`apps/web`) | Vite + React web interface for browser-based Droid interactions. |\n| **Desktop app** (`apps/desktop`) | Electron wrapper that bundles the web UI with the daemon. |\n| **Admin dashboard** (`apps/admin`) | Internal Next.js app for platform management. |\n\n## Repository layout\n\n```\nfactory-mono/\n├── apps/\n│   ├── cli/              # Droid CLI (Bun, TypeScript, Ink)\n│   ├── daemon/           # factoryd daemon (Bun, TypeScript)\n│   ├── backend/          # REST API (Next.js 15)\n│   ├── web/              # Web UI (Vite + React)\n│   ├── desktop/          # Electron desktop app\n│   ├── admin/            # Admin dashboard (Next.js 15)\n│   ├── scripts/          # Build and maintenance scripts\n│   └── ...               # Extensions, functions, signal, relay\n├── packages/\n│   ├── core-ui/          # Design system (mandatory for all UI)\n│   ├── frontend/         # Shared React features and hooks\n│   ├── droid-core/       # AI agent core (tools, LLMs, streaming)\n│   ├── common/           # Shared types, enums, API contracts\n│   ├── models/           # Data model types\n│   ├── services/         # Business logic services\n│   └── ...               # logging, utils, updater, eslint-config\n├── docs/                 # Internal engineering docs\n└── .github/workflows/    # CI/CD pipelines (50+ workflows)\n```\n\n## Quick links\n\n- [Architecture overview](./architecture.md) — system components and data flow\n- [Getting started](./getting-started.md) — setup, build, and run instructions\n- [Glossary](./glossary.md) — key terms\n- [How to contribute](../how-to-contribute/index.md) — development workflow and conventions\n- [CLI app](../apps/cli/index.md) — deep dive into the CLI\n- [Daemon](../apps/daemon.md) — factoryd internals\n- [Backend API](../apps/backend.md) — REST endpoints and services\n",
