            "content": "# Architecture\n\nFactory is a multi-process system. The CLI runs in the user's terminal, talks to a local daemon over WebSocket, and that daemon spawns and supervises agent processes. A cloud backend handles auth, session storage, billing, and LLM proxying.\n\n## Language breakdown\n\n```mermaid\npie title Source lines by language\n    \"TypeScript\" : 88\n    \"JavaScript\" : 5\n    \"CSS/Styled\" : 4\n    \"HTML/JSON/Config\" : 3\n```\n\nThe entire codebase is TypeScript. The CLI and daemon run on Bun; the backend and web apps use Node/Vite with Next.js and React.\n\n## System components\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    subgraph User Machine\n        CLI[\"Droid CLI\\n(apps/cli)\"]\n        Desktop[\"Desktop App\\n(apps/desktop)\"]\n        Web[\"Web App\\n(apps/web)\"]\n        Daemon[\"factoryd\\n(apps/daemon)\"]\n        Agent[\"Agent Process\\n(spawned by daemon)\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph Factory Cloud\n        Backend[\"Backend API\\n(apps/backend)\"]\n        LLM[\"LLM Proxy\"]\n        DB[\"Firestore DB\"]\n    end\n\n    subgraph External\n        GitHub\n        Linear\n        Slack\n        LLMProviders[\"Anthropic / OpenAI / Google\"]\n    end\n\n    CLI -->|\"WebSocket\\nJSON-RPC 2.0\"| Daemon\n    Desktop -->|\"WebSocket\\nJSON-RPC 2.0\"| Daemon\n    Web -->|\"WebSocket\\nJSON-RPC 2.0\"| Daemon\n    Daemon -->|\"stdin/stdout\\nJSON-RPC\"| Agent\n    Agent -->|\"REST\"| Backend\n    CLI -->|\"REST\"| Backend\n    Web -->|\"REST\"| Backend\n    Backend --> DB\n    Backend --> LLM\n    LLM --> LLMProviders\n    Backend --> GitHub\n    Backend --> Linear\n    Backend --> Slack\n```\n\n## Core data flow\n\nA typical agent interaction follows this path:\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant User\n    participant CLI\n    participant Daemon\n    participant Agent\n    participant Backend\n\n    User->>CLI: types a message\n    CLI->>Daemon: daemon.add_user_message (JSON-RPC WS)\n    Daemon->>Agent: stdin JSON-RPC message\n    Agent->>Backend: POST /api/llm/stream\n    Backend-->>Agent: streaming LLM tokens\n    Agent-->>Daemon: stdout tool calls + text\n    Daemon-->>CLI: session update events\n    CLI-->>User: rendered TUI output\n```\n\n## Frontend / web flow\n\nWhen using the web or desktop app, the browser-side `DaemonSessionController` connects over WebSocket to the same daemon and drives the same JSON-RPC protocol. The web app is a lightweight React shell that delegates nearly all state management to `@factory/frontend`.\n\n## Packages and their roles\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    CLI --> droid_core[\"@factory/droid-core\\nAI tools, LLM wrappers, streaming\"]\n    CLI --> common[\"@factory/common\\nShared types and API contracts\"]\n    CLI --> services[\"@factory/services\\nBusiness logic\"]\n    CLI --> frontend_pkg[\"@factory/frontend\\nShared React features\"]\n    Daemon --> daemon_core[\"@factory/daemon-core\\nWebSocket server, session manager\"]\n    Backend --> common\n    Backend --> services\n    Web --> frontend_pkg\n    Desktop --> frontend_pkg\n    frontend_pkg --> core_ui[\"@factory/core-ui\\nDesign system primitives\"]\n```\n\n## Deployment topology\n\n| Environment | Backend | Web | CLI/Daemon |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Production | Vercel (Next.js) | Vercel (Vite) | Installed locally by users |\n| Dev | Local Next.js (port 3000) | Local Vite (port 3002) | Local via `droid-dev` alias |\n| CDE (remote) | Cloud | Cloud | Daemon auto-downloaded onto sandbox |\n\nThe desktop app bundles `factoryd` and manages its lifecycle. Remote cloud development environments (CDEs) download the daemon binary from `downloads.factory.ai` on workspace initialization.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Getting started](./getting-started.md) — how to set up a local dev environment\n- [CLI](../apps/cli/index.md) — CLI architecture and command structure\n- [Daemon](../apps/daemon.md) — daemon internals and WebSocket API\n- [Backend API](../apps/backend.md) — REST endpoints and LLM proxying\n- [droid-core package](../packages/droid-core.md) — AI agent tools and streaming\n",
