            "content": "# Getting started\n\nThis page covers setting up a local development environment for the Factory monorepo.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- **Node.js 18.x** — specified in `.nvmrc`. Use `nvm use` to switch.\n- **Bun 1.3.x** — required for CLI and daemon workspaces.\n- **npm 11.x** — the monorepo uses npm workspaces.\n- A Factory account with access to the staging or production environment.\n\n## Install\n\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/Factory-AI/factory-mono.git\ncd factory-mono\nnpm install\n```\n\n`npm install` runs `npm run setup` automatically via the `postinstall` script.\n\n## Build\n\n```bash\nnpm run build              # build all packages\nnpm run build -- --filter=apps/web  # build a single app\n```\n\n## Run the dev stack\n\nDo **not** use `npm run dev` at the root — it is intentionally disabled.\n\n```bash\n# Start backend, web, storybook, admin, daemon (SSH-compatible)\nnpm run dev:web\n\n# Start backend, web, storybook, admin, desktop (local only)\nnpm run dev:desktop\n```\n\nDev server log files:\n\n| App | Log file |\n|---|---|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n| daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n\n## Run the CLI locally\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli\nnpm run setup          # build and register droid-dev alias\ndroid-dev              # uses local code against hosted API\ndroid-localhost        # uses local code against local API\n```\n\nAfter any code change to the CLI or daemon, rebuild and restart:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup\n# then restart the daemon and open a new session\n```\n\n## Run tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all tests (uses ~9 GB RAM — filter when possible)\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common\n\n# Run a single test file\ncd apps/backend && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run path/to/file.test.ts\n```\n\n## Type-check\n\n```bash\nnpm run typecheck -- --filter=@factory/frontend\n```\n\n## Lint and format\n\n```bash\nnpm run fix     # lint + format (preferred)\nnpm run lint    # lint only\n```\n\n## Key ports\n\n| App | Port |\n|---|---|\n| Backend API | 3000 |\n| Admin dashboard | 3001 |\n| Web app | 3002 |\n| Storybook | (configured in package) |\n| factoryd (production) | 37643 |\n| factoryd (development) | 41723 |\n\n## Environment files\n\nEach app has its own `.env` files. Copy `.env.example` → `.env.local` and fill in the required values. The backend app's `.env` has the most configuration; see `apps/backend/.env.example` for required keys.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Development workflow](../how-to-contribute/development-workflow.md)\n- [Testing](../how-to-contribute/testing.md)\n- [Debugging](../how-to-contribute/debugging.md)\n- [Architecture](./architecture.md)\n",
