            "content": "# Glossary\n\nKey terms used throughout the Factory codebase and documentation.\n\n## Core concepts\n\n**Droid** — The AI coding agent that Factory runs. \"Droid\" refers both to the CLI tool (`droid` command) and to the agent process itself.\n\n**Session** — A single conversation between a user and the Droid agent. Sessions have a persistent ID, can be resumed, and accumulate a message history.\n\n**factoryd** — The Factory daemon process. It runs in the background, manages agent sessions, and exposes a WebSocket/JSON-RPC server. Also called \"the daemon.\"\n\n**Agent loop** — The execution cycle where the agent receives a message, calls LLM APIs, executes tool calls, and streams results back. The loop continues until the agent produces a final response or is interrupted.\n\n**Tool** — A capability exposed to the AI agent, such as reading files, running shell commands, or calling external APIs. Defined in `@factory/droid-core/src/tools`.\n\n**ACP (Agent Control Protocol)** — The JSON-RPC protocol used for communication between the CLI and daemon over WebSocket, and between the daemon and agent process over stdin/stdout.\n\n**CDE (Cloud Development Environment)** — A remote sandbox environment where Factory agents can run. The daemon is auto-downloaded onto CDEs during workspace initialization.\n\n**Mission** — A higher-level autonomous task that decomposes into multiple agent sessions. Missions are used for multi-step work and involve sub-agent parallelization.\n\n**Skill** — A reusable prompt or capability that can be invoked within a session. Skills are markdown files stored in `.factory/skills/` directories.\n\n**Spec mode** — An interactive CLI mode where the agent proposes a plan before executing it. The user reviews and approves before implementation begins.\n\n## Architecture terms\n\n**DaemonSessionController** — The frontend class (`packages/frontend`) that manages WebSocket connections to the daemon and orchestrates session lifecycle from the browser side.\n\n**droid-core** — The `@factory/droid-core` package containing LLM integrations, tool definitions, streaming utilities, and agent core logic.\n\n**SEA (Single Executable Application)** — The compiled binary format for the CLI and daemon. Built using Node.js/Bun's SEA feature for distribution.\n\n**JSON-RPC 2.0** — The protocol used for all inter-process communication: CLI↔Daemon over WebSocket, and Daemon↔Agent over stdin/stdout.\n\n**LLM proxy** — The backend endpoint (`/api/llm/stream`) that receives LLM requests from agents, applies policy, and forwards them to the appropriate provider (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google).\n\n## UI terms\n\n**core-ui** — The `@factory/core-ui` package. The mandatory design system. All UI components must use its primitives (`Box`, `Button`, `Input`, etc.) rather than raw HTML elements.\n\n**Ink** — The React renderer for terminal interfaces. The CLI TUI is built with Ink. See `apps/cli/src/app.tsx`.\n\n**Storybook** — The component browser for the design system. Run via `npm run dev:web` alongside the other apps.\n\n## Workflow terms\n\n**BYOK (Bring Your Own Key)** — A feature that lets users supply their own LLM API keys instead of using Factory's proxied access.\n\n**Relay** — The `apps/relay` service, which handles routing and proxying for certain backend requests.\n\n**Signal** — The `apps/signal` service, likely a notification or event broadcasting service.\n\n**Turbo / Turborepo** — The monorepo build orchestrator. Used for all `npm run build`, `test`, `lint`, and `typecheck` commands. Always pass `--` before `--filter` when running from the root.\n\n**Knip** — Unused export detection tool. Run via `npm run knip`.\n\n## External services\n\n**WorkOS AuthKit** — The authentication provider. Handles OAuth flows and JWT tokens.\n\n**Statsig** — Feature flag provider. Flag definitions live in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`.\n\n**Sentry** — Error monitoring. Integrated across backend, CLI, and desktop apps.\n\n**Firestore** — Primary database for session storage, user data, and platform metadata.\n\n**Orb** — Billing provider for subscription and usage management.\n",
