            "content": "# How to contribute\n\nThis section covers everything needed to work in the Factory monorepo: picking up work, writing code, testing changes, and getting a PR merged.\n\n## Sub-pages\n\n- [Development workflow](./development-workflow.md) — branch, code, test, PR, merge cycle\n- [Testing](./testing.md) — frameworks, patterns, mocks, and running tests\n- [Debugging](./debugging.md) — logs, common errors, troubleshooting runbook\n- [Patterns and conventions](./patterns-and-conventions.md) — error handling, coding style, cross-cutting concerns\n- [Tooling](./tooling.md) — build system, linters, code generators, CI\n\n## PR process\n\n1. Create a branch from `dev` (not `main`). Branch names typically follow the Linear ticket slug: `fac-12345-short-description`.\n2. Write code, following the conventions in [patterns and conventions](./patterns-and-conventions.md).\n3. Run `npm run fix` to lint and format.\n4. Run `npm run typecheck -- --filter=<your-package>` to catch type errors.\n5. Run targeted tests: `npm run test -- --filter=<your-package>`.\n6. Push and open a PR against `dev`.\n\n## PR title format\n\nConventional Commits: `type(scope): description`\n\nTypes: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `refactor`, `test`, `chore`\nScope: workspace name from `apps/*` or `packages/*`, or `monorepo`\n\nExamples:\n```\nfeat(cli): add wiki-upload command\nfix(daemon): prevent session leak on disconnect\nchore(monorepo): upgrade turbo to 2.7\n```\n\n## PR description\n\nThe PR template lives in `.github/pull_request_template.md`. Every PR must include a Linear ticket reference: `Closes FAC-1234`.\n\n## Definition of done\n\n- All CI checks green (typecheck, lint, tests, knip)\n- PR reviewed and approved\n- Linear ticket updated\n- No regressions in affected areas\n\n## Code review expectations\n\nReviews focus on correctness, conventions, and test coverage. Design feedback is out-of-scope unless the PR touches shared abstractions. If you are unsure whether a change needs a design review, ask in the PR.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Architecture](../overview/architecture.md) — understand the system before making changes\n- [Debugging](./debugging.md) — when something breaks during development\n",
