            "content": "# Development workflow\n\n## Branch strategy\n\n- Default branch: `dev`\n- Production branch: `main`\n- Feature branches fork from `dev`, merge back to `dev`\n- Hotfix branches fork from `main`\n- Branch naming: `<linear-ticket>-<short-description>`, e.g., `fac-16604-wiki-dashboard`\n\nReleases are cut from `dev` → `main` via automated workflows.\n\n## Local setup\n\n```bash\n# Full monorepo install\nnpm install\n\n# Start the dev stack\nnpm run dev:web      # backend + web + storybook + admin + daemon\nnpm run dev:desktop  # backend + web + storybook + admin + desktop (local only)\n```\n\nFor CLI development:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli\nnpm run setup          # builds CLI and creates droid-dev / droid-localhost aliases\ndroid-dev              # runs against hosted API\ndroid-localhost        # runs against local API (port 3000)\n```\n\nAfter any CLI or daemon code change, you must rebuild and restart:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/cli && npm run setup\n# kill and restart the daemon process\n# start a new session\n```\n\n## Coding cycle\n\n1. Make changes in your workspace.\n2. Run `npm run fix -- --filter=<your-package>` to lint and auto-fix.\n3. Run `npm run typecheck -- --filter=<your-package>` to check types.\n4. Run tests: `npm run test -- --filter=<your-package>`.\n5. Push and open a PR against `dev`.\n\n**Note:** When running turbo-based scripts from the root, always pass `--` before `--filter`:\n\n```bash\n# Correct\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common\n\n# Wrong (npm eats the --filter flag, turbo runs everything)\nnpm run test --filter=@factory/common\n```\n\n## Adding new packages\n\nNew workspace packages go under `packages/` (shared libraries) or `apps/` (deployable units). Register them in the root `package.json` workspaces array and create a `package.json` with the appropriate name (`@factory/<name>` for packages).\n\nNew API types belong in `packages/common/src/api/<service>/types.ts`.\n\n## Merging\n\n- Squash merges are preferred to keep `dev` history clean.\n- Rebase if the PR has fallen behind `dev` by many commits.\n- CI must be fully green before merging.\n\n## Release process\n\nReleases are automated via GitHub Actions:\n\n- `release-cut.yml` — cuts a release from `dev`\n- `release-bump-version.yml` — bumps versions\n- `cli-release.yml` / `factoryd-release.yml` / `desktop-release.yml` — publish artifacts\n\nSee [deployment](../deployment.md) for details.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Getting started](../overview/getting-started.md)\n- [Testing](./testing.md)\n- [Tooling](./tooling.md)\n",
