            "content": "# Testing\n\n## Test frameworks\n\n| Workspace | Framework | Runner |\n|---|---|---|\n| `apps/backend` | Jest + ts-jest | `npx jest` |\n| `apps/cli` | Jest + ts-jest | `npx jest` |\n| `apps/daemon` | Jest + ts-jest | `npx jest` |\n| `packages/frontend` | Vitest | `npx vitest` |\n| `packages/core-ui` | Vitest | `npx vitest` |\n| `packages/common` | Jest | `npx jest` |\n| `packages/droid-core` | Jest | `npx jest` |\n\n## Running tests\n\n```bash\n# All tests (slow, ~9 GB RAM — filter when possible)\nnpm run test\n\n# Specific workspace (MUST use -- before --filter)\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/frontend --filter=@factory/droid-core\n\n# Single test file\ncd apps/backend && npx jest path/to/file.test.ts\ncd packages/frontend && npx vitest run path/to/file.test.ts\n```\n\n## Unit test conventions\n\nTests are colocated with source files: `foo.ts` → `foo.test.ts`.\n\n**Testing philosophy**: unit tests validate only the public API of a single file. If that file calls code in other files, mock only heavy or non-deterministic calls; keep pure helpers and utilities real.\n\n```ts\n// Top-level mock with requireActual to keep real implementations\njest.mock('./some-service', () => ({\n  ...jest.requireActual('./some-service'),\n  heavyOperation: jest.fn(),\n}));\n\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetAllMocks());\n```\n\n## Frontend tests need jsdom\n\nAny test that uses React hooks, atoms, or browser APIs must declare the jsdom environment at the top of the file:\n\n```ts\n/**\n * @jest-environment jsdom\n */\n```\n\nWithout this, tests fail with `ReferenceError: document is not defined`.\n\n## Mocking patterns\n\n**Simple mock:**\n\n```ts\njest.mock('./module', () => ({\n  ...jest.requireActual('./module'),\n  functionToMock: jest.fn(),\n}));\n\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetAllMocks());\n\nit('test', () => {\n  (functionToMock as jest.Mock).mockResolvedValue('result');\n  // ...\n});\n```\n\n**Singleton isolation** — when a module is a singleton that must be freshly initialized per test:\n\n```ts\nbeforeEach(() => jest.resetModules());\n\nit('test', async () => {\n  const { getService } = await import('./service');\n  // each test gets a fresh module instance\n});\n```\n\n## E2E tests\n\n**Playwright (web):**\n\n```bash\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e\ncd packages/frontend && npm run test:e2e -- --headed --debug\n```\n\n**TUI tests (CLI):**\n\nThe CLI has TUI end-to-end tests in `apps/cli/e2e-tests/` using `@microsoft/tui-test`. These test the full interactive terminal experience.\n\n**Stream JSON-RPC tests:**\n\n`apps/cli/e2e-stream-jsonrpc/` contains integration tests for the daemon-CLI JSON-RPC protocol. Run via `npm run test:e2e-stream-jsonrpc` in the CLI workspace.\n\n## Test utilities\n\n- `packages/test-utils` — shared test helpers and factories\n- Mock files in `__mocks__/` directories are automatically picked up by Jest\n- `apps/cli/fixtures/` — test fixture data for CLI tests\n\n## Checking coverage\n\n```bash\ncd apps/backend && npx jest --coverage\ncd apps/cli && npx jest --coverage\n```\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Patterns and conventions](./patterns-and-conventions.md)\n- [Debugging](./debugging.md)\n- [Tooling](./tooling.md)\n",
