            "content": "# Debugging\n\n## Communication stack\n\n```\nFrontend (DaemonSessionController.ts)\n    ↓ WebSocket JSON-RPC\nDaemon (droid-request-handler.ts)\n    ↓ stdin/stdout JSON-RPC\nCLI (streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.tsx)\n```\n\nIssues are usually at one of these three boundaries.\n\n## Log locations\n\n| Environment | Directory | Key files |\n|---|---|---|\n| Development | `~/.factory-dev/logs/` | `factoryd.log`, `droid-log-single.log`, `console.log` |\n| Production | `~/.factory/logs/` | Same files |\n\nDev stack apps also write to `/tmp/`:\n\n| App | Log file |\n|---|---|\n| backend | `/tmp/factory-dev-backend.log` |\n| admin | `/tmp/factory-dev-admin.log` |\n| desktop | `/tmp/factory-dev-desktop.log` |\n| daemon | `/tmp/factory-dev-daemon.log` |\n\n## Trace a message through the stack\n\n```bash\n# Check the CLI emitted it\ngrep \"your-feature\" ~/.factory-dev/logs/droid-log-single.log\n\n# Check the daemon received/forwarded it\ngrep \"your-feature\" ~/.factory-dev/logs/factoryd.log\n\n# Live stream all dev logs\ntail -f ~/.factory-dev/logs/*.log\n```\n\n## Quick debug checklist\n\n- [ ] Rebuilt CLI after changes: `cd apps/cli && npm run setup`\n- [ ] Restarted daemon process\n- [ ] Started a **new** session (old sessions don't pick up code changes)\n- [ ] Checking the right log directory (`~/.factory-dev/` for dev)\n- [ ] Schema/enum changes are in `@factory/common`\n- [ ] Frontend handler exists for the notification type\n\n## Common issues\n\n**Messages not reaching the frontend:**\n\n1. Check that the notification type is in the `SessionNotificationType` enum (`packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts`)\n2. Verify the schema is defined in `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/cli.ts`\n3. Confirm the frontend handler exists in `DaemonSessionController.ts` (`packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts`)\n\n**Timing issues:**\n\nNotifications sent before a session is registered with the daemon are silently dropped. Always emit notifications after session initialization completes.\n\n**Schema mismatches:**\n\nIf the daemon fails to parse a message, look for JSON-RPC parse errors in `factoryd.log`. Schema validation uses `zod` — mismatches produce descriptive error messages.\n\n**Dev vs prod confusion:**\n\nCheck which binary is running. `droid-dev` runs from source via Bun against hosted dev. `droid-localhost` runs against local API. The compiled `droid` binary is the production build.\n\n## Adding debug logging\n\n```typescript\nimport { logInfo } from '@factory/logging';\n\nlogInfo(`[Feature] Event received: count=${items.length}`);\n```\n\nLogs appear in `droid-log-single.log` (CLI) or `factoryd.log` (daemon).\n\n## Key files for debugging\n\n| Layer | File |\n|---|---|\n| Protocol enums | `packages/common/src/droid/enums.ts` |\n| Protocol schemas | `packages/common/src/droid/schemas/` |\n| CLI runner | `apps/cli/src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.tsx` |\n| Daemon handler | `apps/daemon/src/server/handlers/droid-request-handler.ts` |\n| Frontend controller | `packages/frontend/src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Architecture](../overview/architecture.md) — understand the full communication stack\n- [CLI](../apps/cli/index.md) — CLI-specific debugging\n- [Daemon](../apps/daemon.md) — daemon-specific debugging\n",
