            "content": "# Patterns and conventions\n\n## Error handling\n\nFactory uses typed error classes instead of plain `Error`. The canonical imports are from `@factory/logging/errors`:\n\n```ts\nimport {\n  MetaError,\n  ResponseError400BadRequest,\n  ResponseError404NotFound,\n  // ... other status codes\n} from '@factory/logging/errors';\nimport { logInfo, logWarn, logException } from '@factory/logging';\n```\n\nCore rules:\n\n1. **Bubble by default** — do not wrap with `try/catch` unless you have a concrete reason (fallback, translation to a different error type, or a handled null return).\n2. **Typed errors always** — internal 500s use `MetaError`; user-facing non-200 responses use the matching `ResponseErrorXXX` class. Never throw plain `Error`.\n3. **Breadcrumbs, not noise** — use `logInfo` / `logWarn` to leave context before risky calls. Never call `logError`.\n4. **One or the other** — if you call `logException`, you handle the error locally (no rethrow). Otherwise, do not log — just add breadcrumbs and rethrow.\n5. **Preserve the original stack** — rethrow the original error; only create a new error object when semantics change.\n\n## File organization rules\n\nESLint enforces these conventions automatically:\n\n| Convention | Rule |\n|---|---|\n| Enums go in `enums.ts` | `factory/enum-file-organization` |\n| Types go in `types.ts` | `factory/types-file-organization` |\n| API types in `packages/common/src/api/<service>/types.ts` | Manual + review |\n| No `require()` — use ES6 imports | `import/no-commonjs` |\n| Absolute imports (`@factory/...`, `@/...`) | `import/no-relative-parent-imports` |\n| No `<div>`, `<button>`, `<input>` directly | Custom lint rule |\n\n## UI development\n\nAll UI components must use `@factory/core-ui` primitives:\n\n```ts\n// Correct\nimport { Box, Button, Text } from '@factory/core-ui';\n\n// Wrong\n<div>, <button>, <input>  // never use raw HTML elements\n```\n\nColors come from the semantic color system, never hardcoded:\n\n```ts\n// Correct\nimport { colors } from '@factory/core-ui';\nconst bg = colors.semantics.background.primary;\n\n// Wrong\ncolor: '#ffffff'\n```\n\nSee [frontend architecture](../packages/frontend.md) for full UI conventions.\n\n## State management (frontend)\n\nRedux Toolkit with entity adapters. Select state precisely:\n\n```ts\n// Correct — select one property\nconst session = useSelector((state: RootState) => state.assembly.currentSession);\n\n// Wrong — selects the whole slice\nconst { session } = useSelector((state: RootState) => state.assembly);\n```\n\nComponent length limit: 200–300 lines. Extract long TSX into subcomponents. Move repeated state/effect hooks into custom hooks. Put utility functions in `utils/` files, not in the component body.\n\n## Coding style\n\n- TypeScript everywhere. No JavaScript source files.\n- Named exports preferred over default exports.\n- Function and variable names are verbose and descriptive.\n- Imports are absolute (`@factory/...`, `@/...`), never relative parent paths.\n- `async/await` over `.then()` chains.\n- No `console.log` in production code — use `@factory/logging`.\n\n## Feature flags\n\nFeature flags use Statsig. Definitions live in `packages/common/src/feature-flags/constants.ts`. Use the `FactoryFeatureFlags` object — never hardcode flag names as strings.\n\n```ts\nimport { FactoryFeatureFlags } from '@factory/common/feature-flags';\n\n// React\nconst enabled = useFeatureFlagValue(FactoryFeatureFlags.MyFeature);\n\n// Backend\nconst featureFlags = await getFeatureFlagInstance();\nconst enabled = await featureFlags.checkFlag(FactoryFeatureFlags.MyFeature, orgId);\n```\n\n## Adding new API endpoints\n\n1. Define request/response types in `packages/common/src/api/<service>/types.ts`\n2. Implement the handler in `apps/backend/src/app/api/<service>/route.ts`\n3. Add the client call in `packages/frontend/src/api/` or the CLI's `apps/cli/src/api/`\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Error handling reference](../../docs/error-handling.md) — full error pattern guide\n- [Testing](./testing.md) — test conventions\n- [Tooling](./tooling.md) — ESLint plugins and rules\n",
