            "content": "# Tooling\n\n## Build system\n\nThe monorepo uses **npm workspaces** for package management and **Turborepo** for task orchestration. Turbo handles dependency-aware caching and parallel execution.\n\nAll turbo-based scripts (`test`, `typecheck`, `lint`, `fix`, `build`) must pass `--` before `--filter` when run from the root:\n\n```bash\n# Correct\nnpm run test -- --filter=@factory/common\n\n# Wrong — npm eats --filter, turbo runs everything\nnpm run test --filter=@factory/common\n```\n\nRunning without a filter consumes ~9 GB RAM.\n\n## TypeScript\n\nAll workspaces use TypeScript. The root `tsconfig.json` defines base settings; each workspace extends it. Build info files (`tsconfig.tsbuildinfo`) are gitignored but kept in the workspace for incremental builds.\n\n```bash\nnpm run typecheck -- --filter=apps/cli\n```\n\n## Linting\n\nLint configuration is in `@factory/eslint-config` (`packages/eslint-config/`). The package provides several config presets:\n\n| Config file | Used by |\n|---|---|\n| `base.js` | All workspaces |\n| `frontend.js` | React/web workspaces |\n| `backend.js` | Next.js backend |\n| `factory-next.js` | Next.js apps |\n| `factory-package.js` | Library packages |\n\nThe `plugin.js` file contains **custom Factory lint rules** that enforce codebase conventions:\n\n- `factory/enum-file-organization` — enums must be in `enums.ts`\n- `factory/types-file-organization` — types must be in `types.ts`\n- `factory/no-direct-process-env` — use `@factory/environment` instead of `process.env`\n- `factory/consistent-type-assertions` — restricts `as` type assertions\n- Several others enforcing import patterns, component structure, and naming\n\nRun lint with auto-fix:\n\n```bash\nnpm run fix -- --filter=<workspace>   # lint + format (preferred)\nnpm run lint -- --filter=<workspace>  # lint only\n```\n\n## Formatting\n\nPrettier handles code formatting. Config is in the root `package.json` or `.prettierrc`. `npm run fix` runs Prettier automatically.\n\nStylelint handles CSS-in-JS:\n\n```bash\nnpm run stylelint\n```\n\n## Unused exports\n\n[Knip](https://knip.dev/) detects unused exports across the monorepo:\n\n```bash\nnpm run knip\n```\n\nConfiguration is in `knip.json` at the root.\n\n## Environment variables\n\nThe `@factory/environment` package (`packages/environment/`) provides a typed, validated wrapper over `process.env`. All env var access must go through this package — direct `process.env` access is blocked by the `factory/no-direct-process-env` lint rule.\n\n## CI/CD\n\nThe `.github/workflows/` directory contains 50+ workflows. Key ones:\n\n| Workflow | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `basic-checks.yml` | Lint, typecheck, tests on every PR |\n| `test.yml` | Full test suite |\n| `typecheck.yml` | TypeScript checking |\n| `lint-format-with-healing.yml` | Lint with auto-fix and commit |\n| `cli-release.yml` | Publish CLI binary |\n| `factoryd-release.yml` | Publish daemon binary |\n| `desktop-release.yml` | Package and publish desktop app |\n| `deploy-prod.yml` | Deploy backend + web to Vercel |\n| `playwright-e2e.yml` | E2E browser tests |\n| `cli-e2e-tests.yml` | CLI TUI end-to-end tests |\n| `knip.yml` | Unused export check |\n\n## Storybook\n\nComponent library documentation and browser. Run alongside the dev stack:\n\n```bash\nnpm run dev:web  # starts Storybook as part of the stack\n```\n\nStorybook source is in `apps/storybook/`.\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Development workflow](./development-workflow.md)\n- [Testing](./testing.md)\n- [Patterns and conventions](./patterns-and-conventions.md)\n- [Deployment](../deployment.md)\n",
