            "content": "# Apps\n\nFactory ships several deployable applications. This section covers each one.\n\n## Applications\n\n| App | Tech stack | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| [CLI](./cli/index.md) | Bun, TypeScript, Ink | Primary user interface — the `droid` command |\n| [Daemon](./daemon.md) | Bun, TypeScript, WebSocket | Background process managing agent sessions |\n| [Backend](./backend.md) | Next.js 15, TypeScript | REST API, LLM proxy, auth, billing |\n| [Web](./web.md) | Vite, React 19, TypeScript | Browser-based Droid chat interface |\n| [Desktop](./desktop.md) | Electron, Vite, React 19 | Native desktop app wrapping the web UI |\n| [Admin](./admin.md) | Next.js 15, React 19 | Internal admin dashboard |\n\n## Supporting apps\n\n| App | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/scripts` | Build, deployment, and maintenance scripts |\n| `apps/relay` | Traffic routing and proxying |\n| `apps/signal` | Notification and event broadcasting |\n| `apps/functions` | Firebase Cloud Functions |\n| `apps/storybook` | Component library browser |\n| `apps/factory-vscode-extension` | VS Code integration |\n| `apps/factory-jetbrains-plugin` | JetBrains IDE integration |\n\n## Communication between apps\n\nThe CLI and desktop/web apps all communicate with the daemon via WebSocket using JSON-RPC 2.0. The daemon talks to the agent process over stdin/stdout JSON-RPC. All apps that need cloud data call the backend REST API.\n\nSee [Architecture](../overview/architecture.md) for the full data flow diagram.\n",
