            "content": "# CLI\n\nActive contributors: jonathanlucuix-andre, factory-droid[bot]\n\n## Purpose\n\nThe Droid CLI (`apps/cli`) is the primary interface for the Factory platform. It runs in two modes: an interactive full-screen TUI built with React and Ink, and a headless exec mode for scripted use. The binary is named `droid` and is distributed as a Single Executable Application (SEA).\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/cli/\n├── src/\n│   ├── index.ts               # Entry point — mode detection\n│   ├── main.tsx               # TUI root component\n│   ├── app.tsx                # Main TUI React/Ink app (4,556 lines)\n│   ├── commands/              # ~96 slash commands (exec, wiki-upload, sessions, etc.)\n│   │   ├── exec.ts            # /exec command — launches an agent run (60 KB)\n│   │   ├── wiki-upload.ts     # /wiki-upload command\n│   │   ├── mcp/               # MCP tool management commands\n│   │   ├── skills/            # Skill management\n│   │   └── ...                # One file per command\n│   ├── exec/                  # Agent execution runners\n│   │   ├── streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts   # Main exec runner (54 KB)\n│   │   ├── streamingExecRunner.ts          # Legacy streaming runner\n│   │   ├── renderlessExecRunner.ts         # Headless/renderless runner\n│   │   └── sharedAgentRunner.ts            # Shared runner logic\n│   ├── agent/                 # Tool confirmation, permission handling\n│   ├── controllers/\n│   │   └── SessionController.ts  # Session lifecycle and state (37 KB)\n│   ├── hooks/                 # React hooks for TUI components\n│   ├── components/            # TUI React components (123 dirs/files)\n│   ├── services/              # CLI-side services\n│   ├── api/                   # Backend API client calls\n│   ├── mcp/                   # MCP client integration\n│   ├── acp/                   # Agent Control Protocol helpers\n│   ├── llm-proxy/             # LLM proxy routing\n│   └── utils/                 # 197 utility files\n├── e2e-tests/                 # TUI end-to-end tests (@microsoft/tui-test)\n├── e2e-stream-jsonrpc/        # JSON-RPC integration tests\n└── acp/                       # ACP protocol implementation\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/index.ts` | Entry point. Detects interactive vs headless mode. Bootstraps telemetry, auth, and command registry. |\n| `src/app.tsx` | The full TUI React app. Handles layout, keyboard input, session display, and command dispatch. |\n| `src/controllers/SessionController.ts` | Manages a single session's lifecycle: message sending, streaming, model switching, interruption. |\n| `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` | Core exec runner for the `exec` command. Connects to daemon over JSON-RPC, streams agent output. |\n| `src/exec/renderlessExecRunner.ts` | Headless exec runner for non-interactive use (CI, scripts). |\n| `src/commands/exec.ts` | The `/exec` slash command — the most complex command (60 KB). |\n| `src/commands/index.ts` | Registers all slash commands in the command registry. |\n| `src/commands/registry.ts` | Command registry: map of name → command handler. |\n\n## How it works\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    Entry[\"src/index.ts\\nmode detection\"] -->|\"no args\"| TUI[\"src/app.tsx\\nInk TUI\"]\n    Entry -->|\"exec subcommand\"| ExecCmd[\"commands/exec.ts\"]\n    TUI --> SessionCtrl[\"SessionController.ts\\nsession lifecycle\"]\n    ExecCmd --> StreamRunner[\"exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts\"]\n    SessionCtrl --> StreamRunner\n    StreamRunner -->|\"WebSocket JSON-RPC\"| Daemon[\"factoryd daemon\"]\n    Daemon -->|\"stdin/stdout\"| Agent[\"Agent process\"]\n    Agent -->|\"streaming response\"| StreamRunner\n    StreamRunner -->|\"events\"| SessionCtrl\n    SessionCtrl -->|\"state updates\"| TUI\n```\n\n### Mode detection\n\n`src/index.ts` checks `process.argv`. If the first argument is `exec` (or certain other headless commands), it runs in Commander headless mode. Otherwise, it launches the Ink TUI.\n\n### TUI rendering\n\nThe TUI is a React app rendered to the terminal via Ink. `app.tsx` (4,556 lines) manages the top-level layout, routes keyboard shortcuts to commands, and renders the session message list. Individual commands are React components mounted into the TUI.\n\n### Exec runner\n\nWhen running an agent task, `streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` opens a WebSocket connection to `factoryd`, sends a `daemon.initialize_session` or `daemon.load_session` call, then streams messages to and from the agent process. It handles tool confirmation prompts, interruption, and progress display.\n\n### Slash commands\n\nAll in-session slash commands live in `src/commands/`. Each command exports a `Command` object with a name, description, handler, and optional TUI component. The `CommandRegistry` in `src/commands/registry.ts` maps names to handlers.\n\n### Skill commands\n\nSkills are markdown files in `.factory/skills/` directories. `src/commands/skills/SkillCommandsLoader.ts` discovers and registers them as dynamic slash commands.\n\n## Integration points\n\n- **factoryd daemon** — connected via WebSocket JSON-RPC (port 41723 dev, 37643 prod)\n- **Backend API** — REST calls for auth, sessions, billing, integrations via `src/api/`\n- **@factory/droid-core** — imports tool definitions and LLM utilities\n- **@factory/common** — imports shared types, enums, and API contracts\n- **@factory/services** — imports settings, plugin management, and other services\n\n## Entry points for modification\n\nTo add a new slash command, create a file in `src/commands/`, export a `Command` object, and register it in `src/commands/index.ts`. See `src/commands/rename.ts` for a minimal example.\n\nTo change exec behavior (how agent output is processed), modify `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` or `src/exec/sharedAgentRunner.ts`.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/index.ts` | Entry point and mode detection |\n| `src/app.tsx` | Full TUI app (4,556 lines) |\n| `src/controllers/SessionController.ts` | Session lifecycle management |\n| `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` | Core streaming exec runner |\n| `src/commands/exec.ts` | /exec slash command |\n| `src/commands/index.ts` | Command registration |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Daemon](../daemon.md) — what the CLI connects to\n- [droid-core package](../../packages/droid-core.md) — AI tools and LLM utilities used by the CLI\n- [Command structure](./command-structure.md) — full list of slash commands\n",
