            "content": "# Command structure\n\nThe CLI has ~50 slash commands registered in `src/commands/index.ts`. Each lives in its own file under `src/commands/`.\n\n## Session commands\n\n| Command | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/new` | `new.ts` | Start a new session |\n| `/sessions` | `sessions.ts` | List and switch sessions |\n| `/rename` | `rename.ts` | Rename the current session |\n| `/fork` | `fork.ts` | Fork a session |\n| `/rewind` | `rewind.ts` | Rewind session history |\n| `/clear` | `clear.ts` | Clear session context |\n| `/compact` | `compact.ts` | Compact session to reduce token usage |\n| `/favorite` | `favorite.ts` | Favorite a session |\n| `/share` | `share.ts` | Share a session |\n| `/copy` | `copy.ts` | Copy session output |\n\n## Execution and agent commands\n\n| Command | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/exec` | `exec.ts` | Run an agent task (the core execution command) |\n| `/review` | `review.ts` | Request an agent code review |\n| `/readiness-report` | `readiness-report.ts` | Generate agent readiness report |\n| `/readiness-fix` | `readiness-fix.ts` | Auto-fix readiness issues |\n| `/enter-mission` | `enter-mission.ts` | Enter a multi-step mission |\n| `/exit-mission` | `exit-mission.ts` | Exit current mission |\n| `/missions` | `missions.ts` | List and manage missions |\n| `/mission` | `mission.ts` | Mission management |\n\n## Configuration commands\n\n| Command | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/model` | `model.ts` | Switch AI model |\n| `/settings` | `settings.ts` | Manage settings |\n| `/settings-debug` | `settings-debug.ts` | Debug settings state |\n| `/language` | `language.ts` | Set language preferences |\n| `/ide` | `ide.ts` | Configure IDE integration |\n| `/terminal-setup` | `terminal-setup.ts` | Terminal configuration |\n\n## Tool and integration commands\n\n| Command | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/mcp` | `mcp/mcp.ts` | Manage MCP servers and tools |\n| `/hooks` | `hooks.ts` | Manage lifecycle hooks |\n| `/plugins` | `plugins.ts` | Manage plugins |\n| `/droids` | `droids.ts` | Manage custom droids |\n| `/skills` | `skills.ts` | List and manage skills |\n| `/create-skill` | `create-skill.ts` | Create a new skill |\n| `/install-github-app` | `install-github-app.ts` | Install GitHub integration |\n\n## Diagnostics and utilities\n\n| Command | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/bug` | `bug.ts` | Submit a bug report |\n| `/diagnostics` | `diagnostics.ts` | Run diagnostics |\n| `/cost` | `cost.ts` | Show session cost |\n| `/limits` | `limits.ts` | Show usage limits |\n| `/status` | `status.ts` | Show daemon/session status |\n| `/stats` | `stats/` | Show codebase statistics |\n| `/search` | `search.ts` | Search across sessions |\n| `/git-ai` | `git-ai.ts` | AI-assisted git operations |\n| `/generate-blog` | `generate-blog.ts` | Generate blog post from session |\n\n## Auth commands\n\n| Command | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/login` | `loginCommand.ts` | Log in to Factory |\n| `/logout` | `logoutCommand.ts` | Log out |\n| `/account` | `account.ts` | Show account info |\n| `/billing` | `billing.ts` | Show billing info |\n\n## System commands\n\n| Command | File | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `/help` | `help.ts` | Show help |\n| `/quit` | `quit.ts` | Quit the CLI |\n| `/update` | `update.ts` | Update the CLI |\n| `/daemon` | `daemon.ts` | Daemon management |\n| `/bg-process` | `bg-process.ts` | Background process management |\n| `/ssh` | `ssh.ts` | SSH session management |\n| `/statusline` | `statusline.ts` | Configure the status line |\n\n## Custom commands\n\nCustom commands can be defined in `.factory/droids/` directories as markdown files. `src/commands/custom/CustomCommandsLoader.ts` discovers and registers them dynamically.\n\n## Headless commands\n\nThe CLI also exposes a `droid exec` subcommand that runs non-interactively. This goes through `src/commands/exec.ts` and `src/exec/streamingJsonRpcExecRunner.ts` without the TUI.\n\nSee [CLI index](./index.md) for the full architecture overview.\n",
