            "content": "# Daemon\n\nActive contributors: jonathanlucuix-andre, factory-droid[bot]\n\n## Purpose\n\n`factoryd` is the Factory daemon — a background process that manages agent sessions and provides terminal access. It runs locally (bundled with the desktop app) and on remote cloud development environments (CDEs). The CLI and web/desktop apps connect to it over WebSocket using JSON-RPC 2.0.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/daemon/\n├── src/\n│   ├── index.ts           # Entry point — loads env, runs auto-update, starts DaemonCore\n│   ├── environment.ts     # Env var loading and validation\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   └── UpdateService.ts  # Auto-update logic\n│   ├── telemetry/         # OpenTelemetry tracing client\n│   └── utils/             # Daemon-specific utilities\n\npackages/daemon-core/        # Core daemon logic (imported by apps/daemon)\n├── src/\n│   ├── index.ts           # DaemonCore class — main server\n│   ├── server/            # WebSocket server and JSON-RPC handlers\n│   ├── droid/             # Agent session management\n│   ├── terminal/          # PTY terminal sessions\n│   ├── automations/       # Automation runners\n│   ├── relay/             # Relay connection management\n│   ├── services/          # Internal services\n│   └── utils/             # Utilities\n```\n\nThe `apps/daemon` workspace is a thin wrapper. The real logic lives in `packages/daemon-core`.\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/index.ts` | `DaemonCore` class — instantiated with config, starts the WebSocket server |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/` | WebSocket server, HTTP health endpoints, JSON-RPC request routing |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/droid/` | Agent session lifecycle (initialize, load, interrupt) |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/` | PTY terminal sessions (create, write, resize, close) |\n| `apps/daemon/src/services/UpdateService.ts` | Checks for new daemon versions and applies updates |\n\n## How it works\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    Client[\"CLI / Web / Desktop\"] -->|\"WebSocket JSON-RPC\"| WSServer[\"WebSocket Server\\n(daemon-core/src/server)\"]\n    WSServer --> DroidHandler[\"Droid Request Handler\\n(handles session ops)\"]\n    WSServer --> TerminalHandler[\"Terminal Handler\\n(PTY sessions)\"]\n    DroidHandler -->|\"spawn/stdin\"| AgentProcess[\"Agent Process\\n(droid CLI in exec mode)\"]\n    AgentProcess -->|\"stdout events\"| DroidHandler\n    DroidHandler --> WSServer\n    WSServer -->|\"JSON-RPC events\"| Client\n```\n\n### Session lifecycle\n\n1. Client sends `daemon.initialize_session` → daemon spawns a new agent process\n2. Agent connects back via stdin/stdout JSON-RPC\n3. Client sends `daemon.add_user_message` → daemon forwards to agent stdin\n4. Agent streams responses back via stdout → daemon forwards to client via WebSocket\n5. Client sends `daemon.interrupt_session` → daemon signals the agent to stop\n\n### Terminal sessions\n\nThe daemon provides full terminal (PTY) access independent of agent sessions. This enables the web and desktop apps to run arbitrary shell commands via `daemon.create_terminal`.\n\n## Supported JSON-RPC methods\n\n**Session management:**\n- `daemon.initialize_session` — spawn and initialize a new agent session\n- `daemon.load_session` — attach to an existing session\n- `daemon.add_user_message` — send a message to the active agent\n- `daemon.interrupt_session` — interrupt agent execution\n\n**Terminal:**\n- `daemon.create_terminal` — create a new PTY session\n- `daemon.write_terminal_data` — send input to a terminal\n- `daemon.resize_terminal` — resize the terminal window\n- `daemon.close_terminal` — close a terminal session\n- `daemon.list_terminals` — list active terminal sessions\n\n## HTTP endpoints\n\n- `GET /health` — basic health check with uptime and session count\n- `GET /status` — detailed status including daemon info, terminal sessions, and WebSocket connections\n\n## Ports\n\n| Environment | Port |\n|---|---|\n| Production | 37643 |\n| Development | 41723 |\n\n## Distribution\n\n- **Local**: Bundled inside the Electron desktop app (`apps/desktop`)\n- **Remote CDEs**: Downloaded from `downloads.factory.ai` on workspace initialization\n- **Auto-update**: `UpdateService.ts` checks for new versions on startup and applies them\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `apps/daemon/src/index.ts` | Daemon entry point |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/index.ts` | `DaemonCore` class |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/server/` | WebSocket server and HTTP endpoints |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/droid/` | Agent session management |\n| `packages/daemon-core/src/terminal/` | PTY terminal sessions |\n| `apps/daemon/src/services/UpdateService.ts` | Auto-update |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [CLI](./cli/index.md) — the primary client that connects to the daemon\n- [Architecture](../overview/architecture.md) — full system data flow\n- [Debugging](../how-to-contribute/debugging.md) — daemon log locations and troubleshooting\n",
