            "content": "# Backend\n\nActive contributors: jonathanlucuix-andre, factory-droid[bot]\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/backend` is the cloud API that supports the Factory platform. It handles authentication, session storage, billing, LLM proxying, and third-party integrations. The backend is a Next.js 15 app deployed on Vercel and is the only app that talks directly to Firestore.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/backend/\n├── src/\n│   ├── app/\n│   │   ├── api/             # Next.js App Router API routes\n│   │   │   ├── auth/        # WorkOS auth endpoints\n│   │   │   ├── billing/     # Billing and subscription\n│   │   │   ├── llm/         # LLM proxy and streaming\n│   │   │   ├── sessions/    # Session CRUD and management\n│   │   │   ├── organization/ # Org and user management\n│   │   │   ├── integrations/ # GitHub, Linear, Slack webhooks\n│   │   │   ├── cron/        # Background cron jobs\n│   │   │   ├── daemon/      # Daemon update endpoints\n│   │   │   ├── github/      # GitHub integration\n│   │   │   ├── feature-flags/ # Feature flag endpoint\n│   │   │   ├── bug-reports/ # Bug report submission\n│   │   │   └── ...\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── billing/         # Billing logic (Orb)\n│   │   ├── workos/          # WorkOS auth service\n│   │   ├── integrations/    # Integration connectors\n│   │   ├── computer/        # Computer use / E2B\n│   │   ├── orb/             # Orb billing provider\n│   │   ├── bigquery/        # Analytics\n│   │   └── ...\n│   ├── features/            # Backend feature modules\n│   ├── constants.ts         # Backend constants\n│   └── middleware.ts        # Next.js middleware (auth, rate limiting)\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/middleware.ts` | Auth checking and rate limiting for all API routes |\n| `src/app/api/llm/` | LLM proxy — receives agent LLM requests, applies policy, forwards to providers |\n| `src/app/api/sessions/` | Session create, read, update, delete |\n| `src/app/api/auth/` | WorkOS auth flows (sign in, callback, token refresh) |\n| `src/services/billing/` | Subscription management via Orb |\n| `src/services/workos/` | WorkOS user and org management |\n| `src/app/api/cron/` | Scheduled background jobs |\n\n## How it works\n\nThe backend is a standard Next.js App Router application. API routes live under `src/app/api/`. Authentication middleware in `src/middleware.ts` validates WorkOS JWTs on all protected routes.\n\nThe LLM proxy (`src/app/api/llm/`) is the most critical path. Agents call this endpoint to get completions from Anthropic, OpenAI, or Google. The proxy applies usage limits, strips/adds provider-specific headers, and streams the response back.\n\n```mermaid\ngraph LR\n    Agent -->|\"POST /api/llm/stream\"| LLMProxy[\"LLM Proxy\\n/api/llm\"]\n    LLMProxy -->|\"check limits\"| Firestore\n    LLMProxy -->|\"forward request\"| Anthropic\n    LLMProxy -->|\"or\"| OpenAI\n    LLMProxy -->|\"or\"| Google\n    LLMProxy -->|\"stream tokens\"| Agent\n```\n\n## External integrations\n\n| Service | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| WorkOS | Auth, SSO, user/org management |\n| Firestore | Primary database |\n| Orb | Billing and subscription |\n| Stripe | Payment processing |\n| GitHub | Code integration, webhooks |\n| Linear | Issue tracking integration |\n| Slack | Notification integration |\n| E2B | Computer use sandboxes |\n| Sentry | Error monitoring |\n| Statsig | Feature flags |\n\n## Deployment\n\nDeployed to Vercel. The `vercel.json` at the app root configures routing. Environment variables are managed in Vercel and the `apps/backend/.env` file.\n\nCron jobs run via Vercel's cron feature — configured in `vercel.json` and implemented in `src/app/api/cron/`.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/middleware.ts` | Auth and rate limiting middleware |\n| `src/app/api/llm/` | LLM proxy endpoint |\n| `src/app/api/sessions/` | Session management API |\n| `src/app/api/auth/` | Authentication flows |\n| `src/services/workos/` | WorkOS service integration |\n| `src/services/billing/` | Billing logic |\n| `src/constants.ts` | Backend-wide constants |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [API reference](../api/index.md) — full endpoint listing\n- [Security](../security.md) — auth model and trust boundaries\n- [Deployment](../deployment.md) — Vercel deployment details\n- [How to monitor](../how-to-monitor/index.md) — logging and observability\n",
