            "content": "# Web app\n\nActive contributors: jonathanlucuix-andre, factory-droid[bot]\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/web` is the browser-based interface for the Factory platform. It presents the same Droid chat experience as the desktop app — users can start sessions, send messages, view agent output, and manage their account — but runs in any modern browser without installing software.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/web/\n├── src/\n│   ├── main.tsx           # React root — mounts WebAuthProvider\n│   ├── auth/              # WorkOS AuthKit integration\n│   ├── config/            # App configuration\n│   └── types/             # Web-specific types\n├── e2e/                   # Playwright E2E tests\n├── index.html             # Vite HTML shell\n├── vite.config.ts         # Vite build config\n└── playwright.config.ts   # Playwright test config\n```\n\nThe web app is intentionally thin. Most logic lives in `@factory/frontend` (`packages/frontend/`), which provides the session controller, routing, layout, auth hooks, and all feature components. `apps/web` provides authentication wiring and the Vite entrypoint.\n\n## How it works\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    Browser --> main.tsx\n    main.tsx --> WebAuthProvider[\"WebAuthProvider\\n(auth/WebAuth.provider.tsx)\"]\n    WebAuthProvider -->|\"if authenticated\"| FrontendApp[\"@factory/frontend\\nApp + Router\"]\n    FrontendApp --> DaemonSessionController[\"DaemonSessionController\\n(packages/frontend)\"]\n    DaemonSessionController -->|\"WebSocket JSON-RPC\"| Daemon[\"factoryd daemon\"]\n```\n\n1. `main.tsx` mounts `WebAuthProvider`, which handles the WorkOS auth flow.\n2. After authentication, the frontend app from `@factory/frontend` renders.\n3. `DaemonSessionController` connects over WebSocket to the local or remote daemon.\n4. The daemon manages agent sessions and streams results back.\n\n## Tech stack\n\n- **Vite + React 19** — fast builds and HMR for development\n- **WorkOS AuthKit** — browser-side auth (`@workos-inc/authkit-react`)\n- **TypeScript** throughout\n- **Playwright** — E2E tests in `e2e/`\n\n## E2E tests\n\n```bash\ncd apps/web\nnpx playwright test           # run all tests\nnpx playwright test --headed  # with browser visible\n```\n\nPlaywright config is in `playwright.config.ts`. Tests run against a live local stack.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/main.tsx` | React entry point |\n| `src/auth/` | WorkOS auth provider for the web environment |\n| `vite.config.ts` | Vite build and dev server configuration |\n| `playwright.config.ts` | E2E test configuration |\n| `e2e/` | Playwright test specs |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Desktop app](./desktop.md) — native wrapper with the same UI\n- [@factory/frontend](../packages/frontend.md) — where the actual UI logic lives\n- [Architecture](../overview/architecture.md) — how the web app fits into the system\n",
