            "content": "# Desktop app\n\nActive contributors: jonathanlucuix-andre, factory-droid[bot]\n\n## Purpose\n\n`apps/desktop` is the Electron desktop application. It wraps the web UI with native system integration — managing the `factoryd` daemon process, accessing the local file system, and providing auto-update via S3-distributed binaries. It supports macOS, Windows, and Linux.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\napps/desktop/\n├── src/\n│   ├── main/              # Electron main process\n│   │   ├── index.ts       # Main process entry point\n│   │   ├── daemon/        # Daemon lifecycle management\n│   │   ├── updater/       # Electron auto-updater\n│   │   └── ...\n│   ├── renderer/          # Renderer process (loads the web UI)\n│   ├── preload/           # Preload scripts (context bridge)\n│   └── config/            # Desktop configuration\n├── forge.config.ts        # Electron Forge build config\n├── vite.main.config.ts    # Main process Vite config\n├── vite.renderer.config.ts # Renderer Vite config\n└── vite.preload.config.ts # Preload Vite config\n```\n\n## How it works\n\nElectron has two processes: the **main process** (Node.js, full system access) and the **renderer process** (Chromium, loads the web UI).\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n    Main[\"Main Process\\n(src/main)\"] -->|\"IPC\"| Preload[\"Preload Script\\n(context bridge)\"]\n    Preload -->|\"safe API\"| Renderer[\"Renderer\\n(web UI from @factory/frontend)\"]\n    Main -->|\"spawn + manage\"| Daemon[\"factoryd daemon\"]\n    Main -->|\"check updates\"| Updater[\"Electron auto-updater\\n(S3 distribution)\"]\n```\n\nThe main process:\n1. Spawns and manages the `factoryd` daemon binary embedded in the app bundle\n2. Listens for the daemon to become ready on its WebSocket port\n3. Passes the daemon URL to the renderer via the preload context bridge\n4. Handles auto-update checks on startup\n\nThe renderer loads the same `@factory/frontend` React app as the web app, but with desktop-specific auth and daemon connection wiring.\n\n## Build and packaging\n\nThe desktop app is built with [Electron Forge](https://www.electronforge.io/) (`forge.config.ts`). Packaging:\n\n```bash\ncd apps/desktop\nnpm run build    # build for development\nnpm run make     # package for distribution\n```\n\nThe CI workflow `desktop-build.yml` runs builds on every PR. The `desktop-release.yml` workflow publishes releases.\n\n## Auto-update\n\nUpdates are distributed via S3. The updater checks for new versions on startup. The `VERSIONING.md` file in the app root documents the versioning scheme. The `@factory/updater` package (`packages/updater/`) provides shared update utilities.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/main/index.ts` | Electron main process entry |\n| `src/main/daemon/` | Daemon process lifecycle |\n| `forge.config.ts` | Build and packaging configuration |\n| `VERSIONING.md` | Versioning and update scheme |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Daemon](./daemon.md) — the daemon that the desktop app manages\n- [Web app](./web.md) — the UI that the renderer loads\n- [Deployment](../deployment.md) — desktop release process\n",
