            "content": "# @factory/core-ui\n\nActive contributors: jonathanlucuix-andre, factory-droid[bot]\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/core-ui` is the mandatory design system for all Factory UI development. Every UI component must use its primitives — never raw HTML elements or custom styled components that duplicate what the library provides. It ships layout primitives, form components, typography, icons, and a semantic color system with light/dark mode support.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/core-ui/src/\n├── primitives/        # 32 UI primitive components\n│   ├── Box/           # Base layout container\n│   ├── Flex/          # Flexbox layout\n│   ├── Grid/          # CSS Grid layout\n│   ├── Button/        # Button with variants and sizes\n│   ├── Input/         # Text input\n│   ├── TextArea/      # Multi-line text input\n│   ├── Dropdown/      # Dropdown menu\n│   ├── Select/        # Select/combobox\n│   ├── Modal/         # Dialog/modal\n│   ├── Toast/         # Notification toasts\n│   ├── Tooltip/       # Hover tooltips\n│   ├── Collapsible/   # Expand/collapse panel\n│   ├── ScrollArea/    # Custom scrollable container\n│   ├── Avatar/        # User avatar\n│   ├── Card/          # Content card\n│   └── ...            # More primitives\n├── typography/        # Text and heading components\n├── colors/            # Semantic color tokens\n├── tokens/            # Design tokens (spacing, sizing)\n├── icons/             # Icon components\n├── fonts/             # Font definitions\n├── hooks/             # Shared UI hooks\n├── styles/            # Global styles and resets\n└── index.ts           # Public API — all exports\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| Export | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `Box` | Base layout container. Accepts all CSS-in-JS style props. |\n| `Flex` | Flexbox container. Shorthand over `Box` with `display: flex`. |\n| `Grid` | CSS Grid container. |\n| `Button` | Button with `ButtonVariant` and `ButtonSize` variants. |\n| `Input` | Text input field. |\n| `Dropdown`, `DropdownItem` | Dropdown menu. |\n| `Modal` | Dialog overlay with `ModalSize` and `ModalVariant`. |\n| `Toast`, `ToastProvider` | Notification toasts with `ToastVariant`. |\n| `Tooltip`, `TooltipProvider` | Hover tooltip. |\n| `colors` | Semantic color object — `colors.semantics.background.primary`, etc. |\n\n## Usage rules\n\n```ts\n// Import from @factory/core-ui\nimport { Box, Button, Text, colors } from '@factory/core-ui';\n\n// Use semantic colors — never hardcode\n<Box style={{ backgroundColor: colors.semantics.background.primary }}>\n\n// Use Button, never <button>\n<Button variant={ButtonVariant.Primary} size={ButtonSize.Medium}>\n  Submit\n</Button>\n\n// Use Text/Header, never <p> or <h1>\n<Text>Some content</Text>\n```\n\nViolations are caught by the `factory/no-raw-html-elements` ESLint rule and code review.\n\n## Storybook\n\nAll components are documented in Storybook. Run the dev stack (`npm run dev:web`) to browse them. Storybook source is in `apps/storybook/`.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/index.ts` | Public API — all exported components and types |\n| `src/primitives/` | Individual component implementations |\n| `src/colors/` | Semantic color tokens for light and dark mode |\n| `src/tokens/` | Spacing, sizing, and other design tokens |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Frontend package](./frontend.md) — uses core-ui for all rendered components\n- [Patterns and conventions](../how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md) — UI development rules\n",
