            "content": "# @factory/frontend\n\nActive contributors: jonathanlucuix-andre, factory-droid[bot]\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/frontend` is the shared frontend library used by both `apps/web` and `apps/desktop`. It contains the React routing, auth integration, feature components, session management, API client, and the `DaemonSessionController` that drives all communication with the daemon. Neither the web nor desktop apps have substantial UI logic of their own — it all lives here.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/frontend/src/\n├── router/\n│   ├── RootApp.tsx           # Root React app component (exported as RootApp)\n│   └── initRouter.ts         # Router initialization\n├── app/                      # App-level providers and layout\n├── auth/                     # Auth context, hooks, and types\n├── views/                    # Top-level page views\n├── layouts/                  # Layout components\n├── features/                 # Feature modules\n│   ├── sessions/             # Session list, message display, session management\n│   ├── settings/             # User and org settings\n│   ├── automations/          # Automation runner UI\n│   ├── missions/             # Mission management UI\n│   ├── wiki/                 # Wiki browsing UI\n│   ├── analytics/            # Usage analytics\n│   ├── feature-flags/        # Client-side feature flag hooks\n│   ├── onboarding/           # New user onboarding flow\n│   ├── terminal/             # Terminal component\n│   └── ...\n├── services/\n│   ├── session/\n│   │   └── DaemonSessionController.ts  # WebSocket/JSON-RPC daemon client\n│   └── consoleLogCollector.ts          # Console log capture for bug reports\n├── api/                      # HTTP API clients\n├── hooks/                    # Shared React hooks\n└── utils/                    # Utility functions\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/router/RootApp.tsx` | The root React component exported to web and desktop apps |\n| `src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | Manages WebSocket connection to the daemon; handles session lifecycle, message streaming |\n| `src/features/sessions/` | Session list, message rendering, conversation UI |\n| `src/features/settings/` | User preferences and configuration UI |\n| `src/features/wiki/` | Wiki browsing and display |\n| `src/features/automations/` | Automation scheduling and history |\n| `src/auth/` | Auth context and WorkOS integration |\n\n## How it works\n\n```mermaid\nsequenceDiagram\n    participant Web/Desktop App\n    participant RootApp\n    participant DaemonSessionController\n    participant factoryd\n\n    Web/Desktop App->>RootApp: mount\n    RootApp->>DaemonSessionController: connect\n    DaemonSessionController->>factoryd: WebSocket connect\n    Note over DaemonSessionController,factoryd: JSON-RPC 2.0 over WebSocket\n    RootApp->>User: render session list\n    User->>RootApp: select session / send message\n    RootApp->>DaemonSessionController: sendMessage(text)\n    DaemonSessionController->>factoryd: daemon.add_user_message\n    factoryd-->>DaemonSessionController: streaming events\n    DaemonSessionController-->>RootApp: session state updates\n    RootApp-->>User: render agent response\n```\n\n`DaemonSessionController` is the central communication hub. It maintains a persistent WebSocket connection to the daemon, handles reconnection, and exposes an event-based API that React components subscribe to via hooks.\n\n## State management\n\nFeature state uses Redux Toolkit. The `sessions` feature slice holds the message tree, current session, and streaming state. Components select state precisely rather than taking the whole slice.\n\n## UI component rules\n\nAll components use `@factory/core-ui` primitives. Direct HTML elements (`div`, `button`, `input`) are banned by ESLint. See [core-ui](./core-ui.md) and [patterns and conventions](../how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md).\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/router/RootApp.tsx` | Root app component |\n| `src/services/session/DaemonSessionController.ts` | Daemon WebSocket client |\n| `src/features/sessions/` | Core chat UI |\n| `src/auth/` | Authentication context |\n| `src/index.ts` | Package public API |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [core-ui](./core-ui.md) — design system used by all components here\n- [Daemon](../apps/daemon.md) — the service DaemonSessionController connects to\n- [Web app](../apps/web.md) — imports RootApp\n- [Desktop app](../apps/desktop.md) — imports RootApp\n",
