            "content": "# @factory/common\n\nActive contributors: jonathanlucuix-andre, factory-droid[bot]\n\n## Purpose\n\n`@factory/common` is the shared contract layer for the entire monorepo. It exports TypeScript types, enums, Zod schemas, API type definitions, and constants that every other package and app imports. This is the single source of truth for the data structures that cross package boundaries.\n\n## Directory layout\n\n```\npackages/common/src/\n├── agent/               # Agent readiness types\n├── agentReadiness/      # Agent readiness check types\n├── api/                 # API type definitions by service\n│   ├── session/         # Session CRUD types\n│   ├── daemon/          # Daemon API types\n│   ├── droid/           # Droid communication types\n│   ├── integrations/    # Third-party integration types\n│   ├── llm/             # LLM request/response types\n│   ├── billing/         # Billing API types\n│   ├── cli/             # CLI API types\n│   ├── updater/         # Update API types\n│   └── ...\n├── automations/         # Automation types\n├── billing/             # Billing and subscription types\n├── cli/                 # CLI-specific shared types\n├── daemon/              # Daemon config and constants\n├── desktop/             # Desktop integration types\n├── documents/           # Document types\n├── droid/               # Droid configuration and schema types\n│   ├── enums.ts         # SessionNotificationType and other enums\n│   ├── schemas/         # Zod schemas for CLI notifications\n│   └── ...\n├── events/              # Event types\n├── feature-flags/\n│   └── constants.ts     # FactoryFeatureFlags — ALL feature flag definitions\n├── images/              # Image types\n├── integrations/        # Integration types (GitHub, Linear, Slack, etc.)\n├── llm/                 # LLM provider types\n├── memory/              # Memory/context types\n├── node/                # Node environment types\n├── organization/        # Org and user types\n├── policy/              # Policy types\n├── relay/               # Relay types\n├── repositories/        # Repository types\n├── security/            # Security policy types\n├── session/             # Session types (core domain object)\n├── sessionV2/           # Updated session types\n├── settings/            # Settings types\n├── shared/              # Shared utility types\n├── tags/                # Tagging types\n├── terminal/            # Terminal types\n├── timeline/            # Timeline types\n├── tools/               # Tool types\n├── updater/             # Update types\n├── usage/               # Usage tracking types\n├── wiki/                # Wiki types\n└── workspaces/          # Workspace types\n```\n\n## Key abstractions\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/feature-flags/constants.ts` | `FactoryFeatureFlags` — all feature flag definitions |\n| `src/droid/enums.ts` | `SessionNotificationType` and other communication enums |\n| `src/droid/schemas/` | Zod schemas for CLI→daemon notification payloads |\n| `src/session/` | Core `Session` type and related types |\n| `src/api/*/types.ts` | API request/response shapes by service |\n| `src/daemon/` | Daemon config constants (ports, machine IDs) |\n\n## Adding new API types\n\nWhen adding a new API endpoint, types go in the matching service directory:\n\n```\npackages/common/src/api/<service>/types.ts\n```\n\nExample for a new `notes` endpoint:\n```\npackages/common/src/api/notes/types.ts\n```\n\nThen import in both the backend handler and the frontend/CLI client. This ensures type safety across the request/response boundary without duplication.\n\n## Feature flags\n\nAll feature flag definitions live in `src/feature-flags/constants.ts`:\n\n```ts\nexport const FactoryFeatureFlags = {\n  MyFeature: {\n    displayName: 'My Feature',\n    statsigName: 'my_feature',\n    defaultValue: false,\n  },\n};\n```\n\nNever access feature flags with raw string names — always use the `FactoryFeatureFlags` object.\n\n## Key source files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `src/feature-flags/constants.ts` | All feature flag definitions |\n| `src/droid/enums.ts` | Communication enums |\n| `src/droid/schemas/` | Notification payload schemas |\n| `src/session/` | Session domain types |\n| `src/api/` | API type definitions |\n\n## Related pages\n\n- [Patterns and conventions](../how-to-contribute/patterns-and-conventions.md) — how to add API types\n- [Backend](../apps/backend.md) — primary consumer of API types\n- [CLI](../apps/cli/index.md) — imports communication schemas and enums\n",
